    'https://us02web.zoom.us/j/87477024015?pwd=gVpnKPDuNsoZ0giaFoA7gicVcI6afV.1',
    '{"id":"01K9E41XHRK251N6EH1E5MY0BJ","title":"PTO Exchange // New North Weekly Meeting","summary":{"notes":"## **Webinar and Landing Page Enhancements**\n\nThe team has improved the webinar landing page to boost registration and engagement ahead of the next session.  \n\n- **A new webinar landing page version** was developed with clearer text and image breaks, plus revised copy encouraging users to \"secure their spot\" instead of simply \"fill out the form\" (06:25)  \n    - Colin plans to add color backgrounds to enhance visual appeal before launch  \n    - Sam requested redirecting the old landing page URL to this new page once live, ensuring a smooth transition  \n    - Nina highlighted LinkedIn ad restrictions on using terms linked to financing, influencing ad copy choices  \n    - The webinar title changed from “demo” to “webinar” to reduce perceived user effort and increase attendance  \n\n- **Discussion on ad copy messaging** focused on simplifying the value proposition to something like “Turn your PTO into financial flexibility” (19:00)  \n    - Sam emphasized the need to distill the complex PTO product into a clear, catchy headline that explains benefits without sounding too salesy  \n    - Colin suggested a graphic showing PTO conversion options (cash, volunteer time, retirement contributions) to visually explain the offer  \n    - Nina warned that using words like “cash” in LinkedIn ads could lower ad ranking due to platform policies  \n    - The team agreed to rewrite ad headlines and integrate product screenshots for better clarity and appeal  \n\n## **Lead Generation and Campaign Performance**\n\nLead generation efforts are showing positive momentum with strong engagement signals and plans to scale paid media.  \n\n- **The “Unlock the Power of PTO” campaign** generated **14 clicks**, with **12 form opens** and **1 booked meeting**, at a cost per lead **22% below the industry benchmark of $1200** (22:21)  \n    - Switching to maximum delivery increased weekly reach **2.5 times** to **649 users**, primarily targeting HR directors, managers, and VPs  \n    - Sam indicated budget discussions for 2026 are ongoing, with plans to concentrate spend from **early-mid February through June**, the peak window for benefits decision-making  \n    - The fall is less favorable due to open enrollments and finalized budgets, so ad spend will be reduced then  \n    - Sam requested collaboration to optimize spend, test new offers, and diversify ads during the high-impact period  \n\n- **Benchmark report submissions** are coming in with some duplicate entries noted, but leads are qualifying well (21:00)  \n    - Dan is actively moving leads to SQL status for follow-up  \n    - Webinar registrations are modest but ongoing, with two for the next Wednesday session and a plan to keep webinars biweekly as long as engagement sustains  \n    - Sam expressed excitement to increase lead volume through paid media and new campaign ideas in 2026  \n\n## **CRM and Integration Workflow Improvements**\n\nThe integration between Heyreach and HubSpot is operational with further refinements planned to improve data flow and lead attribution.  \n\n- **A private app API connection** was built to selectively export contacts from Heyreach to HubSpot by checking a box, allowing control over CRM lead imports (10:15)  \n    - Colin is still working on passing message threads into HubSpot activity logs to maintain communication history  \n    - Sam will confirm if the team has ongoing Heyreach access; Colin will resend login details if needed  \n    - Sam is investigating ways to update lead source labels for LinkedIn and New North contacts to reflect accurate origins rather than generic “integration” tags (12:28)  \n    - Colin suggested workflows or property updates in HubSpot could solve this, with Sam coordinating triggers and workflow setup  \n\n- **Sam and Colin plan to finalize an approved list of integrations** and tools for public messaging by next Tuesday’s call to clarify which payroll providers can be discussed (14:21)  \n    - This list is critical for marketing copy and compliance around integrations claims  \n    - The team uses a channel to track Heyreach responses for easy email list management and opt-outs  \n\n## **Website Content and Ad Creative Development**\n\nContent creation for the website and ads is progressing with a clear review and approval process aimed at timely launches.  \n\n- **Drafts of website page copy** based on last week’s spreadsheet are underway, with delivery expected next week for review (13:43)  \n    - After copy approval, design and then development phases will follow sequentially  \n    - Colin committed to sharing copy documents promptly for Sam’s team to provide feedback  \n\n- **New LinkedIn ad mockups** have been created for the upcoming webinar scheduled in six days (15:21)  \n    - Sam reviewed initial ads, emphasizing the need for clearer benefit statements rather than generic product messaging  \n    - The team plans to revise headlines to better communicate PTO’s financial flexibility benefits based on customer insights  \n    - Visuals will be refined with product screenshots or graphical representations of PTO conversion options to improve engagement  \n\n## **Meeting and Planning Logistics**\n\nScheduling considerations were addressed to ensure continued collaboration through upcoming holidays and vacations.  \n\n- **Colin will be on vacation from November 20th through November 30th**, prompting a reschedule of the regular Thursday call to Wednesday between 3–5 PM Eastern Time (26:18)  \n    - Sam agreed to the Wednesday slot if Josh is available; otherwise, the Monday call remains unchanged  \n    - The team will cancel meetings during Thanksgiving week due to low availability and holidays (28:11)  \n\n- **December planning sessions** are anticipated to finalize offers and campaign tweaks ahead of the peak lead generation window in early 2026 (25:48)  \n    - These sessions will build on the Benchmark Report success and integrate upcoming website and webinar content launches  \n    - Sam will provide updated customer lists and integration approvals ahead of next Monday’s call to support email outreach and messaging accuracy  \n\n- Colin will send the slide deck from this meeting for reference, per Sam’s request (29:09)","outline":null,"keywords":["Webinar Landing Page","Heyreach Integration","HubSpot Workflow","LinkedIn Ads","Benchmark Report","PTO Exchange"],"overview":"- **Webinar Landing Page Update:** New design boosts user engagement with clearer text and revised call-to-action for registrations.  \n- **Ad Messaging Simplification:** Focus on clear headlines like “Turn your PTO into financial flexibility” to improve user understanding.  \n- **Strong Campaign Performance:** “Unlock the Power of PTO” campaign yielded 14 clicks, at a cost per lead 22% below the benchmark.  \n- **CRM Enhancements:** New API connection improves data flow between Heyreach and HubSpot, with ongoing refinements for lead tracking.  \n- **Website and Ad Copy Development:** Drafts due next week for review; emphasis on clear benefit statements in LinkedIn ads.  \n- **Meeting Rescheduling Notes:** Colin''s vacation prompts a shift to Wednesday calls; December planning sessions aimed at early 2026 campaigns.","action_items":"\n**Colin Costigan**\nSet up redirection from old to new webinar landing page URL (07:47)\nSend Heyreach login credentials again for access (11:38)\nContinue work on pushing Heyreach messages into HubSpot activity logs (10:55)\nShare drafted website copy documents next week for review (13:42)\nUpdate and rewrite LinkedIn ad copy reflecting feedback for clearer messaging (20:53)\nCancel meetings for Thanksgiving week (28:21)\nSend slide deck as requested (29:09)\n\n**Sam Lieberman**\nConfirm customer list for sending the survey email and inform Colin by end of day (09:34)\nReiterate with team about Heyreach access and integration details (11:30)\nProvide a concrete list of approved integrations and permissions for marketing collateral ahead of next Tuesday’s call (14:21)\nSlack Josh to verify customer list readiness for email send (09:38)\nGet back to Colin with trigger info for a HubSpot workflow to tag New North leads (13:17)\nProvide customer list and integration lists for upcoming reviews (28:47)\n\n**Josh**\nSend notifications via channel listing Heyreach responses for cleaning email recipient list (15:05)\nTarget initial survey email send for tomorrow (09:38)\n\n**Rob and Steve**\nProvide clarity on list of integrations approved for marketing mention (14:06)\n"},"duration":29.979999542236328,"speakers":[{"id":0,"name":"Colin Costigan"},{"id":1,"name":"Nina Belina"},{"id":2,"name":"Sam Lieberman"}],"sentences":[{"text":"Hey.","index":0,"end_time":190.79,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":190.47,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Hi.","index":1,"end_time":192.07,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":191.59,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"Hey, Colin.","index":2,"end_time":263.06,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":262.26,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"Hey, Sam.","index":3,"end_time":264.1,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":263.38,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"How''s it going?","index":4,"end_time":265.78,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":265.06,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"It''s going, man.","index":5,"end_time":267.94,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":266.82,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"How about yourself?","index":6,"end_time":269.86,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":268.98,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Going well.","index":7,"end_time":272.1,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":271.379,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"Nice.","index":8,"end_time":273.14,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":272.66,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You guys might have been one of the most boring Monday night games I''ve ever seen.","index":9,"end_time":278.66,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":274.26,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Oh, my God, it was so boring.","index":10,"end_time":281.22,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":279.78,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"I was, like, out at the bar and I was like, I just want to go home.","index":11,"end_time":285.39,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":282.51,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"Yeah, I. I made it to halftime and I was like, I. I don''t feel like watching this anymore.","index":12,"end_time":293.07,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":285.63,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It was so bad.","index":13,"end_time":294.91,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":293.63,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"But they won.","index":14,"end_time":295.87,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":295.07,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"They did win.","index":15,"end_time":296.99,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":296.19,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I''ll take it.","index":16,"end_time":298.67,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":297.869,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"They have a big, big Sunday night matchup now.","index":17,"end_time":301.79,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":298.91,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"Are you a Sirianni fan?","index":18,"end_time":304.91,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":302.83,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yes, I am Sirianni fan.","index":19,"end_time":308.35,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":306.35,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"I know he''s a. I know he''s a bit of a.","index":20,"end_time":311.21,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":309.05,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"He''s a bit of a clown, but he''s, like, the most winning head coach in the first five seasons of, like, NFL history and won a Super Bowl.","index":21,"end_time":324.73,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":312.81,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"Like, I, you know, I''ll give him the benefit of the doubt for now.","index":22,"end_time":328.01,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":324.73,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"Yeah, it''s when they started.","index":23,"end_time":329.61,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":328.25,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"It''s better than Brian Dayball.","index":24,"end_time":332.77,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":331.21,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"It''s better than, like, when they start losing.","index":25,"end_time":336.48,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":332.77,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"I think his leash will be short due to his.","index":26,"end_time":339.48,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":336.48,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"Due to his antics, but for the time being, he''s been a great head coach.","index":27,"end_time":345.72,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":339.48,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":28,"end_time":346.4,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":346.04,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"At least him and the fans aren''t yelling at each other anymore.","index":29,"end_time":349.24,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":346.4,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That was crazy last year.","index":30,"end_time":350.84,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":349.56,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I mean.","index":31,"end_time":352.04,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":351.48,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":32,"end_time":352.72,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":352.36,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"I don''t know.","index":33,"end_time":353.24,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":352.72,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"It''s.","index":34,"end_time":353.88,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":353.32,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"It''s tough to be a head coach in Philadelphia.","index":35,"end_time":357.72,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":354.2,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"I feel like you really can''t do anything right.","index":36,"end_time":361.33,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":357.72,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"Like, you win in Green Bay on Monday night, and, like, everyone''s like, why do you only score 10 points?","index":37,"end_time":367.57,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":361.49,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"Like, yeah, it''s like, they won the game.","index":38,"end_time":370.25,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":367.57,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"What are you gonna do?","index":39,"end_time":371.05,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":370.25,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"Like, they''re.","index":40,"end_time":371.65,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":371.05,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"They''re seven and two.","index":41,"end_time":372.73,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":371.65,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"Like, I.","index":42,"end_time":373.37,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":372.73,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"You know, I''m not gonna complain.","index":43,"end_time":374.77,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":373.37,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"Yeah, I gotcha.","index":44,"end_time":377.37,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":376.53,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Is Josh joining today?","index":45,"end_time":378.45,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":377.37,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"He should be.","index":46,"end_time":381.05,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":380.37,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"I don''t know if he''s jumping on later whatnot.","index":47,"end_time":383.81,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":381.05,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"We can get started.","index":48,"end_time":384.69,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":383.81,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"Sounds good.","index":49,"end_time":386.06,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":385.5,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Pull up the screen.","index":50,"end_time":389.02,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":387.82,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right.","index":51,"end_time":391.22,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":390.78,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"A lot of things to go through in a short amount of time.","index":52,"end_time":394.14,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":391.22,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So I know the plan is to get the first batch of the.","index":53,"end_time":398.3,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":395.26,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Well, actually, I''ll start with the webinar.","index":54,"end_time":400.42,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":399.02,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we did do slight updates to the webinar page that currently stands.","index":55,"end_time":404.7,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":400.42,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, we updated, like, some spacing and just made it a little cleaner.","index":56,"end_time":409.82,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":405.34,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":57,"end_time":411.18,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":410.54,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"But we actually also pause this real quick while I pull up in HubSpot.","index":58,"end_time":418.75,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":412.67,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Did make another version that we could maybe launch for the next webinar that is here.","index":59,"end_time":432.83,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":418.83,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We kept the top pretty much the same.","index":60,"end_time":437.79,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":435.31,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We did change the phrase above the form instead of just fill out the form.","index":61,"end_time":443.03,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":437.79,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"To register to, like, secure spot.","index":62,"end_time":444.71,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":443.03,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"By registering below, this was changed to register, so I''ll check on why that''s not published, but.","index":63,"end_time":451.39,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":444.71,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then we just kind of like, split up the content to have some images and text just to, like, break it up a little bit.","index":64,"end_time":456.349,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":451.47,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, I like that.","index":65,"end_time":458.91,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":457.15,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"I''m thinking I want to go back through and add maybe some color to the background and some spots, but otherwise it''s coming together.","index":66,"end_time":466.84,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":460.27,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That would be great.","index":67,"end_time":468.2,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":467.32,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"Can.","index":68,"end_time":469.08,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":468.68,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"When you''re done with this, can we turn the URL of this just to the old landing page and just archive the old landing page and then.","index":69,"end_time":482.76,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":470.44,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"Yeah, we can.","index":70,"end_time":484.76,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":484.2,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We can swap them up.","index":71,"end_time":485.88,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":484.76,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"Yeah, like, wherever that URL is out, we''ll just redirect to the new page.","index":72,"end_time":490.12,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":486.04,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, we can set that up.","index":73,"end_time":491.84,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":490.44,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, I just set this up.","index":74,"end_time":492.84,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":491.84,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"As you can see, it''s like a preview, so no one lands here.","index":75,"end_time":495.24,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":493,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, perfect.","index":76,"end_time":497.05,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":496.09,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"Yeah, I like this a lot better.","index":77,"end_time":498.65,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":497.21,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"And yeah, this is kind of like what we''re looking for.","index":78,"end_time":503.69,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":498.73,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"And just like, I don''t know, make the webinar or make the landing pages just look a little bit nicer, a little cleaner.","index":79,"end_time":509.69,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":503.69,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"Okay.","index":80,"end_time":511.29,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":510.73,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"For the benchmark report that campaign launched and paid on Monday.","index":81,"end_time":516.65,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":513.37,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then for the customer survey, I just showed you guys that we updated the landing page, so everything''s nice and smooth there.","index":82,"end_time":524.21,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":517.13,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I did make one more tweak so that, um.","index":83,"end_time":527.06,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":524.21,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Because, like, there are some que.","index":84,"end_time":530.38,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":528.18,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Some sections with, like, nine questions, and we kind of broke it up.","index":85,"end_time":533.14,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":530.38,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"The only change that I made was I kept, like, the headers consistent, like, in their sections.","index":86,"end_time":540.34,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":533.22,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So if I answer these instead of this going away, when I go to the next series, it''ll still be there, so the questions make more sense.","index":87,"end_time":547.7,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":540.58,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, perfect.","index":88,"end_time":549.22,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":548.02,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"And then we also put together an email.","index":89,"end_time":553.62,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":550.5,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Nice.","index":90,"end_time":555.6,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":555.28,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"That could be sent out for this.","index":91,"end_time":557.08,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":555.76,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I''m not sure if you want to change any of the content, but just did a mock up of, like, a gift card.","index":92,"end_time":561.2,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":557.08,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Now that I''m looking at it here, I can also make the gift card text here a little bigger because that''s just a graphic.","index":93,"end_time":566.4,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":561.36,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But other than that, I know you were working with your team to, like, know exactly what customers to send this out to.","index":94,"end_time":573.44,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":568.16,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yes.","index":95,"end_time":574.64,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":574.16,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"Let me get back to you on that.","index":96,"end_time":576.88,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":574.8,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"Josh was aiming for tomorrow for the first send.","index":97,"end_time":581.2,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":578.96,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, let me.","index":98,"end_time":583.21,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":582.09,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"Let me slack him right now and see if he has that.","index":99,"end_time":588.57,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":583.69,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"All right.","index":100,"end_time":590.49,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":589.93,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, I think you guys were talking to.","index":101,"end_time":597.85,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":595.29,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I think it was Rob about something.","index":102,"end_time":602.09,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":599.45,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Rob.","index":103,"end_time":602.69,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":602.33,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You''re talking to Rob about integrations.","index":104,"end_time":604.01,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":602.69,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You''re talking to someone else about the customer list, Steve.","index":105,"end_time":607.78,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":604.01,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":106,"end_time":608.58,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":608.1,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yes.","index":107,"end_time":610.1,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":609.62,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"Okay.","index":108,"end_time":610.62,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":610.26,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"I Just slack, Josh.","index":109,"end_time":611.54,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":610.62,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"I''ll try and get that.","index":110,"end_time":612.74,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":611.54,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"Hopefully get that to you by the end of the day.","index":111,"end_time":615.22,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":612.98,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"We also set up a connection between Heyreach and HubSpot, but it is the way that it''s set up right now is not just every conversation goes to HubSpot.","index":112,"end_time":625.22,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":615.94,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So what we did is set up.","index":113,"end_time":628.58,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":626.1,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I set up a.","index":114,"end_time":630.26,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":629.22,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Basically an API, but a private app inside of your HubSpot account that''s connected to Heyreach.","index":115,"end_time":636.53,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":631.38,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And so at any point, and this is the person I tested with, if.","index":116,"end_time":640.21,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":636.85,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"If you guys let me know, or if you guys also always have access to heyreach, all you need to do with, like, if we want to send Francisco to HubSpot, we just hit this checkbox.","index":117,"end_time":651.93,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":641.89,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You can select multiple people if you want, export to CRM, PTO, exchange HubSpot, and then it''ll load what''s their lead stage, who should be the owner, and what''s their status, and then it''ll push them over.","index":118,"end_time":663.04,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":651.93,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So here''s one that I tested with Kimber, who had responded in August, and then Dan reached back out because she said she, like, wanted to wait till November.","index":119,"end_time":673.32,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":664,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then she just also said, not ready yet.","index":120,"end_time":676.08,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":673.32,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So the one thing I''m working on still is getting the messages passed through into their activity.","index":121,"end_time":680.8,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":676.16,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, do the message.","index":122,"end_time":684.92,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":681.52,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"Oh, you''re still working through, like, showing the messages.","index":123,"end_time":687.68,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":684.92,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"Showing the messages in the actual activity.","index":124,"end_time":689.48,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":687.68,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":125,"end_time":689.92,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":689.48,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, let me.","index":126,"end_time":692.1,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":690.66,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"I will reiterate that too.","index":127,"end_time":694.5,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":692.42,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"Do we have hay reach access?","index":128,"end_time":697.54,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":695.94,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"You do.","index":129,"end_time":698.46,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":698.02,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I can send you the login again if you need it.","index":130,"end_time":700.18,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":698.46,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, great.","index":131,"end_time":702.42,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":701.22,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"Thank you.","index":132,"end_time":703.22,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":702.58,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"That would be helpful.","index":133,"end_time":705.54,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":703.38,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"I had another question for you, and I don''t know if you need.","index":134,"end_time":711.62,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":707.7,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"This isn''t really something for you to work on, but I just wanted.","index":135,"end_time":715.46,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":712.1,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"I wonder if you know this.","index":136,"end_time":716.66,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":715.46,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"Can you scroll all the way down?","index":137,"end_time":718.29,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":716.93,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"Like, we''re.","index":138,"end_time":723.45,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":721.25,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"We''re working on attributing some of the stuff from New north, like the LinkedIn requests or, you know, other tools or whatnot.","index":139,"end_time":733.89,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":723.45,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"So we see this thing where it says, like, this contact was created from offline sources from integration.","index":140,"end_time":739.73,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":734.69,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"Is there a way to get that to say something other than integration, or is it always going to say integration?","index":141,"end_time":746.57,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":740.13,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"Do you know that I need to.","index":142,"end_time":748.53,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":746.57,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"Check with our developers on that?","index":143,"end_time":750.05,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":748.53,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I''m sure there''s a way, even if it is like a workflow or something that we just have to set up to change, like, original source.","index":144,"end_time":757.97,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":750.61,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, like, I was looking into it today.","index":145,"end_time":762.01,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":758.85,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"I. I think it might have to be a workflow, but I want to make sure that we''re assigning all these leads that are coming in through LinkedIn as, like, new North.","index":146,"end_time":773.09,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":762.01,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":147,"end_time":773.92,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":773.6,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That have connected.","index":148,"end_time":775.2,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":774.24,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"Yeah, I''m with you.","index":149,"end_time":776.72,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":775.76,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, we can explore that.","index":150,"end_time":778.4,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":777.2,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I''m just looking at.","index":151,"end_time":779.2,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":778.4,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Here''s all the scopes that we set up, the API key logs of it running through.","index":152,"end_time":784.16,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":779.76,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We didn''t do a web hook.","index":153,"end_time":786.72,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":785.28,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I''m sure there''s a way that we can set that up.","index":154,"end_time":790.32,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":787.84,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"If a workflow is a last result or last resort, then.","index":155,"end_time":794.32,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":791.2,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Then we''ll just build that.","index":156,"end_time":796.56,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":795.36,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right, let me look into it.","index":157,"end_time":799.2,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":797.12,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"It might just be a property that we have to update instead of, like, the original source or whatever, but I will.","index":158,"end_time":808.24,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":799.52,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"I guess I''m going to try and figure out a solution.","index":159,"end_time":811.44,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":808.8,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"I might need your help of, like, what the trigger for the workflow is so that.","index":160,"end_time":815.16,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":811.44,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah.","index":161,"end_time":816.72,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":815.16,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"When they''re getting integrated from.","index":162,"end_time":818.16,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":816.72,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"Hey, Reach.","index":163,"end_time":818.72,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":818.16,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"We know that it''s a new north lead.","index":164,"end_time":821.04,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":818.88,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"Yep.","index":165,"end_time":821.92,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":821.36,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":166,"end_time":823,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":822.48,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":167,"end_time":823.52,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":823,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":168,"end_time":823.92,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":823.6,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So still working on the messages, and then we''re also in the midst of drafting page copy for all the website stuff that we put in that spreadsheet last week.","index":169,"end_time":832.27,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":823.92,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Perfect.","index":170,"end_time":833.47,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":832.91,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"Do we.","index":171,"end_time":834.11,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":833.47,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"Is.","index":172,"end_time":834.51,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":834.11,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"Is that like, something we''ll get next week, you think?","index":173,"end_time":838.11,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":834.83,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":174,"end_time":838.63,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":838.27,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we''ll share copy with you, copy documents, and then once those are approved, then we''ll go into design.","index":175,"end_time":844.51,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":838.63,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Once design''s approved, then we''ll develop.","index":176,"end_time":846.19,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":844.59,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, perfect.","index":177,"end_time":848.27,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":846.99,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"Sounds good.","index":178,"end_time":849.11,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":848.43,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"I''ll keep an eye out.","index":179,"end_time":850.19,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":849.11,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":180,"end_time":851.15,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":850.59,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then the only other things on your side were.","index":181,"end_time":853.55,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":851.79,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Have you had a chance to sync with Rob on what we can say about integrations?","index":182,"end_time":857.63,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":853.87,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, I mean, let me.","index":183,"end_time":866.11,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":861.47,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"We talked to him briefly about it.","index":184,"end_time":868.47,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":866.59,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"I think we probably need, like, a more concrete answer.","index":185,"end_time":871.79,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":868.47,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"I. I would go under the assumption for now of, like, we can talk about all the payroll providers, I think, and if we need to adjust later, you know, we might remove some, but there''s certainly some that we can talk about where we don''t really care.","index":186,"end_time":888.87,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":871.79,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"But I will.","index":187,"end_time":889.91,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":889.11,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"I''ll get a concrete answer for you for our call next Tuesday.","index":188,"end_time":894.63,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":890.79,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":189,"end_time":895.63,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":895.19,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And if you have a list of tools, that would be great as well.","index":190,"end_time":898.55,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":895.63,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I will get you a whole list and we''ll find out more for, like, approved.","index":191,"end_time":904.47,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":898.55,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":192,"end_time":905.59,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":905.03,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Then where we landed last week was Josh said him and Dan would just send a message into our channel that has all the hey Reach responses coming in.","index":193,"end_time":914.51,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":906.87,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"If we want to remove people from emails.","index":194,"end_time":916.55,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":914.51,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yes.","index":195,"end_time":917.54,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":917.22,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"We just have that in there as a reminder.","index":196,"end_time":919.86,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":918.26,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yep.","index":197,"end_time":920.82,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":920.18,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":198,"end_time":922.34,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":921.7,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We also went ahead and mocked up some ads.","index":199,"end_time":924.74,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":922.5,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Obviously, the next webinar is in six days, so we might be looking at maybe launching these for the next one.","index":200,"end_time":932.3,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":926.34,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Or we could get them up pretty quickly, but we just mock these up for LinkedIn to go to the landing page.","index":201,"end_time":938.98,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":932.3,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Any initial thoughts reading through these?","index":202,"end_time":944.27,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":942.67,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, I''m just reading through them.","index":203,"end_time":946.19,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":944.75,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"Future.","index":204,"end_time":948.91,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":948.51,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"Yeah, I mean, I think they look good.","index":205,"end_time":955.63,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":953.63,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"Let me think about, I guess like the headline that we want to do Again, something that you talked about with the website copy specifically of like, we kind of do a poor job of like distilling what the benefit is in like one line of text.","index":206,"end_time":981.4,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":956.35,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"So I kind of want to like maybe have maybe some of the web page copy will inform this.","index":207,"end_time":990.36,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":981.88,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"But like, is there a way we can say just like, use your PTO for cash?","index":208,"end_time":998.71,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":990.36,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"That''s not as like crass, I guess, or like as direct.","index":209,"end_time":1005.87,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":998.87,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"Like it''s a little bit more catchy.","index":210,"end_time":1007.71,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1005.87,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"But like, I just feel like we have a lot of prospects that are like, the future of PTO is benefits.","index":211,"end_time":1015.23,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1007.71,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"Like, you know, I don''t really know what that means.","index":212,"end_time":1018.71,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1015.23,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"Like in.","index":213,"end_time":1019.86,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1018.87,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It''s like we need to do a better job of being like, you can take your unused PTO and you can exchange the value for financial rewards and, or, or like transforming unused PTO into cash or, or whatever it is, like, or retirement contributions, something like that.","index":214,"end_time":1039.49,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1020.01,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"Like we, I think something a little.","index":215,"end_time":1041.49,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1039.49,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"More educational like from the forefront.","index":216,"end_time":1043.85,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1041.49,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I just think like people like, we sh.","index":217,"end_time":1047.77,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1044.81,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"It''s a complex product and like people don''t understand it and we need to figure out a way to like distill it down into one headline of like you can take your unused PTO and transform it into financial rewards.","index":218,"end_time":1062.76,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1048.01,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"And that''s wordy in itself, but like.","index":219,"end_time":1065.8,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1063,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"We would just need to be careful of how we word it because LinkedIn is a little bit tricky when you know, you use the words link to financing.","index":220,"end_time":1074.76,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1065.8,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"So it''s just to see like what can be used as a title.","index":221,"end_time":1078.44,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1074.84,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":222,"end_time":1080.13,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1079.81,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"What do you mean by that?","index":223,"end_time":1081.73,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1080.69,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"So for example, if you use the words cash or anything related to, you know, selling somebody something, even if it''s, you know, on the visual, on the copy, it could push the ad down in ranking when it''s going to turn up to somebody because they know, they''re not sure if it''s, you know, okay or not.","index":224,"end_time":1102.05,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1082.13,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"Like it''s.","index":225,"end_time":1103.21,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1102.21,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"It''s always very tricky when it''s something connected to any kind of currency, like any kind of value finance or things like that.","index":226,"end_time":1112.15,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1103.21,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"Interesting.","index":227,"end_time":1113.43,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1112.71,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"I did not know that.","index":228,"end_time":1114.63,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1113.51,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"Okay.","index":229,"end_time":1117.83,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1117.19,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"I mean, again, I think there''s a way to say it that''s not just like exchange your PTO for cash.","index":230,"end_time":1123.99,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1117.83,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"But I, I think we need to illustrate more of like this is the plot.","index":231,"end_time":1130.39,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1124.23,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"This is what we do.","index":232,"end_time":1131.67,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1130.55,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"And like, also I kind of feel like we want to maybe lead them in the direction of like, see the, like this, this, this webinar is always just going to be like a product demo.","index":233,"end_time":1145.21,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1131.67,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"I don''t really want to write product demo on the ad copy obviously, but like we want to let them know that you''re going to be able to see like the inner workings of the platform and like how it works for them.","index":234,"end_time":1162.97,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1145.21,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"I feel like what about.","index":235,"end_time":1164.8,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1163.36,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I mean it''s kind of like simple and high level, but it, what if the headline was like do or, or get more with your pto and then the graphic even can show like maybe even like a drop down type mimic of all of the different things you actually can convert your PTO for?","index":236,"end_time":1180.24,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1165.52,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I think that would be good.","index":237,"end_time":1182.72,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1181.6,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"We can get you some product screenshots if, if you need that for.","index":238,"end_time":1186.16,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1182.72,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"Yeah, I mean I don''t think it has to be even directly platform related.","index":239,"end_time":1190.04,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1186.72,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Like, I think just like a.","index":240,"end_time":1191.28,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1190.04,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It''s like the question is like what do you want to exchange your PTO for in the graphic?","index":241,"end_time":1196.75,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1192.63,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then a drop down that''s like expanded and shows like cash volunteer, time off, like all these different things.","index":242,"end_time":1203.35,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1196.75,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, I, I like that too.","index":243,"end_time":1205.27,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1203.51,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"I think we title, I think we title the webinar, like turn your time off into financial flexibility or something.","index":244,"end_time":1214.55,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1205.27,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"Yeah, or time off meets financial flexibility.","index":245,"end_time":1217.83,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1214.87,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"So like, you know, maybe you get rid of financial, but like something that like directs them to what we do a little bit further because you''re, you''re right.","index":246,"end_time":1230.4,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1217.99,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"Like it''s just, it''s a difficult product to like write bad copy.","index":247,"end_time":1236.48,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1230.4,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"Yeah, it''s hard to get it down in like four or five words.","index":248,"end_time":1239.04,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1236.88,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But that does remind me one other change that we made.","index":249,"end_time":1242.32,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1240,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Anina brought this up.","index":250,"end_time":1243.56,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1242.64,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It was great ideas.","index":251,"end_time":1244.4,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1243.56,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Demo can feel a little intensive for people.","index":252,"end_time":1248.34,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1244.98,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we did switch it to webinar as a test to see if people are engaged a little more.","index":253,"end_time":1252.82,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1249.14,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":254,"end_time":1253.82,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1253.3,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"I like demo can feel like they have to do something versus hopping on a webinar.","index":255,"end_time":1257.18,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1253.82,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"They know they can just watch.","index":256,"end_time":1258.18,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1257.18,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, perfect.","index":257,"end_time":1260.02,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1258.82,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":258,"end_time":1261.38,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1260.82,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right, so we''ll rewrite those.","index":259,"end_time":1262.98,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1261.78,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We did have some ad copy, but we can work on some updated versions there.","index":260,"end_time":1267.7,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1262.98,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I also wanted to go through so the benchmark reports.","index":261,"end_time":1272.1,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1268.9,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Gotten some submissions, which is great to see.","index":262,"end_time":1275.29,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1272.1,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, looks like this person, I was looking at this person last night.","index":263,"end_time":1278.45,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1276.09,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"They submitted two like different responses, which was interesting.","index":264,"end_time":1281.41,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1278.45,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yes, I did see that.","index":265,"end_time":1282.89,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1281.41,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"Yes, we have seen some benchmark reports come in.","index":266,"end_time":1288.81,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1284.25,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"We have like a sequence to, to follow up with all those People, we''re excited for the, you know, like, ads to start running.","index":267,"end_time":1298.93,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1288.969,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"Like, we''d like to see some more form fill outs, but we think it looks good.","index":268,"end_time":1302.29,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1298.93,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"Those are good qualified leads for us.","index":269,"end_time":1304.05,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1302.29,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"So like we''re, you know, we''re excited.","index":270,"end_time":1306.45,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1304.05,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"Yeah, I saw Dan moving some of them to SQL, which is great to see.","index":271,"end_time":1310.37,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1306.69,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yes.","index":272,"end_time":1311.25,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1310.77,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":273,"end_time":1312.61,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1312.05,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And you guys are getting submissions on these as well for the webinar?","index":274,"end_time":1315.89,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1312.61,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yep, we got a couple.","index":275,"end_time":1317.41,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1316.21,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"I think we have two for next Wednesday.","index":276,"end_time":1319.89,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1317.569,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"So yeah, also like, want to get more people on that, but like we said we''re going to keep it bi weekly as long as we have, you know, know, some submissions or some people attend because these are good, you know, if they''re, if they''re getting on.","index":277,"end_time":1334.78,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1320.21,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"I mean that''s a, a good lead for us to follow.","index":278,"end_time":1336.86,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1334.86,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"That''s pretty much a first meeting.","index":279,"end_time":1338.06,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1336.86,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Almost.","index":280,"end_time":1338.54,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1338.14,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Almost.","index":281,"end_time":1339.82,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1339.42,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":282,"end_time":1340.38,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1339.9,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"So that''s good.","index":283,"end_time":1341.34,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1340.46,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":284,"end_time":1342.38,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1341.82,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then looking at some metrics, so the Unlock the Power of PTO legion form got 14 clicks, 12 of them opening up the actual form and one of them did book a meeting.","index":285,"end_time":1354.78,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1343.34,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"The cost per lead is actually 22% below the industry benchmark for that at 1200.","index":286,"end_time":1362.66,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1356.82,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Always, of course, looking for ways to optimize the budget, but we are at a good clip there.","index":287,"end_time":1369.34,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1363.3,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But always looking for ways to bring that down.","index":288,"end_time":1370.9,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1369.34,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We did actually 2 1/2 x the week over week delivery, so we reached 649 users because we switched to maximum delivery for the campaign.","index":289,"end_time":1381.14,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1371.54,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And all the impressions we''re seeing are HR directors, managers and VPs.","index":290,"end_time":1385.61,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1382.25,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, that''s good.","index":291,"end_time":1388.09,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1386.65,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"We are like in talks about budget for next year and figuring out like how much we want to spend and how much flexibility that we have.","index":292,"end_time":1405.37,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1390.33,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"So I''ll have more like, I guess information about that in the next like month or so.","index":293,"end_time":1413,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1406.33,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"But we were talking and we feel that like our first meeting sweet spot is basically from like early to mid February all the way to June is when we get the most traction.","index":294,"end_time":1429.24,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1413.32,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"People are out of the holidays, they''re starting to evaluate benefits decisions.","index":295,"end_time":1434.4,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1429.72,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"It hasn''t reached the summer yet in when people are taking vacation.","index":296,"end_time":1437.96,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1434.4,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"And then the fall is tough because you have open enrollment and you have the end of the year where like decisions have probably already been made for, for most of most companies.","index":297,"end_time":1447.99,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1438.31,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"But we''re talking about like ramping up more spend with our LinkedIn advertising like during that time.","index":298,"end_time":1459.99,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1450.07,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"And I want to make you guys aware and I also want to think about like, if we have more money to spend, you know, what are, you know, do we just further spend on Some of the ads that we already have.","index":299,"end_time":1475.28,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1460.71,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"Are we running different ads?","index":300,"end_time":1476.6,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1475.28,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"Are we, like, trying different things?","index":301,"end_time":1478,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1476.6,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"But we''re trying to lean more into paid media in 2026.","index":302,"end_time":1483.84,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1478,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"We''re trying to think about it a little bit more strategically.","index":303,"end_time":1486.96,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1483.92,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"You guys obviously manage that for us, so I want to keep you kind of in the.","index":304,"end_time":1493.21,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1487.52,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"In the loop as.","index":305,"end_time":1494.25,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1493.21,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"As we talk about that.","index":306,"end_time":1495.61,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1494.25,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":307,"end_time":1496.49,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1496.01,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So, I mean, gut instinct is I do not like putting all eggs in one basket.","index":308,"end_time":1500.97,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1496.81,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So, you know, if we''re going and ramping up spend on LinkedIn, that enables us to have more variation testing.","index":309,"end_time":1506.93,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1500.97,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But also different offers like we talked about, like, we can do, you know, keep running the Benchmark Report.","index":310,"end_time":1512.09,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1506.93,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We can come up with a whole new offer.","index":311,"end_time":1513.53,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1512.09,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We can do video series ads.","index":312,"end_time":1516.49,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1513.61,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We can highlight the.","index":313,"end_time":1518.25,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1516.49,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"The podcast, the webinars.","index":314,"end_time":1519.93,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1518.25,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I mean, we can actually tie some.","index":315,"end_time":1521.61,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1519.93,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Some good budget to all of.","index":316,"end_time":1523.05,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1521.61,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, sounds good.","index":317,"end_time":1526.79,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1524.79,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"Perfect.","index":318,"end_time":1530.39,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1529.83,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"I will have more information as we, like, finalize it, but I do know we really want to capitalize on that time frame that I outlined, and we want to work with you to make sure that we''re maximizing our spend.","index":319,"end_time":1544.19,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1530.39,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"And we''re really getting a lot of first meetings, like, during that time.","index":320,"end_time":1547.75,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1544.19,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":321,"end_time":1548.43,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1548.07,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And to me, that means that December we should probably have some.","index":322,"end_time":1551.57,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1548.43,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Some good planning sessions similar to what we did for the Benchmark Report, come up with maybe some tweaks or even just a full new offer that we can promote.","index":323,"end_time":1561.37,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1551.57,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, perfect.","index":324,"end_time":1563.05,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1561.93,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"Love that.","index":325,"end_time":1563.49,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1563.05,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"And so we''ll have a lot coming into fruition at once.","index":326,"end_time":1565.61,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1563.49,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I mean, the website, the webinar series like the Benchmark Report, all these things are like coming to a head at a time together.","index":327,"end_time":1573.01,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1565.61,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And so more budget just allows us to play around more in that playground.","index":328,"end_time":1575.93,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1573.01,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, great.","index":329,"end_time":1577.79,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1576.33,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":330,"end_time":1579.07,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1578.51,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right.","index":331,"end_time":1580.91,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1580.35,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That is pretty much everything.","index":332,"end_time":1582.19,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1581.07,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Except.","index":333,"end_time":1582.99,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1582.35,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Do you want to mention.","index":334,"end_time":1584.67,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1583.63,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So for our meeting next Thursday, I am.","index":335,"end_time":1587.71,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1585.23,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I''m actually on vacation from the 20th through the whole next week.","index":336,"end_time":1594.43,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1589.15,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So I wanted to see if you want to move our call to Wednesday.","index":337,"end_time":1599.87,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1595.63,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I''m available from 3 to 5 Eastern Time.","index":338,"end_time":1604.79,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1600.19,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Or.","index":339,"end_time":1605.43,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1605.03,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Or 