INSERT INTO compass_notes (contract_id, meeting_id, note_type, title, content_raw, note_date, status, action_items, is_auto_generated)
SELECT
  new_meeting.contract_id,
  new_meeting.meeting_id,
  'meeting',
  'Meeting Notes: PTO Exchange // New North Weekly Meeting',
  '## **Webinar and Landing Page Enhancements**

The team has improved the webinar landing page to boost registration and engagement ahead of the next session.  

- **A new webinar landing page version** was developed with clearer text and image breaks, plus revised copy encouraging users to "secure their spot" instead of simply "fill out the form" (06:25)  
    - Colin plans to add color backgrounds to enhance visual appeal before launch  
    - Sam requested redirecting the old landing page URL to this new page once live, ensuring a smooth transition  
    - Nina highlighted LinkedIn ad restrictions on using terms linked to financing, influencing ad copy choices  
    - The webinar title changed from “demo” to “webinar” to reduce perceived user effort and increase attendance  

- **Discussion on ad copy messaging** focused on simplifying the value proposition to something like “Turn your PTO into financial flexibility” (19:00)  
    - Sam emphasized the need to distill the complex PTO product into a clear, catchy headline that explains benefits without sounding too salesy  
    - Colin suggested a graphic showing PTO conversion options (cash, volunteer time, retirement contributions) to visually explain the offer  
    - Nina warned that using words like “cash” in LinkedIn ads could lower ad ranking due to platform policies  
    - The team agreed to rewrite ad headlines and integrate product screenshots for better clarity and appeal  

## **Lead Generation and Campaign Performance**

Lead generation efforts are showing positive momentum with strong engagement signals and plans to scale paid media.  

- **The “Unlock the Power of PTO” campaign** generated **14 clicks**, with **12 form opens** and **1 booked meeting**, at a cost per lead **22% below the industry benchmark of $1200** (22:21)  
    - Switching to maximum delivery increased weekly reach **2.5 times** to **649 users**, primarily targeting HR directors, managers, and VPs  
    - Sam indicated budget discussions for 2026 are ongoing, with plans to concentrate spend from **early-mid February through June**, the peak window for benefits decision-making  
    - The fall is less favorable due to open enrollments and finalized budgets, so ad spend will be reduced then  
    - Sam requested collaboration to optimize spend, test new offers, and diversify ads during the high-impact period  

- **Benchmark report submissions** are coming in with some duplicate entries noted, but leads are qualifying well (21:00)  
    - Dan is actively moving leads to SQL status for follow-up  
    - Webinar registrations are modest but ongoing, with two for the next Wednesday session and a plan to keep webinars biweekly as long as engagement sustains  
    - Sam expressed excitement to increase lead volume through paid media and new campaign ideas in 2026  

## **CRM and Integration Workflow Improvements**

The integration between Heyreach and HubSpot is operational with further refinements planned to improve data flow and lead attribution.  

- **A private app API connection** was built to selectively export contacts from Heyreach to HubSpot by checking a box, allowing control over CRM lead imports (10:15)  
    - Colin is still working on passing message threads into HubSpot activity logs to maintain communication history  
    - Sam will confirm if the team has ongoing Heyreach access; Colin will resend login details if needed  
    - Sam is investigating ways to update lead source labels for LinkedIn and New North contacts to reflect accurate origins rather than generic “integration” tags (12:28)  
    - Colin suggested workflows or property updates in HubSpot could solve this, with Sam coordinating triggers and workflow setup  

- **Sam and Colin plan to finalize an approved list of integrations** and tools for public messaging by next Tuesday’s call to clarify which payroll providers can be discussed (14:21)  
    - This list is critical for marketing copy and compliance around integrations claims  
    - The team uses a channel to track Heyreach responses for easy email list management and opt-outs  

## **Website Content and Ad Creative Development**

Content creation for the website and ads is progressing with a clear review and approval process aimed at timely launches.  

- **Drafts of website page copy** based on last week’s spreadsheet are underway, with delivery expected next week for review (13:43)  
    - After copy approval, design and then development phases will follow sequentially  
    - Colin committed to sharing copy documents promptly for Sam’s team to provide feedback  

- **New LinkedIn ad mockups** have been created for the upcoming webinar scheduled in six days (15:21)  
    - Sam reviewed initial ads, emphasizing the need for clearer benefit statements rather than generic product messaging  
    - The team plans to revise headlines to better communicate PTO’s financial flexibility benefits based on customer insights  
    - Visuals will be refined with product screenshots or graphical representations of PTO conversion options to improve engagement  

## **Meeting and Planning Logistics**

Scheduling considerations were addressed to ensure continued collaboration through upcoming holidays and vacations.  

- **Colin will be on vacation from November 20th through November 30th**, prompting a reschedule of the regular Thursday call to Wednesday between 3–5 PM Eastern Time (26:18)  
    - Sam agreed to the Wednesday slot if Josh is available; otherwise, the Monday call remains unchanged  
    - The team will cancel meetings during Thanksgiving week due to low availability and holidays (28:11)  

- **December planning sessions** are anticipated to finalize offers and campaign tweaks ahead of the peak lead generation window in early 2026 (25:48)  
    - These sessions will build on the Benchmark Report success and integrate upcoming website and webinar content launches  
    - Sam will provide updated customer lists and integration approvals ahead of next Monday’s call to support email outreach and messaging accuracy  

- Colin will send the slide deck from this meeting for reference, per Sam’s request (29:09)',
  '2025-11-13 18:30:00+00',
  'published',
  '[{"text":"Set up redirection from old to new webinar landing page URL (07:47)","completed":false},{"text":"Send Heyreach login credentials again for access (11:38)","completed":false},{"text":"Continue work on pushing Heyreach messages into HubSpot activity logs (10:55)","completed":false},{"text":"Share drafted website copy documents next week for review (13:42)","completed":false},{"text":"Update and rewrite LinkedIn ad copy reflecting feedback for clearer messaging (20:53)","completed":false},{"text":"Cancel meetings for Thanksgiving week (28:21)","completed":false},{"text":"Send slide deck as requested (29:09)","completed":false},{"text":"Confirm customer list for sending the survey email and inform Colin by end of day (09:34)","completed":false},{"text":"Reiterate with team about Heyreach access and integration details (11:30)","completed":false},{"text":"Provide a concrete list of approved integrations and permissions for marketing collateral ahead of next Tuesday’s call (14:21)","completed":false},{"text":"Slack Josh to verify customer list readiness for email send (09:38)","completed":false},{"text":"Get back to Colin with trigger info for a HubSpot workflow to tag New North leads (13:17)","completed":false},{"text":"Provide customer list and integration lists for upcoming reviews (28:47)","completed":false},{"text":"Send notifications via channel listing Heyreach responses for cleaning email recipient list (15:05)","completed":false},{"text":"Target initial survey email send for tomorrow (09:38)","completed":false},{"text":"Provide clarity on list of integrations approved for marketing mention (14:06)","completed":false}]'::jsonb,
