INSERT INTO compass_notes (contract_id, meeting_id, note_type, title, content_raw, note_date, status, action_items, is_auto_generated)
SELECT
  new_meeting.contract_id,
  new_meeting.meeting_id,
  'meeting',
  'Meeting Notes: Powerhouse Gym & Ideometry: Weekly Sync',
  '## **HubSpot System Stabilization and Workflow Optimization**

The team agreed that the core HubSpot system is nearing stability, with ongoing fixes focused on workflow overlaps and lead management (07:44).

- **Nina Belina reported resolving parallel workflow conflicts in HubSpot** by staggering start times, preventing contacts from being manually removed from lists (07:44)
    - This fix ensures contacts now appear correctly in both the hot and club visited lists without overlap.
    - Milan Wagner confirmed that sales added a "last activity" or "last engagement" date column to track contact interactions more accurately.
    - Nina clarified that HubSpot can only track context and activity going forward, not retroactively.
    - This update reduces daily system errors and improves lead tracking accuracy.

- **Milan Wagner and Yefei Jin agreed that HubSpot work remains the priority for this month**, reserving a **bucket of about 10 hours** monthly for ongoing HubSpot support and tweaks (19:30)
    - Colin Costigan confirmed **24 hours remain for this month’s work**, refreshed with a new purchase of **29 hours** at the start of the month (09:56).
    - The team expects HubSpot issues to taper off as workflows mature, aiming to avoid core fixes extending into December.
    - Yefei emphasized the need for early issue reporting to prevent prolonged workflow problems.
    - Milan noted that recent fixes on lead sources and contact methods have addressed most core HubSpot priorities (24:31).

- **Marketing drip campaigns are active and being validated for effectiveness**, with particular attention to Facebook meta leads and re-enrolling reinquired contacts (25:17)
    - Milan shared that the lead drip campaign has delivered emails to **1,022 leads** over two months and confirmed re-enrollment for repeat inquires will be turned back on.
    - Colin clarified that meta lead counts from HubSpot closely match form submissions, with minor differences due to reinquiries.
    - The team agreed all website form leads funnel through HubSpot workflows.
    - Ensuring drip campaigns reach all appropriate leads remains a key performance metric.

## **SMS Marketing Integration and Platform Evaluation**

The group is weighing options between HubSpot’s SMS marketing feature and Aircall’s third-party SMS platform, balancing cost and functionality (31:20).

- **HubSpot SMS marketing was favored for initial rollout due to lower costs and easier automation setup**, with estimated additional costs around **$600** (39:38)
    - Milan reported Aircall’s SMS platform costs approximately **$1,100 total** including per-message fees, nearly double HubSpot’s price (39:43).
    - HubSpot supports automated SMS triggered by lead status or form submissions, facilitating marketing workflows.
    - Milan is tasked with clarifying integration and trigger details between HubSpot, Aircall, and third-party SMS tools.
    - Yefei emphasized the value of starting with the cheaper HubSpot option for quicker setup and troubleshooting.

- **SMS marketing use cases include automated notifications for offers, first inquiries, and missed appointments**, enhancing engagement (32:26)
    - Responses to SMS messages would notify contact owners via email for follow-up through Aircall or HubSpot.
    - HubSpot would consolidate SMS replies into lead lists, while Aircall offers two-way texting within reps’ personal SMS platforms.
    - Milan has a scheduled call with a HubSpot rep to gather more technical details and pricing clarifications (39:16).
    - The team plans to test SMS flows and train Milan on editing and running campaigns to enable agile mid-month adjustments.

## **Website Development Strategy and Resource Allocation**

The team is balancing ongoing small fixes on the current Squarespace site against a potential larger WordPress redesign, mindful of resource constraints (09:39).

- **Colin explained that the current monthly hours (around 25) are mostly allocated between HubSpot and Squarespace facelift work**, limiting capacity for a full WordPress rebuild without additional contracts (10:18)
    - The option to start a WordPress redesign was discussed but would consume hours rapidly, leaving no time for HubSpot improvements.
    - Yefei suggested continuing small UI fixes on Squarespace for now, emphasizing planning for a future larger site build with e-commerce and POS integration.
    - Colin noted Shopify integration could be added as a simple button in Squarespace or as a dedicated page in a new WordPress site.
    - The team is deferring any major website overhaul until a comprehensive cost and timeline comparison is completed.

- **The team confirmed that unused hours roll over fully, with no partial hour forfeiture**, ensuring efficient use of purchased time (18:18)
    - Colin detailed **188 total hours purchased historically**, with about **180 hours delivered so far**, and a current credit of **22.25 hours** available (19:10).
    - This rollover enables flexibility during months with fluctuating workload demands.
    - Yefei emphasized the need to keep the current system stable before engaging in major website projects.
    - Milan agreed to monitor daily issues to help draw a clear line for system stability.

## **Data Track Integration and Documentation Preparation**

The team is preparing detailed documentation for a third party building a new POS system to replace Data Track, clarifying integration points and system rationale (04:21).

- **Yefei Jin and Milan Wagner are leading efforts to add context on Data Track’s key features and integration with HubSpot and Aircall**, aiming for delivery by Thursday (11:11)
    - Milan will add a new section summarizing Data Track’s **top five features**, focusing on sales processing and member check-in functions.
    - They will document why the team switched from Salesforce and Rank DNA to HubSpot and Aircall, highlighting cost and functionality benefits.
    - The document will outline the reasons for separating syncs (member status, transactions) and the cost/complexity of each (05:22).
    - Yefei stressed including in-scope and planned features like e-signature workflows, noting PandaDoc is a temporary workaround.

- **The document will provide a high-level overview first, with technical screenshots and details available upon follow-up requests**, managing client expectations (16:54)
    - Colin suggested providing screenshots from Make.com to show workflow complexity without overwhelming on initial calls.
    - Yefei expects Motion IQ to lead the initial meeting and ask questions to clarify integration needs.
    - The team will prepare to explain the rationale behind multiple syncs and the potential need for APIs.
    - This approach supports transparent vendor collaboration and informed POS system design.

## **Operational Process Improvements and Team Collaboration**

The team is focused on refining daily workflows and communication protocols to speed issue resolution and improve system reliability (20:12).

- **Yefei highlighted the need for rapid reporting of issues by gym staff to avoid delays in fixes**, aiming to eliminate core system bugs by December (23:50)
    - Milan acknowledged that while some occasional breaks occur, the majority of workflows are stable.
    - Nina clarified that some recent issues stemmed from adding workflows not originally designed for multiple parallel processes.
    - The team agreed that new feature requests are expected after core stability is reached.
    - Yefei proposed a goal of one full week without system breakage or urgent questions to mark stability (38:28).

- **Colin and Yefei plan to assist Milan with HubSpot workflow management training**, enabling more autonomous control of marketing lists and campaign adjustments (40:11)
    - Milan has started exploring HubSpot’s flow pages but has not yet made changes.
    - Colin assured that workflow editing is straightforward once the necessary contact properties and triggers are understood.
    - This training will reduce dependency on external support and allow faster mid-month campaign tweaks.
    - The team will continue collaborating closely on HubSpot and Squarespace tasks to maintain progress.

