    '{"id":"01K9ABNAGPSJKSQD60VDFQX2BT","title":"Ponce Bank // MiD: Weekly Marketing Meeting","summary":{"notes":"## **Communication and Collaboration Setup**\n\nThe team agreed to improve communication channels by moving from email to Slack for faster, clearer project coordination (06:50).\n\n- **Tristan Pelligrino committed to setting up a dedicated Slack channel** today to replace slower email threads (06:50)  \n    - Slack will centralize updates and quick questions, addressing Victor Garcia’s concern about emails getting lost  \n    - Victor confirmed Slack invites are the only requirement to join on their side, signaling readiness for adoption  \n    - Colin Costigan noted Christina’s recent request to hold off on Slack until app download feasibility is confirmed, causing a brief pause  \n    - The team plans to monitor Slack adoption and adjust process if needed for better engagement  \n\n- **Victor highlighted the need for organized project tracking similar to Asana, aiming to replicate that structure within HubSpot** (08:29)  \n    - Tristan introduced Pulse, their real-time status portal synced with ClickUp, which tracks tasks and contract hours (09:25)  \n    - Victor and Christina need to accept Pulse invites to access up-to-date project progress and resource usage  \n    - This system is key to avoid miscommunication and ensure transparency as development intensifies  \n    - The approach aligns with Victor’s goal to keep deliverables and requests clearly documented and visible  \n\n## **HubSpot Integration and Sales Process Enhancement**\n\nThe team clarified that HubSpot can support advanced cross-sell recommendations if enriched with accurate customer data and defined sales logic (12:25).\n\n- **Tristan explained HubSpot’s flexibility with custom objects to map any sales-related data, enabling tailored upsell and cross-sell suggestions** (12:25)  \n    - The technical capability depends on the quality and completeness of data attached to each contact  \n    - Business logic for product recommendations must be defined clearly before automation can work effectively  \n    - Colin added that integration with core systems like MuleSoft or Salesforce will determine how much data flows into HubSpot (13:33)  \n    - The team must coordinate with backend systems to ensure relevant account and product info is synchronized  \n\n- **Victor emphasized the bank’s cautious stance on AI tools due to data integrity concerns but noted the potential for faster, smarter customer experience** (14:07)  \n    - He aims to shift perception to see AI as an enabler for better sales results and customer service  \n    - The discussion revealed a strategic tension between innovation and data security that will need ongoing management  \n    - This sets a context for careful AI integration planning, balancing risk with efficiency gains  \n\n## **Survey Deployment and Feedback Collection**\n\nThe team planned to finalize and distribute a targeted survey by Friday to gather customer insights, with results due by the 14th (15:04).\n\n- **Colin and Tristan are updating the survey to include flow logic that tailors questions to respondents, improving data quality and engagement** (15:04)  \n    - This approach reduces survey fatigue by preventing irrelevant questions  \n    - Victor will handle the email sending using the bank’s existing contact list once the survey is finalized  \n    - The team agreed to provide Victor with both raw data and summarized reports for full transparency (15:38)  \n    - This feedback loop will inform ongoing project decisions and measure early success  \n\n- **Victor strongly supports using Slack to keep the team organized and responsive during survey rollout and later project phases** (15:47)  \n    - Tristan and Colin confirmed Slack is their main internal and client communication channel (16:04)  \n    - While Victor proposed multiple Slack channels by project area, Tristan recommended keeping it simpler with one channel per client to avoid complexity (16:22)  \n    - The team agreed on this streamlined approach to maintain clarity and ease of use  \n\n## **Project Planning and Timeline Alignment**\n\nThe project plan and survey updates are being synchronized to maintain a clear timeline and deliverable tracking (16:48).\n\n- **Colin is adjusting project dates and adding references to Asana to align with the survey schedule and client expectations** (16:48)  \n    - Christina requested these adjustments to integrate task management with familiar tools for stakeholders  \n    - This reflects a priority on transparency and ease of tracking progress across teams  \n    - The planned survey launch on Friday and results by the 14th set concrete milestones that drive project pacing  \n    - Victor confirmed satisfaction with the current coordination and timeline, signaling readiness to proceed (16:57)","outline":null,"keywords":["HubSpot Integration","Project Communication","Survey Implementation","CRM Cross-Selling","Slack Collaboration","Data Integrity"],"overview":"- **Communication Shift to Slack:** Move from email to Slack for quicker updates and clearer project coordination.  \n- **Dedicated Slack Channel Setup:** A new Slack channel will centralize communication, addressing concerns over email visibility.  \n- **HubSpot Enhancements for Sales:** HubSpot can provide customized recommendations if integrated with accurate customer data.  \n- **Cautious AI Adoption:** The bank is careful about AI tools due to data security but sees potential for improved customer service.  \n- **Targeted Customer Survey Launch:** A survey will be finalized by Friday, aiming for insights by the 14th.  \n- **Project Timeline Alignment:** Project dates are being adjusted to synchronize with the survey schedule and maintain clarity.","action_items":"\n**Colin Costigan**\nAdjust and update the project plan with new dates and include Asana references, integrating with survey updates (16:48)\nFinalize survey flow logic, test, and deliver the updated survey for review ahead of Friday send-out (15:04)\nResend Pulse project management tool invites to Victor and Christina (09:25)\n\n**Tristan Pelligrino**\nSet up and send Slack channel invitation once client confirms ability to download/use Slack (06:50)\nProvide detailed survey report, summarizing and sharing raw data after survey completion (15:38)\nResend Pulse invites and explain the tool’s functionality to client (09:25)\n\n**Victor Garcia**\nDecide on Slack adoption on client side and coordinate internally for Slack invitation acceptance (15:58)\nReview and provide feedback on the updated project plan and survey once received (16:48)\nFollow up internally on the AI integration concerns to reconcile faster insights with data integrity policy (14:07)\n"},"duration":17.139999389648438,"speakers":[{"id":0,"name":"Colin Costigan"},{"id":1,"name":"victor garcia"},{"id":2,"name":"Tristan Pelligrino"}],"sentences":[{"text":"Hey, Victor.","index":0,"end_time":251.77,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":250.89,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It.","index":1,"end_time":255.78,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":255.54,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"How''s it going, Tristan?","index":2,"end_time":282.11,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":281.31,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"What''s going on?","index":3,"end_time":283.31,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":282.59,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Do we have Victor on or.","index":4,"end_time":284.67,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":283.31,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"I think he joined a few.","index":5,"end_time":286.19,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":284.99,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I just got an email that he joined a few minutes ago, but I haven''t seen him pop up.","index":6,"end_time":293.31,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":286.51,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Gotcha.","index":7,"end_time":294.99,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":294.27,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Sorry about that, guys.","index":8,"end_time":301.79,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":300.83,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"I literally just.","index":9,"end_time":302.75,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":301.79,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"I''ve been in one meeting, and then it called me because of DNS changes.","index":10,"end_time":307.51,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":302.99,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"So back and forth, all good.","index":11,"end_time":310.1,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":307.51,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"How are you doing, Victor?","index":12,"end_time":311.38,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":310.26,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I''m doing great.","index":13,"end_time":314.1,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":312.9,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Doing great.","index":14,"end_time":314.86,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":314.26,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Can''t complain.","index":15,"end_time":315.62,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":314.86,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"How are you guys doing?","index":16,"end_time":316.66,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":315.7,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Doing all right.","index":17,"end_time":318.02,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":317.22,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I won''t speak for Tristan, I guess.","index":18,"end_time":321.38,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":319.86,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Tristan, are you doing all right?","index":19,"end_time":322.54,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":321.38,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I''m doing all right, too.","index":20,"end_time":323.62,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":322.54,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":21,"end_time":324.18,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":323.7,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Looks pretty locked in.","index":22,"end_time":325.5,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":324.5,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"So I didn''t want to, you know, cash so really quick, guys, just because I know that this is a big project and, you know, I want to make sure that I respect y'' all times and how we communicate.","index":23,"end_time":338.66,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":325.5,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"I didn''t want to be intrusive and say, hey, we should do this, but I don''t.","index":24,"end_time":342.54,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":339.14,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"I''m not sure if you guys do that with other clients.","index":25,"end_time":345.62,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":342.54,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"You know, typically with a project like this, how is it that you guys communicate?","index":26,"end_time":349.62,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":346.5,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Yeah, I mean, I can talk to that, Colin.","index":27,"end_time":352.86,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":350.9,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"I mean, the big thing, Victor, we have, you know, the weekly meetings in place, and we.","index":28,"end_time":358.74,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":352.86,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"We had that Monday.","index":29,"end_time":359.62,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":358.74,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"You.","index":30,"end_time":359.86,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":359.62,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"I think you were on PTO for that one, right?","index":31,"end_time":361.7,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":359.86,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Or.","index":32,"end_time":362.18,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":361.78,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":33,"end_time":362.74,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":362.26,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"But now with Christina making these changes, she''s only suggesting that the.","index":34,"end_time":366.98,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":362.74,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"The head of that person is in meetings instead of everybody, and then if that person''s not in, then that other person substitutes.","index":35,"end_time":373.07,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":366.98,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"So you''re not going to see all of us all the time anymore.","index":36,"end_time":376.11,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":373.31,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Okay.","index":37,"end_time":376.91,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":376.27,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So, yeah, there might be.","index":38,"end_time":378.91,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":377.71,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Try to figure out the best way to, you know, because we have a couple pieces here to.","index":39,"end_time":384.19,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":379.31,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"To communicate.","index":40,"end_time":385.27,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":384.27,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So one, weekly meetings, which are great.","index":41,"end_time":387.79,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":385.27,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"That''s where we go through, you know, status action items and things like that.","index":42,"end_time":392.67,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":388.67,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Number two, we.","index":43,"end_time":394.67,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":393.55,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"We often do set up dedicated Slack channels with our clients so we can share information, like, directly and.","index":44,"end_time":401.79,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":394.67,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"And, you know, much faster than.","index":45,"end_time":403.71,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":401.79,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Than email, per se.","index":46,"end_time":404.87,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":403.71,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Do you know what the requirements are on your side for.","index":47,"end_time":409.03,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":405.75,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"For joining a Slack community?","index":48,"end_time":410.55,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":409.11,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Send us the invite.","index":49,"end_time":411.79,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":410.63,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"That''s the requirement.","index":50,"end_time":412.59,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":411.79,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Send us the invite.","index":51,"end_time":413.59,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":412.59,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Okay.","index":52,"end_time":414.47,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":413.99,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"All right, we will do that.","index":53,"end_time":415.51,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":414.47,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"I''ll.","index":54,"end_time":415.79,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":415.51,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"I''ll set that up, Colin.","index":55,"end_time":417.27,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":415.79,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"We.","index":56,"end_time":418.79,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":418.47,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"We''ll get that in place today, but.","index":57,"end_time":421.51,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":418.79,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Because Christina''s email was to hold off on.","index":58,"end_time":424.17,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":421.93,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Oh, was it?","index":59,"end_time":425.21,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":424.33,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Let''s keep email for now until I see if we can download Slack.","index":60,"end_time":430.33,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":426.41,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then she asked about text.","index":61,"end_time":432.49,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":431.05,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"She sent that two hours ago.","index":62,"end_time":434.97,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":433.53,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Oh, you''re right.","index":63,"end_time":437.77,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":437.05,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"No, I do see it.","index":64,"end_time":439.57,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":438.33,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"You''re copied on it.","index":65,"end_time":440.41,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":439.57,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Victor, hold on.","index":66,"end_time":442.81,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":440.41,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"It was in the email that you created the HubSpot survey link.","index":67,"end_time":446.57,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":442.81,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":68,"end_time":447.53,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":446.97,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Communication.","index":69,"end_time":448.25,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":447.61,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"The survey link.","index":70,"end_time":450.46,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":449.5,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Let''s keep.","index":71,"end_time":453.02,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":452.38,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Oh, I missed that part.","index":72,"end_time":454.42,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":453.02,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Maybe I thought that that was for something else.","index":73,"end_time":456.22,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":454.42,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Until I see if we can download Slack first.","index":74,"end_time":458.66,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":456.46,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Perhaps for quick questions.","index":75,"end_time":459.94,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":458.66,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Can we just text?","index":76,"end_time":460.94,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":459.94,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"I think text would be worse than email.","index":77,"end_time":464.06,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":461.82,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I completely agree.","index":78,"end_time":465.98,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":464.54,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"All right, so let me.","index":79,"end_time":468.78,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":467.26,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Give me one second because I want to take care of this now.","index":80,"end_time":471.66,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":469.5,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"I''m not going to wait for this.","index":81,"end_time":473.1,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":471.66,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Can I reach.","index":82,"end_time":475.02,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":474.22,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Oh, all right.","index":83,"end_time":495.56,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":476.28,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"So that.","index":84,"end_time":496.52,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":495.88,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"That''s in play right now.","index":85,"end_time":497.6,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":496.52,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"So I''ll keep you guys posted on that text.","index":86,"end_time":500.04,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":497.6,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Sorry to say, trash email, hate it.","index":87,"end_time":504.13,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":501.25,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Get.","index":88,"end_time":504.65,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":504.29,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Everything gets lost.","index":89,"end_time":505.57,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":504.65,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"I think we''re on the same page about that all across the board.","index":90,"end_time":508.45,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":505.81,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Listen, I. I''ve.","index":91,"end_time":510.29,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":509.09,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"What you guys do, I do on a very, very small scale.","index":92,"end_time":514.77,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":510.69,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"So I literally just had a client download Asana and I literally put them through the ringer of.","index":93,"end_time":520.77,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":514.85,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"This is how we''re going to stay organized.","index":94,"end_time":522.37,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":520.93,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"For every project.","index":95,"end_time":523.09,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":522.37,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"You want these deliverables, you put that in there so that I know what you guys want.","index":96,"end_time":527.01,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":523.17,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"And.","index":97,"end_time":527.38,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":527.17,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"And I kind of want it to feel the same way with HubSpot because everybody has wants and needs and I want to make sure that I kind of.","index":98,"end_time":534.65,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":527.45,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"That we.","index":99,"end_time":535.21,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":534.65,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Sorry.","index":100,"end_time":535.85,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":535.29,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Get things done on that.","index":101,"end_time":537.85,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":536.25,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Yes.","index":102,"end_time":539.61,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":539.13,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"So.","index":103,"end_time":540.13,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":539.85,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":104,"end_time":540.37,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":540.13,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So.","index":105,"end_time":540.57,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":540.37,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So, Victor.","index":106,"end_time":541.09,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":540.57,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Yes.","index":107,"end_time":541.29,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":541.09,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Slack''s big.","index":108,"end_time":542.33,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":541.29,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"We can get that set up.","index":109,"end_time":544.09,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":542.73,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So we''ll wait on your queue there.","index":110,"end_time":546.89,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":545.21,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"The other piece is we have Pulse in place that we''ve sent invites to that gives you a real time status into tasks within our project management.","index":111,"end_time":558.25,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":547.69,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"I see that you and Christina are both invited, but doesn''t look like you''ve accepted that invite yet.","index":112,"end_time":565.03,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":559.75,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"If you can resend that.","index":113,"end_time":566.27,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":565.11,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"I''m not sure what Pulse is, but I will definitely look into that.","index":114,"end_time":569.11,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":566.27,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Yeah, that''s our own system basically that gives you all the tasks to dos everything.","index":115,"end_time":575.99,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":569.27,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"And I think as things start to get more frequent, once we are actually in the weeds and developing things, it would be good to make sure you''re on top of that because our team works.","index":116,"end_time":589.69,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":576.15,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So basically, you know, if you have Asana, you all use Asana internally, is that right?","index":117,"end_time":593.89,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":589.69,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"For Project Manager, so we use ClickUp, very similar.","index":118,"end_time":596.81,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":593.89,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"But this view, Victor gives you the same information and ClickUp that we have.","index":119,"end_time":602.53,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":597.05,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"It''s actually pulling the data out and presenting it to you in a portal.","index":120,"end_time":605.69,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":602.53,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So this is also what tracks the hours for your contract as well.","index":121,"end_time":610.53,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":606.09,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So you can see how many hours were used in a month.","index":122,"end_time":612.53,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":610.53,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"All of that is in place.","index":123,"end_time":613.69,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":612.53,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So we''ll resend those Invites out to you and Christina today.","index":124,"end_time":618.23,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":613.69,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"And then so that''s, you know, key for.","index":125,"end_time":622.31,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":619.03,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"For status and then anything else there.","index":126,"end_time":624.63,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":622.31,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Victor, before we move on to, you know, the specific surveys and such, I.","index":127,"end_time":631.39,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":624.63,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Mean, I did have a. I mean, I guess this goes into a completely new topic and thought process.","index":128,"end_time":636.47,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":631.39,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Had a meeting.","index":129,"end_time":639.27,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":638.23,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"It has to do with HubSpot.","index":130,"end_time":640.91,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":639.67,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"But before we do that, I think we''re done here.","index":131,"end_time":643.47,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":640.91,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Unless there''s any other comments from Colin.","index":132,"end_time":645.24,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":643.47,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"No, I got all the notes and everything from the team and Christina on the spreadsheet and the questionnaire.","index":133,"end_time":652.35,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":646.19,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And so we''re just making those tweaks and we''ll send that over to you.","index":134,"end_time":654.75,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":652.35,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, cool.","index":135,"end_time":655.87,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":654.91,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Obviously, I don''t know what your capabilities are, but I''m assuming that you guys, from what Christina told me, you guys did this HubSpot integration with the other bank that she worked with, correct?","index":136,"end_time":666.19,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":657.15,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Yeah, we, we did that ideometry did.","index":137,"end_time":669.55,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":666.99,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"And then just markers in demand overall have.","index":138,"end_time":672.43,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":669.55,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"I mean, Colin and I are working on other migrations right now.","index":139,"end_time":676.51,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":672.71,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So.","index":140,"end_time":676.75,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":676.51,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Yeah, we''re right in the middle of this.","index":141,"end_time":678.39,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":676.75,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Okay.","index":142,"end_time":679.35,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":678.79,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"So the question that I had was I had a meeting last week with a Bank of America exec and they kind of threw at me what they do for their sales process.","index":143,"end_time":692.31,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":679.67,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"And I thought that this was pretty interesting that we don''t have it.","index":144,"end_time":695.59,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":692.79,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"But then again, we''re a small bank, so I would.","index":145,"end_time":697.71,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":695.59,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"I''m not surprised either when a customer, when a customer walks in and they type in their name into the CRM, the CRM gives them a, you know, a 30,000 foot view on what they could potentially sell.","index":146,"end_time":711.78,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":697.71,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Sell their customers based on what they have in their profile, their accounts, whatever.","index":147,"end_time":717.46,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":712.02,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"So if, let''s say, you know, customer walks in and he owns three properties with our bank and you know, a few mortgages that were able to cross sell him into potentially, you know, opening a business account or such.","index":148,"end_time":733.63,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":717.78,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Does HubSpot have that capability where if we plug in certain things that they can suggest to cross sell certain things based on that customer''s criteria, it all.","index":149,"end_time":745.99,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":734.91,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Really boils down to data attached to the, to the contact.","index":150,"end_time":749.07,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":745.99,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"I mean, HubSpot has custom objects that pretty much give you the ability to really define any kind of object that you like.","index":151,"end_time":757.08,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":749.15,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So it''s really about the data.","index":152,"end_time":759.56,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":758.04,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Can we get accurate data?","index":153,"end_time":761.28,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":759.8,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Can we attach it to or assign it to a specific contact?","index":154,"end_time":764.36,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":761.28,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"And then what''s the logic to say, hey, you know, here, here are the existing products.","index":155,"end_time":770.28,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":764.84,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Right.","index":156,"end_time":770.68,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":770.36,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"For an existing customer, what are, what''s the upsell or cross sell logic that we want to put in place.","index":157,"end_time":776.12,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":770.68,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So I think technically, the flexibility is there.","index":158,"end_time":781.23,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":777.08,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"It''s more even on the business process.","index":159,"end_time":782.87,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":781.23,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"I think it might even be the hardest part to.","index":160,"end_time":784.79,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":782.87,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"To figure out or to work through.","index":161,"end_time":786.39,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":784.79,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"The business process on who''s in.","index":162,"end_time":788.27,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":786.87,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"On Bonsen or on.","index":163,"end_time":789.59,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":788.27,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Yeah, just like what.","index":164,"end_time":790.71,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":789.75,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Like, how do you do.","index":165,"end_time":791.87,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":790.95,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"What are the products that you want to define and attach?","index":166,"end_time":794.47,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":791.87,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Like, where does that information come from?","index":167,"end_time":796.03,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":794.47,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"How do we attach it to the contact record?","index":168,"end_time":797.83,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":796.03,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"What''s the logic?","index":169,"end_time":799.27,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":798.31,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"You know, all of that.","index":170,"end_time":800.23,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":799.27,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So the capability of us giving that.","index":171,"end_time":802.95,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":800.23,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"You know, that.","index":172,"end_time":803.87,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":803.11,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"That push to.","index":173,"end_time":805.39,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":803.87,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"To our sales team is there.","index":174,"end_time":807.15,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":805.39,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"It''s just we have to fill the criteria for it.","index":175,"end_time":809.43,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":807.31,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"That''s all.","index":176,"end_time":809.83,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":809.43,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"I.","index":177,"end_time":810.11,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":809.83,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"That''s.","index":178,"end_time":810.79,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":810.35,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, because I really.","index":179,"end_time":812.67,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":810.79,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Oh, sorry.","index":180,"end_time":813.23,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":812.75,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Go ahead.","index":181,"end_time":813.55,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":813.23,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"I was gonna say it''s really going to largely depend on this, like, mulesoft Salesforce, other core possible, like, conversation.","index":182,"end_time":820.83,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":813.63,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Because, you know, as Tristan mentioned, it depends on the criteria.","index":183,"end_time":824.39,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":820.909,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So if we have information in the HubSpot workflow that''s like, this is their bank balance.","index":184,"end_time":828.91,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":824.39,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"This is how many properties they''re signed up with you on.","index":185,"end_time":831.75,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":829.15,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"This is, you know, X, Y and Z that would say, like, okay, cool.","index":186,"end_time":834.87,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":831.75,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Let''s see if they want to do this.","index":187,"end_time":836.03,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":834.87,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All of that information tied to that contact record in HubSpot.","index":188,"end_time":839.85,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":836.89,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So if it really depends on how much we can get shared from mulesoft Salesforce, you know, however we set that integration up.","index":189,"end_time":846.81,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":839.85,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Got you.","index":190,"end_time":847.97,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":847.29,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Okay.","index":191,"end_time":848.57,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":847.97,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"So, yeah, the.","index":192,"end_time":850.37,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":848.57,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"The biggest thing that this bank.","index":193,"end_time":852.17,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":850.37,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"And you guys saw the email.","index":194,"end_time":854.29,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":852.25,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"When it comes to this whole AI thing, the.","index":195,"end_time":856.17,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":854.29,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"The bank is scared of that whole thing because of data and data integrity, in a sense, which I completely understand.","index":196,"end_time":862.49,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":856.17,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"But we also need to understand that if we have this information in a faster, quicker, efficient way, we''re able to produce better results for.","index":197,"end_time":869.78,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":862.65,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"And a better experience for our customers.","index":198,"end_time":871.62,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":869.86,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"So if we have some type of AI tool that kind of gives us.","index":199,"end_time":875.3,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":872.18,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"That syncs everything together and, you know, suggests certain things that makes our job easier.","index":200,"end_time":881.22,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":875.62,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"They don''t see it that way.","index":201,"end_time":882.98,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":881.78,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"I''m trying to make it that way.","index":202,"end_time":884.42,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":883.06,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, I got you.","index":203,"end_time":886.58,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":884.98,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right, so we''re good on that note, then, surveys.","index":204,"end_time":890.94,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":887.14,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"I have no problem sending them over a link so that I can develop the email since we already have the emails in house.","index":205,"end_time":897.34,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":892.06,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"From what I read, we''re able to bump that timeline to when Friday, I.","index":206,"end_time":904.86,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":899.9,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Think, is when Christina wants to get that email out.","index":207,"end_time":906.7,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":904.86,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So Tristan and I are working on the updated survey today to have, like, all the flow logic and everything, because we don''t need everyone answering every question.","index":208,"end_time":914.22,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":906.7,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But so we''re building that and we''re going to test it and then send that over to you guys to review so it can be sent out to the team on Friday and then all results back, I think, by the 14th.","index":209,"end_time":926.15,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":915.5,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yep.","index":210,"end_time":927.03,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":926.47,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"And obviously, you guys are going to be able to see those results.","index":211,"end_time":931.19,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":928.87,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Are we going to see those results as well?","index":212,"end_time":932.87,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":931.19,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah.","index":213,"end_time":934.03,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":933.19,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I mean, basically, in the back end of the form builder we''re using, it''ll be like a spreadsheet.","index":214,"end_time":937.11,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":934.03,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, cool.","index":215,"end_time":938.63,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":937.51,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"So, yeah, we''ll get you a report, like, on the summary and the insights.","index":216,"end_time":942.99,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":938.79,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Victor, we''ll give you the raw data, too, just so you can see where it came from.","index":217,"end_time":947.02,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":942.99,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So please.","index":218,"end_time":947.82,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":947.1,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Okay.","index":219,"end_time":949.34,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":948.78,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"I mean, that.","index":220,"end_time":949.9,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":949.34,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"That''s it for me personally.","index":221,"end_time":951.34,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":949.9,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"I. I want to try to push that slack thing, because if we can stay organized through there, that''ll make our lives 10 times easier.","index":222,"end_time":958.54,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":951.34,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"We agree.","index":223,"end_time":960.14,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":958.7,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"We, like, we''re in slack all day.","index":224,"end_time":962.94,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":961.1,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"I mean, that''s what we.","index":225,"end_time":963.94,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":963.02,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"That''s what we.","index":226,"end_time":964.5,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":963.94,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"That''s our internal and our client, like, main channel.","index":227,"end_time":967.42,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":964.5,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We''re up for it, man.","index":228,"end_time":968.86,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":967.66,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"I.","index":229,"end_time":969.5,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":969.1,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"100%.","index":230,"end_time":970.42,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":969.74,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Do you guys break it down not just for the channel itself, but do you break it down where it''s like.","index":231,"end_time":975.97,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":970.42,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Let''s say we''re doing data integration in one channel and then design in another?","index":232,"end_time":981.29,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":975.97,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"We typically don''t just because, you know, we''re working with, like, one or two people typically, you know, on the other side.","index":233,"end_time":988.01,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":982.41,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So it just makes that more complex.","index":234,"end_time":989.61,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":988.01,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So we would have, like, a ponsse markers in demand channel and then work through that.","index":235,"end_time":994.33,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":989.69,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Yeah, got it.","index":236,"end_time":995.29,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":994.49,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Okay, perfect.","index":237,"end_time":996.17,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":995.29,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"So we''re good to go, guys.","index":238,"end_time":997.61,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":996.25,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"I''ll figure out on my end about this whole slack thing, and I''ll wait on you guys for the.","index":239,"end_time":1003.34,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":998.86,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"For the survey, and we''ll go from there.","index":240,"end_time":1005.86,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1004.14,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Oh, and the updated project plan as well?","index":241,"end_time":1008.3,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1005.86,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Yeah, I''m kind of looping that in with the survey updates.","index":242,"end_time":1011.06,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1008.86,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, cool.","index":243,"end_time":1011.74,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1011.06,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Yeah, I got the spreadsheet.","index":244,"end_time":1012.54,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1011.74,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I just have to adjust some dates, and Christina wanted me to add in some references to, like, asana, so.","index":245,"end_time":1017.34,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1012.54,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Sounds good.","index":246,"end_time":1018.54,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1017.82,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"So we''re good to go, guys.","index":247,"end_time":1019.78,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1018.62,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Thank you.","index":248,"end_time":1020.22,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1019.78,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":249,"end_time":1020.62,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1020.22,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right.","index":250,"end_time":1020.98,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1020.62,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Thanks, Victor.","index":251,"end_time":1021.5,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1020.98,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"All right, thanks, Victor.","index":252,"end_time":1022.22,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1021.5,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You too.","index":253,"end_time":1023.58,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1023.02,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"}],"dateString":"2025-11-05T18:00:00.000Z","host_email":"colin.costigan@marketersindemand.com","meeting_link":"https://us02web.zoom.us/j/84571935764?pwd=dHf4atV26KWfJUFOcbonT5MjgpBJu5.1","participants":["tristan.pelligrino@marketersindemand.com,colin.costigan@marketersindemand.com,victor.garcia@poncebank.net","tristan.pelligrino@marketersindemand.com","victor.garcia@poncebank.net"],"transcript_url":"https://app.fireflies.ai/view/01K9ABNAGPSJKSQD60VDFQX2BT","organizer_email":"colin.costigan@marketersindemand.com"}'::jsonb,
    '{"label":"positive","confidence":0.9,"bullets":["Aligned on using weekly meetings and Pulse for project tracking and task transparency.","Deferred Slack rollout pending Christina''s confirmation; email remains primary for now.","Confirmed survey launch Friday with responses due by the 14th; custom logic in place.","Explored HubSpot''s cross-sell potential; Victor to define business logic and data inputs.","Colin to update project plan and survey spreadsheet with new dates and Asana references."],"highlights":[{"quote":"I want to try to push that slack thing, because if we can stay organized through there, that''ll make our lives 10 times easier.","speaker":"Victor Garcia"},{"quote":"Pulse gives you a real time status into tasks within our project management.","speaker":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"quote":"We''re building that and we''re going to test it and then send that over to you guys to review.","speaker":"Colin Costigan"}],"topics":["delivery","communication","integration","survey"],"model":"openai/gpt-4-1106-preview","version":1,"generated_at":"2025-11-13T00:00:00Z"}'::jsonb,
    '{"fireflies_summary":{"notes":"## **Communication and Collaboration Setup**\n\nThe team agreed to improve communication channels by moving from email to Slack for faster, clearer project coordination (06:50).\n\n- **Tristan Pelligrino committed to setting up a dedicated Slack channel** today to replace slower email threads (06:50)  \n    - Slack will centralize updates and quick questions, addressing Victor Garcia’s concern about emails getting lost  \n    - Victor confirmed Slack invites are the only requirement to join on their side, signaling readiness for adoption  \n    - Colin Costigan noted Christina’s recent request to hold off on Slack until app download feasibility is confirmed, causing a brief pause  \n    - The team plans to monitor Slack adoption and adjust process if needed for better engagement  \n\n- **Victor highlighted the need for organized project tracking similar to Asana, aiming to replicate that structure within HubSpot** (08:29)  \n    - Tristan introduced Pulse, their real-time status portal synced with ClickUp, which tracks tasks and contract hours (09:25)  \n    - Victor and Christina need to accept Pulse invites to access up-to-date project progress and resource usage  \n    - This system is key to avoid miscommunication and ensure transparency as development intensifies  \n    - The approach aligns with Victor’s goal to keep deliverables and requests clearly documented and visible  \n\n## **HubSpot Integration and Sales Process Enhancement**\n\nThe team clarified that HubSpot can support advanced cross-sell recommendations if enriched with accurate customer data and defined sales logic (12:25).\n\n- **Tristan explained HubSpot’s flexibility with custom objects to map any sales-related data, enabling tailored upsell and cross-sell suggestions** (12:25)  \n    - The technical capability depends on the quality and completeness of data attached to each contact  \n    - Business logic for product recommendations must be defined clearly before automation can work effectively  \n    - Colin added that integration with core systems like MuleSoft or Salesforce will determine how much data flows into HubSpot (13:33)  \n    - The team must coordinate with backend systems to ensure relevant account and product info is synchronized  \n\n- **Victor emphasized the bank’s cautious stance on AI tools due to data integrity concerns but noted the potential for faster, smarter customer experience** (14:07)  \n    - He aims to shift perception to see AI as an enabler for better sales results and customer service  \n    - The discussion revealed a strategic tension between innovation and data security that will need ongoing management  \n    - This sets a context for careful AI integration planning, balancing risk with efficiency gains  \n\n## **Survey Deployment and Feedback Collection**\n\nThe team planned to finalize and distribute a targeted survey by Friday to gather customer insights, with results due by the 14th (15:04).\n\n- **Colin and Tristan are updating the survey to include flow logic that tailors questions to respondents, improving data quality and engagement** (15:04)  \n    - This approach reduces survey fatigue by preventing irrelevant questions  \n    - Victor will handle the email sending using the bank’s existing contact list once the survey is finalized  \n    - The team agreed to provide Victor with both raw data and summarized reports for full transparency (15:38)  \n    - This feedback loop will inform ongoing project decisions and measure early success  \n\n- **Victor strongly supports using Slack to keep the team organized and responsive during survey rollout and later project phases** (15:47)  \n    - Tristan and Colin confirmed Slack is their main internal and client communication channel (16:04)  \n    - While Victor proposed multiple Slack channels by project area, Tristan recommended keeping it simpler with one channel per client to avoid complexity (16:22)  \n    - The team agreed on this streamlined approach to maintain clarity and ease of use  \n\n## **Project Planning and Timeline Alignment**\n\nThe project plan and survey updates are being synchronized to maintain a clear timeline and deliverable tracking (16:48).\n\n- **Colin is adjusting project dates and adding references to Asana to align with the survey schedule and client expectations** (16:48)  \n    - Christina requested these adjustments to integrate task management with familiar tools for stakeholders  \n    - This reflects a priority on transparency and ease of tracking progress across teams  \n    - The planned survey launch on Friday and results by the 14th set concrete milestones that drive project pacing  \n    - Victor confirmed satisfaction with the current coordination and timeline, signaling readiness to proceed (16:57)","outline":null,"keywords":["HubSpot Integration","Project Communication","Survey Implementation","CRM Cross-Selling","Slack Collaboration","Data Integrity"],"overview":"- **Communication Shift to Slack:** Move from email to Slack for quicker updates and clearer project coordination.  \n- **Dedicated Slack Channel Setup:** A new Slack channel will centralize communication, addressing concerns over email visibility.  \n- **HubSpot Enhancements for Sales:** HubSpot can provide customized recommendations if integrated with accurate customer data.  \n- **Cautious AI Adoption:** The bank is careful about AI tools due to data security but sees potential for improved customer service.  \n- **Targeted Customer Survey Launch:** A survey will be finalized by Friday, aiming for insights by the 14th.  \n- **Project Timeline Alignment:** Project dates are being adjusted to synchronize with the survey schedule and maintain clarity.","action_items":"\n**Colin Costigan**\nAdjust and update the project plan with new dates and include Asana references, integrating with survey updates (16:48)\nFinalize survey flow logic, test, and deliver the updated survey for review ahead of Friday send-out (15:04)\nResend Pulse project management tool invites to Victor and Christina (09:25)\n\n**Tristan Pelligrino**\nSet up and send Slack channel invitation once client confirms ability to download/use Slack (06:50)\nProvide detailed survey report, summarizing and sharing raw data after survey completion (15:38)\nResend Pulse invites and explain the tool’s functionality to client (09:25)\n\n**Victor Garcia**\nDecide on Slack adoption on client side and coordinate internally for Slack invitation acceptance (15:58)\nReview and provide feedback on the updated project plan and survey once received (16:48)\nFollow up internally on the AI integration concerns to reconcile faster insights with data integrity policy (14:07)\n"},"migrated_from":"contract_meetings","original_id":"e9adb87e-2111-4fc8-88fd-df00d1e697d2","master_marketer":{"status":"migrated"}}'::jsonb,
