-- Meeting: MiD//Noetic: Weekly Set Meeting  5/8 - Onwards (2025-11-05 19:00:00+00)
WITH new_meeting AS (
  INSERT INTO compass_meetings (contract_id, meeting_date, source, external_id, title, participants, duration_seconds, recording_url, transcript, sentiment, raw_metadata, created_at, updated_at)
  VALUES (
    '1f878142-1760-4df2-805b-1f114427475d',
    '2025-11-05 19:00:00+00',
    'fireflies',
    '01K8RZDWWAKQEF05S4AHTKERM7',
    'MiD//Noetic: Weekly Set Meeting  5/8 - Onwards',
    '{"nancieruder","Rachel Curtis","Colin Costigan","Colin Costigan","Nathalie Mintjens"}'::text[],
    3890,
    'https://us02web.zoom.us/j/85039954260?pwd=7GrXTMosQASbwQapyiVncGn3aAbQCz.1',
    '{"id":"01K8RZDWWAKQEF05S4AHTKERM7","title":"MiD//Noetic: Weekly Set Meeting  5/8 - Onwards","summary":{"notes":"## **Podcast Production and Asset Management**\n\nThe team confirmed enhancements to podcast workflows and asset usage to reduce delays and improve content quality.\n\n- **Nancy** and **Rachel** agreed to pause on the volume of **quote cards** to assess their value and streamline production (09:01)  \n    - **Colin** explained quote cards help readers quickly assess content relevance before watching videos.  \n    - They decided to pre-select concise, polished quotes via email for review before design, reducing back-and-forth.  \n    - The group agreed to occasionally include subtle **Noetic promotion** in quote cards to boost brand presence.  \n    - Use of ellipses to shorten longer quotes on cards was accepted to maintain clarity and engagement.\n\n- The **podcast episode schedule** was updated with **Mike Linton’s** recording moved to next week and **Kate Warnock’s** to **November 12th**, with **Patrick McMaster** tentatively after Kate (24:36)  \n    - Frameworks for all guests are prepared, with Kate’s episode promising strong content around a recent merger and rebrand.  \n    - Nancy will complete episode descriptors for Mike Linton by Friday or Monday at the latest (24:42).  \n    - Natalie created a **guest tracking tab** in the spreadsheet with color-coded progress and final frameworks for better organization (30:08).  \n    - Nancy plans to clean up tentative guest statuses to maintain an accurate pipeline.\n\n- The team is improving internal coordination by reviewing the podcast production checklist and adjusting episode sections to optimize speaker time (27:51)  \n    - There is a focus on reducing unnecessary back-and-forth in asset approvals while maintaining effectiveness.  \n    - Nancy confirmed guest invitations are sent to all confirmed participants, ensuring platform access before recording.\n\n## **Marketing Campaign Performance and Lead Generation**\n\nThe group reviewed recent marketing campaign metrics highlighting progress and ongoing challenges in lead quality and volume.\n\n- The **healthcare campaign** generated **9 clicks** and **3 form fills** last week, producing **3 leads** at a notably lower cost per lead than usual, signaling improved targeting efficiency (36:49)  \n    - Nancy and Natalie are evaluating lead quality before entering them into the sales pipeline.  \n    - Nancy reported limited new leads in the last week but expects some to still appear in the system.  \n    - LinkedIn remains the most effective channel for outreach, especially where email deliverability is blocked, as seen in the **Marriott** and **Truist** accounts (38:44).  \n    - Persistent outreach via LinkedIn and leveraging personal networks increased booked meetings despite email filters.\n\n- Paid display ads under the **Ad Role** program yielded **4 clicks** but are not expected to drive direct leads, aligning with their usual awareness role (41:30).  \n- The team recognizes the **head of marketing audience** as competitive and costly, but targeting is reaching the right titles, with click volume needing improvement (41:36).\n\n## **Website Engagement and Content Strategy**\n\nOngoing website performance metrics show positive trends, with identified opportunities to boost engagement through better content linking and AI-related offerings.\n\n- October saw a **2% increase** in website views compared to September, alongside longer average session durations and more pages viewed per session, indicating stronger visitor engagement (41:58)  \n    - Visitors are spending about twice as long on the site, suggesting content resonates well with the target audience.  \n    - Colin recommended adding more internal links on the homepage and other pages to guide visitors toward key services like brand diagnostics.  \n    - Nancy suggested integrating content around AI offerings to capitalize on current market trends and visitor interest.\n\n- The team is considering a dedicated **AI workshop** offering as a new product separate from the playbook, responding to client needs for leadership and skill development in AI adoption (43:10)  \n    - Colin described a workshop focused on AI governance, company policy, and operationalizing AI use across teams.  \n    - Nancy emphasized the importance of training teams not only in individual AI use but also in coordinated workflows and governance.  \n    - They plan to develop landing page content and targeted ads to assess AI adoption levels and drive workshop interest.\n\n- Visual process mapping, like the **ABM campaign flowchart** shared by Colin, is proposed as a creative tool to illustrate AI integration and marketing workflows, helping prospects see where AI fits into their operations (52:48)  \n    - Nancy highlighted the value of collaborative whiteboard sessions for process mapping, which fosters understanding and buy-in.  \n    - The approach targets mid-level companies that may not have top-tier consulting support but need practical solutions.  \n    - Messaging will avoid fearmongering around AI-driven job cuts, focusing instead on empowerment and team effectiveness.\n\n## **Email List Health and Client Engagement**\n\nThe team reported significant improvements in newsletter deliverability and outlined plans for a major client outreach in November.\n\n- Following a recent cleanup, the team reduced the **newsletter bounce rate** to **22 bounces** across all lists, a substantial improvement signaling better list hygiene (01:02:10)  \n    - Rachel confirmed the cleanup and ongoing maintenance efforts, though natural attrition from marketer moves continues.  \n    - Nancy explained that many bounced contacts came from Wells Fargo, whose marketing function was decentralized after 2018-2019 reputational issues and leadership changes.\n\n- The **Thankful Mailer** campaign will be a key client engagement push in November, featuring personalized messages for each contact on client lists (01:02:59)  \n    - Rachel is preparing mock-ups and will share examples with the team ahead of the mailing.  \n    - The campaign aims to reinforce relationships ahead of the holiday season with a fresh, customized approach.\n\n- The team planned to confirm the need for a meeting on **November 19th** given the Thanksgiving holiday schedule, with Colin out from November 20th to December 1st (01:03:29)  \n    - Nancy and Rachel agreed to assess whether the meeting is necessary closer to the date to accommodate the holiday week’s irregularities.\n\n## **Creative Asset Development and A/B Testing**\n\nNew creative assets for healthcare and CMO campaigns are ready for launch after A/B testing finalization and minor design tweaks.\n\n- Two cover design options for the **healthcare** and **first-year CMO playbook chunks** were reviewed and approved for A/B testing, emphasizing bright, engaging visuals with improved headline highlights (13:00)  \n    - Rachel and Nancy recommended extending the green highlight fully across the headline for clarity and impact.  \n    - The creatives are designed to stop audience scrolling and prompt engagement, with Rachel praising the fresh, light, and bright style.\n\n- Organic social assets were updated by removing extraneous elements like a butterfly icon to simplify visuals and enhance focus (15:56)  \n    - Color adjustments were made to maintain brand consistency while adding subtle dimension for visual interest.  \n    - Colin prepared complementary ad copy, with **8** total ad variations (four per infographic) ready for deployment (18:25).\n\n- Ad copy wording was refined to avoid alienating the audience, shifting from finger-wagging tones to provocative questions that encourage self-reflection about marketing ROI and CEO communication (21:50)  \n    - Nancy and Colin agreed on phrasing like, \"Are you prepared to answer your CEO’s questions?\" to engage without judgment.  \n    - The goal is to keep messaging brief, clear, and compelling to maximize scroll-stopping potential.\n\n## **Operational Coordination and Process Improvements**\n\nThe team enhanced internal tracking and communication processes to support smoother project execution and accountability.\n\n- The leadership team condensed their quarterly planning meeting into a full-day session attended by **4 leaders**, setting priorities and \"rocks\" for the coming period (11:44)  \n    - Colin recognized Natalie’s role in managing communications during his absence at the meeting, ensuring continuity.\n\n- Internal spreadsheet tools were updated to reflect the latest recording schedules, guest confirmations, and framework deliveries, improving transparency and follow-up (30:08)  \n    - The guest tracking tab includes color-coded step completion and stores final podcast frameworks for quick reference.\n\n- Communication protocols for sharing podcast access with external consultants like **Raki at Noetic** were clarified, with invitations resent to ensure timely access (12:09).  \n- The team agreed to maintain a flexible meeting schedule in November due to holidays, with decisions on session necessity made closer to dates (01:03:46).","outline":null,"keywords":["Podcast production","Marketing ROI","AI training","Workflow mapping","Healthcare campaign","Lead generation"],"overview":"- **Podcast Workflow Improvements:** Enhanced assets and workflows to reduce delays, focusing on quote card value and concise selection.  \n- **Updated Podcast Schedule:** Guest recordings adjusted; episode descriptors will be finalized by Friday for better planning.  \n- **Marketing Campaign Metrics:** Recent healthcare campaign yielded 3 leads with improved cost efficiency; continuing to evaluate lead quality.  \n- **Website Performance Gains:** 2% increase in views and longer session times indicate stronger engagement; internal linking and AI content are priorities.  \n- **Email List Cleanup:** Reduced bounce rate to 22; upcoming Thankful Mailer campaign aims to enhance client relationships before holidays.  \n- **Creative Assets Ready:** New designs for healthcare and CMO campaigns approved; ad copy refined for audience engagement with provocative questions.","action_items":"\n**Nancy Cruder**\nFollow up with Waymo client process and keep team updated on progress (09:50)\nProvide Mike Linton podcast descriptors to Rachel by Friday or latest Monday (24:42)\nConfirm and update Kate Warnock podcast date as November 12 (25:51)\nContinue follow-up and scheduling efforts with Patrick McMaster and others for podcasts TBD (26:12)\nSend podcast frameworks to Colin and Natalie after review (30:08)\nLead hand-delivery and/or mailing of Marriott promotional packets and continue LinkedIn outreach (37:52)\nMonitor healthcare campaign leads for quality and share updates (01:04:25)\n\n**Rachel Curtis**\nInvite Raki from Noetic Consultants to access points tracking account and follow up with signup instructions (12:28)\nDeliver and share Thanksgiving “thankful mailer” campaign mocks and final emails with team (01:02:52)\nConfirm podcast platform invitation received by Christine McCain’s assistant (28:04)\nCoordinate and update podcast scheduling sheet order and status with Natalie and Nancy (29:02)\nAssist with podcast asset checklist review for episodes and ads (28:04)\nTrack and report newsletter bounce rate post-cleanup and monitor (01:00:02)\n\n**Colin Costigan**\nSend invite to Raki and ensure access to points tracking account (12:19)\nIncorporate feedback and launch A/B tests for healthcare and CMO playbook covers with design adjustments (14:08)\nRemove butterfly graphic and adjust colors in organic assets and ads as per feedback (16:06)\nProvide mock-up explanations for ad structure and assist with ad copy revisions (19:00)\nDevelop ad copy with reframed marketing ROI messaging and share updated versions (23:56)\nContinue podcast episode framework review and update scheduling relative to guest readiness (26:48)\nOversee podcast quote card process improvements; send curated quote lists with polished and concise edits before design (33:47)\nSupport healthcare campaign lead evaluation with Natalie and share quality feedback (37:24)\nCollaborate on AI-related workshop marketing concept, ad creative, landing page copy, and graphics development (43:10)\nMonitor web metrics and advise on website interlinking and AI content opportunities (41:30)\nCoordinate Thanksgiving week meeting decisions and schedule reminders (01:03:46)\n\n**Nathalie Mintjens**\nCreate and maintain guest tracking tab and podcast framework archive in the shared spreadsheet for improved organization (30:08)\n"},"duration":64.83000183105469,"speakers":[{"id":0,"name":"nancieruder"},{"id":1,"name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"id":2,"name":"Colin Costigan"},{"id":3,"name":"Colin Costigan"},{"id":4,"name":"Nathalie Mintjens"}],"sentences":[{"text":"It.","index":0,"end_time":204.64,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":204.4,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Hello.","index":1,"end_time":232.41,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":232.09,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Hey.","index":2,"end_time":233.37,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":232.97,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"How''s it going?","index":3,"end_time":233.93,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":233.37,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Good.","index":4,"end_time":235.13,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":234.73,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"How''s it going for you?","index":5,"end_time":236.41,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":235.13,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"It''s going.","index":6,"end_time":238.57,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":237.85,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Can you believe it''s November?","index":7,"end_time":241.05,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":239.61,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"No, I can''t believe.","index":8,"end_time":243.77,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":242.73,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And mostly that it''s dark at like 5pm I know.","index":9,"end_time":247.81,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":243.85,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I was just saying this to Nancy.","index":10,"end_time":249.29,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":247.81,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"I was like, you know, summer Fridays, I think we need those throughout the year because we don''t get summer Fridays.","index":11,"end_time":253.73,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":249.29,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"But we should do it, like, once a month so that we can enjoy the sunshine.","index":12,"end_time":258.42,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":253.73,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"She''s like, you know, it''s a decent idea.","index":13,"end_time":260.5,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":258.42,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Say, remember that.","index":14,"end_time":261.7,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":260.5,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"There you go.","index":15,"end_time":263.06,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":262.42,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Now I need to slowly go to my co workers and have them put that in their evaluations, too.","index":16,"end_time":267.38,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":263.3,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"So we''re making progress.","index":17,"end_time":268.74,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":267.46,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":18,"end_time":270.02,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":269.46,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I can''t believe.","index":19,"end_time":273.38,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":272.58,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"And it''s going to be even.","index":20,"end_time":274.5,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":273.46,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Just going to keep getting darker, Colin.","index":21,"end_time":276.9,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":274.98,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"I know.","index":22,"end_time":277.66,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":277.14,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I was.","index":23,"end_time":278.1,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":277.66,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We have a bunch of trees in our front and backyard, and so there''s leaves everywhere right now.","index":24,"end_time":282.61,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":278.58,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And I was like, oh, it''d be great.","index":25,"end_time":283.61,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":282.61,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You know, once I''m done with the workday, take Marley out there, let her, like, jump around on the leaves.","index":26,"end_time":287.13,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":283.61,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But it''s like pitch black.","index":27,"end_time":288.41,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":287.13,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That''s true.","index":28,"end_time":290.05,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":289.29,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Maybe, like, bag some up for the weekend.","index":29,"end_time":292.17,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":290.05,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Yeah, maybe.","index":30,"end_time":293.29,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":292.41,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That''s so cute.","index":31,"end_time":295.21,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":294.09,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Oh, my gosh.","index":32,"end_time":295.81,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":295.21,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"She''s.","index":33,"end_time":296.17,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":295.81,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"How old is she now?","index":34,"end_time":297.289,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":296.25,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"How many?","index":35,"end_time":297.69,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":297.289,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Nine months.","index":36,"end_time":298.49,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":297.77,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So she''s starting to get a personality a little bit.","index":37,"end_time":301.45,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":299.13,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"She''s got a personality for sure.","index":38,"end_time":303.29,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":301.53,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"She also wants to.","index":39,"end_time":306.65,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":304.41,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"She''s, like, crawling around, scooting around, but she wants to just skip straight to walking.","index":40,"end_time":310.85,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":306.89,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"She probably will.","index":41,"end_time":312.05,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":311.01,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":42,"end_time":312.69,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":312.21,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Getting pretty close.","index":43,"end_time":313.93,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":313.25,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"She''s, like, almost standing up completely on her own.","index":44,"end_time":315.97,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":313.93,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That''s crazy.","index":45,"end_time":317.57,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":316.53,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"She''s smart.","index":46,"end_time":318.29,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":317.57,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Which is good and bad for you.","index":47,"end_time":321.09,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":319.65,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Yes.","index":48,"end_time":321.89,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":321.41,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We are ordering all of the childproofing materials.","index":49,"end_time":325.41,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":321.89,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Oh, my gosh.","index":50,"end_time":326.69,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":325.81,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Do you want, like, a million of them now or you''re like, I''m good where I am.","index":51,"end_time":329.97,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":326.69,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"They have, like, kits.","index":52,"end_time":331.17,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":330.05,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We''re just trying to decide, like, is magnetic the way to go for, like, the locks or just, like, complex, like, squeeze and twist locks?","index":53,"end_time":339.5,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":331.65,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Also, like, corner guards for tables.","index":54,"end_time":342.86,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":340.46,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":55,"end_time":344.22,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":343.66,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"We''Ll get it figured.","index":56,"end_time":347.02,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":346.14,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Her first Halloween, it was great.","index":57,"end_time":349.42,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":347.02,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"She.","index":58,"end_time":350.14,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":349.74,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We don''t have a sidewalk by our house, so, like, we didn''t take her out.","index":59,"end_time":354.58,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":350.38,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Obviously, she was asleep by then, too.","index":60,"end_time":356.1,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":354.58,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But.","index":61,"end_time":356.46,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":356.1,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So, I mean, she was a cute little pumpkin.","index":62,"end_time":361.34,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":358.46,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That''s pretty much it.","index":63,"end_time":362.14,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":361.34,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Oh, that''s so cute.","index":64,"end_time":363.53,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":362.41,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"I feel like that''s a rite of passage for every little kid.","index":65,"end_time":365.85,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":363.53,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":66,"end_time":366.33,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":366.01,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I think my wife and I were both pumpkins for our first Halloween.","index":67,"end_time":369.85,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":366.33,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we''re like, we got to.","index":68,"end_time":370.81,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":369.85,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I love that.","index":69,"end_time":371.73,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":371.13,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"I think I Even was a pumpkin.","index":70,"end_time":373.25,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":371.73,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"My first Holly.","index":71,"end_time":374.33,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":373.25,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"I gotta.","index":72,"end_time":375.33,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":374.65,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I''ll see if I can find the picture real quick.","index":73,"end_time":376.89,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":375.33,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yes.","index":74,"end_time":377.29,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":376.89,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Geez.","index":75,"end_time":377.85,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":377.29,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"It''s kind of funny.","index":76,"end_time":379.13,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":378.329,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"They''ve got, like, the round head and they''re bald and.","index":77,"end_time":382.49,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":379.37,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yeah, she''s.","index":78,"end_time":384.45,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":383.77,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"She''s starting to get a little head of hair.","index":79,"end_time":385.89,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":384.45,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It''s like.","index":80,"end_time":386.25,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":385.89,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It''s just crazy.","index":81,"end_time":387.13,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":386.25,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I made my kids when my oldest was three and my second one was one, and the other one wasn''t born yet.","index":82,"end_time":395.86,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":388.9,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"My daughter, who was three, was a bumblebee.","index":83,"end_time":399.98,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":397.78,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"And because she was a bumblebee, I made my son be a flower.","index":84,"end_time":403.06,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":399.98,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Oh.","index":85,"end_time":404.26,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":403.78,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"And when he got older, I got a lot of heat for that.","index":86,"end_time":407.86,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":404.34,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Why?","index":87,"end_time":408.9,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":408.5,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Because he was like, that''s so cute.","index":88,"end_time":411.7,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":409.46,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Why did you make me be a flower?","index":89,"end_time":413.54,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":411.86,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Mom?","index":90,"end_time":413.94,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":413.54,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"It was a baby.","index":91,"end_time":415.3,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":414.26,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"That''s what I said.","index":92,"end_time":417.23,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":416.55,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"I''m like, because of bumblebee flower.","index":93,"end_time":418.95,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":417.23,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Like, my friends definitely pick more aggressive costumes.","index":94,"end_time":422.19,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":418.95,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"One of my friends babies was a squirrel.","index":95,"end_time":423.99,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":422.19,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Like, I feel like that''s far more aggressive than a flower.","index":96,"end_time":427.83,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":424.63,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"I.","index":97,"end_time":428.71,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":428.31,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"In my neighborhood, we got a ton of trick or treaters, and it''s just really fun to see, like, what''s.","index":98,"end_time":433.63,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":429.11,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"What are the happening costumes now?","index":99,"end_time":435.75,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":433.63,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"And one of my favorites was that there was these three girls.","index":100,"end_time":441.56,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":436.23,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"They were probably middle school, and they were only.","index":101,"end_time":445.48,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":441.56,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"You''d only see this in this area.","index":102,"end_time":447.2,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":445.48,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"They were Secret Service.","index":103,"end_time":449.2,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":447.68,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Oh, wow.","index":104,"end_time":450.8,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":450,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So they had, like, fake earpieces.","index":105,"end_time":453,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":451.36,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"They had.","index":106,"end_time":453.6,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":453,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"They had their badge clipped, you know, right here, like their work badge.","index":107,"end_time":458.28,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":453.68,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"And they were in, like, white button downs and dark clothes.","index":108,"end_time":462.08,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":458.28,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"And it.","index":109,"end_time":462.8,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":462.08,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"It was just funny.","index":110,"end_time":463.68,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":462.8,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"There were three of them.","index":111,"end_time":464.32,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":463.68,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"That''s adorable.","index":112,"end_time":464.88,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":464.32,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Like, you know, tucking into the head.","index":113,"end_time":466.64,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":464.88,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"So creative.","index":114,"end_time":467.76,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":466.96,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"I saw a few parents who were six, seven.","index":115,"end_time":469.52,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":467.76,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"No, I''ve been, like, so out of the loop on what that means.","index":116,"end_time":474.49,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":472.09,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"There''s like, this thing, and the kids are, like, six, seven.","index":117,"end_time":477.13,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":474.57,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"And so that''s all I know about it.","index":118,"end_time":478.61,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":477.13,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I don''t know.","index":119,"end_time":478.97,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":478.61,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Like, yeah, that''s all anybody knows about it.","index":120,"end_time":480.49,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":478.97,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"There''s like, a song.","index":121,"end_time":481.21,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":480.49,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"If you see a six, seven, just go six, seven.","index":122,"end_time":483.53,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":481.61,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":123,"end_time":484.17,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":483.69,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But I love the creativity.","index":124,"end_time":486.05,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":484.65,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"A lot of Louvre robbers this year.","index":125,"end_time":487.77,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":486.05,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"A lot of that, like, Korean show with the purple hair.","index":126,"end_time":494.01,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":488.89,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"So, yeah, there were several that were referencing shows that I had never heard of.","index":127,"end_time":498.25,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":494.41,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"But, yeah, here you can see her.","index":128,"end_time":501.71,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":498.95,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Costume and a little bit of her personality.","index":129,"end_time":503.59,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":501.71,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Oh, she''s so cute.","index":130,"end_time":509.35,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":506.79,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Oh, my gosh.","index":131,"end_time":510.79,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":509.83,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"And ironically, I''m wearing the same quarter zip right now.","index":132,"end_time":513.43,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":511.27,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Adorable.","index":133,"end_time":515.03,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":514.07,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Oh, my gosh.","index":134,"end_time":516.39,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":515.43,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":135,"end_time":517.43,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":517.11,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"She looks like she has a little mischief in her.","index":136,"end_time":519.51,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":517.43,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Oh, for sure.","index":137,"end_time":520.95,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":519.83,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":138,"end_time":521.83,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":521.35,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"So cute.","index":139,"end_time":522.95,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":522.23,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Hi, Natalie.","index":140,"end_time":524.39,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":523.43,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Hello.","index":141,"end_time":525.29,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":524.97,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"How are you doing?","index":142,"end_time":526.25,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":525.45,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Good.","index":143,"end_time":527.05,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":526.65,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"We Were just talking about Halloween.","index":144,"end_time":529.13,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":527.29,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"We hadn''t.","index":145,"end_time":529.69,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":529.13,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"We hadn''t dove in yet.","index":146,"end_time":530.65,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":529.69,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Gang''s all here.","index":147,"end_time":531.41,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":530.65,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Tracy will not be joining us today so we can get started.","index":148,"end_time":535.69,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":531.41,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Sounds good.","index":149,"end_time":536.89,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":536.17,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Are we still enjoying getting the agenda beforehand?","index":150,"end_time":541.45,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":538.65,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yes, definitely.","index":151,"end_time":543.05,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":541.77,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"I had a look at it.","index":152,"end_time":544.41,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":543.13,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"The only addition is that we want to pause on podcast assets and just talk a little bit about like, the breakdown of the assets and like how we''re using each in particular.","index":153,"end_time":560.24,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":545.21,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Just wondering whether or not, like, we''re having so much.","index":154,"end_time":564.72,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":562.16,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"There''s so much volume for each episode and so we''re wanting.","index":155,"end_time":568.4,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":564.88,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Wondering about the value of the.","index":156,"end_time":571.76,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":568.4,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"What do we call them, Rachel?","index":157,"end_time":573.28,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":572,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Quote cards.","index":158,"end_time":574,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":573.28,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Quote cards.","index":159,"end_time":574.92,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":574.24,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Just so we just want to pause on that.","index":160,"end_time":577.56,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":574.92,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"But otherwise, I like the agenda that you have and I want to make sure we do spend time on the metrics insights and like, what do we do with that information?","index":161,"end_time":587.48,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":577.56,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yep.","index":162,"end_time":588.6,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":588.04,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"I should probably start out also by telling you that I did have a good call with Waymo.","index":163,"end_time":595.32,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":590.12,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Fantastic.","index":164,"end_time":596.76,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":596.04,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And it''s, you know, I''m not going to count my chickens, but I mean, she definitely has needs.","index":165,"end_time":603.88,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":597,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"She definitely has budget.","index":166,"end_time":605,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":603.88,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"She, she needs to get her boss on board.","index":167,"end_time":608.13,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":605.24,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"And I think it''s going to be one of those, like the biggest challenge isn''t so much that is there a need there?","index":168,"end_time":614.81,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":609.57,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"It''s like she''s really, really, really busy.","index":169,"end_time":617.49,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":614.81,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"And so it''s just figuring out how to kind of insert in that process.","index":170,"end_time":623.09,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":618.05,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"So stay tuned.","index":171,"end_time":624.21,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":623.25,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Thank you for the update.","index":172,"end_time":625.97,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":625.01,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That was great to hear.","index":173,"end_time":626.85,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":625.97,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Nancy, you''re familiar with Adventist, right?","index":174,"end_time":629.97,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":627.81,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Mm, yes.","index":175,"end_time":631.9,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":631.1,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"So.","index":176,"end_time":632.3,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":631.9,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And have you ever done any work with them in the past?","index":177,"end_time":634.66,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":632.38,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"No.","index":178,"end_time":635.02,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":634.66,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"So I actually on the their finance side actually just got them as a lead for another client of mine.","index":179,"end_time":641.74,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":635.9,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And I''m wondering if maybe I can.","index":180,"end_time":643.82,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":642.3,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Just be like, hey, do you guys.","index":181,"end_time":646.38,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":644.7,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Have any, you know, leadership consulting needs.","index":182,"end_time":650.38,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":646.38,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You know, sorts of things?","index":183,"end_time":651.62,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":650.46,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"See if I can leak into that.","index":184,"end_time":652.86,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":651.62,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, that''d be amazing.","index":185,"end_time":654.3,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":653.18,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":186,"end_time":655.06,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":654.54,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, she was the VP of finance over there.","index":187,"end_time":657.5,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":655.06,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Mm.","index":188,"end_time":658.35,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":657.95,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":189,"end_time":660.43,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":659.79,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right, so we''ll dive in October.","index":190,"end_time":662.63,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":660.43,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We delivered 159 points and as we''re entering into November, we have 98.","index":191,"end_time":667.39,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":662.63,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Also, I really want to just say thank you to Natalie for sending all the communications.","index":192,"end_time":673.31,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":667.39,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"On Monday, we had our leadership meeting, so I was out of pocket in Virginia, so she was doing all the communication and really appreciate that.","index":193,"end_time":681.79,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":673.31,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Then I woke up, hopped on the road at 4am yesterday and got back.","index":194,"end_time":686.09,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":682.19,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So I could hop onto my call.","index":195,"end_time":687.37,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":686.09,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Was your U.S. planning, right?","index":196,"end_time":689.05,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":687.37,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"It was.","index":197,"end_time":689.77,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":689.21,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Wow, that''s a lot.","index":198,"end_time":691.29,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":690.09,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"It was.","index":199,"end_time":692.81,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":692.25,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It was a full day.","index":200,"end_time":693.85,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":692.89,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Usually we do two, but we had to do like a Monday this.","index":201,"end_time":697.17,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":694.17,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We usually do like a Thursday Friday, but we had to do a Monday this time and just kind of condense it all.","index":202,"end_time":701.77,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":697.17,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But it was a very, very productive session.","index":203,"end_time":704.09,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":701.85,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"How many people attend that right now?","index":204,"end_time":707.93,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":704.89,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Just four.","index":205,"end_time":708.41,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":707.93,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It''s the leadership team.","index":206,"end_time":711.38,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":710.5,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We work through a bunch of things, come up with all of our rocks, and then work with the team to.","index":207,"end_time":715.38,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":711.38,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Have all of those come to fruition.","index":208,"end_time":717.14,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":715.7,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Gotcha.","index":209,"end_time":718.58,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":717.86,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Also, quick question on the points before we move on.","index":210,"end_time":721.86,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":718.98,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Are you able to see who from Noetic has an account?","index":211,"end_time":724.82,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":721.94,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"I''m only asking because I was meeting with Raki and she was asking me.","index":212,"end_time":729.46,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":725.62,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"If she had an account to get.","index":213,"end_time":730.78,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":729.46,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Into the points, and I wasn''t sure.","index":214,"end_time":732.9,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":730.78,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"So I can always give her my.","index":215,"end_time":734.42,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":733.22,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Account, but I can send her an invite.","index":216,"end_time":736.7,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":734.42,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I think I have at one point.","index":217,"end_time":737.7,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":736.7,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But I can check.","index":218,"end_time":738.34,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":737.7,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That''d be great.","index":219,"end_time":739.72,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":739.08,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Thank you.","index":220,"end_time":740.44,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":739.72,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Just because I want to make sure she has that because the breakdown is great for her.","index":221,"end_time":744.2,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":740.44,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"She can see, like, when we paid all the different things.","index":222,"end_time":746.84,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":744.2,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Okay, Racky is not in here.","index":223,"end_time":750.32,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":748.84,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So I will shoot her an invite right now.","index":224,"end_time":752.68,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":750.32,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Perfect.","index":225,"end_time":753.56,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":753.08,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"And I will message her and let.","index":226,"end_time":754.92,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":753.56,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Her know Raki at Noetic Consultants.","index":227,"end_time":758.2,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":754.92,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right.","index":228,"end_time":770.01,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":769.73,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"She should get an email to her inbox.","index":229,"end_time":771.81,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":770.01,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Sign up.","index":230,"end_time":772.45,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":771.81,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It is like a token that expires in, I think, 24 hours.","index":231,"end_time":775.33,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":772.53,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So if she needs that again, let yourself know.","index":232,"end_time":778.13,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":775.41,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, great.","index":233,"end_time":779.25,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":778.45,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Thank you so much.","index":234,"end_time":780.05,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":779.25,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Yeah, of course.","index":235,"end_time":780.81,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":780.21,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And we updated the finance spreadsheet for ads and everything and the receipts in there.","index":236,"end_time":785.05,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":780.81,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So if anyone has any questions, please.","index":237,"end_time":786.69,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":785.05,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Just let us know.","index":238,"end_time":787.41,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":786.69,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Thank you so much.","index":239,"end_time":789.01,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":788.05,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Of course.","index":240,"end_time":789.73,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":789.17,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right, so based on the feedback, we''ve updated and we have two cover options to a B test for the healthcare and first year CMOs.","index":241,"end_time":798.36,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":791.24,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So dive into these.","index":242,"end_time":800.28,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":798.76,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Zoom out a little bit.","index":243,"end_time":803.88,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":802.6,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Oh, cool.","index":244,"end_time":807.16,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":806.44,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Nice and bright.","index":245,"end_time":812.52,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":811.72,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"It''s different than what we''ve done.","index":246,"end_time":813.8,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":812.52,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Her hair''s a little.","index":247,"end_time":815.72,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":814.68,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Little more put together.","index":248,"end_time":816.82,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":816.1,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":249,"end_time":817.78,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":817.3,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Great.","index":250,"end_time":818.98,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":818.58,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Yeah, I like it.","index":251,"end_time":821.3,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":820.42,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":252,"end_time":822.1,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":821.62,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then this was option number two.","index":253,"end_time":824.26,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":822.1,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yes.","index":254,"end_time":825.42,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":824.98,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Oops.","index":255,"end_time":825.94,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":825.42,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I need this bar to go away.","index":256,"end_time":830.58,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":829.06,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I have this.","index":257,"end_time":831.38,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":830.74,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We''ve been using this tool called Whisper, so I can just talk right into my microphone and types on screen for me.","index":258,"end_time":837.38,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":831.62,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Sometimes it gets in the way, though.","index":259,"end_time":839.86,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":838.42,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Cool.","index":260,"end_time":840.9,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":840.42,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":261,"end_time":842.75,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":842.43,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"All right, so are we good to launch these as the A B test?","index":262,"end_time":846.91,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":842.75,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, I think we''re good.","index":263,"end_time":849.23,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":848.19,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":264,"end_time":850.43,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":849.87,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then for first year cmo.","index":265,"end_time":853.39,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":851.07,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Here''S cover number one.","index":266,"end_time":860.99,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":859.79,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"How do you feel about the green, Rachel?","index":267,"end_time":867.81,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":865.39,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"I knew you''re gonna ask me that.","index":268,"end_time":869.73,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":868.13,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"I like the green.","index":269,"end_time":871.97,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":870.85,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"I just don''t like it going off the side.","index":270,"end_time":873.89,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":871.97,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Like, I''m fine with it.","index":271,"end_time":876.13,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":875.01,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Highlighted.","index":272,"end_time":876.85,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":876.13,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"I feel like.","index":273,"end_time":877.65,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":876.85,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Like, I like the concept if it was, like, the whole line where it looks intentional.","index":274,"end_time":882.37,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":878.21,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"What do you think, Nancy?","index":275,"end_time":884.77,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":883.41,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Or we just highlight.","index":276,"end_time":888.69,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":887.57,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Budget is on the line and all green.","index":277,"end_time":890.25,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":888.69,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Yeah, we could have that go across.","index":278,"end_time":891.57,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":890.25,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I like that.","index":279,"end_time":892.69,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":891.89,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Highlight all the way across.","index":280,"end_time":894.54,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":893.5,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"All right, thank you.","index":281,"end_time":897.18,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":895.58,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":282,"end_time":898.14,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":897.5,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"That was easy.","index":283,"end_time":899.02,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":898.14,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"And then number two.","index":284,"end_time":900.86,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":899.66,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Oh, fun.","index":285,"end_time":902.7,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":901.9,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":286,"end_time":907.5,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":907.1,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"It''s a good headline too.","index":287,"end_time":908.7,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":907.5,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":288,"end_time":909.98,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":909.5,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":289,"end_time":911.5,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":910.94,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right, well, we will get this line all across the size of the page, and then are we good to launch that as well?","index":290,"end_time":919.58,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":912.3,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yes.","index":291,"end_time":921.63,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":921.31,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"And these are for the playbook chunks?","index":292,"end_time":925.79,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":921.79,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yes.","index":293,"end_time":927.31,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":926.91,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":294,"end_time":927.67,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":927.31,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So the rest of the documents in here as well?","index":295,"end_time":929.31,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":927.67,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah.","index":296,"end_time":936.23,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":930.99,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"So this is 10 pages.","index":297,"end_time":937.39,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":936.23,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Okay.","index":298,"end_time":937.95,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":937.39,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yep.","index":299,"end_time":938.59,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":938.03,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Wow, this looks great.","index":300,"end_time":940.27,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":939.15,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Fantastic.","index":301,"end_time":942.51,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":941.63,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right, next up, we have some organic assets based on that we''ve updated based on the feedback in our call last week.","index":302,"end_time":949.34,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":943.23,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":303,"end_time":950.38,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":949.74,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"So we went larger with the bar here.","index":304,"end_time":958.54,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":956.94,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Sorry, Rachel, I cut you off.","index":305,"end_time":961.34,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":959.9,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Sorry.","index":306,"end_time":961.86,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":961.5,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"I was going to say, I still feel like we don''t need that butterfly that''s in the corner.","index":307,"end_time":964.86,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":961.86,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"This one?","index":308,"end_time":966.06,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":965.34,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":309,"end_time":966.94,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":966.46,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"What do you think, Nancy?","index":310,"end_time":968.38,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":967.1,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Yeah, I don''t think we need it.","index":311,"end_time":970.9,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":969.82,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"I would just lose it.","index":312,"end_time":971.9,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":970.9,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Okay.","index":313,"end_time":973.02,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":972.46,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"The rest looks great.","index":314,"end_time":974.62,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":973.5,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":315,"end_time":976.04,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":975.72,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And I think that was.","index":316,"end_time":977,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":976.04,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, we were good.","index":317,"end_time":978.28,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":977.48,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"We were good.","index":318,"end_time":979,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":978.36,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":319,"end_time":979.44,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":979.08,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"That looked amazing.","index":320,"end_time":980.36,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":979.44,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Oh, love it.","index":321,"end_time":981.2,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":980.52,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"With the new color, that''s.","index":322,"end_time":982.6,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":981.2,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"See, that''s fun.","index":323,"end_time":983.8,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":982.76,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"It''s engaging.","index":324,"end_time":984.76,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":983.8,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"It''s not just, like the same thing.","index":325,"end_time":988.12,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":985.16,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"What do you think, Nancy?","index":326,"end_time":990.04,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":988.6,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"I like it.","index":327,"end_time":990.76,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":990.04,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":328,"end_time":991.24,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":990.76,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"This is.","index":329,"end_time":992.12,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":991.48,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"His teeth kind of remind me of Tom Cruise.","index":330,"end_time":994.68,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":992.76,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You guys notice that Tom Cruise''s teeth are not in the center of his face?","index":331,"end_time":998.04,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":994.68,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Oh, I. I''m gonna notice that next time.","index":332,"end_time":1001.08,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":999,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"I.","index":333,"end_time":1001.48,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1001.08,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Ever since I figured that out, I can''t not look at it in any movies.","index":334,"end_time":1005.48,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1002.24,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And that''s so funny.","index":335,"end_time":1007.52,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1005.48,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"I got to pull that up.","index":336,"end_time":1009.12,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1008.08,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I have never noticed that.","index":337,"end_time":1010.8,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1009.12,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"You know, he gives this coconut cake to people that''s like over $100 at the holiday season, and it''s this big thing.","index":338,"end_time":1017.36,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1010.88,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"This is his time.","index":339,"end_time":1018.64,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1017.68,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Oh, you''re so right.","index":340,"end_time":1020.8,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1018.8,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"His teeth are a little off.","index":341,"end_time":1024,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1022.8,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"There''s a lot about Tom Cruise that''s a little off.","index":342,"end_time":1028.48,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1025.92,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yeah, that is more.","index":343,"end_time":1030.31,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1028.95,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"A little bit.","index":344,"end_time":1031.03,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1030.31,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"But I want one of the coconut cakes.","index":345,"end_time":1033.51,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1031.59,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":346,"end_time":1036.23,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1035.67,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right, great.","index":347,"end_time":1036.91,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1036.23,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we''re good with this and then.","index":348,"end_time":1038.31,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1036.91,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":349,"end_time":1039.71,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1039.35,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we can just adjust the butterfly to.","index":350,"end_time":1041.27,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1039.71,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"To get rid of that and just kind of use the orange side that we have here.","index":351,"end_time":1044.39,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1041.27,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We also, if we''re getting rid of the.","index":352,"end_time":1046.07,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1044.39,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"The butterfly, could we put under pressure in the noetic, like, bluish green that way, like, it has a little bit more dimension.","index":353,"end_time":1055.35,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1046.07,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"We''re not, like, changing everything.","index":354,"end_time":1056.55,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1055.35,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":355,"end_time":1057.67,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1057.35,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yep.","index":356,"end_time":1059.43,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1058.87,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"And you can keep that one the exact same, but that way, like, it''s, it has like that little extra pop that''s on the side that we''re losing.","index":357,"end_time":1067.03,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1059.51,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Yes.","index":358,"end_time":1069.91,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1069.43,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"And then no butterfly.","index":359,"end_time":1071.19,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1070.07,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Perfect.","index":360,"end_time":1071.67,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1071.19,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"What do you think, Nancy?","index":361,"end_time":1077.11,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1075.91,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"I''m good.","index":362,"end_time":1078.23,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1077.59,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Great.","index":363,"end_time":1079.19,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1078.79,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":364,"end_time":1080.07,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1079.51,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Thank you.","index":365,"end_time":1080.79,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1080.15,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"All right.","index":366,"end_time":1081.71,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1081.27,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Glad my graphic design skills stood up to the test there.","index":367,"end_time":1084.63,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1081.71,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yes.","index":368,"end_time":1085.55,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1085.23,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"That second one was so fun and light and bright and, like, exactly what we''re aiming for.","index":369,"end_time":1090.99,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1085.79,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Perfect.","index":370,"end_time":1092.19,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1091.63,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"And then we''ve also written ads to go with these, so we have the intro text and everything in here as well.","index":371,"end_time":1098.51,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1092.51,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We can read through these now if you want, or we can just send.","index":372,"end_time":1101.55,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1099.39,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"This over as a document.","index":373,"end_time":1102.67,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1101.55,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"How many are there?","index":374,"end_time":1106.19,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1105.31,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"I think we went with four per.","index":375,"end_time":1109.55,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1107.47,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Right, Natalie, am I remembering that correctly?","index":376,"end_time":1113.89,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1112.37,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Would that be total?","index":377,"end_time":1115.57,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1113.89,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Yes, four per infographic.","index":378,"end_time":1119.33,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1116.45,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"So eight total.","index":379,"end_time":1120.37,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1119.49,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"So this would be.","index":380,"end_time":1127.089,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1124.93,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"I, I, I''m trying to, I''m lost on, like, where this appears like.","index":381,"end_time":1135.05,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1127.33,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Oh, like on LinkedIn, like the company.","index":382,"end_time":1138.57,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1135.05,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Like, it''s the asset we were just looking at.","index":383,"end_time":1146.33,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1140.01,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"So what I''m confused about is the copy.","index":384,"end_time":1149.65,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1147.69,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Where does, where does the introductory text show up?","index":385,"end_time":1152.89,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1149.65,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yeah, let me, let me pull up a mock up real quick.","index":386,"end_time":1156.57,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1153.37,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I guess I was thinking that the, the COVID that we were just looking at was the thing that people were going to see that they would then click.","index":387,"end_time":1170.22,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1160.25,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":388,"end_time":1179.42,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1178.86,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So let''s see if I can zoom in on this as well.","index":389,"end_time":1182.46,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1179.82,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"This is, this is a mock up.","index":390,"end_time":1185.98,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1182.7,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Of one of our ads that we.","index":391,"end_time":1187.62,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1186.06,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Are setting up at Marketers in Demand.","index":392,"end_time":1189.18,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1187.62,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So, like, we have headline text and everything in here.","index":393,"end_time":1192.89,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1190.17,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So headline actually is, it''s interesting that they call it a headline.","index":394,"end_time":1198.89,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1192.97,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Like, it''s actually highlighted down here.","index":395,"end_time":1200.73,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1198.89,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I see.","index":396,"end_time":1201.29,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1200.81,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"So that visual we were just looking at would be the thing that would be sitting where this picture is.","index":397,"end_time":1205.45,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1201.29,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Correct.","index":398,"end_time":1206.25,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1205.69,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then the copy is like part of the post, if you will.","index":399,"end_time":1209.69,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1206.33,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Correct.","index":400,"end_time":1210.45,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1210.01,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then the CTA takes them to.","index":401,"end_time":1212.29,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1210.45,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Download the actual PDF.","index":402,"end_time":1213.93,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1212.29,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, I got it.","index":403,"end_time":1216.34,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1215.38,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Okay.","index":404,"end_time":1216.82,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1216.34,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"All right, now we''re super zoomed in.","index":405,"end_time":1219.38,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1217.86,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, I think we can just look at them real quick.","index":406,"end_time":1222.9,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1220.82,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Can you scroll down?","index":407,"end_time":1240.46,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1239.46,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"I''m going to come back to number one.","index":408,"end_time":1241.86,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1240.46,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Keep going.","index":409,"end_time":1249.9,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1249.42,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"I really like three and four for number one.","index":410,"end_time":1270.71,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1264.3,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"I, I just worry that it, like, it''s a little bit insulting, you know, like, I don''t know.","index":411,"end_time":1290.51,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1274.15,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"And, and then, like, I''m at a loss to how to fix it.","index":412,"end_time":1293.11,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1290.51,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Like, if you go in the door of what, what''s marketing''s ROI like, I think it''s true that you don''t necessarily, you''re not necessarily speaking in terms of the right metrics.","index":413,"end_time":1305.98,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1293.11,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"It''s Just that, like, I don''t want to be wagging a finger at them.","index":414,"end_time":1309.98,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1305.98,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"I want them to be like, oh, my gosh.","index":415,"end_time":1311.46,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1309.98,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yeah, that''s me.","index":416,"end_time":1312.38,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1311.46,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"But not like, oh, my gosh, that''s me.","index":417,"end_time":1315.42,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1312.7,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"You know, I''m not sure how to fix it.","index":418,"end_time":1319.1,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1315.98,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"What if it is?","index":419,"end_time":1324.07,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1323.43,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"What if it''s more of, like, a probing question of when your CEO asks, what''s marketing''s roi?","index":420,"end_time":1331.27,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1325.91,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Are you showing vanity metrics or are you proving pipeline contribution?","index":421,"end_time":1335.83,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1331.99,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Or even just.","index":422,"end_time":1337.91,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1336.71,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Are you really ready?","index":423,"end_time":1338.95,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1337.91,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":424,"end_time":1339.83,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1339.35,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Are you prepared to answer that question?","index":425,"end_time":1341.59,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1340.07,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":426,"end_time":1342.31,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1341.83,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":427,"end_time":1342.95,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1342.47,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Because then it''s just a provocative question instead of saying, like, not.","index":428,"end_time":1346.85,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1343.11,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"You''re not doing the right thing.","index":429,"end_time":1347.85,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1346.85,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah.","index":430,"end_time":1349.37,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1348.33,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Something along those lines, I think.","index":431,"end_time":1350.89,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1349.37,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Okay.","index":432,"end_time":1351.57,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1351.13,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And for the second one, it''s much more.","index":433,"end_time":1353.53,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1351.57,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"It.","index":434,"end_time":1354.97,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1354.65,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"It''s.","index":435,"end_time":1355.45,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1354.97,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"It''s an easier thing.","index":436,"end_time":1356.57,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1355.53,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"I just think marketing budgets get cut first.","index":437,"end_time":1362.41,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1356.57,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Not because the work doesn''t matter.","index":438,"end_time":1364.17,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1362.49,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"I just think because the dashboard doesn''t speak.","index":439,"end_time":1373.29,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1370.89,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"CEO is a little too cute.","index":440,"end_time":1376.7,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1373.9,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Like what?","index":441,"end_time":1378.22,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1376.86,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"A little bit too hard.","index":442,"end_time":1381.42,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1380.3,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"So I think it''s just a reword.","index":443,"end_time":1382.82,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1381.42,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"I mean, it definitely is.","index":444,"end_time":1383.82,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1382.82,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"To the fact that, like, dashboard is not.","index":445,"end_time":1385.82,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1383.82,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"It''s not getting us there.","index":446,"end_time":1389.58,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1387.5,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":447,"end_time":1396.78,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1396.46,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"I don''t know if metric solves helps.","index":448,"end_time":1399.99,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1396.78,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It helps.","index":449,"end_time":1400.71,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1399.99,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yeah, that might be fine.","index":450,"end_time":1406.55,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1405.43,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Or maybe, you know, because the metrics don''t translate to CEO speak.","index":451,"end_time":1410.31,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1406.55,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"I don''t know.","index":452,"end_time":1412.55,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1411.83,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"That one''s just a wording thing.","index":453,"end_time":1415.99,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1414.31,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"I think the other ones are really good.","index":454,"end_time":1418.31,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1416.39,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Obviously, we''re trying to stop the scroll here.","index":455,"end_time":1422.71,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1420.39,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yes.","index":456,"end_time":1424.07,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1423.59,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":457,"end_time":1424.59,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1424.23,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Keep them very brief, but also that they jump out.","index":458,"end_time":1428.51,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1424.59,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":459,"end_time":1429.31,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1428.83,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Yep.","index":460,"end_time":1430.99,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1430.43,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Okay.","index":461,"end_time":1432.03,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1431.39,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":462,"end_time":1433.15,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1432.59,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"How do we feel about.","index":463,"end_time":1433.95,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1433.15,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Because the metrics don''t speak to the CEO.","index":464,"end_time":1435.87,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1433.95,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":465,"end_time":1436.91,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1436.43,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Okay.","index":466,"end_time":1438.19,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1437.63,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Lovely.","index":467,"end_time":1440.39,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1439.79,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right, we will spin those up.","index":468,"end_time":1441.71,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1440.39,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right, so we have the spreadsheet.","index":469,"end_time":1446.39,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1444.91,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We went through and made an update, and I think, Rachel, based on our last call, you and Tracy were going.","index":470,"end_time":1454.43,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1446.39,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Through and making some changes as well.","index":471,"end_time":1455.71,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1454.43,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yes.","index":472,"end_time":1458.08,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1457.68,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"I believe it was more just we put things in the right order.","index":473,"end_time":1461.44,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1458.08,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Mike Linton will now be next week instead of this week, so that will push things a little bit.","index":474,"end_time":1471.92,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1462.08,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"So we have to adjust that.","index":475,"end_time":1474.4,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1472.8,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"And what''s my deadline on the Mike Linton descriptors?","index":476,"end_time":1479.84,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1476.56,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Rachel?","index":477,"end_time":1480.64,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1480,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"I would say if you could get them to me by end of day Friday.","index":478,"end_time":1485.53,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1482.33,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Worst case if it''s Monday, that''s okay.","index":479,"end_time":1487.93,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1485.77,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Okay.","index":480,"end_time":1492.25,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1491.69,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"The most important thing is, like, the introduction of this is coming and then the description for the podcast.","index":481,"end_time":1498.01,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1492.73,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Okay.","index":482,"end_time":1498.97,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1498.41,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"And our team just alerted Natalie and I that these assets are done, so we''re running them through the checklist.","index":483,"end_time":1504.09,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1499.21,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Great.","index":484,"end_time":1504.97,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1504.57,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Thank you so much.","index":485,"end_time":1506.09,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1504.97,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Of course.","index":486,"end_time":1507.13,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1506.65,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I also wanted to say that the very next one is Christine.","index":487,"end_time":1519.41,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1508.21,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"And so that date is correct.","index":488,"end_time":1521.97,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1520.37,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"That''s tomorrow.","index":489,"end_time":1522.77,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1521.97,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Kate Warnock.","index":490,"end_time":1524.21,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1522.85,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Let me just confirm that that date is.","index":491,"end_time":1528.69,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1526.05,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"No, Kate Warnock moved, but I have a confirmed new date.","index":492,"end_time":1539.82,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1534.46,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"It is.","index":493,"end_time":1540.7,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1539.98,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"It''s up a day.","index":494,"end_time":1549.62,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1548.62,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"It''s Wednesday the 12th.","index":495,"end_time":1550.94,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1549.62,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Okay.","index":496,"end_time":1552.3,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1551.74,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then Patrick McMaster is at large.","index":497,"end_time":1558.86,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1553.18,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"It''s moving.","index":498,"end_time":1562.82,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1562.18,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"It''s not today and it''ll be soon.","index":499,"end_time":1567.7,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1563.94,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"But the way it''s looking right now is probably going to be after Kate Warnock.","index":500,"end_time":1571.7,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1567.7,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Okay.","index":501,"end_time":1573.38,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1572.82,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Are you like the same week, later.","index":502,"end_time":1575.22,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1573.54,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"In the week or.","index":503,"end_time":1576.1,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1575.22,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Not sure, not sure.","index":504,"end_time":1580.66,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1578.98,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Like, we offered him.","index":505,"end_time":1582.1,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1580.74,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"We''re going back and forth.","index":506,"end_time":1583.46,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1582.58,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"We''ve offered him several dates, like in the teens of November.","index":507,"end_time":1586.98,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1583.46,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Gotcha.","index":508,"end_time":1588.2,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1587.72,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":509,"end_time":1588.68,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1588.2,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Well, luckily we have all the frameworks for all of them already developed.","index":510,"end_time":1594.76,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1589.88,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":511,"end_time":1596.28,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1595.88,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"And I, you know, I went so far as sent him his framework.","index":512,"end_time":1599.88,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1596.28,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"So that one squared away I have.","index":513,"end_time":1603.639,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1601.72,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Kate Warnock is on my to dos.","index":514,"end_time":1607.64,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1605.4,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Perfect.","index":515,"end_time":1608.6,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1608.2,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":516,"end_time":1609,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1608.6,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, we were just going to ask for an update there if you needed any changes to anything, but took your feedback from the last call where, you know, make some sections a little shorter for your speaking.","index":517,"end_time":1619.25,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1609,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And the, the one section that goes through like a look in the past, you know, evaluation type of thing, we did update several of those.","index":518,"end_time":1631.57,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1620.85,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"The first two are kind of framed a little similar because it is like a look in the past, lessons learned.","index":519,"end_time":1636.29,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1631.57,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then it goes into like more of a personalized, um, I mean.","index":520,"end_time":1639.3,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1636.29,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Cause Kate has.","index":521,"end_time":1640.94,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1639.3,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"When I opened up that thing to start working on the framework and then did the research, and she had just launched a new brand two days prior to us developing that framework, I was.","index":522,"end_time":1649.78,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1641.82,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Like, oh, my goodness, this is gonna.","index":523,"end_time":1650.86,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1649.78,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Be a kick ass episode.","index":524,"end_time":1652.62,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1650.86,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So that''s really what all of our questions dive into is like, merger happened in I think May, and then a rebrand happened five months later.","index":525,"end_time":1661.58,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1653.02,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Like, it''s all about that timeline, the communication internally, externally.","index":526,"end_time":1666.67,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1661.58,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So I feel really strongly about what that one.","index":527,"end_time":1669.27,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1667.47,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But let me know if you have any feedback.","index":528,"end_time":1670.75,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1669.27,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Very good, Will do.","index":529,"end_time":1672.35,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1671.23,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Thanks for the heads up.","index":530,"end_time":1673.63,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1672.51,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Of course.","index":531,"end_time":1674.51,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1673.87,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then, Rachel, these are the other ones that we''re also going through the checklist and we''ll be sharing if everything''s.","index":532,"end_time":1683.07,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1676.03,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All good on those.","index":533,"end_time":1683.79,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1683.07,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Perfect.","index":534,"end_time":1685.39,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1684.83,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Rachel, on Christine McCain.","index":535,"end_time":1689.31,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1685.63,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Did we get confirmation from her assistant that she did get the platform invite?","index":536,"end_time":1696,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1690.2,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"I think we did.","index":537,"end_time":1696.84,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1696,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Christine Calvin is.","index":538,"end_time":1699.88,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1697.24,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Yeah, let me double check.","index":539,"end_time":1702.76,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1700.12,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"I see what you did there.","index":540,"end_time":1705.12,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1704.28,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Christine from McCain Foods.","index":541,"end_time":1706.76,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1705.12,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Oh, good catch.","index":542,"end_time":1709.2,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1706.92,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Because I was very confused.","index":543,"end_time":1710.52,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1709.2,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Yeah, I think it''s Calvine''s.","index":544,"end_time":1713.52,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1711.56,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Is how you say her last name, Christine?","index":545,"end_time":1716.13,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1713.52,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yeah, she has it.","index":546,"end_time":1717.57,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1716.45,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"We, we spoke to her assistant, Karen.","index":547,"end_time":1719.89,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1717.81,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"And you were saying that you''re going to cancel the original?","index":548,"end_time":1722.21,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1719.97,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, that''s right.","index":549,"end_time":1723.85,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1722.85,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Okay.","index":550,"end_time":1724.29,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1723.85,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Just wanted to make sure that we were squared away.","index":551,"end_time":1727.65,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1724.61,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Sometimes when I do it in advance, like, it''s good because the leader wants it in advance, but then I forget that I did it.","index":552,"end_time":1734.21,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1727.65,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Beautiful.","index":553,"end_time":1735.33,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1734.53,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"And we can see.","index":554,"end_time":1736.73,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1735.49,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"What I think we should do is when we have our next internal marketing.","index":555,"end_time":1740.05,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1736.73,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Let''s go over this sheet, make sure everything is, like, in the right order.","index":556,"end_time":1742.89,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1740.05,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"And.","index":557,"end_time":1743.25,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1742.89,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yeah, and I need to do a wave with these people who are neither yeses nor no''s from Phil Cook onward and.","index":558,"end_time":1753.05,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1743.85,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"And clean that up a bit.","index":559,"end_time":1754.33,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1753.05,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":560,"end_time":1757.45,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1756.97,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":561,"end_time":1757.69,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1757.45,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And as soon as that''s updated, if you either just like a comment in the sheet or send me an email and we''ll just go through and establish based on recording dates when we''ll get the framework over to you.","index":562,"end_time":1766.77,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1757.69,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":563,"end_time":1767.21,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1766.77,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Nobody is real after Patrick, who''s now coming after Kate, like everybody else is a tbd.","index":564,"end_time":1777.62,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1767.21,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Do you want me to adjust that, Rachel, just to come after?","index":565,"end_time":1780.42,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1778.18,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Feel free.","index":566,"end_time":1781.54,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1780.9,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":567,"end_time":1782.54,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1782.18,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"And I think that the next after Patrick is likely to be Mac McGee, because I am booked now to speak with him not for the podcast, but, like, as a precursor to the podcast.","index":568,"end_time":1797.38,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1782.54,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"But I''m not going to count my chickens until he says yes.","index":569,"end_time":1801.58,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1798.78,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Understood.","index":570,"end_time":1802.86,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1802.14,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right, perfect.","index":571,"end_time":1805.5,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1804.62,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Thank you.","index":572,"end_time":1806.78,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1806.22,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Anything else?","index":573,"end_time":1807.82,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1807.1,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":574,"end_time":1809.06,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1808.7,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"For this sheet, if you go to the guest to tab at the bottom, I created another view just in case this is helpful to keep track where we highlight it in green when those steps are done.","index":575,"end_time":1821.1,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1809.06,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"And then also added the final podcast frameworks here that we get back from Nancy so we can keep better organization of everything.","index":576,"end_time":1828.5,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1821.1,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Thank you, Natalie.","index":577,"end_time":1830.06,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1829.14,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"That''s amazing.","index":578,"end_time":1830.66,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1830.06,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Yeah, that''s great.","index":579,"end_time":1831.7,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1830.82,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Thank you so much.","index":580,"end_time":1833.14,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1832.1,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Lovely.","index":581,"end_time":1838.26,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1837.62,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":582,"end_time":1839.7,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1839.06,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"I love it.","index":583,"end_time":1841.22,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1840.42,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"So the.","index":584,"end_time":1843.5,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1842.98,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"The podcast question that we have, Rachel and I were trying to dissect, like, how do we get out of so much back and forth?","index":585,"end_time":1851.62,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1843.5,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"And it''s.","index":586,"end_time":1852.53,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1852.01,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"And it''s delaying us.","index":587,"end_time":1854.41,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1852.53,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"You know, we have this, like, backlog, and we want to be able to always hit our cadence with the least amount of wear and tear.","index":588,"end_time":1861.69,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1854.49,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"So, you know, there''s a lot of ways in which we can try to simplify, but we.","index":589,"end_time":1868.85,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1863.29,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"We don''t want to lose effectiveness.","index":590,"end_time":1871.13,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1868.85,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"And so that made me question the quote cards, like, how.","index":591,"end_time":1877.85,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1872.01,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"How important are they?","index":592,"end_time":1881.15,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1880.03,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Because that''s one of the places where, like, I. I have a bias that people want to see.","index":593,"end_time":1887.47,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1881.79,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"They want to see video.","index":594,"end_time":1891.79,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1890.19,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Right.","index":595,"end_time":1892.23,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1891.87,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"They want to see people talking, whether it''s a snippet or what have you.","index":596,"end_time":1896.11,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1892.23,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"So I just want to better Understand, like, how are we using the quote cards?","index":597,"end_time":1901.07,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1897.55,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"And do you think that they are important to keep in the mix?","index":598,"end_time":1905.47,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1901.07,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"So I''ve always been a fan of quote cards because I''m a read before I open type of person, if that makes sense.","index":599,"end_time":1912.76,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1906.4,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So, like, even if I see a video start autoplaying, which LinkedIn does I need to see, like, is what they''re saying, like, does it matter to me?","index":600,"end_time":1921.32,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1912.76,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Should I even open and expand this?","index":601,"end_time":1922.8,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1921.32,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"A quote card is a much easier.","index":602,"end_time":1924.64,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1922.8,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Like, oh, wow, okay, cool.","index":603,"end_time":1926.92,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1924.72,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That actually is something I want to dive into.","index":604,"end_time":1929.28,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1926.92,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Does that make sense?","index":605,"end_time":1931.6,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1930.64,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":606,"end_time":1932.62,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1932.26,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":607,"end_time":1933.02,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1932.62,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"So I think you''re saying some people are more.","index":608,"end_time":1934.74,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1933.02,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"I mean, I never click on the sound on the video.","index":609,"end_time":1938.06,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1934.74,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"I just read the supers.","index":610,"end_time":1939.94,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1938.06,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Right?","index":611,"end_time":1940.82,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1940.42,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":612,"end_time":1941.7,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1941.38,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I mean, I think everyone goes about it a little differently.","index":613,"end_time":1943.94,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1941.7,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I just know in today''s world, like, it almost even relates to, like, emails, you know, all sorts of things.","index":614,"end_time":1949.62,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1945.06,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We have so much information flowing.","index":615,"end_time":1951.22,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1949.62,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You know, people are reading the equivalent of like hundreds of newspapers a day nowadays with just emails and social media and everything.","index":616,"end_time":1959.01,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1952.34,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So people are skimming largely across the board.","index":617,"end_time":1962.33,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1959.25,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And that''s why I find, like, a quote card with, you know, 10 to 20 words is very easy, digestible, and kind of points them into like, okay, this content is actually relevant to me.","index":618,"end_time":1971.41,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1962.33,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So if we keep them, I hear you.","index":619,"end_time":1975.33,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1972.69,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"If we keep them, how do we get to.","index":620,"end_time":1979.81,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1976.29,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"How do we get faster to quotes that are very, like, concise, well said and attention grabbing?","index":621,"end_time":1987,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1980.61,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Like, I know you said that you have clients who want it said exactly like the person said it, but.","index":622,"end_time":1993.08,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1987,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"But we''re more of the mind that, like, we want it said well so that look at it polished.","index":623,"end_time":1999.04,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1993.16,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"And somebody would look at it and be like, oh, wow, that''s interesting.","index":624,"end_time":2002.2,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1999.04,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Right?","index":625,"end_time":2002.52,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2002.2,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"I would like more.","index":626,"end_time":2003.4,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2002.52,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"And I would say, like, half the time the quotes are not feeling that way.","index":627,"end_time":2008.68,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2004.76,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"They''re like, clunky or the grammar''s weird or whatever.","index":628,"end_time":2011.32,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2008.68,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Rachel, I know you said that the AI function within Riverside can help with that.","index":629,"end_time":2020.04,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2013.4,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Like, should we be leading with that instead of me suggesting snippets like, what''s the better way?","index":630,"end_time":2026.04,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2020.6,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Well, I think one thing that we can do is before even designing, developing, like, those quote cards, we could just send a list and be like, here are the, you know, top quotes that we found or like, that we feel strongly about inside of here, direct quote and like a reword to be polished.","index":631,"end_time":2043.61,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2027.8,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then I think that would help because we''re going into, like, design pretty quickly.","index":632,"end_time":2047.89,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2044.01,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So I think if we take a step back and just say, like, content wise, are we comfortable with this and then.","index":633,"end_time":2052.93,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2047.89,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And we could just do it as an email.","index":634,"end_time":2054.49,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2052.93,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yeah, because I would think.","index":635,"end_time":2056.09,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2054.57,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"I think that that would help us.","index":636,"end_time":2058.41,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2056.65,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Even though it''s like an extra step.","index":637,"end_time":2059.97,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2058.41,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"I think it would lead to a less back and forth.","index":638,"end_time":2064.25,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2059.97,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"And as you''re doing that, a couple of things to bear in mind.","index":639,"end_time":2067.93,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2064.65,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"One is that we want it to be just like a really easy but polished get like something insightful, kind of meaty, but said concisely.","index":640,"end_time":2077.94,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2068.58,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Two, I''d love to have in the mix something that does do a little bit of noetic promotion where appropriate.","index":641,"end_time":2088.1,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2078.26,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"So if it''s once in a while me being quoted and I''m saying just a snippet that''s insightful and has relevance to them and doesn''t feel cringy, you know, consider putting those in the mix too.","index":642,"end_time":2102.92,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2089.06,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"The same as we do are doing with the video snippets.","index":643,"end_time":2106.12,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2102.92,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, we can absolutely do that.","index":644,"end_time":2108.28,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2106.52,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"One question on the quote cards.","index":645,"end_time":2110.2,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2108.6,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Just because sometimes, usually not you, but the guest can be a bit long winded and it''s like a powerful quote, but it''d be way too long to put on a quote card.","index":646,"end_time":2117.76,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2110.36,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"How do you feel about ellipses?","index":647,"end_time":2119,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2117.76,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Where like we kind of start with like the frame and then like ellipses and like connect to the end of what that like powerful quote is.","index":648,"end_time":2127.32,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2119.24,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I''m fine with that.","index":649,"end_time":2129.64,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2128.2,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"You can also do like the dot, dot, dot.","index":650,"end_time":2132.28,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2129.64,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yeah, that''s.","index":651,"end_time":2133.12,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2132.52,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":652,"end_time":2133.36,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2133.12,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Ellipses.","index":653,"end_time":2133.96,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2133.36,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, that''s the ellipses.","index":654,"end_time":2135.36,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2134.2,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Okay.","index":655,"end_time":2135.64,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2135.36,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"I didn''t know if you meant.","index":656,"end_time":2136.52,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2135.64,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"I didn''t know what you meant.","index":657,"end_time":2137.88,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2136.84,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"I think I hopefully got that term.","index":658,"end_time":2140.12,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2138.2,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, I''m.","index":659,"end_time":2140.72,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2140.12,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"I''m fine with that.","index":660,"end_time":2141.56,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2140.72,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"I mean, I, I think that people get it.","index":661,"end_time":2146.28,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2141.56,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yep.","index":662,"end_time":2147.32,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2146.68,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right.","index":663,"end_time":2148.45,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2148.05,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And nobody wants to listen to somebody struggling to get to the point.","index":664,"end_time":2154.05,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2149.01,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":665,"end_time":2154.85,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2154.53,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And honestly, I''ve even seen.","index":666,"end_time":2156.29,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2154.85,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And personally, I feel like if there''s an ellipses and it''s like, oh, I really like how that started and how it ended.","index":667,"end_time":2161.69,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2156.61,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I actually.","index":668,"end_time":2162.13,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2161.69,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It kind of eggs me on more to watch the episode and see what.","index":669,"end_time":2164.97,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2162.29,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That full quote was.","index":670,"end_time":2165.97,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2164.97,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":671,"end_time":2167.97,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2167.49,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"All right, Fantastic.","index":672,"end_time":2170.25,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2169.17,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, Natalie, we''ll update the process on that then.","index":673,"end_time":2173.57,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2170.25,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Amazing.","index":674,"end_time":2174.69,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2174.21,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Thank you so much.","index":675,"end_time":2175.65,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2174.69,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Of course.","index":676,"end_time":2176.41,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2175.89,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then we have Mike''s episode delivered.","index":677,"end_time":2180.13,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2176.41,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Tomorrow and reminder Rachel that with Mike Linton, his guy Jeff wants all the assets.","index":678,"end_time":2191.81,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2180.13,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yes, got it.","index":679,"end_time":2194.05,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2192.37,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Not from an approval standpoint, but it''s because he.","index":680,"end_time":2198.05,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2194.45,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"He has a podcast and so they''ll be a little bit more elaborate in their promotion.","index":681,"end_time":2206.28,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2199.56,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Okay, got it.","index":682,"end_time":2208.44,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2206.68,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":683,"end_time":2210.52,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2209.88,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right.","index":684,"end_time":2211.8,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2211.24,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Going through some ads.","index":685,"end_time":2213.16,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2211.8,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So healthcare campaign.","index":686,"end_time":2215.48,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2214.04,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Nine clicks and three form fills.","index":687,"end_time":2217.84,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2215.64,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So Three leads coming through last week at a much lower cost per lead than we''ve seen traditionally, so trending in the right direction.","index":688,"end_time":2224.52,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2217.84,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So.","index":689,"end_time":2225.02,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2224.76,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"So I wanted to ask you, what were those three leads?","index":690,"end_time":2229.57,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2225.09,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yeah, I can go download the.","index":691,"end_time":2232.69,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2230.93,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I feel like we got a slew, but then we didn''t last week and I just want to make sure I''m not missing anything.","index":692,"end_time":2240.61,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2233.09,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":693,"end_time":2245.09,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2244.69,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So Natalie and I are also, like evaluating because some of them aren''t super high quality leads, which just leads us to make targeting changes.","index":694,"end_time":2251.97,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2245.09,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And so we''re evaluating them before passing them into pipedrive.","index":695,"end_time":2255.5,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2252.7,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I see.","index":696,"end_time":2256.86,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2256.3,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Okay.","index":697,"end_time":2257.5,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2256.86,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Because I haven''t seen anything new in the last week or so.","index":698,"end_time":2261.58,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2258.62,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":699,"end_time":2263.34,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2262.78,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And this was for last week.","index":700,"end_time":2266.22,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2263.58,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":701,"end_time":2267.82,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2267.26,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"So they may.","index":702,"end_time":2268.86,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2268.139,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"One or several may still pop in.","index":703,"end_time":2271.58,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2269.5,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Sounds nice.","index":704,"end_time":2272.18,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2271.58,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yes.","index":705,"end_time":2272.54,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2272.18,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":706,"end_time":2273.26,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2272.7,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"I did want to tell you, just FYI, that with all of those Marriott people, what I ended up doing is I tried to hand deliver a package to them because they''re.","index":707,"end_time":2286.46,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2273.42,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":708,"end_time":2286.66,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2286.46,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"With the book and the personal note.","index":709,"end_time":2287.94,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2286.66,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I was not successful in hand delivering their security was not having it.","index":710,"end_time":2292.98,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2288.02,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"But what I did do is I, I mailed them like I physically mailed them.","index":711,"end_time":2300.06,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2294.58,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"So they should have gotten them yesterday or today.","index":712,"end_time":2304.58,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2300.06,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"And then I''m going to follow up in the meantime.","index":713,"end_time":2307.33,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2305.41,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"I did get.","index":714,"end_time":2308.21,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2307.33,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"So the challenge with Marriott is that my emails do not go through and I only learn like a day or two later.","index":715,"end_time":2315.09,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2308.21,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"So I know it''s like their filter that''s like back.","index":716,"end_time":2318.81,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2315.33,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"So it like sits in purgatory.","index":717,"end_time":2320.05,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2318.81,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Then they don''t let me through.","index":718,"end_time":2321.25,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2320.13,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"But on LinkedIn, I did get traction with one person, Tanya, and she agreed to meet, but I''ve not landed it.","index":719,"end_time":2331.69,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2321.89,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"And I was trying to pull this back into email and again, it won''t go through, so.","index":720,"end_time":2335.12,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2331.69,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"So I''m knocking at the door with Marriott.","index":721,"end_time":2338.11,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2335.43,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"There''s something there.","index":722,"end_time":2339.03,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2338.11,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"I also with Truist, I did get a bite for a conversation.","index":723,"end_time":2345.35,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2340.23,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"There''s three truest people.","index":724,"end_time":2347.27,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2345.51,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"I triangulated the truest people with Wells Fargo people because the Wells.","index":725,"end_time":2353.71,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2348.07,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Because the truest people are former Wells Fargo people.","index":726,"end_time":2356.47,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2353.71,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"They weren''t answering me.","index":727,"end_time":2357.99,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2356.87,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"And so I reached out to a couple of my Wells Fargo former clients and said, do you know so and so?","index":728,"end_time":2363.46,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2357.99,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Do you know so and so?","index":729,"end_time":2364.3,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2363.46,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Can I drop your name?","index":730,"end_time":2365.3,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2364.3,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"And that got me through with this one woman, so I''m booked with her.","index":731,"end_time":2370.18,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2365.78,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Just.","index":732,"end_time":2370.66,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2370.26,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Okay.","index":733,"end_time":2371.22,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2370.74,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But I feel like there''s something there too, because whenever you get multiple.","index":734,"end_time":2376.02,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2372.26,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"So just chipping away.","index":735,"end_time":2379.62,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2376.58,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"It''s slow going, but chipping away.","index":736,"end_time":2384.1,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2381.94,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":737,"end_time":2384.9,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2384.42,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I think LinkedIn has definitely proven to be the best channel and it''s really?","index":738,"end_time":2390.17,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2385.54,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Not only just for you guys, but we''re seeing that kind of across the board.","index":739,"end_time":2392.77,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2390.17,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"People are so inundated with emails.","index":740,"end_time":2394.89,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2393.33,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It''s really.","index":741,"end_time":2395.25,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2394.89,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Another reminder is almost how I think of the emails.","index":742,"end_time":2399.33,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2395.25,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And there was.","index":743,"end_time":2400.77,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2400.05,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":744,"end_time":2402.89,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2402.53,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"And there''s.","index":745,"end_time":2403.25,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2402.89,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Oh, Tanya.","index":746,"end_time":2403.85,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2403.25,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":747,"end_time":2404.17,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2403.85,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So that was her.","index":748,"end_time":2405.01,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2404.17,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Tanya Galarza.","index":749,"end_time":2406.53,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2405.49,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yep.","index":750,"end_time":2407.25,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2406.77,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":751,"end_time":2407.65,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2407.25,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":752,"end_time":2408.77,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2408.21,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We have those notifications come through in our internal slack and I responded with the fire emoji.","index":753,"end_time":2413.89,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2409.49,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I was excited about her response.","index":754,"end_time":2415.41,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2413.97,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":755,"end_time":2418.58,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2418.34,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"So I was trying to get her to email me, but it wasn''t working.","index":756,"end_time":2424.1,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2418.58,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Just writing her back and telling her it bounced.","index":757,"end_time":2429.22,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2427.14,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"So in.","index":758,"end_time":2432.82,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2430.9,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Can you go back to the deck?","index":759,"end_time":2434.82,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2433.3,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yes.","index":760,"end_time":2435.54,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2435.14,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Sorry, I was just pulling up Hate reach.","index":761,"end_time":2437.06,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2435.54,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"There.","index":762,"end_time":2444.03,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2443.79,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Was there a question before I dove into the rest?","index":763,"end_time":2456.99,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2454.99,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I''m just reading it again.","index":764,"end_time":2458.11,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2456.99,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":765,"end_time":2464.71,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2464.27,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"So the.","index":766,"end_time":2465.23,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2464.71,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"The new heads of marketing.","index":767,"end_time":2468.31,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2465.39,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"It''s just.","index":768,"end_time":2470.99,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2470.47,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"It.","index":769,"end_time":2471.23,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2470.99,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"It''s just a competitive space.","index":770,"end_time":2472.71,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2471.23,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yeah, it is.","index":771,"end_time":2473.83,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2472.79,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Get their attention.","index":772,"end_time":2474.71,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2473.83,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"It is.","index":773,"end_time":2477.91,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2477.43,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But we are getting in front of the right titles, which is great.","index":774,"end_time":2481.71,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2477.91,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It.","index":775,"end_time":2481.99,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2481.71,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And we''re seeing some clicks.","index":776,"end_time":2483.43,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2481.99,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We obviously want to see more click volume, but yeah, it is.","index":777,"end_time":2487.55,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2484.07,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It''s a very expensive audience.","index":778,"end_time":2490.47,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2487.55,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":779,"end_time":2491.51,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2490.95,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":780,"end_time":2492.47,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2491.91,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Okay.","index":781,"end_time":2494.28,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2493.96,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"I think that''s everything on that page.","index":782,"end_time":2496.2,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2494.28,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":783,"end_time":2497.12,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2496.68,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then add role is the programmatic display.","index":784,"end_time":2499.2,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2497.12,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So again, not typically a lead driver.","index":785,"end_time":2501.44,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2499.2,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But we did see four clicks, so that''s great.","index":786,"end_time":2504.28,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2501.44,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right.","index":787,"end_time":2508.6,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2508.12,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then I know we wanted to dive into this as well.","index":788,"end_time":2510.44,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2508.6,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Was there anything specific or just kind of go over everything?","index":789,"end_time":2512.52,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2510.44,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Let''s just go over it.","index":790,"end_time":2516.92,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2515.56,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Okay.","index":791,"end_time":2517.72,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2517.16,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"So this is comparing October to September, so continuing to see upward trends.","index":792,"end_time":2522.59,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2518.43,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"A 2% increase in overall views to the website.","index":793,"end_time":2525.47,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2522.83,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Not a substantial increase, but better than going down.","index":794,"end_time":2528.67,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2526.11,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"When that''s combined with average session duration and views per session increasing as well, that means that we''re getting the right.","index":795,"end_time":2535.47,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2530.11,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"People to the site.","index":796,"end_time":2536.35,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2535.47,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So they''re spending twice as long on the site than they were in September.","index":797,"end_time":2540.91,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2536.51,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Meaning that they''re finding content valuable.","index":798,"end_time":2543.07,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2540.91,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"They''re navigating around.","index":799,"end_time":2544.19,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2543.15,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And I know we even joked last week that you guys are going on the site and you''re probably bringing down the average engagement time because you know.","index":800,"end_time":2550.4,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2544.76,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Exactly where to go.","index":801,"end_time":2551.16,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2550.4,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So the fact that we''re seeing this average so high, it''s a great indicator that the content is resonating with people.","index":802,"end_time":2556.76,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2551.24,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"What I will say about that is I think there are opportunities on the site to increase some interlinking.","index":803,"end_time":2563.28,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2558.28,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And what I mean by that is different places, like on the homepage or other pages, we can reference brand diagnostics, the services that you guys provide, rather than relying on people to use the navigation.","index":804,"end_time":2575.46,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2563.28,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Does that make sense?","index":805,"end_time":2576.98,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2576.02,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And I know we Also talked about and I think you''re doing this in your retreat but like the AI offering and really how we can even get content for that on the website.","index":806,"end_time":2588.34,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2579.14,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":807,"end_time":2590.66,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2590.18,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"So let''s talk about that for a minute.","index":808,"end_time":2593.14,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2590.9,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"So the here''s, here''s my thought is that know in these conferences obviously it''s all AI all the time and you know the whole notion of the ability to really slice and dice creative assets a million different ways when you''re like high volume, like that''s not our wheelhouse.","index":809,"end_time":2614.75,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2593.14,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"The thing that really came up for me when I was like listening to all of the trends and the needs is really around training and, and when I say training like not per se like we, we certainly do how we have a basic training, we could build a more sophisticated one around teaching people how to navigate within AI.","index":810,"end_time":2636.92,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2615.55,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"But more so what I was hearing is like getting people the skill sets that they need for this AI world.","index":811,"end_time":2644.6,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2637.4,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"So things like.","index":812,"end_time":2645.88,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2644.84,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Let me just show you.","index":813,"end_time":2647.96,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2647,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Can I, can I pull on my screen.","index":814,"end_time":2650.12,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2647.96,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"I wrote this.","index":815,"end_time":2651.48,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2650.64,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"I''m not saying it''s like amazing or anything, but I wrote this email and this will give you the gist of it.","index":816,"end_time":2667.36,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2651.48,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Jason, I was at the a Master marketing last month and as you will easily imagine, AI was everywhere.","index":817,"end_time":2677.68,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2672.64,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"One of the key insights I gave that I want to share with you is the need for strong leadership and human based skilled to be developed.","index":818,"end_time":2682.98,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2677.68,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Alongside the radical changes AI is bringing critical power skills now include this is the list and noetic.","index":819,"end_time":2693.02,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2682.98,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"We are hard at work developing and delivering curriculum of this nature, blah blah blah blah.","index":820,"end_time":2696.98,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2693.02,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"So this guy is doing AI training, training within Wells Fargo by the way sent him this note and got a bounce that he''s no longer there.","index":821,"end_time":2706.54,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2696.98,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"So there''s that but because he had come in through New north efforts.","index":822,"end_time":2714.48,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2707.42,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"But this, this is kind of the fodder right here.","index":823,"end_time":2717.84,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2714.64,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Basically it''s like in order for us to manage effectively where we''re managing in a bot non bot world, these are the skills that the humans need to have.","index":824,"end_time":2728.4,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2718.24,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"And as you can see it''s a lot more around, you know, human to human contact as well as just being more of a curator as opposed to.","index":825,"end_time":2743.95,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2730,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"And a thinker as opposed to a doer.","index":826,"end_time":2746.47,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2743.95,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":827,"end_time":2747.35,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2746.87,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So I''m, I''m handing you like a ball of clay.","index":828,"end_time":2751.39,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2747.83,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Right.","index":829,"end_time":2751.71,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2751.39,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Like it''s just, it''s the notion of what it is.","index":830,"end_time":2753.79,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2751.71,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"But my question is like what could we do with that?","index":831,"end_time":2756.95,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2753.79,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"I mean we have the playbook way, right?","index":832,"end_time":2763.87,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2758.55,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Is it ads, is it email, secret?","index":833,"end_time":2766.51,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2764.43,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Like what is it?","index":834,"end_time":2768.83,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2766.59,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"I think AI is a massive buzzword.","index":835,"end_time":2772.51,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2769.71,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And I would love to tap into it.","index":836,"end_time":2773.79,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2772.51,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I think it''s a different offer than.","index":837,"end_time":2775.589,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2773.79,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"A playbook is what I would probably.","index":838,"end_time":2777.15,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2775.589,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Prefer to lean into.","index":839,"end_time":2778.11,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2777.15,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And it would be maybe a workshop or something along those lines.","index":840,"end_time":2784.99,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2778.19,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So there''s a lot of buzzwords even in the bucket of AI.","index":841,"end_time":2789.14,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2785.47,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"One of them is governance.","index":842,"end_time":2790.42,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2789.14,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You know, AI governance and how even company policy applies to AI.","index":843,"end_time":2794.82,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2790.98,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I think that is certainly something that many businesses are struggling with.","index":844,"end_time":2798.5,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2795.14,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Either they are just like, yeah, guys, go use ChatGPT, or they''re like, I don''t want anything AI.","index":845,"end_time":2804.74,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2799.46,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Or they''re somewhere stuck in the middle and they''re getting mixed results from everyone.","index":846,"end_time":2809.38,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2806.26,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I think what teams need is a process and a system and, like, almost boundaries to operate within.","index":847,"end_time":2816.28,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2809.38,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And I think that a workshop where you guys walk them through that and establish, you know, probably meeting with executives of, like, how do you want, how do you envision AI working within your company?","index":848,"end_time":2825.96,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2816.68,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"What are the problems you''re dealing with?","index":849,"end_time":2827.36,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2825.96,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"How can AI streamline those and make your employees more effective?","index":850,"end_time":2830.84,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2827.36,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then disseminating that information, you know, probably with some policy or guideline documentation to the rest of the team.","index":851,"end_time":2837.48,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2831.4,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Does that make sense?","index":852,"end_time":2838.92,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2837.96,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yes, it does.","index":853,"end_time":2839.76,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2839,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"And I''m going to add on to that, which is that I think by and large, a lot of organizations thus far have only figured out, like, people are working as individuals, gaining efficiencies and doing things faster and perhaps more robustly, but they''re not operationalized as a team doing that.","index":854,"end_time":2863.12,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2839.76,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"And so one thing that we''ve done in the past that I think it''s just like a cousin to is process mapping.","index":855,"end_time":2873.3,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2863.84,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yes.","index":856,"end_time":2874.26,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2873.86,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Or ways of working workflow mapping.","index":857,"end_time":2876.62,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2874.26,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"I''m using those, like, interchangeably, where we do a workshop and we walk through, you know, the core processes and map it visually and then determine where and how AI should come in and shouldn''t come in.","index":858,"end_time":2892.5,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2876.62,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"And then.","index":859,"end_time":2893.86,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2893.3,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"And then it''s a cousin to what you''re saying, because then you figure out, okay, this is how we want to do it.","index":860,"end_time":2898.42,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2894.02,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"And then you make, you know, your governance kind of around that.","index":861,"end_time":2902.48,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2898.98,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"But it''s like without that, people aren''t coming together in any kind of a coordinated manner.","index":862,"end_time":2909.68,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2902.72,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":863,"end_time":2910.72,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2910.24,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And there''s a few things.","index":864,"end_time":2913.04,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2911.36,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"There''s even like the scare approach of.","index":865,"end_time":2915.68,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2913.04,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I mean, we''ve all heard, like, Shopify and Salesforce eliminating 3/4 of their staff to replace with AI, even Refine Labs.","index":866,"end_time":2924.84,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2916.24,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Nancy, I''m not sure if you''re familiar with Refine Labs, but they, they.","index":867,"end_time":2927.76,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2924.84,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You.","index":868,"end_time":2929.72,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2929.6,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Know, went through and they had a retreat, told everyone everything was great.","index":869,"end_time":2934.88,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2929.72,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then the next week fired 80% of their staff.","index":870,"end_time":2937.36,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2934.88,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I don''t know how much of that was rooted in AI versus also they got acquired.","index":871,"end_time":2942.56,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2938.24,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So you know, there''s a lot of a mixed bag there.","index":872,"end_time":2945.96,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2944.24,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But I think there are some like stories to tap into there.","index":873,"end_time":2949.12,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2945.96,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You know, if we''re talking to executives, it might be making your team more effective, but if we''re talking to the actual marketing personnel on their team, it might be like bringing the best work out of people.","index":874,"end_time":2961.9,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2949.36,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Not truly just an effective approach, but like amplifying their work.","index":875,"end_time":2966.7,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2962.06,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So I think there''s a few things that we can tap into there.","index":876,"end_time":2970.54,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2968.46,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then also I know, I think we can have a landing page dedicated to this and just ask a few high level questions of is your team currently using AI?","index":877,"end_time":2978.62,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2970.699,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then we could have logic branch out of that, like if you are using it, like what departments?","index":878,"end_time":2984.08,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2978.7,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Or we can even dive into like how are you using it?","index":879,"end_time":2986.32,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2984.08,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Just kind of like really probably three or five light questions just to get a feel for is it even being used?","index":880,"end_time":2992.16,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2986.32,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"How is it being used?","index":881,"end_time":2993.04,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2992.16,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then that gives you some insight to email them.","index":882,"end_time":2995.36,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2993.04,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Be like, hey, you know, thanks for filling out a form.","index":883,"end_time":2997.48,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2995.36,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You know, I see that X, Y and Z is happening at your company.","index":884,"end_time":3001.32,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2998.52,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We actually offer workshops to get your team, you know, all on the same page about hey, how AI should be.","index":885,"end_time":3007.48,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3002.2,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Used at your company.","index":886,"end_time":3008.87,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3007.48,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Because I think we''d be like, have we expressly done it exactly like that before?","index":887,"end_time":3012.91,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3008.87,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"No, but I think we''d be really good at it because it''s not different than doing process mapping workflow.","index":888,"end_time":3019.39,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3012.99,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"That''s pretty much what AI is.","index":889,"end_time":3022.27,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3019.71,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah.","index":890,"end_time":3023.63,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3022.67,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"I mean so, and we''re doing it, we''re modeling it for ourselves so that everybody else.","index":891,"end_time":3029.11,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3023.63,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Because a lot of the team hasn''t done process mapping.","index":892,"end_time":3032.03,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3029.11,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"I''ve done process mapping.","index":893,"end_time":3033.79,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3032.43,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"And so we''re going to actually see it, Rachel, you know, in our off site next week.","index":894,"end_time":3039.29,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3034.35,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"I, I like that idea of like if you could get somebody to engage with, like where are you at?","index":895,"end_time":3046.89,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3041.61,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"And then the follow up can be around, here''s how we could help you.","index":896,"end_time":3050.97,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3046.97,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yeah, I think that''s good.","index":897,"end_time":3056.57,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3055.45,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"The only thing I would say around the, the staff reduction is that the hype and the fear are really beleaguering people.","index":898,"end_time":3067.56,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3056.57,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"And I, and I worry a bit about like the turning people off.","index":899,"end_time":3072.92,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3068.68,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"So I just want to stay away from the fear mongering.","index":900,"end_time":3076.76,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3073.56,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yes.","index":901,"end_time":3077.36,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3077,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You know, you want us to be more like the help, not the, not the like pouring salt in the wound of what people are already worried about.","index":902,"end_time":3088.16,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3077.36,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"It''s like me know what to do with it.","index":903,"end_time":3089.69,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3088.16,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"There was a guy at ANA who was one of the last speakers, and I so appreciated him.","index":904,"end_time":3093.97,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3089.69,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"And I felt like everybody in the room was like, yes, thank you.","index":905,"end_time":3096.33,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3093.97,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Because he gave really practical tips.","index":906,"end_time":3100.33,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3096.49,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"He, you know, a lot of the people other than that were showing us shiny, cool AI things, but then they just kept talking about, like, how big it is and how you got to get on the train.","index":907,"end_time":3112.65,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3101.69,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"And it''s like, huh, okay, why don''t you tell me how?","index":908,"end_time":3117.7,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3112.73,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"I think how is cool.","index":909,"end_time":3121.5,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3120.34,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And I also think I''m even just picturing a graphic, because as part of our rock last quarter, Tristan and I rebuilt, like, our entire ABM process, and it''s mapped out in a whole different flow now.","index":910,"end_time":3130.98,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3121.5,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And I''m even thinking looking at that from a macro level and then having, like, a graphic effect to zoom in on just one of those, like, nodes or aspects that''s happening, I think tying into that could be really cool, like taking the macro, but even diving into the micro action that is happening and how this affects the whole chain of events from a process standpoint.","index":911,"end_time":3152.42,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3132.34,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I kind of know what you mean.","index":912,"end_time":3154.58,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3153.22,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"So, like, here, let me.","index":913,"end_time":3157.06,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3155.7,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"This is going to be probably kind.","index":914,"end_time":3159.18,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3157.86,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Of crazy to look at, but this is how Tristan.","index":915,"end_time":3161.94,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3159.18,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"My brains work, so don''t judge me.","index":916,"end_time":3166.66,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3162.1,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I''m excited to see.","index":917,"end_time":3168.95,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3168.03,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"This might be a scribble.","index":918,"end_time":3171.87,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3168.95,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"That''s fine.","index":919,"end_time":3172.59,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3171.87,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"So this is everything that is happening in an ABM campaign at a macro level.","index":920,"end_time":3180.11,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3174.03,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we have Smart Lead that we''re using to send emails.","index":921,"end_time":3183.23,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3180.75,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"This is a process map.","index":922,"end_time":3184.27,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3183.23,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Exactly.","index":923,"end_time":3184.99,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3184.43,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So it''s sending webhooks from Smart Lead, which is where we''re sending emails, defining variables, and then going and basically analyzing what.","index":924,"end_time":3192.86,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3186.11,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"What is coming in.","index":925,"end_time":3193.93,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3193.01,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Is it a bounce?","index":926,"end_time":3194.97,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3193.93,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Is it a reply?","index":927,"end_time":3195.93,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3194.97,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Is that reply positive and mapping into a flow?","index":928,"end_time":3200.13,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3195.93,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we''re doing sentiment analysis in here.","index":929,"end_time":3202.21,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3200.37,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So, like, what I''m saying is, I think a cool graphic would be showing a flowchart like this and then having, like, almost a magnifying glass to call out one specific node.","index":930,"end_time":3212.73,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3202.21,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I''m totally with you.","index":931,"end_time":3213.73,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3212.73,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yes.","index":932,"end_time":3214.13,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3213.73,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"I''m totally with you.","index":933,"end_time":3214.89,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3214.13,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"And I just think that people, a lot of people don''t know to think like this.","index":934,"end_time":3220.05,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3214.89,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":935,"end_time":3221.01,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3220.61,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But it is what it takes because, like, for the longest time within an organization, you know, you.","index":936,"end_time":3227.41,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3221.17,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"You take on a new tool.","index":937,"end_time":3230.05,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3228.77,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Right?","index":938,"end_time":3230.77,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3230.37,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Like, okay, now we''re using money.com or whatever it is, but what you really need to do is step back and look at the whole ecosystem like this and then take it down its path.","index":939,"end_time":3240.05,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3230.77,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"And when you visualize it like this, you''re able to see where those opportunities lie.","index":940,"end_time":3247.17,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3240.05,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"And then also like at what step or steps is it?","index":941,"end_time":3253.21,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3247.69,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Is it not great?","index":942,"end_time":3254.25,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3253.29,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yeah, you know, like we''re getting stuck.","index":943,"end_time":3256.73,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3254.73,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":944,"end_time":3257.69,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3257.37,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Like, where do we have to settle?","index":945,"end_time":3258.89,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3257.69,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You know, like we didn''t have the technology to do it how we wanted here also, I mean, a large pain.","index":946,"end_time":3264.81,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3258.97,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"There''s.","index":947,"end_time":3265.09,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3264.81,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right, so there''s a few ideas.","index":948,"end_time":3266.13,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3265.09,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I want to make sure I speak coherently.","index":949,"end_time":3267.69,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3266.13,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"One thing is marketing teams, especially when remote, I miss whiteboard sessions.","index":950,"end_time":3273.29,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3268.41,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That is not something you can easily do remote.","index":951,"end_time":3275.43,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3273.79,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So like, that''s another type of ad creative that we can dive into.","index":952,"end_time":3277.95,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3275.43,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But it''s not.","index":953,"end_time":3278.63,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3277.95,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"It''s not.","index":954,"end_time":3279.11,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3278.63,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":955,"end_time":3279.35,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3279.11,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I mean, we could hop into a mirror board and like.","index":956,"end_time":3281.23,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3279.35,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But it''s just.","index":957,"end_time":3281.91,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3281.23,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It doesn''t have that same effect.","index":958,"end_time":3282.99,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3281.91,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But we can.","index":959,"end_time":3284.11,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3283.07,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It doesn''t.","index":960,"end_time":3284.71,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3284.11,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"And like when we would process map like this, and of course you''re just drawing boxes and arrows or whatever, but you do it on a whiteboard so that you can erase and rewrite.","index":961,"end_time":3295.31,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3284.71,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Because sometimes, you know, and it''s in that collaboration where people are saying like, well, no, actually there''s a thing before that, you know, and so then you''re like, okay, hang on.","index":962,"end_time":3305.08,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3295.31,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yeah, make that box.","index":963,"end_time":3306.64,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3305.24,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"You know, and it really does take the village of the people in the room.","index":964,"end_time":3310.08,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3306.64,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"But I really do like the idea of showing it.","index":965,"end_time":3314.84,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3310.08,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"And I think it''s like seeding the idea of this work needing to be done.","index":966,"end_time":3320.68,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3314.84,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"And I think that, look, this is not for the Procter and Gambles, you know, this is more for the Northern Arizona health.","index":967,"end_time":3330.53,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3320.76,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Like, they''re, they''re not at that highest level of sophistication, because at the highest level of sophistication, They''ve already hired McKinsey and they''re doing it.","index":968,"end_time":3338.77,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3331.41,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":969,"end_time":3339.77,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3339.41,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"This is, this is for teams that are a little bit scrappier.","index":970,"end_time":3341.81,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3339.77,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"A little bit scrappier.","index":971,"end_time":3343.17,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3342.05,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":972,"end_time":3343.65,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3343.17,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then another thing, even diving in or playing off of the cmo, you know, style ads is, you know, when your CEO or CFO is like, where''s my marketing roi?","index":973,"end_time":3355.02,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3344.05,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Or like, hey, we should do this.","index":974,"end_time":3356.3,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3355.02,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"They''re.","index":975,"end_time":3357.34,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3356.86,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"They''re focused on this last step that''s happening.","index":976,"end_time":3360.06,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3357.34,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"They are not considering everything else going into all of that process.","index":977,"end_time":3364.94,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3360.14,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Right, right.","index":978,"end_time":3366.14,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3364.94,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"So we could even have a cool video showing that type of thing.","index":979,"end_time":3369.98,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3367.1,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We just keep like zooming out, thinking.","index":980,"end_time":3372.02,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3370.54,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Of it as an ad, as a post, maybe both.","index":981,"end_time":3375.82,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3372.02,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Each.","index":982,"end_time":3376.47,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3376.23,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yeah, I mean, I think we can have a mix.","index":983,"end_time":3378.31,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3376.47,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I mean, I could even see a video ad that we could create where it''s like almost like a zoom out effect, you know, like your CEO said.","index":984,"end_time":3385.39,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3378.31,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"This, but here''s actually every step compelling headline to say, like, because I think the insight at this very moment is that organizations need to move from individual AI increased efficiency to operationalized team effectiveness and efficiency.","index":985,"end_time":3405.23,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3385.39,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"And I just think most people don''t know how to do it.","index":986,"end_time":3407.75,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3405.23,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":987,"end_time":3408.47,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3407.99,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And I mean AI is, is still so infantile and it''s only, it''s never going away.","index":988,"end_time":3414.87,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3409.27,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I think that''s one thing that everyone probably can agree on at this point.","index":989,"end_time":3418.63,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3414.87,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Maybe not everyone, but I think most people would, would agree with that.","index":990,"end_time":3424.11,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3419.83,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And if you don''t know how to, if you don''t learn how to use it, then you may be left behind.","index":991,"end_time":3428.87,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3424.11,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, but the, but the thing is too that makes it trickier still is that, you know, you look at a process map like this and you have a lot of people involved in the different steps and not everybody''s involved in every step.","index":992,"end_time":3441.26,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3429.5,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Part of the mayhem right now is that let''s say, let''s take a process like this, let''s say that there''s 20 people total touching it and probably nobody totally end to end.","index":993,"end_time":3453.66,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3441.98,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Amongst those 20 people, you have varying levels of, of knowledge, mastery and capability in their own individualized AI capabilities.","index":994,"end_time":3465.68,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3453.82,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":995,"end_time":3466.4,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3466,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So that adds to kind of the, you know, the most.","index":996,"end_time":3468.96,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3466.4,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Well, not only personnel knowledge base, but like AI knowledge base.","index":997,"end_time":3472.72,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3468.96,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Are you actually.","index":998,"end_time":3473.44,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3472.8,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That''s what I meant.","index":999,"end_time":3474.28,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3473.6,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yeah, that''s what I meant.","index":1000,"end_time":3475.36,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3474.28,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"But also the truth is, is that like, okay, that''s new, but it''s really not new because the truth is that people have varying and always will degrees of effective communication skills and ability to collaborate well and do thoughtful handoffs.","index":1001,"end_time":3492.25,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3475.36,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Right.","index":1002,"end_time":3492.57,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3492.25,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"So like humans have always been messy and we''ve always been in different places with our learning curves.","index":1003,"end_time":3497.29,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3492.57,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"So like, it''s just another form of that.","index":1004,"end_time":3500.41,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3497.29,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"It''s evolution.","index":1005,"end_time":3501.93,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3501.13,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I''m cracking up that now I''m, I''m now where I am right now is chat GPT 5.0.","index":1006,"end_time":3508.65,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3502.17,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"And I keep asking CHAT how to do all the things that I don''t know how to do and want to learn to do in AI.","index":1007,"end_time":3517.04,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3509.21,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"It''s just kind of mind blowing.","index":1008,"end_time":3519,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3517.36,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Right?","index":1009,"end_time":3519.24,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3519,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"You''re like, help me know how to do this.","index":1010,"end_time":3521.76,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3519.24,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Oh.","index":1011,"end_time":3522.52,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3522.16,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I mean, I''ve built GPTs and I use ChatGPT to help me build them.","index":1012,"end_time":3526.48,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3522.52,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It''s called vibe coding.","index":1013,"end_time":3527.8,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3526.48,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I don''t know who came up with.","index":1014,"end_time":3528.68,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3527.8,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That name, but yeah, yeah, exactly.","index":1015,"end_time":3530.96,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3528.68,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Like, help me know how to do this.","index":1016,"end_time":3532.24,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3530.96,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Right.","index":1017,"end_time":3532.56,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3532.24,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"So yeah, so I think, I think there''s definitely something here.","index":1018,"end_time":3536.64,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3533.2,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Let us know what else you need from us to do It.","index":1019,"end_time":3540.67,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3537.63,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"I think that from a workflow standpoint, it could be any of the major workflows that marketing teams are using.","index":1020,"end_time":3550.35,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3542.11,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"And a typical workflow, you know, would be like a campaign workflow, where you''re going from, you know, brief to execution.","index":1021,"end_time":3560.67,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3551.87,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yeah, I mean, I think we can.","index":1022,"end_time":3564.84,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3563.48,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We can generalize some things a little bit so that it does apply to a larger audience.","index":1023,"end_time":3569.08,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3565,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So let us come up with some creative for that and some.","index":1024,"end_time":3574.64,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3571.56,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Some ad copy.","index":1025,"end_time":3575.6,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3574.64,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then from there, you know, if we feel good with that, we can also write, like, landing page copy and help you guys to develop that as another place for people to go.","index":1026,"end_time":3584.6,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3575.6,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That''s great.","index":1027,"end_time":3586.44,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3585.8,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Okay.","index":1028,"end_time":3586.92,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3586.52,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"And that ties into what I was.","index":1029,"end_time":3588.88,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3586.92,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Recommending with these metrics as well.","index":1030,"end_time":3590.28,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3588.88,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Rachel, on our bounce rate with the newsletter, did you happen to look at the October 1st to see if we improved?","index":1031,"end_time":3601.66,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3592.86,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"I can tell you that right now.","index":1032,"end_time":3604.3,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3602.78,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Because we did that big cleanup.","index":1033,"end_time":3610.22,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3608.62,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yes, we did.","index":1034,"end_time":3611.74,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3610.7,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Of course, the minute after you do a cleanup, you know, three more marketers moved on.","index":1035,"end_time":3616.42,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3612.46,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"So.","index":1036,"end_time":3616.58,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3616.42,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"But Wells Fargo, I mean, there''s got to be something going on there.","index":1037,"end_time":3619.97,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3616.73,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I mean, when I was.","index":1038,"end_time":3620.77,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3619.97,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"When we were cleaning up that list.","index":1039,"end_time":3621.81,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3620.77,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It was a lot of.","index":1040,"end_time":3623.13,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3621.81,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So what happened with Wells Fargo, long story short, is that pre2020, they invested a lot in marketing.","index":1041,"end_time":3631.37,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3623.13,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"They had a CMO who was really all about it.","index":1042,"end_time":3634.09,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3631.37,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"2018, 2019, they got pummeled in the press for sales malpractices.","index":1043,"end_time":3641.21,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3635.53,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"It really was not as big of a scandal as it was made to be in the press.","index":1044,"end_time":3648.26,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3642.98,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Their senior leadership did not do a good enough job of mea culpa and apologizing.","index":1045,"end_time":3655.3,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3648.74,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"So it got kind of dragged out.","index":1046,"end_time":3657.38,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3655.7,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"They suffered financially and baron reputationally.","index":1047,"end_time":3661.78,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3657.78,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"CMO left and the marketing function got, like, decimated, and they pulled.","index":1048,"end_time":3669.38,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3661.94,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"They.","index":1049,"end_time":3670.01,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3669.81,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"They were a department centralized.","index":1050,"end_time":3672.13,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3670.01,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"They pulled them all into the business units and fired or had many, many, many retire.","index":1051,"end_time":3677.73,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3672.37,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"So, like, literally, I''ve heard people call it, like, the diaspora of Wells Fargo marketing.","index":1052,"end_time":3684.69,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3678.69,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"So we had been working with them for, like, seven years through to, like, 2021, and kind of watched it happen.","index":1053,"end_time":3692.21,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3685.17,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"It was sad.","index":1054,"end_time":3693.41,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3692.29,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"I don''t think they deserved the punishment that they got, but whatever.","index":1055,"end_time":3697.97,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3694.85,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Um, I''m not saying that people weren''t.","index":1056,"end_time":3699.97,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3698.45,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"There weren''t bad actors there.","index":1057,"end_time":3701.09,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3699.97,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Like, there were some.","index":1058,"end_time":3702.05,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3701.09,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"So anyway, those people have all now gone on to other places, but a good number of them also retired because people tended to go there and stay.","index":1059,"end_time":3710.93,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3702.85,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"So that''s why there''s such a big Wells Fargo alumni group.","index":1060,"end_time":3714.93,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3710.93,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yeah, it was retired or started their own firm or just, like, pure freelance.","index":1061,"end_time":3719.73,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3715.25,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, yeah.","index":1062,"end_time":3722.65,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3720.05,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"What I found as I dug into the bounces is like you can''t always find them.","index":1063,"end_time":3727.04,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3722.65,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, go ahead, Rach.","index":1064,"end_time":3729.36,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3727.28,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Sorry.","index":1065,"end_time":3730.04,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3729.6,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"We went down significantly.","index":1066,"end_time":3731.16,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3730.04,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"We''re down to 22 across all of the different lists, so it''s like a very, very big jump.","index":1067,"end_time":3737.12,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3731.16,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":1068,"end_time":3738,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3737.44,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, that''s really good.","index":1069,"end_time":3739.36,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3738.4,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":1070,"end_time":3741.12,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3740.64,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"I also want to make you guys aware, Colin and Natalie, that we do a big push to all of our contacts for Thanksgiving.","index":1071,"end_time":3755.1,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3742.96,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"We do something called the thankful mailer.","index":1072,"end_time":3757.9,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3755.82,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Rachel, can you send that to these guys just so they see it?","index":1073,"end_time":3761.82,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3758.86,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Oh, I don''t know.","index":1074,"end_time":3764.62,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3763.82,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Well, we''re at our last minute, so we don''t have to do it right now, but just, just, just send them like once you have it mocked up, I know you''re so be receiving it.","index":1075,"end_time":3772.98,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3764.62,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"And I added them to the email list, so they both should have gotten.","index":1076,"end_time":3776.62,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3772.98,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Yes.","index":1077,"end_time":3778.14,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3777.66,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Going to be cool doing it different this year.","index":1078,"end_time":3781.03,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3779.11,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Exciting.","index":1079,"end_time":3782.07,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3781.43,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So that''s a big push for us.","index":1080,"end_time":3785.91,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3783.91,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yes.","index":1081,"end_time":3788.07,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3787.51,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"In, in November.","index":1082,"end_time":3790.63,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3789.35,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yeah, it''s going to be great.","index":1083,"end_time":3793.99,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3790.87,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"And you''ll get one example, but each person''s going to get, like, have their own message that''s custom to them for their client list, so you''ll get a feel for it.","index":1084,"end_time":3804.91,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3794.87,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"I don''t need to spam you with all of them unless you want to see all of them.","index":1085,"end_time":3807.51,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3804.91,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"But.","index":1086,"end_time":3807.74,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3807.51,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"But they''re going to be very similar.","index":1087,"end_time":3809.17,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3807.81,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Okay, great.","index":1088,"end_time":3810.53,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3809.73,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And we could chat about this more.","index":1089,"end_time":3813.41,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3811.97,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I don''t know what your guys company holiday looks like for Thanksgiving, but I am out that entire week.","index":1090,"end_time":3819.73,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3813.41,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Natalie, I think you''re here on the.","index":1091,"end_time":3823.929,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3822.05,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Wednesday before Thanksgiving, correct?","index":1092,"end_time":3825.81,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3823.929,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yes.","index":1093,"end_time":3827.41,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3826.85,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"So if you want to.","index":1094,"end_time":3828.61,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3827.81,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"If you guys are in and wanted to have that meeting with Natalie, you.","index":1095,"end_time":3831.73,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3828.61,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Can certainly do that.","index":1096,"end_time":3832.61,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3831.73,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So you.","index":1097,"end_time":3833.98,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3833.5,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"We''re good.","index":1098,"end_time":3834.7,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3833.98,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"We''re good on the 12th and we''re good on the 19th.","index":1099,"end_time":3837.66,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3834.7,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":1100,"end_time":3838.46,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3838.06,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":1101,"end_time":3838.74,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3838.46,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I''m flying out Thursday the 20th and I don''t.","index":1102,"end_time":3841.86,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3838.74,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I''m not back to the office until.","index":1103,"end_time":3843.18,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3841.86,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"The 1st of December.","index":1104,"end_time":3844.3,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3843.18,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Why don''t we.","index":1105,"end_time":3845.1,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3844.46,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Can we determine on the 19th whether or not we think we need a meeting?","index":1106,"end_time":3848.22,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3845.1,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yeah, no problem.","index":1107,"end_time":3849.18,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3848.46,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I know.","index":1108,"end_time":3849.66,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3849.26,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Because it''s a little bit of a funky week.","index":1109,"end_time":3851.42,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3849.66,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"It is.","index":1110,"end_time":3852.98,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3852.46,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So like we''ll hold it, but then we can just decide as we get closer.","index":1111,"end_time":3857.18,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3852.98,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Sounds like a plan.","index":1112,"end_time":3858.7,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3857.82,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":1113,"end_time":3860.02,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3859.54,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"All right.","index":1114,"end_time":3860.42,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3860.02,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Just added a reminder to my calendar.","index":1115,"end_time":3861.94,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3860.42,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, fantastic.","index":1116,"end_time":3864.18,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3862.42,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right, well, we got a lot.","index":1117,"end_time":3865.14,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3864.34,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Of things if those new healthcare leads are legit or not, so I''ll keep an eye.","index":1118,"end_time":3870.26,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3865.14,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yep.","index":1119,"end_time":3871.14,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3870.58,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Okay.","index":1120,"end_time":3872.14,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3871.7,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"And Natalie and I are running all the podcasts through the checklist and we.","index":1121,"end_time":3876.1,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3872.14,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Have some new ads to launch, so all exciting things.","index":1122,"end_time":3878.18,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3876.1,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":1123,"end_time":3879.14,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3878.66,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Thanks.","index":1124,"end_time":3879.54,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3879.14,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Thank you all so much.","index":1125,"end_time":3880.98,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3880.02,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"}],"dateString":"2025-11-05T19:00:00.000Z","host_email":"colin.costigan@marketersindemand.com","meeting_link":"https://us02web.zoom.us/j/85039954260?pwd=7GrXTMosQASbwQapyiVncGn3aAbQCz.1","participants":["nancie@noeticconsultants.com,colin.costigan@marketersindemand.com,samantha@noeticconsultants.com,nathalie.mintjens@marketersindemand.com,rachel@noeticconsultants.com,tracy@noeticconsultants.com","nancie@noeticconsultants.com","samantha@noeticconsultants.com","nathalie.mintjens@marketersindemand.com","rachel@noeticconsultants.com","tracy@noeticconsultants.com"],"transcript_url":"https://app.fireflies.ai/view/01K8RZDWWAKQEF05S4AHTKERM7","organizer_email":"colin.costigan@marketersindemand.com"}'::jsonb,
    '{"label":"positive","confidence":0.91,"bullets":["Aligned on creative A/B tests for healthcare and first-year CMO campaigns; assets approved for launch.","Team agreed to streamline quote card workflow by reviewing quotes before final design production.","Nancy reported promising business development traction with Waymo and initial progress at Truist.","October delivery reached 159 points; team entering November with 98 and maintained consistent velocity.","Discussed launching AI training workshops aligned to evolving client needs in team effectiveness."],"highlights":[{"quote":"We are hard at work developing and delivering curriculum of this nature.","speaker":"nancieruder"},{"quote":"We delivered 159 points and as we''re entering into November, we have 98.","speaker":"Colin Costigan"},{"quote":"I''m knocking at the door with Marriott. There''s something there.","speaker":"nancieruder"}],"topics":["delivery","creative","workflow","training","leadgen"],"model":"openai/gpt-4","version":1,"generated_at":"2025-11-13T00:00:00Z"}'::jsonb,
    '{"fireflies_summary":{"notes":"## **Podcast Production and Asset Management**\n\nThe team confirmed enhancements to podcast workflows and asset usage to reduce delays and improve content quality.\n\n- **Nancy** and **Rachel** agreed to pause on the volume of **quote cards** to assess their value and streamline production (09:01)  \n    - **Colin** explained quote cards help readers quickly assess content relevance before watching videos.  \n    - They decided to pre-select concise, polished quotes via email for review before design, reducing back-and-forth.  \n    - The group agreed to occasionally include subtle **Noetic promotion** in quote cards to boost brand presence.  \n    - Use of ellipses to shorten longer quotes on cards was accepted to maintain clarity and engagement.\n\n- The **podcast episode schedule** was updated with **Mike Linton’s** recording moved to next week and **Kate Warnock’s** to **November 12th**, with **Patrick McMaster** tentatively after Kate (24:36)  \n    - Frameworks for all guests are prepared, with Kate’s episode promising strong content around a recent merger and rebrand.  \n    - Nancy will complete episode descriptors for Mike Linton by Friday or Monday at the latest (24:42).  \n    - Natalie created a **guest tracking tab** in the spreadsheet with color-coded progress and final frameworks for better organization (30:08).  \n    - Nancy plans to clean up tentative guest statuses to maintain an accurate pipeline.\n\n- The team is improving internal coordination by reviewing the podcast production checklist and adjusting episode sections to optimize speaker time (27:51)  \n    - There is a focus on reducing unnecessary back-and-forth in asset approvals while maintaining effectiveness.  \n    - Nancy confirmed guest invitations are sent to all confirmed participants, ensuring platform access before recording.\n\n## **Marketing Campaign Performance and Lead Generation**\n\nThe group reviewed recent marketing campaign metrics highlighting progress and ongoing challenges in lead quality and volume.\n\n- The **healthcare campaign** generated **9 clicks** and **3 form fills** last week, producing **3 leads** at a notably lower cost per lead than usual, signaling improved targeting efficiency (36:49)  \n    - Nancy and Natalie are evaluating lead quality before entering them into the sales pipeline.  \n    - Nancy reported limited new leads in the last week but expects some to still appear in the system.  \n    - LinkedIn remains the most effective channel for outreach, especially where email deliverability is blocked, as seen in the **Marriott** and **Truist** accounts (38:44).  \n    - Persistent outreach via LinkedIn and leveraging personal networks increased booked meetings despite email filters.\n\n- Paid display ads under the **Ad Role** program yielded **4 clicks** but are not expected to drive direct leads, aligning with their usual awareness role (41:30).  \n- The team recognizes the **head of marketing audience** as competitive and costly, but targeting is reaching the right titles, with click volume needing improvement (41:36).\n\n## **Website Engagement and Content Strategy**\n\nOngoing website performance metrics show positive trends, with identified opportunities to boost engagement through better content linking and AI-related offerings.\n\n- October saw a **2% increase** in website views compared to September, alongside longer average session durations and more pages viewed per session, indicating stronger visitor engagement (41:58)  \n    - Visitors are spending about twice as long on the site, suggesting content resonates well with the target audience.  \n    - Colin recommended adding more internal links on the homepage and other pages to guide visitors toward key services like brand diagnostics.  \n    - Nancy suggested integrating content around AI offerings to capitalize on current market trends and visitor interest.\n\n- The team is considering a dedicated **AI workshop** offering as a new product separate from the playbook, responding to client needs for leadership and skill development in AI adoption (43:10)  \n    - Colin described a workshop focused on AI governance, company policy, and operationalizing AI use across teams.  \n    - Nancy emphasized the importance of training teams not only in individual AI use but also in coordinated workflows and governance.  \n    - They plan to develop landing page content and targeted ads to assess AI adoption levels and drive workshop interest.\n\n- Visual process mapping, like the **ABM campaign flowchart** shared by Colin, is proposed as a creative tool to illustrate AI integration and marketing workflows, helping prospects see where AI fits into their operations (52:48)  \n    - Nancy highlighted the value of collaborative whiteboard sessions for process mapping, which fosters understanding and buy-in.  \n    - The approach targets mid-level companies that may not have top-tier consulting support but need practical solutions.  \n    - Messaging will avoid fearmongering around AI-driven job cuts, focusing instead on empowerment and team effectiveness.\n\n## **Email List Health and Client Engagement**\n\nThe team reported significant improvements in newsletter deliverability and outlined plans for a major client outreach in November.\n\n- Following a recent cleanup, the team reduced the **newsletter bounce rate** to **22 bounces** across all lists, a substantial improvement signaling better list hygiene (01:02:10)  \n    - Rachel confirmed the cleanup and ongoing maintenance efforts, though natural attrition from marketer moves continues.  \n    - Nancy explained that many bounced contacts came from Wells Fargo, whose marketing function was decentralized after 2018-2019 reputational issues and leadership changes.\n\n- The **Thankful Mailer** campaign will be a key client engagement push in November, featuring personalized messages for each contact on client lists (01:02:59)  \n    - Rachel is preparing mock-ups and will share examples with the team ahead of the mailing.  \n    - The campaign aims to reinforce relationships ahead of the holiday season with a fresh, customized approach.\n\n- The team planned to confirm the need for a meeting on **November 19th** given the Thanksgiving holiday schedule, with Colin out from November 20th to December 1st (01:03:29)  \n    - Nancy and Rachel agreed to assess whether the meeting is necessary closer to the date to accommodate the holiday week’s irregularities.\n\n## **Creative Asset Development and A/B Testing**\n\nNew creative assets for healthcare and CMO campaigns are ready for launch after A/B testing finalization and minor design tweaks.\n\n- Two cover design options for the **healthcare** and **first-year CMO playbook chunks** were reviewed and approved for A/B testing, emphasizing bright, engaging visuals with improved headline highlights (13:00)  \n    - Rachel and Nancy recommended extending the green highlight fully across the headline for clarity and impact.  \n    - The creatives are designed to stop audience scrolling and prompt engagement, with Rachel praising the fresh, light, and bright style.\n\n- Organic social assets were updated by removing extraneous elements like a butterfly icon to simplify visuals and enhance focus (15:56)  \n    - Color adjustments were made to maintain brand consistency while adding subtle dimension for visual interest.  \n    - Colin prepared complementary ad copy, with **8** total ad variations (four per infographic) ready for deployment (18:25).\n\n- Ad copy wording was refined to avoid alienating the audience, shifting from finger-wagging tones to provocative questions that encourage self-reflection about marketing ROI and CEO communication (21:50)  \n    - Nancy and Colin agreed on phrasing like, \"Are you prepared to answer your CEO’s questions?\" to engage without judgment.  \n    - The goal is to keep messaging brief, clear, and compelling to maximize scroll-stopping potential.\n\n## **Operational Coordination and Process Improvements**\n\nThe team enhanced internal tracking and communication processes to support smoother project execution and accountability.\n\n- The leadership team condensed their quarterly planning meeting into a full-day session attended by **4 leaders**, setting priorities and \"rocks\" for the coming period (11:44)  \n    - Colin recognized Natalie’s role in managing communications during his absence at the meeting, ensuring continuity.\n\n- Internal spreadsheet tools were updated to reflect the latest recording schedules, guest confirmations, and framework deliveries, improving transparency and follow-up (30:08)  \n    - The guest tracking tab includes color-coded step completion and stores final podcast frameworks for quick reference.\n\n- Communication protocols for sharing podcast access with external consultants like **Raki at Noetic** were clarified, with invitations resent to ensure timely access (12:09).  \n- The team agreed to maintain a flexible meeting schedule in November due to holidays, with decisions on session necessity made closer to dates (01:03:46).","outline":null,"keywords":["Podcast production","Marketing ROI","AI training","Workflow mapping","Healthcare campaign","Lead generation"],"overview":"- **Podcast Workflow Improvements:** Enhanced assets and workflows to reduce delays, focusing on quote card value and concise selection.  \n- **Updated Podcast Schedule:** Guest recordings adjusted; episode descriptors will be finalized by Friday for better planning.  \n- **Marketing Campaign Metrics:** Recent healthcare campaign yielded 3 leads with improved cost efficiency; continuing to evaluate lead quality.  \n- **Website Performance Gains:** 2% increase in views and longer session times indicate stronger engagement; internal linking and AI content are priorities.  \n- **Email List Cleanup:** Reduced bounce rate to 22; upcoming Thankful Mailer campaign aims to enhance client relationships before holidays.  \n- **Creative Assets Ready:** New designs for healthcare and CMO campaigns approved; ad copy refined for audience engagement with provocative questions.","action_items":"\n**Nancy Cruder**\nFollow up with Waymo client process and keep team updated on progress (09:50)\nProvide Mike Linton podcast descriptors to Rachel by Friday or latest Monday (24:42)\nConfirm and update Kate Warnock podcast date as November 12 (25:51)\nContinue follow-up and scheduling efforts with Patrick McMaster and others for podcasts TBD (26:12)\nSend podcast frameworks to Colin and Natalie after review (30:08)\nLead hand-delivery and/or mailing of Marriott promotional packets and continue LinkedIn outreach (37:52)\nMonitor healthcare campaign leads for quality and share updates (01:04:25)\n\n**Rachel Curtis**\nInvite Raki from Noetic Consultants to access points tracking account and follow up with signup instructions (12:28)\nDeliver and share Thanksgiving “thankful mailer” campaign mocks and final emails with team (01:02:52)\nConfirm podcast platform invitation received by Christine McCain’s assistant (28:04)\nCoordinate and update podcast scheduling sheet order and status with Natalie and Nancy (29:02)\nAssist with podcast asset checklist review for episodes and ads (28:04)\nTrack and report newsletter bounce rate post-cleanup and monitor (01:00:02)\n\n**Colin Costigan**\nSend invite to Raki and ensure access to points tracking account (12:19)\nIncorporate feedback and launch A/B tests for healthcare and CMO playbook covers with design adjustments (14:08)\nRemove butterfly graphic and adjust colors in organic assets and ads as per feedback (16:06)\nProvide mock-up explanations for ad structure and assist with ad copy revisions (19:00)\nDevelop ad copy with reframed marketing ROI messaging and share updated versions (23:56)\nContinue podcast episode framework review and update scheduling relative to guest readiness (26:48)\nOversee podcast quote card process improvements; send curated quote lists with polished and concise edits before design (33:47)\nSupport healthcare campaign lead evaluation with Natalie and share quality feedback (37:24)\nCollaborate on AI-related workshop marketing concept, ad creative, landing page copy, and graphics development (43:10)\nMonitor web metrics and advise on website interlinking and AI content opportunities (41:30)\nCoordinate Thanksgiving week meeting decisions and schedule reminders (01:03:46)\n\n**Nathalie Mintjens**\nCreate and maintain guest tracking tab and podcast framework archive in the shared spreadsheet for improved organization (30:08)\n"},"migrated_from":"contract_meetings","original_id":"756549b0-1d62-4eeb-adb5-66ec0a0bd6ee","master_marketer":{"status":"migrated"}}'::jsonb,
