    '{"id":"01K8VY3MDMYNXWGCTK1KPYF5B7","title":"EASE // MiD - Weekly Meeting","summary":{"notes":"## **Podcast Production and Content Scheduling**\n\nThe team is advancing the podcast production with clear next steps and finalized content assets.\n\n- **The episode with Ed Rocha is set for recording next Tuesday**, after completing the first round of assets and pending final title approval from Josh Santo (02:02)  \n    - Josh plans to finalize the episode title focused on \"quality letters\" to better align with Rocha''s book  \n    - Two pre-interviews are completed with one more scheduled, ensuring a steady content pipeline  \n    - Finalizing this episode will help build a backlog of content for consistent release  \n    - This schedule aims to reduce last-minute rush and improve overall episode readiness\n\n- **Content updates include script reviews and video edits tied to podcast episodes and related campaigns** (03:26)  \n    - Josh shared voiceover feedback via Slack and is integrating sales team input on three key video scripts  \n    - One script remains to be delivered, and some edits involve wording and visuals, reflecting cross-team collaboration  \n    - Julia’s feedback on visuals is incorporated before animation starts, ensuring quality and alignment  \n    - This process supports a polished final product that meets both marketing and product needs\n\n## **Marketing Outreach and Campaign Preparation**\n\nThe outreach campaign is progressing with targeted contact list refinement and campaign readiness.\n\n- **Baylee and Paul are finalizing a new contact list focusing on CC roles at director level and above** to enhance campaign targeting (02:28)  \n    - The list is undergoing last-minute tweaks before full deployment  \n    - This focus aims to improve engagement by reaching decision-makers directly  \n    - Timely completion of the list is critical to align with upcoming campaign launches  \n    - The refined targeting is expected to increase response rates and campaign ROI\n\n- **Video content edits are nearing completion pending final approvals from Josh and team feedback** (03:18)  \n    - Iterative review cycles with input from sales and product teams help ensure messaging accuracy  \n    - The final approval step will trigger the next phase of campaign rollout  \n    - This structured review reduces risks of misalignment or messaging errors during launch  \n    - Ensuring these steps supports a smooth campaign start expected soon\n\n## **Cross-Functional Collaboration and Feedback Integration**\n\nThe team is actively managing multiple feedback loops across sales, product, and creative teams to refine outputs.\n\n- **Josh is coordinating with sales management to review video scripts and incorporate their suggestions** (03:33)  \n    - Sales feedback focuses on wording and visual elements for clearer messaging  \n    - This collaborative review reflects a strategy to align marketing materials with sales priorities  \n    - Josh plans to clear outstanding tasks to accelerate content delivery and campaign readiness  \n    - The integration of sales perspectives helps improve content relevance for target audiences\n\n- **Visual feedback from Julia and Andrea has been incorporated into video edits before animation** (05:24)  \n    - The team used Figma and Slack for detailed markup and comment sharing, ensuring transparency  \n    - This detailed review process aims to catch issues early and reduce rework post-production  \n    - Bringing in design experts late in the process ensures final visuals meet brand and product standards  \n    - The approach balances speed with quality assurance for marketing assets\n\n## **Workload Management and Timeline Commitments**\n\nJosh is balancing multiple demands but has set clear priorities and blocked time to progress key tasks.\n\n- **Josh has blocked time tomorrow to focus on script reviews and feedback integration** to maintain momentum (06:40)  \n    - Prioritizing script completion will enable faster video production and campaign readiness  \n    - Clearing these tasks is seen as essential to avoid bottlenecks and support upcoming launches  \n    - Baylee confirms the scripts are nearly finalized, signaling readiness for next steps  \n    - This time management reflects a practical approach to handle growing workload pressure\n\n- **The team acknowledges increasing workload but is confident about steady progress on deliverables** (07:29)  \n    - Josh notes that tasks keep adding up but remains committed to advancing key projects  \n    - Baylee’s recognition of the busy schedule supports realistic planning and resource allocation  \n    - This shared understanding helps maintain team morale and focus during peak periods  \n    - The approach balances urgency with achievable deadlines for quality output","outline":null,"keywords":["Podcast","Outreach Campaign","Video Editing","Script Review","Ed Rocha","Sales Feedback"],"overview":"- **Podcast Recording Scheduled:** Episode with Ed Rocha is set for next Tuesday, title pending final approval.  \n- **Content Pipeline Strengthened:** Pre-interviews complete; aim to build a backlog for consistent episode releases.  \n- **Outreach Campaign Targeting:** New contact list focuses on CC roles at director level to improve engagement and response rates.  \n- **Video Edits Nearing Completion:** Final approvals needed to trigger the next phase of campaign rollout; collaboration ensures messaging accuracy.  \n- **Feedback Integration Ongoing:** Coordination with sales enhances video content; detailed reviews to catch issues early and maintain quality.  \n- **Workload Management Focused:** Clear priorities set to avoid bottlenecks; team committed to advancing projects despite increasing task demands.","action_items":"\n**Josh Santo**\nProvide finalized podcast episode title for Ed Rocha episode to team for assets completion (01:53)\nConduct scheduled podcast recording with Ed Rocha next Tuesday (02:02)\nDeliver pending training script and review sales team feedback on scripts for video content (06:07)\nReview and respond to Julia’s visual feedback for product and platform videos before animation starts (04:40)\nBlock time to finalize script comments and approvals, collaborating with Paula and sales team as needed (06:07)\n\n**Baylee Gunnell**\nFinalize outreach campaign contact list focused on CC roles and prepare for campaign launch (02:28)\nCoordinate video editing incorporating feedback and prepare for submission of final approval on voiceover re-recording (05:24)\nConfirm reception and convey Julia’s feedback on visuals to animation team (04:50)\n"},"duration":7.980000019073486,"speakers":[{"id":0,"name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"id":1,"name":"Josh Santo"}],"sentences":[{"text":"Are things slowing down at least a little bit or still crazy?","index":0,"end_time":4.08,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":0.16,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"You know, I don''t know.","index":1,"end_time":7.68,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":5.44,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"It''s like both at the same time.","index":2,"end_time":11.12,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":9.44,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":3,"end_time":12,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":11.52,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":4,"end_time":15.84,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":15.36,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"Let''s.","index":5,"end_time":16.64,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":16.16,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"Like no events or anything.","index":6,"end_time":18.4,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":17.04,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"Just things that gotta get done.","index":7,"end_time":21.2,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":18.4,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":8,"end_time":22.48,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":21.92,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Just different kind of crazy.","index":9,"end_time":25.28,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":23.44,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah, exactly.","index":10,"end_time":26.89,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":25.77,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"Exactly.","index":11,"end_time":29.29,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":28.49,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"But I could have to move this anyway.","index":12,"end_time":34.33,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":31.29,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"Got a lot that I owe you guys.","index":13,"end_time":37.93,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":36.01,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"I think I. I don''t think it''s too much.","index":14,"end_time":42.25,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":38.09,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"We can get into it, but I think there''s just a few things that I don''t think it should be too crazy.","index":15,"end_time":49.53,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":43.77,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"But we''ll see about that.","index":16,"end_time":54.02,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":52.5,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"We''ll get into it.","index":17,"end_time":56.42,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":55.22,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Okay, so just for your podcast, this.","index":18,"end_time":62.1,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":59.14,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"This is one thing we need for me is the title that you want to do for this episode with @ Rocha.","index":19,"end_time":68.74,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":62.1,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So we just finished the first round of assets, and just once we hear back from you in the title, we''ll get everything else wrapped up.","index":20,"end_time":77.38,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":70.02,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah, so I saw some of the titles.","index":21,"end_time":79.88,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":78,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"Definitely gonna change it.","index":22,"end_time":81.12,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":79.88,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"He wrote this book.","index":23,"end_time":82.8,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":81.6,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"Oh, you had it just right on hand.","index":24,"end_time":86.72,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":83.84,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Ready to go.","index":25,"end_time":88.48,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":87.68,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Ready to go.","index":26,"end_time":89.2,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":88.56,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"What''s on my desk?","index":27,"end_time":90.08,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":89.2,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"Just like everything else.","index":28,"end_time":91.28,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":90.08,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"I have to.","index":29,"end_time":93.559,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":93.04,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Do a cleanup over here.","index":30,"end_time":95.12,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":93.559,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"That''s the other thing is.","index":31,"end_time":96.24,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":95.12,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"Got so much to do in life.","index":32,"end_time":99.12,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":97.28,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":33,"end_time":100,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":99.44,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So I''m thinking something around the quality letters.","index":34,"end_time":106.25,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":102.32,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"Something.","index":35,"end_time":107.61,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":107.21,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"Oh, yeah.","index":36,"end_time":108.57,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":107.93,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Colon something.","index":37,"end_time":109.61,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":108.57,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":38,"end_time":112.01,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":111.53,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"Okay.","index":39,"end_time":112.81,"sp