  'meeting',
  'Meeting Notes: Inside Tracker // New North Weekly Connect',
  '## **Podcast Production and Scheduling**

The team will pause weekly calls starting next week due to Gil''s travel, maintaining episode flow with planned recordings and edits. (00:00)  
- **Gil** confirmed he will be in Berlin next week and unable to join calls, prompting cancellation of the next meeting.  
- He plans to record **two episodes this week**, with one already released and the next expected to be ready within **one week**.  
- Gil is actively working on guest engagement and pipeline management to sustain episode production through the **end of the year**.  
- The team agreed to use new vertical clip formats, which will add an extra day to production, but this delay is manageable given current release schedules.  

## **Content Quality and Client Feedback**

Positive client feedback on formatting improvements is fostering new business opportunities and stronger client relationships. (02:31)  
- Gil shared improved episode formatting with guest **Joy Spain**, who responded positively and is considering starting her own podcast.  
- The previous guest, **Dr. Komite**, also requested format changes, showing responsiveness to client feedback.  
- Gil intends to refer potential new clients like Joy Spain to Baylee’s team, expanding client acquisition possibilities.  
- Baylee confirmed capacity to onboard new clients, signaling readiness for incoming referrals.  

## **Download Metrics and Audience Engagement**

Podcast downloads remain strong, indicating steady audience engagement and growth potential. (04:14)  
- The show achieved over **40,000 downloads in the last 90 days** and **14,000 in the last 30 days**, signaling healthy listener retention and growth.  
- These metrics support continued investment in episode production and format innovation to maintain audience interest.  

## **Resource Management and Workflow Adjustments**

Adjusting meeting frequency will help balance workload and align points-based resource allocation with delivery capacity. (04:55)  
- Baylee highlighted a current **points deficit** where deliveries exceed allocated capacity, risking resource strain.  
- To address this, the team agreed to shift meetings from weekly to **every other week**, reducing points use to **five points** per meeting cycle.  
- Gil approved this change, suggesting Slack for ongoing communication to maintain workflow without weekly calls.  
- This adjustment aims to improve operational efficiency and prevent burnout while sustaining output quality.',
  '2025-11-06 14:30:00+00',
  'published',
  '[{"text":"Cancel the meeting scheduled for next week due to travel commitments (00:08)","completed":false},{"text":"Send episode document to the team today (03:26)","completed":false},{"text":"Send another episode document to the team tomorrow (03:26)","completed":false},{"text":"Continue to improve guest communication and maintain pipeline for episodes through the end of the year (01:30)","completed":false},{"text":"Finalize and template new vertical clip format to implement for upcoming episodes, requiring one additional day (01:08)","completed":false},{"text":"Monitor and report podcast download metrics regularly (04:14)","completed":false},{"text":"Adjust meeting schedule to biweekly and reduce points allocation accordingly (05:08)","completed":false}]'::jsonb,
  true
FROM new_meeting;

-- Meeting: New North ABM Presentation - Legal Services/AI Readiness Assessment (2025-11-06 16:30:00+00)
WITH new_meeting AS (
  INSERT INTO compass_meetings (contract_id, meeting_date, source, external_id, title, participants, duration_seconds, recording_url, transcript, sentiment, raw_metadata, created_at, updated_at)
  VALUES (
    '965b21f3-8748-420c-aaf3-b3fdcaa2f504',
    '2025-11-06 16:30:00+00',
    'fireflies',
    '01K987QV4QAZBQD5CZBC6MB1DT',
    'New North ABM Presentation - Legal Services/AI Readiness Assessment',
    '{"Michael A Hadley","Nathalie Mintjens","Kirk Fackre1","Samuel Bagnall","Nathalie Mintjens","Jeffery Lauria","Ruby Pontbriand","Ruby Pontbriand"}'::text[],
    2443,
    'https://teams.microsoft.com/l/meetup-join/19:meeting_ZTIzN2FhOGQtNWU4NS00MzFhLThjMmQtN2FiNmZiOTBkMWUx@thread.v2/0?context={"Tid":"0188564a-93de-489c-bf54-1927d4a9ed28","Oid":"12c1a142-ac12-4942-a3ac-7d7dceb82476"}',
    '{"id":"01K987QV4QAZBQD5CZBC6MB1DT","title":"New North ABM Presentation - Legal Services/AI Readiness Assessment","summary":{"notes":"## **Target Market and Customer Segmentation**\n\nThe team agreed to focus the ABM campaign on **legal services firms with 20 to 100 employees** to maximize business potential and minimize low-value leads (08:50).\n\n- The initial target of firms with **2 to 3 attorneys and small admin teams** was rejected because such small firms often lack IT leadership and rarely generate meaningful business (08:38)\n    - **Michael Hadley** and **Ruby Pontbriand** emphasized that firms under 20 employees tend to generate many leads but little actual business, often becoming costly “C clients” (10:36)\n    - **Kirk Fackre** noted legal firms have reduced admin roles, so targeting firms with around **10 employees** or more better aligns with current structures (12:05)\n    - The group agreed targeting firms with **20 to 100 employees** will reach organizations more likely to invest in AI governance and assessments (11:35)\n    - Marketing and sales teams will revise outreach strategies to reflect this updated firm size focus and explore whether in-house IT teams exist within these firms to tailor targeting (16:13)\n\n- The targeting shift aims to prioritize firms where **I Corps can be the primary IT partner**, rather than competing against established managed IT providers (09:23)\n    - This approach reduces competition and positions the company as a leader in AI readiness in legal tech for SMBs (11:29)\n\n## **ABM Campaign Structure and Engagement Tracking**\n\nThe ABM plan uses a **multi-channel approach** combining brand awareness and targeted outreach to generate qualified leads and enable sales follow-up (17:35).\n\n- The campaign starts with **brand awareness** using three channels: direct emails, direct LinkedIn messages (from Ruby), and paid LinkedIn ads (17:35)\n    - Engagement is tracked through clicks on emails, ads, and LinkedIn responses, feeding into a **lead scoring model** to identify highly engaged leads (18:58)\n    - Once a lead hits a **score of 10**, indicating strong engagement such as form submissions or quiz completions, the lead is passed to sales for personalized follow-up (34:55)\n    - Sales follow-up will also include a new seller who will proactively reach out more aggressively, complementing marketing’s efforts (19:06)\n    - The lead scoring assigns values such as **+3 for page views** and higher scores for direct contact or content downloads, ensuring prioritization of interested prospects (34:05)\n\n- The plan includes ongoing **weekly campaign performance reviews**, analyzing LinkedIn analytics, email clicks, and responses to optimize messaging and budget allocation (39:12)\n    - The initial launch is scheduled for **Monday the 17th**, following an email warm-up period to ensure proper delivery (39:05)\n\n## **Content Strategy and Sales Enablement**\n\nThe campaign is supported by a mix of educational content, interactive tools, and sales enablement assets designed to build credibility and facilitate deal closure (36:48).\n\n- Key content includes an **interactive AI readiness quiz and scorecard** that captures contact info and readiness scores, feeding into lead scoring and follow-up (31:35)\n    - The AI readiness assessment page is optimized for SEO targeting the keyword **“AI for business”**, which has high search volume and low difficulty, to boost organic traffic once published (31:35)\n    - The page is currently under internal review by **Ruby Pontbriand**, **Sam Bagnall**, and **Jeffery Lauria**, with Jeffery expected to finalize approval by the end of the week (32:54)\n\n- Sales enablement materials include **objection handling guides, positioning documents, and assessment overviews** to ensure the sales team can confidently address prospects (36:48)\n    - **Kirk Fackre** requested a sample excerpt from an actual assessment to better equip sales; **Jeffery Lauria** committed to delivering this by week’s end (37:28)\n    - Additional enablement will be developed for other ongoing campaigns to provide consistent support across product lines (35:49)\n\n- Content strategy will also incorporate relevant **blogs and organic LinkedIn posts** aligned with the campaign, focusing on AI governance, compliance, and ROI storytelling to address client concerns (22:20)\n    - Ruby highlighted the importance of differentiating paid ads from organic content to maximize reach and engagement (29:01)\n    - An action was agreed to compile and develop blog ideas surfaced during discussions to support both paid and organic channels (22:55)\n\n## **Paid Media and Keyword Strategy**\n\nLinkedIn is prioritized as the main paid channel for the campaign due to its proven higher engagement rates, while Google search ads are deprioritized because of limited relevant commercial keyword traffic (24:26).\n\n- Keyword research showed **high search volume for general AI and AI for legal services**, but very low search volume for **“AI readiness assessment”** specifically, limiting paid search effectiveness (25:05)\n    - Nathalie Mintjens recommended focusing budget on LinkedIn ads where targeting and engagement are stronger for the niche product (24:26)\n    - Jeffery Lauria raised concerns about aligning product offerings with actual search intent and suggested further analysis to ensure market fit (25:05)\n    - The team agreed to a deeper review of search terms using Google Ads and SEO tools like **Ahrefs**, with Nathalie offering to export keyword lists for internal review (28:04)\n\n- The group recognized the need to integrate high-volume keywords into website content, blogs, and product messaging to better align with customer search behavior and improve organic traffic (27:52)\n    - A sidebar discussion among key team members was proposed to analyze keyword data and refine product-market alignment (28:30)\n\n## **Process Improvements and Next Steps**\n\nClear timelines, responsibilities, and process steps were established to ensure smooth campaign execution and continuous improvement (38:13).\n\n- Nathalie will update outreach emails and targeting to reflect the revised firm size focus and share these with Ruby’s team for review immediately (20:35)\n    - Emails will be loaded into marketing tools and warmed up before the **launch on Monday the 17th** (39:05)\n    - Ongoing weekly monitoring will track performance metrics to refine campaign elements as needed (39:12)\n\n- Ruby will onboard **Kristen** to manage sales enablement tools and ensure alignment with other campaigns (36:12)\n    - This will address previous gaps where sales enablement was less structured (36:25)\n\n- Michael Hadley explicitly confirmed that going forward, the company will **not target firms with fewer than 10 to 20 employees** for any product line, solidifying the strategic focus on SMBs with meaningful IT needs (39:40)\n\n- Jeffery Lauria committed to delivering a **sample assessment excerpt by week’s end** to support sales (37:46)\n- The AI readiness SEO landing page is under final internal review with a goal for prompt publication (32:54)","outline":null,"keywords":["Account-Based Marketing","AI Readiness Assessment","Legal Services","Lead Scoring","LinkedIn Ads","Sales Enablement"],"overview":"- **Focus on Target Market:** ABM campaign targets legal firms with 20 to 100 employees for better engagement.\n\n- **Multi-Channel ABM Approach:** Campaign will use emails, LinkedIn messages, and paid ads for brand awareness and lead generation.\n\n- **Lead Scoring System:** Leads scoring 10 or above will receive personalized follow-up based on engagement metrics.\n\n- **Content and Sales Support:** Educational content and sales materials will enhance credibility and aid in closing deals.\n\n- **Keyword Strategy Emphasis:** Prioritize high-volume keywords in LinkedIn ads; Google search ads are deprioritized due to low relevance.\n\n- **Process and Timeline Clarity:** Weekly monitoring and defined responsibilities will ensure smooth execution and ongoing campaign improvements.","action_items":"\n**Nathalie Mintjens**\nUpdate targeting strategy to focus on firms with 20-100 employees and adjust outreach emails accordingly (15:46)\nShare updated ABM plan and outreach email drafts with Ruby Pontbriand for review (40:07)\nExport and share keyword lists from Google Ads and Ahrefs tools to relevant stakeholders (28:30)\nCoordinate on incorporating AI-related blog and organic LinkedIn content ideas to align with the ABM campaign (24:26)\nManage email domain warm-up ahead of campaign launch (38:13)\n\n**Ruby Pontbriand**\nReview updated ABM plan and outreach emails from Nathalie and provide feedback (40:07)\nMeet with sales enablement lead Kristen to brief her on new and existing campaigns and ensure availability of sales tools (36:12)\n\n**Jeffery Lauria**\nReview and approve the AI readiness assessment SEO landing page currently in internal review (32:54)\nProvide sales team with sample AI readiness assessments by end of week to aid sales enablement (37:46)\n\n**Michael A Hadley**\nSupport Ruby Pontbriand and Kristen in ensuring sales enablement assets are comprehensive and aligned with campaigns (35:49)\n\n**Kirk Fackre**\nReview existing campaign sales enablement materials and identify gaps with marketing team for improvement (38:02)\n"},"duration":40.709999084472656,"speakers":[{"id":0,"name":"Michael A Hadley"},{"id":1,"name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"id":2,"name":"Kirk Fackre1"},{"id":3,"name":"Samuel Bagnall"},{"id":4,"name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"id":5,"name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"id":6,"name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"id":7,"name":"Ruby Pontbriand"}],"sentences":[{"text":"Hello.","index":0,"end_time":25.04,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":24.72,"speaker_name":"Michael A Hadley"},{"text":"Hello.","index":1,"end_time":26.89,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":26.57,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Morning.","index":2,"end_time":29.21,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":28.81,"speaker_name":"Kirk Fackre1"},{"text":"Morning.","index":3,"end_time":30.65,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":30.25,"speaker_name":"Samuel Bagnall"},{"text":"How''s Chicago, Natalie?","index":4,"end_time":46.41,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":44.65,"speaker_name":"Michael A Hadley"},{"text":"Getting too cold.","index":5,"end_time":48.65,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":47.53,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Yeah, same thing here.","index":6,"end_time":50.65,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":49.37,"speaker_name":"Michael A Hadley"},{"text":"Is it wicked windy there?","index":7,"end_time":64.34,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":62.9,"speaker_name":"Michael A Hadley"},{"text":"It is windy.","index":8,"end_time":68.26,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":65.78,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Dark also.","index":9,"end_time":70.34,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":68.98,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Every time I finish work, it''s pitch black outside.","index":10,"end_time":72.9,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":70.66,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"What time does the sun go down?","index":11,"end_time":77.78,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":76.5,"speaker_name":"Samuel Bagnall"},{"text":"Like 4:30.","index":12,"end_time":78.84,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":77.96,"speaker_name":"Samuel Bagnall"},{"text":"Five?","index":13,"end_time":80.28,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":79.88,"speaker_name":"Samuel Bagnall"},{"text":"Yeah, about.","index":14,"end_time":81.88,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":81.16,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Yeah, like 4:30.","index":15,"end_time":83.48,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":82.36,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":16,"end_time":84.24,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":83.88,"speaker_name":"Samuel Bagnall"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":17,"end_time":84.52,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":84.24,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"I just.","index":18,"end_time":84.92,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":84.52,"speaker_name":"Samuel Bagnall"},{"text":"Here.","index":19,"end_time":85.24,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":84.92,"speaker_name":"Samuel Bagnall"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":20,"end_time":86.28,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":85.8,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Throws me off a lot.","index":21,"end_time":87.56,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":86.28,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"I think it''s like 8pm already.","index":22,"end_time":89.16,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":87.64,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":23,"end_time":90.2,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":89.72,"speaker_name":"Samuel Bagnall"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":24,"end_time":92.32,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":91.96,"speaker_name":"Samuel Bagnall"},{"text":"They''re gonna change that whole thing.","index":25,"end_time":94.2,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":92.32,"speaker_name":"Michael A Hadley"},{"text":"Daylight savings.","index":26,"end_time":98.52,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":97.4,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Yep.","index":27,"end_time":99.64,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":99.08,"speaker_name":"Michael A Hadley"},{"text":"Get rid of it.","index":28,"end_time":100.96,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":100.12,"speaker_name":"Michael A Hadley"},{"text":"All right.","index":29,"end_time":103.42,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":100.96,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"We don''t need it.","index":30,"end_time":111.17,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":110.29,"speaker_name":"Michael A Hadley"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":31,"end_time":114.05,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":113.57,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"I''d rather have more sunshine in the evening, in the morning.","index":32,"end_time":118.05,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":114.05,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Agreed.","index":33,"end_time":120.37,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":119.65,"speaker_name":"Michael A Hadley"},{"text":"But for some reason they talk about it, they don''t do it.","index":34,"end_time":129.25,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":126.05,"speaker_name":"Michael A Hadley"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":35,"end_time":132.029,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":131.709,"speaker_name":"Samuel Bagnall"},{"text":"I''m on Team Daylight Morning.","index":36,"end_time":136.029,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":134.189,"speaker_name":"Kirk Fackre1"},{"text":"So I guess I''m the outlier here.","index":37,"end_time":137.869,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":136.189,"speaker_name":"Kirk Fackre1"},{"text":"Oh, you like it?","index":38,"end_time":141.309,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":140.349,"speaker_name":"Michael A Hadley"},{"text":"I get up really early and I don''t, you know, I don''t mind.","index":39,"end_time":146.909,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":142.349,"speaker_name":"Kirk Fackre1"},{"text":"I don''t like that it gets dark.","index":40,"end_time":148.709,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":147.389,"speaker_name":"Kirk Fackre1"},{"text":"At 4:30, but I''d rather have light in the morning.","index":41,"end_time":151.149,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":148.709,"speaker_name":"Michael A Hadley"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":42,"end_time":154.869,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":154.509,"speaker_name":"Samuel Bagnall"},{"text":"I will say I was struggling to get up past couple weeks before it changed.","index":43,"end_time":158.1,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":154.869,"speaker_name":"Samuel Bagnall"},{"text":"When it was getting bright at like 7.","index":44,"end_time":159.7,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":158.1,"speaker_name":"Samuel Bagnall"},{"text":"It''s like.","index":45,"end_time":160.3,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":159.86,"speaker_name":"Samuel Bagnall"},{"text":"It was hard to get up at like 6:30.","index":46,"end_time":161.78,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":160.3,"speaker_name":"Samuel Bagnall"},{"text":"So dark.","index":47,"end_time":162.82,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":162.1,"speaker_name":"Samuel Bagnall"},{"text":"But it''s a little better now, but.","index":48,"end_time":165.46,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":163.38,"speaker_name":"Samuel Bagnall"},{"text":"Oh, come on, don''t change.","index":49,"end_time":167.94,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":166.42,"speaker_name":"Michael A Hadley"},{"text":"I know I''m switching, but all of.","index":50,"end_time":169.82,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":168.02,"speaker_name":"Samuel Bagnall"},{"text":"A sudden you''re changing.","index":51,"end_time":171.14,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":169.82,"speaker_name":"Michael A Hadley"},{"text":"You''re jumping on Kurt''s bandwagon.","index":52,"end_time":173.26,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":171.14,"speaker_name":"Michael A Hadley"},{"text":"And this is.","index":53,"end_time":173.82,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":173.26,"speaker_name":"Samuel Bagnall"},{"text":"This is the first time I''ve really felt that.","index":54,"end_time":175.46,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":173.82,"speaker_name":"Samuel Bagnall"},{"text":"So I don''t know.","index":55,"end_time":176.18,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":175.46,"speaker_name":"Samuel Bagnall"},{"text":"I think for kids to go to school in the dark kind of stinks too.","index":56,"end_time":182.1,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":178.74,"speaker_name":"Kirk Fackre1"},{"text":"Like that''s the other side.","index":57,"end_time":183.67,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":182.1,"speaker_name":"Kirk Fackre1"},{"text":"Of course, the start time should be later.","index":58,"end_time":186.47,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":184.47,"speaker_name":"Kirk Fackre1"},{"text":"Like my.","index":59,"end_time":186.87,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":186.47,"speaker_name":"Kirk Fackre1"},{"text":"When my kids were in high school, like they had to get a 7 o'' clock bus, which seemed kind of nuts to me.","index":60,"end_time":192.31,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":186.87,"speaker_name":"Kirk Fackre1"},{"text":"Yeah, same.","index":61,"end_time":194.87,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":194.07,"speaker_name":"Samuel Bagnall"},{"text":"I think that''s why they had daylight savings.","index":62,"end_time":199.23,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":197.03,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Right.","index":63,"end_time":199.509,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":199.23,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Was originally it was because of the war.","index":64,"end_time":202.47,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":199.99,"speaker_name":"Michael A Hadley"},{"text":"Oh.","index":65,"end_time":203.75,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":203.27,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"Something like that.","index":66,"end_time":207.43,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":206.47,"speaker_name":"Michael A Hadley"},{"text":"So I don''t know.","index":67,"end_time":210.84,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":210,"speaker_name":"Michael A Hadley"},{"text":"I looked it up once.","index":68,"end_time":211.76,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":210.84,"speaker_name":"Michael A Hadley"},{"text":"I don''t remember.","index":69,"end_time":212.64,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":211.76,"speaker_name":"Michael A Hadley"},{"text":"I''m old.","index":70,"end_time":214.16,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":213.52,"speaker_name":"Michael A Hadley"},{"text":"I can''t remember that stuff.","index":71,"end_time":215.92,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":214.32,"speaker_name":"Michael A Hadley"},{"text":"So I''d like to just get rid of it all together.","index":72,"end_time":231.84,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":226.72,"speaker_name":"Michael A Hadley"},{"text":"Do all of the states have daylight savings?","index":73,"end_time":238.25,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":236.01,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"No, Arizona doesn''t or the southern part doesn''t.","index":74,"end_time":242.41,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":238.65,"speaker_name":"Samuel Bagnall"},{"text":"So only Navajo county, like that kind of reservation is the only one who does in Arizona.","index":75,"end_time":248.77,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":243.37,"speaker_name":"Samuel Bagnall"},{"text":"But the rest doesn''t.","index":76,"end_time":249.69,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":248.77,"speaker_name":"Samuel Bagnall"},{"text":"It''s interesting.","index":77,"end_time":251.13,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":250.249,"speaker_name":"Samuel Bagnall"},{"text":"Weird.","index":78,"end_time":252.65,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":252.09,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":79,"end_time":253.37,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":252.89,"speaker_name":"Samuel Bagnall"},{"text":"I don''t know if there are any others though.","index":80,"end_time":261.26,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":260.26,"speaker_name":"Samuel Bagnall"},{"text":"But I know Arizona doesn''t do it.","index":81,"end_time":263.14,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":261.26,"speaker_name":"Samuel Bagnall"},{"text":"If they can do it, we can do it.","index":82,"end_time":275.54,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":273.54,"speaker_name":"Michael A Hadley"},{"text":"Okay.","index":83,"end_time":282.46,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":282.02,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":84,"end_time":282.66,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":282.46,"speaker_name":"Samuel Bagnall"},{"text":"So it was implemented by Germany and Austria, Hungary in 191916 during World War I.","index":85,"end_time":288.97,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":282.66,"speaker_name":"Samuel Bagnall"},{"text":"So I knew it was through.","index":86,"end_time":291.37,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":290.33,"speaker_name":"Michael A Hadley"},{"text":"Through the war because.","index":87,"end_time":292.41,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":291.37,"speaker_name":"Michael A Hadley"},{"text":"Oh.","index":88,"end_time":295.89,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":295.53,"speaker_name":"Samuel Bagnall"},{"text":"Then it was reintroduced during World War II.","index":89,"end_time":298.65,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":295.89,"speaker_name":"Samuel Bagnall"},{"text":"Okay.","index":90,"end_time":301.21,"speaker_id":6,"start_time":300.73,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Interesting.","index":91,"end_time":301.85,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":301.21,"speaker_name":"Samuel Bagnall"},{"text":"But why?","index":92,"end_time":303.05,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":302.33,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Hello?","index":93,"end_time":305.85,"speaker_id":7,"start_time":305.37,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Hello.","index":94,"end_time":307.21,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":306.65,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Hey.","index":95,"end_time":307.93,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":307.45,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Sorry about that.","index":96,"end_time":309.13,"speaker_id":6,"start_time":308.33,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Wrapping up a call.","index":97,"end_time":311.93,"speaker_id":6,"start_time":310.89,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Allegedly with Healthy Humor.","index":98,"end_time":317.3,"speaker_id":6,"start_time":314.66,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"You know them, right?","index":99,"end_time":319.46,"speaker_id":6,"start_time":318.26,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"No.","index":100,"end_time":320.98,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":320.66,"speaker_name":"Michael A Hadley"},{"text":"Who are they?","index":101,"end_time":321.54,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":320.98,"speaker_name":"Samuel Bagnall"},{"text":"Healthy Humor.","index":102,"end_time":322.66,"speaker_id":6,"start_time":321.78,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"They''re a new client, I think Jeff said.","index":103,"end_time":327.14,"speaker_id":7,"start_time":322.66,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Oh, in New York?","index":104,"end_time":328.66,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":327.62,"speaker_name":"Michael A Hadley"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":105,"end_time":329.14,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":328.66,"speaker_name":"Michael A Hadley"},{"text":"They do clown stuff at hospitals and.","index":106,"end_time":332.26,"speaker_id":7,"start_time":330.18,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Help the kids feel better.","index":107,"end_time":333.78,"speaker_id":6,"start_time":332.26,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Oh, yeah, they''re a pro bono client.","index":108,"end_time":336.18,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":334.18,"speaker_name":"Michael A Hadley"},{"text":"Yes.","index":109,"end_time":336.74,"speaker_id":7,"start_time":336.26,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"I''m here.","index":110,"end_time":340.67,"speaker_id":6,"start_time":340.11,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Will Jeff be joining or is this it for today?","index":111,"end_time":344.99,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":341.95,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"He''s.","index":112,"end_time":349.11,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":348.67,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"He''s invited.","index":113,"end_time":349.75,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":349.11,"speaker_name":"Samuel Bagnall"},{"text":"I think he accepted, but I don''t know.","index":114,"end_time":351.79,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":349.75,"speaker_name":"Samuel Bagnall"},{"text":"Well, I am.","index":115,"end_time":353.87,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":352.91,"speaker_name":"Michael A Hadley"},{"text":"One.","index":116,"end_time":364.36,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":364.12,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"All right.","index":117,"end_time":381.36,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":380.92,"speaker_name":"Michael A Hadley"},{"text":"I sent them an im.","index":118,"end_time":382.68,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":381.36,"speaker_name":"Michael A Hadley"},{"text":"Okay.","index":119,"end_time":385.64,"speaker_id":6,"start_time":385.08,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"He said yes.","index":120,"end_time":392.77,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":391.89,"speaker_name":"Michael A Hadley"},{"text":"There he is.","index":121,"end_time":407.49,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":406.69,"speaker_name":"Michael A Hadley"},{"text":"Sorry, I didn''t get a notice.","index":122,"end_time":410.41,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":409.09,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"The meeting started and I was lollyglagging on another meeting, so I apologize.","index":123,"end_time":415.65,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":410.41,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"Thank you, Mike, for the heads up.","index":124,"end_time":417.37,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":416.17,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"No worries.","index":125,"end_time":418.65,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":418.01,"speaker_name":"Michael A Hadley"},{"text":"All right, we can jump in.","index":126,"end_time":423.85,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":421.13,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Today we''re going to discuss the ABM plan for the new AI readiness assessment.","index":127,"end_time":429.29,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":424.01,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"And starting off for this offer, we.","index":128,"end_time":432.57,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":429.93,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Will be targeting Legal Services.","index":129,"end_time":434.73,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":432.57,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"And then just for the agenda today, so we''ll start by talking about key accounts and the Persona that we want to target.","index":130,"end_time":442.73,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":436.33,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"We''re going to visualize the ABM approach.","index":131,"end_time":445.3,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":443.38,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"So looking at all the different platforms.","index":132,"end_time":448.06,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":445.54,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"And touch points we''ll use and how.","index":133,"end_time":449.5,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":448.06,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"They all connect together.","index":134,"end_time":450.5,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":449.5,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"We''ll talk about the messaging, define lead scoring, and how we''re going to track.","index":135,"end_time":456.22,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":451.14,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Engagement and results in this campaign.","index":136,"end_time":458.9,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":456.22,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"We''ll take a look at the sales enablement content we''ve developed so that once.","index":137,"end_time":464.02,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":459.46,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"We do get leads, how do we make sure that we can close them?","index":138,"end_time":466.82,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":464.02,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"And then we''ll take a look at.","index":139,"end_time":468.34,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":467.14,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Next steps and, and the timeline.","index":140,"end_time":470.11,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":468.34,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Anything missing from this that you wanted to discuss?","index":141,"end_time":473.95,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":471.55,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Looks good to me.","index":142,"end_time":477.63,"speaker_id":6,"start_time":476.75,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Yeah, I think you got it.","index":143,"end_time":478.99,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":477.71,"speaker_name":"Michael A Hadley"},{"text":"Great.","index":144,"end_time":480.27,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":479.87,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Okay.","index":145,"end_time":482.95,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":482.43,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"So starting with the targeting.","index":146,"end_time":484.47,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":482.95,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"So when we did the role play.","index":147,"end_time":486.39,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":484.47,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Sales call, we talked about this.","index":148,"end_time":488.15,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":486.39,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"A little bit of we''re going after.","index":149,"end_time":490.23,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":488.15,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Legal Services, but what specific size should we be looking at?","index":150,"end_time":493.87,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":490.23,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"And the conclusion we came to is.","index":151,"end_time":496.47,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":494.19,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Firms with two to three attorneys that.","index":152,"end_time":499.44,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":496.47,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Have a small administrative team.","index":153,"end_time":501.68,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":499.44,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"So these are firms that are likely beginning to explore AI tools.","index":154,"end_time":506.16,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":502.16,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Their employees are probably using them individually.","index":155,"end_time":509.52,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":506.8,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"But they don''t know how to get that next step.","index":156,"end_time":511.76,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":509.92,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"They don''t have the security, knowledge, governance, or data readiness to implement it organization wide.","index":157,"end_time":517.84,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":511.76,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"And then let me ask a question.","index":158,"end_time":521.52,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":518.88,"speaker_name":"Michael A Hadley"},{"text":"We''re going after two to three attorney companies.","index":159,"end_time":524.08,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":521.52,"speaker_name":"Michael A Hadley"},{"text":"Why?","index":160,"end_time":530.31,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":530.07,"speaker_name":"Kirk Fackre1"},{"text":"So we talked about this in the call and we said that if we go a little bit above.","index":161,"end_time":537.11,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":532.15,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"So firms with 2 to 3 attorneys likely link to firms with 5 to 20 total employees.","index":162,"end_time":544.79,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":537.27,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"And then we think that if we.","index":163,"end_time":547.35,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":545.59,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Go above this 20 threshold, we''re likely.","index":164,"end_time":549.55,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":547.35,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Targeting companies that already have a managed.","index":165,"end_time":552.19,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":549.55,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"IT provider or in house tech leadership.","index":166,"end_time":555.15,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":552.19,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"So by staying under that, I Corps will be the first to come in.","index":167,"end_time":559.87,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":555.63,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"And help with this.","index":168,"end_time":560.75,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":559.87,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"I think referring back to my notes.","index":169,"end_time":566.11,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":563.39,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"Yeah, I think we just talked about not going enterprise and work in the SMB.","index":170,"end_time":571.51,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":566.59,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"I don''t think we have it defined.","index":171,"end_time":572.87,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":571.51,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"Two or three attorneys.","index":172,"end_time":574.11,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":572.87,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"I think we just started talking about SMBs.","index":173,"end_time":576.67,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":574.35,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"Go ahead, Mike.","index":174,"end_time":580.02,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":579.38,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"Sorry.","index":175,"end_time":580.38,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":580.02,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"No, I look at that as cheese.","index":176,"end_time":582.1,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":580.38,"speaker_name":"Michael A Hadley"},{"text":"Not a lot of opportunity.","index":177,"end_time":585.14,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":583.7,"speaker_name":"Michael A Hadley"},{"text":"They''re too hard to sell to.","index":178,"end_time":586.86,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":585.38,"speaker_name":"Kirk Fackre1"},{"text":"Yeah, I mean our sweet spot in general is 20 to 60 employees.","index":179,"end_time":591.86,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":586.86,"speaker_name":"Kirk Fackre1"},{"text":"Putting aside AI readiness, it''s awfully hard to sell even an assessment to a firm of that size.","index":180,"end_time":601.62,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":593.3,"speaker_name":"Kirk Fackre1"},{"text":"And it''s hard to see what the upside would be if we did.","index":181,"end_time":604.34,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":601.62,"speaker_name":"Kirk Fackre1"},{"text":"Okay.","index":182,"end_time":606.83,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":606.43,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Yeah, I would agree because I mean, ideally, ultimately what we''d like to do is, you know, we get these leads, we want to close them.","index":183,"end_time":614.67,"speaker_id":7,"start_time":607.07,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Right.","index":184,"end_time":615.11,"speaker_id":7,"start_time":614.75,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"And then we want to.","index":185,"end_time":616.11,"speaker_id":7,"start_time":615.11,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Right.","index":186,"end_time":616.59,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":616.19,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"Sell, get an AI assessment in the door, but then we want to grow them into an Encompass client or another programs or services client.","index":187,"end_time":624.35,"speaker_id":7,"start_time":616.59,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"So those ones, if it''s just a.","index":188,"end_time":627.35,"speaker_id":6,"start_time":624.59,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"You know, 20, 20 person firm, that wouldn''t really be worth our.","index":189,"end_time":631.83,"speaker_id":7,"start_time":627.35,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Worth the ticket.","index":190,"end_time":634.03,"speaker_id":7,"start_time":633.03,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"So I think definitely increasing this would be good.","index":191,"end_time":636.63,"speaker_id":7,"start_time":634.03,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":192,"end_time":637.35,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":636.95,"speaker_name":"Michael A Hadley"},{"text":"Natalie, other MSPs when it comes to AI and cyber security and stuff like that, they really don''t have their act together a lot of the msps.","index":193,"end_time":650.39,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":637.35,"speaker_name":"Michael A Hadley"},{"text":"So.","index":194,"end_time":651.27,"speaker_id":6,"start_time":650.87,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"I think we should go after the 20 plus, not go after two or three.","index":195,"end_time":660.33,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":653.59,"speaker_name":"Michael A Hadley"},{"text":"It just makes.","index":196,"end_time":661.13,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":660.33,"speaker_name":"Michael A Hadley"},{"text":"Gives me hot stomach issues when you talk about two to three.","index":197,"end_time":665.21,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":661.13,"speaker_name":"Michael A Hadley"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":198,"end_time":666.01,"speaker_id":6,"start_time":665.53,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"I think we''d get a lot of leads, Natalie, but I don''t think we''d get any actual business out of it, so.","index":199,"end_time":674.25,"speaker_id":7,"start_time":668.89,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"And we really want to get the business.","index":200,"end_time":676.25,"speaker_id":7,"start_time":674.89,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"And the other Mike''s point, a lot of those other MSPs aren''t doing a whole lot with AI readiness.","index":201,"end_time":684.25,"speaker_id":7,"start_time":678.57,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"They''re kind of behind the curve.","index":202,"end_time":685.73,"speaker_id":7,"start_time":684.49,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"We''re like right on the cusp of.","index":203,"end_time":687.37,"speaker_id":7,"start_time":685.73,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Wouldn''t even be a competition really a little bit.","index":204,"end_time":693.15,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":689.31,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"But I''d say we come out top.","index":205,"end_time":695.03,"speaker_id":7,"start_time":693.15,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"And I would say any time that we go into these opportunities, it''s always going to be competition.","index":206,"end_time":703.99,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":695.51,"speaker_name":"Michael A Hadley"},{"text":"So we just have to beat that competition.","index":207,"end_time":706.63,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":704.47,"speaker_name":"Michael A Hadley"},{"text":"But you know, I would if I was going to go to a low number below 20, maybe 10 or 15, but 20 is better.","index":208,"end_time":716.47,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":706.71,"speaker_name":"Michael A Hadley"},{"text":"20.","index":209,"end_time":717.934,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":717.43,"speaker_name":"Michael A Hadley"},{"text":"20 to 100 would be great.","index":210,"end_time":721.67,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":718.046,"speaker_name":"Michael A Hadley"},{"text":"What do you guys think?","index":211,"end_time":724.95,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":723.83,"speaker_name":"Michael A Hadley"},{"text":"Yeah, I agree.","index":212,"end_time":726.43,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":725.83,"speaker_name":"Kirk Fackre1"},{"text":"The other vector is that I used to sell into legal and it used to be you would have like one admin per lawyer.","index":213,"end_time":732.63,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":726.43,"speaker_name":"Kirk Fackre1"},{"text":"That''s not the way it is anymore.","index":214,"end_time":734.07,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":732.63,"speaker_name":"Kirk Fackre1"},{"text":"They''ve, even before AI hit, they''ve cut a lot of the fat.","index":215,"end_time":739.75,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":734.79,"speaker_name":"Kirk Fackre1"},{"text":"Not fat, they''ve reduced the admin size.","index":216,"end_time":742.87,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":739.99,"speaker_name":"Kirk Fackre1"},{"text":"So it''s more.","index":217,"end_time":743.59,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":742.95,"speaker_name":"Kirk Fackre1"},{"text":"I think maybe a 10 person firm might have one admin.","index":218,"end_time":747.41,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":743.59,"speaker_name":"Kirk Fackre1"},{"text":"It''s not the same ratio as it used to be.","index":219,"end_time":749.89,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":747.65,"speaker_name":"Kirk Fackre1"},{"text":"They do a lot of that stuff because my wife worked at a lot of firms too and a lot of the stuff they have admins do, they just do it themselves?","index":220,"end_time":759.65,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":751.65,"speaker_name":"Michael A Hadley"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":221,"end_time":760.569,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":760.05,"speaker_name":"Kirk Fackre1"},{"text":"Using tools.","index":222,"end_time":761.57,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":760.569,"speaker_name":"Michael A Hadley"},{"text":"Yep.","index":223,"end_time":762.77,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":762.21,"speaker_name":"Kirk Fackre1"},{"text":"So I have a question.","index":224,"end_time":764.69,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":763.73,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"Two actually three questions.","index":225,"end_time":766.45,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":764.77,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"So the first one is more of a statement.","index":226,"end_time":768.37,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":766.69,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"I''m going to go back and look at the notes.","index":227,"end_time":770.37,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":768.85,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"If we misled in the prior meeting, we apologize.","index":228,"end_time":773.41,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":770.37,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"Second question is when we talk about going after, you know, this segment or this segment, so you know, 2 users or 20 users versus 50 users, how does the approach differ?","index":229,"end_time":789.65,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":774.13,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"And I guess my question is, you know, like when we, when we go after, what does that mean?","index":230,"end_time":797.53,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":791.41,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"Does that mean we targeted our emails?","index":231,"end_time":799.97,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":797.53,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"Only the companies with two users, same content, same approach, just targeting to a smaller, different audience.","index":232,"end_time":807.13,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":799.97,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"And then how do we target to that audience?","index":233,"end_time":809.01,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":807.13,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"Yeah, so it would be a different targeting strategy.","index":234,"end_time":814.93,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":810.85,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"I''d have to think about that more and come back to you with some ideas of how it''s going to differ.","index":235,"end_time":821.33,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":816.05,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"If we go for these 20 to.","index":236,"end_time":822.73,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":821.33,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"100 employee companies.","index":237,"end_time":824.77,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":822.73,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"You will get smaller ones, they will come anyways, the larger ones will come, but it''s just whether you target those.","index":238,"end_time":833.33,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":826.61,"speaker_name":"Michael A Hadley"},{"text":"So.","index":239,"end_time":834.69,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":834.29,"speaker_name":"Michael A Hadley"},{"text":"So then my follow up question is, is everything else we''re going to discuss based on your assumption of five to 20 or two to three attorneys, should we step away, let you redo this or is it still going to be relevant information?","index":240,"end_time":851.25,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":835.33,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"Yeah, I think a lot of it.","index":241,"end_time":855.81,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":853.41,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"So when we look at this.","index":242,"end_time":857.89,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":855.97,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Emails for example, this will likely change because a lot of this is talking about.","index":243,"end_time":866.45,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":859.73,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"How these firms are probably, their employees are probably using AI individually and then I corps can come in and make sure that they have their data in the right place in order to control this firm wide.","index":244,"end_time":882.7,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":868.85,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"When it comes to the ads, a.","index":245,"end_time":886.1,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":883.5,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Lot of our ads remain the same.","index":246,"end_time":887.58,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":886.1,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"So these are, we have different approaches that we''re taking for our ads.","index":247,"end_time":891.86,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":887.9,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"We have a lot of educational content.","index":248,"end_time":893.82,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":891.86,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Which I think is stuff that despite the firm size they will be interested in.","index":249,"end_time":898.74,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":894.22,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Especially we''re targeting people like managing partners.","index":250,"end_time":901.26,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":898.74,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"This is accessible information that they would want to read about.","index":251,"end_time":904.7,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":901.9,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"It''s how to make sure that you''re using AI securely in your firm, which of these tools is right for your.","index":252,"end_time":911.67,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":905.26,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Specific use cases and your security needs.","index":253,"end_time":916.31,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":911.67,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"And then we also link to the.","index":254,"end_time":918.95,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":917.35,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Scorecard or quiz that we''ve made.","index":255,"end_time":921.99,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":920.07,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"A lot of these will stay the same.","index":256,"end_time":923.91,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":922.39,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"I think it''s mostly just the direct.","index":257,"end_time":925.549,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":923.99,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Outreach that I''ll need to work on more.","index":258,"end_time":927.91,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":925.549,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Mike, you have a question?","index":259,"end_time":929.75,"speaker_id":6,"start_time":928.79,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"I do.","index":260,"end_time":930.87,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":930.23,"speaker_name":"Michael A Hadley"},{"text":"I guess I could put my hand down now.","index":261,"end_time":935.59,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":933.51,"speaker_name":"Michael A Hadley"},{"text":"My question is, is that what we did on the other campaigns targeted two to three firms?","index":262,"end_time":944.84,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":937.16,"speaker_name":"Michael A Hadley"},{"text":"No.","index":263,"end_time":945.72,"speaker_id":6,"start_time":945.32,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"No.","index":264,"end_time":946.2,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":945.8,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Okay.","index":265,"end_time":947.32,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":946.68,"speaker_name":"Michael A Hadley"},{"text":"Still me.","index":266,"end_time":952.12,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":951.4,"speaker_name":"Michael A Hadley"},{"text":"Okay.","index":267,"end_time":955.24,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":954.6,"speaker_name":"Michael A Hadley"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":268,"end_time":957,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":956.44,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Why I''m so against that, Just so you know.","index":269,"end_time":961.12,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":958.36,"speaker_name":"Michael A Hadley"},{"text":"Because it''s all cheese, you know, at the end of the day, all you''re doing is bringing in C clients where all they do is complain and they complain about everything.","index":270,"end_time":970,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":961.12,"speaker_name":"Michael A Hadley"},{"text":"So we don''t want them.","index":271,"end_time":971.92,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":970.24,"speaker_name":"Michael A Hadley"},{"text":"Okay.","index":272,"end_time":973.6,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":973.04,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":273,"end_time":974.44,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":974.08,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"So I will.","index":274,"end_time":975,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":974.44,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Yeah, I''ll update this slide.","index":275,"end_time":976.48,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":975,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"In terms of the actual titles, this might change a little bit with bigger firms.","index":276,"end_time":983.52,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":978.88,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"So with these smaller firms, we''re going after a lot of the higher executive leadership and then also actual users.","index":277,"end_time":992.46,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":984.08,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"So attorneys partner people in operations and.","index":278,"end_time":995.46,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":992.54,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Then also secondary titles like the more.","index":279,"end_time":998.06,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":995.46,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Administrative staff, who they don''t have the.","index":280,"end_time":1000.98,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":998.06,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Buying or decision making power, but they.","index":281,"end_time":1003.9,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1000.98,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Are able to maybe take ideas to their leadership.","index":282,"end_time":1006.54,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1003.9,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"If we''re targeting this 20 to 100.","index":283,"end_time":1010.14,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1007.58,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Employees, I''ll have to research if that size company does have IT departments already in house.","index":284,"end_time":1018.22,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1010.38,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"If so, that might be another group that we want to target.","index":285,"end_time":1021.73,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1018.93,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":286,"end_time":1023.73,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1023.25,"speaker_name":"Michael A Hadley"},{"text":"So when we''re doing this and when we''re going at the non decision makers, we''ve been building one pagers that we can give them or a tool if they do sell it upstream to the decision maker, they can have something they can provide.","index":287,"end_time":1043.09,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1023.73,"speaker_name":"Michael A Hadley"},{"text":"So or even when we go to the decision makers, we can provide them with that as well.","index":288,"end_time":1051.13,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1043.73,"speaker_name":"Michael A Hadley"},{"text":"So.","index":289,"end_time":1051.53,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1051.13,"speaker_name":"Michael A Hadley"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":290,"end_time":1052.21,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1051.85,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Okay.","index":291,"end_time":1052.65,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1052.21,"speaker_name":"Michael A Hadley"},{"text":"All right.","index":292,"end_time":1055.85,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1055.21,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"And then for this user journey.","index":293,"end_time":1059.61,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1057.53,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"So this is a map that shows.","index":294,"end_time":1063.53,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1059.69,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"You how the whole ABM plan works together with all the different tools that we''re using.","index":295,"end_time":1068.33,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1063.53,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"So we have two layers to the plan.","index":296,"end_time":1071.57,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1069.21,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"We have brand awareness at the start.","index":297,"end_time":1073.79,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1071.57,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"So this is the first time we get in front of people.","index":298,"end_time":1076.03,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1073.79,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"First time hearing about I Corps and.","index":299,"end_time":1078.31,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1076.43,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"This AI readiness assessment.","index":300,"end_time":1080.11,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1078.31,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"And then so what we do during this layer is we have three different channels that we''re using.","index":301,"end_time":1086.27,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1080.67,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"We''re sending direct emails to people, we''re sending direct LinkedIn messages to people which come from Ruby.","index":302,"end_time":1093.07,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1086.51,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"And then they also see paid ads on LinkedIn.","index":303,"end_time":1096.11,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1093.15,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Now while they''re receiving all of this, we are on the back end measuring all of their engagement.","index":304,"end_time":1102.53,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1097.07,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Whether that''s clicking on links in the emails, clicking on ads, responding to LinkedIn.","index":305,"end_time":1107.85,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1102.53,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Messages and then we use a lead.","index":306,"end_time":1109.97,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1107.85,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Scoring model to determine once they become an engaged lead.","index":307,"end_time":1113.61,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1109.97,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Once they become engaged, that''s when we.","index":308,"end_time":1116.65,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1114.41,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Then pass them off to Ruby and Sam for actual follow up where they''re able to send more targeted messaging to them.","index":309,"end_time":1124.01,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1116.65,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"So they really look at like what.","index":310,"end_time":1125.33,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1124.01,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Firm are they at, what''s their experience.","index":311,"end_time":1126.89,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1125.33,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"And how can we really get them.","index":312,"end_time":1128.76,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1127.41,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"To this next step of booking a meeting with i4.","index":313,"end_time":1131.96,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1128.76,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"This is how the whole thing works together.","index":314,"end_time":1135.32,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1132.76,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Any questions about this?","index":315,"end_time":1137.4,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1135.96,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"No, just we''re adding another person to this process, which is one of our sellers.","index":316,"end_time":1144.76,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1138.2,"speaker_name":"Michael A Hadley"},{"text":"Okay.","index":317,"end_time":1146.04,"speaker_id":6,"start_time":1145.48,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"And what I think it will do is offer a different type of communication with them where the marketing people are trying to set up a meeting for seller and this seller is going to try to set up a meeting for herself.","index":318,"end_time":1162.37,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1146.04,"speaker_name":"Michael A Hadley"},{"text":"So.","index":319,"end_time":1164.29,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1163.97,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"And I think she''ll be a little bit more aggressive.","index":320,"end_time":1167.89,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1164.29,"speaker_name":"Michael A Hadley"},{"text":"So we''ll see how it works out, you know.","index":321,"end_time":1169.97,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1167.89,"speaker_name":"Michael A Hadley"},{"text":"Yeah, that''s great.","index":322,"end_time":1171.97,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1170.37,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"That will essentially be her taking over.","index":323,"end_time":1174.09,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1171.97,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"This portion over here.","index":324,"end_time":1175.57,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1174.09,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"So once we''ve seen a little bit.","index":325,"end_time":1177.65,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1175.97,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Of engagement from the contact, pass them up to the salesperson so they can continue.","index":326,"end_time":1181.51,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1177.65,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Right.","index":327,"end_time":1182.87,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1182.47,"speaker_name":"Michael A Hadley"},{"text":"Right.","index":328,"end_time":1186.15,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1185.75,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"So then for this direct outreach, I''m going to work on this, kind of edit these a little bit, do research on how we should be targeting those larger firms and then send them over.","index":329,"end_time":1201.03,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1191.35,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"To your team to review.","index":330,"end_time":1202.15,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1201.03,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":331,"end_time":1203.59,"speaker_id":7,"start_time":1203.27,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"And one thing I would say there.","index":332,"end_time":1204.95,"speaker_id":6,"start_time":1203.59,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Just a note on the targeting or you know, a theme or angle for your content is to reference back our notes from the, the AI readiness training discussion that we had with Jeff a couple weeks back where we talked a lot about the governance piece, the compliance piece, like data data.","index":333,"end_time":1232.02,"speaker_id":7,"start_time":1204.95,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"I can''t think of the word.","index":334,"end_time":1234.99,"speaker_id":6,"start_time":1233.87,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Loss protection.","index":335,"end_time":1236.11,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1235.15,"speaker_name":"Kirk Fackre1"},{"text":"No, data like data integrity.","index":336,"end_time":1239.47,"speaker_id":7,"start_time":1237.15,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Right.","index":337,"end_time":1239.95,"speaker_id":7,"start_time":1239.55,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"So that''s the thing.","index":338,"end_time":1241.07,"speaker_id":7,"start_time":1240.27,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"I think that those larger firms are, they''re very AI governance and compliance isn''t something that they can ignore anymore.","index":339,"end_time":1249.469,"speaker_id":7,"start_time":1241.07,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"And so that''s where we come in as an expert to really assess their use case of AI and help them actually develop an entire plan for adopting it.","index":340,"end_time":1258.63,"speaker_id":7,"start_time":1249.87,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Not just for productivity, but for compliance.","index":341,"end_time":1261.9,"speaker_id":7,"start_time":1258.63,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":342,"end_time":1263.5,"speaker_id":6,"start_time":1262.94,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"And I think a lot of it is we want to focus on the storytelling of the ROI piece and that these are real, real results that affect their bottom line with increased productivity, doing more with less.","index":343,"end_time":1284.78,"speaker_id":7,"start_time":1265.9,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":344,"end_time":1286.31,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1285.91,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"And also the, the articles that Sam and Jeff shared, that too, kind of.","index":345,"end_time":1293.99,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1287.43,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Playing into the fear.","index":346,"end_time":1294.95,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1293.99,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"What could happen if they don''t take this seriously.","index":347,"end_time":1297.99,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1295.11,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Right.","index":348,"end_time":1298.63,"speaker_id":7,"start_time":1298.31,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"All the statistics and articles.","index":349,"end_time":1300.43,"speaker_id":7,"start_time":1298.63,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Yep.","index":350,"end_time":1301.03,"speaker_id":6,"start_time":1300.43,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"So, all right, so question as we''re doing this and what I haven''t seen or maybe I''VE missed this is.","index":351,"end_time":1316.77,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1302.79,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"Are we aligning blogs and aligning LinkedIn to this campaign?","index":352,"end_time":1325.17,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1316.93,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"And if so, do we already have the blogs and the LinkedIn posts already done to the lines with this campaign?","index":353,"end_time":1334.85,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1326.37,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"I guess.","index":354,"end_time":1338.9,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1338.7,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"Ruby, that''s probably.","index":355,"end_time":1339.82,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1338.9,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":356,"end_time":1340.98,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1340.54,"speaker_name":"Michael A Hadley"},{"text":"I mean, I can speak to the social stuff, like LinkedIn stuff.","index":357,"end_time":1344.42,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1340.98,"speaker_name":"Samuel Bagnall"},{"text":"I mean, yeah.","index":358,"end_time":1345.1,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1344.42,"speaker_name":"Samuel Bagnall"},{"text":"So, yeah, I do talk a lot about assessments and then kind of AI stuff.","index":359,"end_time":1350.3,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1345.34,"speaker_name":"Samuel Bagnall"},{"text":"I don''t have a. I want to do like a quote, like, don''t have a legal client.","index":360,"end_time":1354.9,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1351.5,"speaker_name":"Samuel Bagnall"},{"text":"I know we talked about that, Jeff.","index":361,"end_time":1356.14,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1354.9,"speaker_name":"Samuel Bagnall"},{"text":"But yeah, so I''d like to get something like that.","index":362,"end_time":1359.02,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1356.7,"speaker_name":"Samuel Bagnall"},{"text":"But.","index":363,"end_time":1359.3,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1359.02,"speaker_name":"Samuel Bagnall"},{"text":"But yes.","index":364,"end_time":1359.78,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1359.3,"speaker_name":"Samuel Bagnall"},{"text":"So it is aligned.","index":365,"end_time":1360.78,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1359.78,"speaker_name":"Samuel Bagnall"},{"text":"Who''S responsible for providing that content?","index":366,"end_time":1364.63,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1362.87,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"Is that us internally or is that you guys?","index":367,"end_time":1368.31,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1365.27,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"Natalie?","index":368,"end_time":1369.03,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1368.31,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"That''s us.","index":369,"end_time":1370.47,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1369.83,"speaker_name":"Samuel Bagnall"},{"text":"Okay.","index":370,"end_time":1371.59,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1371.03,"speaker_name":"Samuel Bagnall"},{"text":"All right, cool.","index":371,"end_time":1374.79,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1373.91,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"I think we do need to.","index":372,"end_time":1378.15,"speaker_id":6,"start_time":1375.27,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"I know, like, throughout this process, we''ve had a lot of ahas of like, oh, that''d be a great blog post.","index":373,"end_time":1383.51,"speaker_id":7,"start_time":1379.11,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"That''d be a great blog post.","index":374,"end_time":1384.79,"speaker_id":7,"start_time":1383.51,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"So I know we have a couple of ideas in the pipeline, but those aren''t fully fleshed out yet in terms.","index":375,"end_time":1389.79,"speaker_id":7,"start_time":1384.95,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Of, you know, fully planned out blog posts.","index":376,"end_time":1394.66,"speaker_id":6,"start_time":1389.79,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"But I think that''s something we should.","index":377,"end_time":1396.78,"speaker_id":6,"start_time":1394.66,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Take as an action from this call is to put together that list and.","index":378,"end_time":1400.74,"speaker_id":7,"start_time":1396.78,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Get those in development and again, those go out.","index":379,"end_time":1405.5,"speaker_id":6,"start_time":1400.98,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"That''s like the organic channel of.","index":380,"end_time":1409.38,"speaker_id":7,"start_time":1405.5,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"When I say organic, I mean like the not paid because this ABM piece is paid.","index":381,"end_time":1416.02,"speaker_id":7,"start_time":1409.7,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"LinkedIn ads.","index":382,"end_time":1417.1,"speaker_id":7,"start_time":1416.02,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Paid.","index":383,"end_time":1417.54,"speaker_id":6,"start_time":1417.1,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Paid, you know, lead targets or lead gen forms that will show up as like sponsored on LinkedIn.","index":384,"end_time":1427.15,"speaker_id":7,"start_time":1420.39,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"When you''re scrolling the feed, if you ever see something that says sponsored, that''s what that is.","index":385,"end_time":1432.43,"speaker_id":7,"start_time":1427.15,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"But the organic piece is like what we post ON I core LinkedIn just as ourselves.","index":386,"end_time":1439.47,"speaker_id":7,"start_time":1432.43,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Right.","index":387,"end_time":1439.75,"speaker_id":7,"start_time":1439.47,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"It''s not paid.","index":388,"end_time":1440.39,"speaker_id":7,"start_time":1439.75,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"We''re not, you know, it''s just a post.","index":389,"end_time":1442.63,"speaker_id":6,"start_time":1440.39,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"And that''s how we usually do when we post our blogs every week or the other content that we post throughout the week.","index":390,"end_time":1448.85,"speaker_id":7,"start_time":1442.95,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"So we should definitely be incorporating similar AI content into that organic push as.","index":391,"end_time":1456.49,"speaker_id":7,"start_time":1450.21,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Well.","index":392,"end_time":1456.77,"speaker_id":6,"start_time":1456.49,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"And then getting into the paid media.","index":393,"end_time":1469.17,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1466.13,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"So one of the learnings we''ve had.","index":394,"end_time":1471.73,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1470.05,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"From the other campaigns is that LinkedIn works the best specifically for I core.","index":395,"end_time":1477.29,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1471.73,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"And I think the offerings that we have, this is where we see the most amount of engagement.","index":396,"end_time":1481.49,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1477.29,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"And then for this campaign, I did.","index":397,"end_time":1484.57,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1482.61,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Do some research into Google search ads and looked at potential keywords we could.","index":398,"end_time":1488.53,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1484.57,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Target for this assessment, and the results are not great.","index":399,"end_time":1492.77,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1488.53,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"There''s very few monthly searches on specifically what we''re offering.","index":400,"end_time":1496.53,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1493.09,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"So my recommendation for this is to.","index":401,"end_time":1499.01,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1496.85,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Put our budget into LinkedIn, which we know works.","index":402,"end_time":1501.6,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1499.01,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"And I think we''ll get better results than trying on Google as well.","index":403,"end_time":1504.96,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1501.92,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Well, wait a minute, can you better define that?","index":404,"end_time":1508.88,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1505.6,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"So what you''re telling me is what we''re offering, there''s no Google search results, it''s low.","index":405,"end_time":1515.04,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1509.36,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"So what?","index":406,"end_time":1517.2,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1515.92,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"So that, that to me sounds like an issue.","index":407,"end_time":1520.64,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1518.4,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"But, but with that said, what are people searching for?","index":408,"end_time":1526,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1520.64,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"And should we realign this for what people are searching for?","index":409,"end_time":1531.45,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1527.45,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"At least some of it with some of those keywords.","index":410,"end_time":1536.65,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1531.85,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"So I guess.","index":411,"end_time":1537.85,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1537.13,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"Can you better explain what you just said?","index":412,"end_time":1540.65,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1538.57,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":413,"end_time":1541.69,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1541.21,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"So when I did keyword research, people are searching a lot about AI in general.","index":414,"end_time":1546.89,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1541.93,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"AI for legal services as well.","index":415,"end_time":1549.69,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1547.61,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Those are high, have high search traffic.","index":416,"end_time":1552.73,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1549.77,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"The issue is they''re not searching specifically for an AI assessment, likely because that''s.","index":417,"end_time":1558.87,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1553.19,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Just not a well known thing at this point.","index":418,"end_time":1561.27,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1558.87,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"So people are searching best SaaS tools.","index":419,"end_time":1563.95,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1561.67,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"For legal services, for example, or how.","index":420,"end_time":1567.19,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1563.95,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"To implement AI into my law firm.","index":421,"end_time":1570.07,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1567.19,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"So those are great things that we could target on searches organically through SEO.","index":422,"end_time":1575.03,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1570.47,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"We can write a blog post about.","index":423,"end_time":1577.43,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1575.91,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Safe AI adoption in law firms.","index":424,"end_time":1579.99,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1578.07,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Those aren''t commercial searches though.","index":425,"end_time":1582.33,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1580.41,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"And so I don''t think our budget would be well spent there when they''re.","index":426,"end_time":1587.01,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1582.89,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"More informational instead of commercial.","index":427,"end_time":1589.29,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1587.01,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"So let me, let me ask a whole other question then.","index":428,"end_time":1593.77,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1590.73,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"Where do you get that information?","index":429,"end_time":1597.05,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1595.61,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"Is that from Sam Rush or the Rush program?","index":430,"end_time":1599.45,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1597.13,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"Is that where do you get who''s searching for what words?","index":431,"end_time":1602.89,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1599.45,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"And then more specifically, should we be implementing for everything that we do going forward?","index":432,"end_time":1610.08,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1603.45,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"Forget the ABM campaign for a moment.","index":433,"end_time":1613.36,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1611.12,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"Should we be implementing those keywords into whatever blog, into whatever website, whatever we''re doing?","index":434,"end_time":1622.08,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1613.68,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"So even though we may be writing a blog about financial and assessments, which they''re not looking for, then maybe we should be adding some of those words they are looking for, for.","index":435,"end_time":1633.88,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1622.64,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"And how do we get those words?","index":436,"end_time":1636.12,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1634.04,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"So how did you come up with those words that people searching for?","index":437,"end_time":1639.84,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1636.68,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"And does Ruby have the power to do that?","index":438,"end_time":1641.84,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1639.84,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"And if so, you know, we should probably get a list of those words that people are searching for relevant to AI for a couple reasons.","index":439,"end_time":1648.84,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1641.84,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"First and foremost, build it into whatever our product line is and our blogs.","index":440,"end_time":1653.24,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1649,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"But the second reason is to understand what people actually looking for.","index":441,"end_time":1657.08,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1653.4,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"Are we even on base?","index":442,"end_time":1658.76,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1657.32,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"Are we even in the same arena?","index":443,"end_time":1661.33,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1659.25,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"You know, you''re telling me they''re not looking for assessments?","index":444,"end_time":1664.45,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1661.49,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"Well then that''s great.","index":445,"end_time":1666.37,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1664.93,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"Then what are they looking for?","index":446,"end_time":1668.09,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1666.45,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"And then maybe we should be offering those products and services that they''re looking for.","index":447,"end_time":1672.05,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1668.09,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"So do we have that intelligence?","index":448,"end_time":1674.29,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1672.45,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"And regardless, we should be in sync with new north as well.","index":449,"end_time":1679.41,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1675.49,"speaker_name":"Michael A Hadley"},{"text":"Yeah, exactly.","index":450,"end_time":1681.65,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1679.73,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"So do we have that intelligence?","index":451,"end_time":1683.81,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1682.21,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":452,"end_time":1685.22,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1684.86,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"So I use just the Google search ads platform itself to find keywords and.","index":453,"end_time":1690.34,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1685.22,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"How many monthly searches they have.","index":454,"end_time":1691.82,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1690.34,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Your team does have access to that.","index":455,"end_time":1693.82,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1692.14,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"That''s through your ad account.","index":456,"end_time":1695.34,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1693.98,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"For the actual organic searches, like for SEO, we use ahrefs, that is a paid tool that we use internally.","index":457,"end_time":1705.26,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1696.62,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"But I can like just export a list of keywords and share that with you.","index":458,"end_time":1708.94,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1705.26,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Okay.","index":459,"end_time":1709.66,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1709.1,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"All right.","index":460,"end_time":1710.3,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1709.9,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":461,"end_time":1710.58,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1710.3,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"So, so Ruby, Mike and I think we should probably have a sidebar about.","index":462,"end_time":1715.58,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1710.58,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"Haha.","index":463,"end_time":1716.22,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1715.66,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"Sidebar.","index":464,"end_time":1716.74,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1716.22,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"You get it.","index":465,"end_time":1717.34,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1716.74,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"You''ve been watching too much Court tv.","index":466,"end_time":1721.18,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1719.1,"speaker_name":"Michael A Hadley"},{"text":"I have been watching too much Court, but I think we should have a side conversation about those analytics and it would be great, at least from my perspective, and leading some of these AI initiatives to truly understand what the people are looking for.","index":467,"end_time":1737.02,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1721.5,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":468,"end_time":1738.42,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1738.18,"speaker_name":"Samuel Bagnall"},{"text":"What the people looking for, absolutely.","index":469,"end_time":1740.9,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1738.42,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":470,"end_time":1741.74,"speaker_id":7,"start_time":1741.38,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"And it''s also important, I think, to understand the difference between the, the paid search keywords that Natalie was mentioning and then the organic search keywords, because they are, they have separate volumes and they have separate use cases for the content and the channel.","index":471,"end_time":1759.86,"speaker_id":7,"start_time":1741.74,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"So the channel being, you know, Google Ads versus LinkedIn, that''s like the channel.","index":472,"end_time":1765.94,"speaker_id":7,"start_time":1760.5,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"And to determine what channel to use, that''s where we''re looking at for the paid search words.","index":473,"end_time":1773.25,"speaker_id":7,"start_time":1766.18,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"What''s going to be the best bang for our buck kind of a thing.","index":474,"end_time":1775.81,"speaker_id":7,"start_time":1773.25,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"But I think it''d be awesome if we can, yeah.","index":475,"end_time":1778.85,"speaker_id":7,"start_time":1776.77,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Have a chat about that and yeah, be great to make sure we''re actually creating a product or a service that people are wanting and searching for because we know AI is top of mind.","index":476,"end_time":1790.93,"speaker_id":7,"start_time":1778.85,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"But I thought we just need to know what, what is top of mind.","index":477,"end_time":1795.1,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1791.49,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"Right.","index":478,"end_time":1795.5,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1795.1,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"So those key searches, things of that nature.","index":479,"end_time":1798.3,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1795.66,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"So yeah.","index":480,"end_time":1799.5,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1798.86,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"Cool, cool, cool, cool.","index":481,"end_time":1801.1,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1799.58,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"I like these ads though.","index":482,"end_time":1803.46,"speaker_id":7,"start_time":1802.46,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"I think they all look nice.","index":483,"end_time":1804.54,"speaker_id":7,"start_time":1803.46,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Yeah, they actually, they very, very good job all around.","index":484,"end_time":1809.1,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1805.82,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"Thanks.","index":485,"end_time":1811.34,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1810.86,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"I''ll let our design team know.","index":486,"end_time":1813.34,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1811.74,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"But for these LinkedIn ads, we''re.","index":487,"end_time":1816.38,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1814.38,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"We''re testing out a few different things.","index":488,"end_time":1818.62,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1816.54,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"At the start and seeing what works.","index":489,"end_time":1820.46,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1818.7,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"There are a couple of ads that.","index":490,"end_time":1822.53,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1821.05,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Are promoting a sales call directly like these ones.","index":491,"end_time":1826.17,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1822.53,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"There are a couple of ads that.","index":492,"end_time":1828.05,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1826.49,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Are prompting people to download the content.","index":493,"end_time":1830.49,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1828.05,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"We''ve seen these work really well for financial services and construction.","index":494,"end_time":1835.61,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1830.65,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"People see these books and want to.","index":495,"end_time":1838.01,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1836.17,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Read more about it.","index":496,"end_time":1838.97,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1838.01,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"And then we also have some that.","index":497,"end_time":1841.49,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1839.13,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Promote the quiz or the scorecard that we came up with, see if we can get engagement that way.","index":498,"end_time":1846.49,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1841.49,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"So.","index":499,"end_time":1846.79,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1846.49,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"So first couple of weeks we''ll just.","index":500,"end_time":1848.18,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1846.94,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Be seeing what works best once we.","index":501,"end_time":1850.06,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1848.18,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Have some data we''ll be able to put more budget into the ones that are working better.","index":502,"end_time":1854.7,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1850.06,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Great.","index":503,"end_time":1861.02,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1860.62,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"And then for the website, so we.","index":504,"end_time":1862.979,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1861.02,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Have a couple of pages developed that.","index":505,"end_time":1866.34,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1862.979,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Will be the key landing pages throughout the campaign.","index":506,"end_time":1868.62,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1866.34,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"So first of all, we have the scorecard and quiz page.","index":507,"end_time":1874.28,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1869.82,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"So this is the interactive tool that we developed where people are able to.","index":508,"end_time":1879.04,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1875.08,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Answer questions and then at the end get a score that tells them what.","index":509,"end_time":1882.92,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1879.04,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Their AI readiness is.","index":510,"end_time":1884.44,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1882.92,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Once they submit this quiz, this information goes into HubSpot.","index":511,"end_time":1889,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1885.24,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"So we capture their name, contact information.","index":512,"end_time":1891.56,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1889,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"As well as what score they received.","index":513,"end_time":1893.88,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1892.12,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"And then this is where I Corps.","index":514,"end_time":1895.6,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1894.2,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Takes over and does follow up.","index":515,"end_time":1897.16,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1895.6,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"And then apart from this, we also.","index":516,"end_time":1902.33,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1900.53,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Have the AI readiness assessment itself.","index":517,"end_time":1904.69,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1902.33,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"So this is what.","index":518,"end_time":1907.09,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1905.97,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"This one also has the interactive quiz.","index":519,"end_time":1909.73,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1907.65,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"That people can use.","index":520,"end_time":1910.69,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1909.73,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"This outlines the full assessment, what''s included, why this matters, the steps of the assessment, and then also the expected outcomes that they receive.","index":521,"end_time":1928.78,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1911.49,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"And this is also an SEO page.","index":522,"end_time":1931.5,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1929.34,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"So we are targeting the keyword AI.","index":523,"end_time":1935.34,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1931.82,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"For business specifically, which it has low difficulty and high search volume per month.","index":524,"end_time":1941.34,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1935.34,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"So once this is published, we do.","index":525,"end_time":1943.22,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1941.74,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Think we can rank pretty highly for this.","index":526,"end_time":1945.26,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1943.22,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"And I believe this page is still.","index":527,"end_time":1950.57,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1948.62,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"In review with your team.","index":528,"end_time":1952.13,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1950.57,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"So then once it''s fully approved, then we can get it published.","index":529,"end_time":1956.37,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1952.93,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Is that.","index":530,"end_time":1961.09,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1960.37,"speaker_name":"Michael A Hadley"},{"text":"Who''s that being reviewed by?","index":531,"end_time":1963.29,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1961.25,"speaker_name":"Michael A Hadley"},{"text":"Internally?","index":532,"end_time":1963.97,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1963.29,"speaker_name":"Michael A Hadley"},{"text":"Myself and Sam have reviewed it, and.","index":533,"end_time":1969.89,"speaker_id":6,"start_time":1967.81,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"I believe it''s with Jeff.","index":534,"end_time":1972.69,"speaker_id":7,"start_time":1969.89,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Let''s get a time today then.","index":535,"end_time":1976.05,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1974.45,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"Oh, this is the website that got missed.","index":536,"end_time":1980.51,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1978.35,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"Yes, that got posted by mistake.","index":537,"end_time":1982.67,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1980.83,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"Okay.","index":538,"end_time":1983.07,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1982.67,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"Correct.","index":539,"end_time":1983.47,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1983.07,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Yeah, Let me.","index":540,"end_time":1985.39,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1984.59,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"Send me over the info.","index":541,"end_time":1986.51,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1985.39,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"I''ll go for it one more time.","index":542,"end_time":1987.87,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1986.51,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"I didn''t.","index":543,"end_time":1988.55,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1988.03,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"Thank you, Sam, for sending the scoring.","index":544,"end_time":1990.23,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1988.55,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"I didn''t remember that.","index":545,"end_time":1991.47,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1990.23,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"And then we also did at the very start, when we were focusing on the Copilot readiness assessment, we built a landing page for that as well.","index":546,"end_time":2002.99,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1995.23,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"So this is also here, something that.","index":547,"end_time":2005.81,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2004.17,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"We can publish once it''s reviewed.","index":548,"end_time":2008.65,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2005.81,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"But this won''t be a page that.","index":549,"end_time":2010.81,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2009.45,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"We''Re directly linking to in our current campaign.","index":550,"end_time":2012.89,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2010.81,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"We''ll instead be focusing on the AI readiness assessment.","index":551,"end_time":2016.41,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2013.05,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"If they download the guide, then where do they go to?","index":552,"end_time":2021.21,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2016.97,"speaker_name":"Michael A Hadley"},{"text":"If they download the guide, there''s a.","index":553,"end_time":2024.41,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2022.73,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Page at the end that takes them to the Contact Us page to book a meeting.","index":554,"end_time":2029.45,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2024.41,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Great.","index":555,"end_time":2038.05,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2037.81,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"And then so we''ll look at the actual tracking that we''re going to be using for this.","index":556,"end_time":2044.13,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2039.25,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"So like we talked about, we''ll use.","index":557,"end_time":2047.69,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2044.21,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"A lead scoring threshold that determines when people move from this awareness stage into.","index":558,"end_time":2053.41,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2047.69,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Engagement, where ultimately the salesperson will take over.","index":559,"end_time":2056.85,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2053.41,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"And so we have a formula of.","index":560,"end_time":2059.45,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2057.89,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Different actions here that contacts can take across these platforms.","index":561,"end_time":2063.17,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2059.45,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"So ultimately, once they reach a score of 10, that''s when we consider them.","index":562,"end_time":2068.13,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2063.81,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Highly engaged and they''re ready for more personalized follow up.","index":563,"end_time":2072.37,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2068.13,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"And then each action that they can take has a different score attached to it.","index":564,"end_time":2077.73,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2072.77,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"So viewing the AI assessment page, for example, is a plus three.","index":565,"end_time":2081.81,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2078.05,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"And then say they also click a LinkedIn ad, then they''re at an eight.","index":566,"end_time":2086.47,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2082.29,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"And then say they also accept Ruby''s.","index":567,"end_time":2088.99,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2086.55,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Connection request, then they''ve reached a 10 and they''re ready for the salesperson to start reaching out.","index":568,"end_time":2094.31,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2088.99,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Some things that have much higher intent, like submitting the contact form on LinkedIn or on the website or downloading the piece of content that talks about the AI solutions, that''s immediately a 10 and the salesperson is ready to follow up.","index":569,"end_time":2112.96,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2096.47,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"And is that the same for if they were to complete the quiz?","index":570,"end_time":2117.12,"speaker_id":7,"start_time":2114,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"If they are, I''m actually not sure.","index":571,"end_time":2123.36,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2119.84,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Okay, what do you think?","index":572,"end_time":2124.8,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2123.76,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Should that be a 10?","index":573,"end_time":2125.68,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2124.8,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"I think so, yeah.","index":574,"end_time":2127.44,"speaker_id":6,"start_time":2125.92,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Because that''s enough.","index":575,"end_time":2129.28,"speaker_id":6,"start_time":2127.52,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"I think that''s a lot of engagement.","index":576,"end_time":2130.96,"speaker_id":7,"start_time":2129.6,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"They''ve gone through, you know, 1, 2, 3, 4 screens.","index":577,"end_time":2134.96,"speaker_id":7,"start_time":2130.96,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"They''ve given us information and they''ve given us their contact info.","index":578,"end_time":2138.89,"speaker_id":7,"start_time":2134.96,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"So I would consider that to be a form fill and a hand raiser, so to speak.","index":579,"end_time":2144.93,"speaker_id":7,"start_time":2138.89,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"And they do have the option at the end of that quiz to book a meeting.","index":580,"end_time":2148.45,"speaker_id":7,"start_time":2145.65,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah.","index":581,"end_time":2151.41,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2149.09,"speaker_name":"Michael A Hadley"},{"text":"So, Ruby, I just sent you an im.","index":582,"end_time":2153.81,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2151.41,"speaker_name":"Michael A Hadley"},{"text":"Okay.","index":583,"end_time":2155.01,"speaker_id":6,"start_time":2154.45,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"We should have Kristen work on those other campaigns as well and maybe some of the ones that you guys have been working on and make sure she has the sales enablement tools for those.","index":584,"end_time":2172.22,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2155.73,"speaker_name":"Michael A Hadley"},{"text":"Yep, definitely.","index":585,"end_time":2173.66,"speaker_id":6,"start_time":2172.78,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"I''m going to meet with her in.","index":586,"end_time":2174.62,"speaker_id":6,"start_time":2173.66,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"A little bit and get her up.","index":587,"end_time":2175.58,"speaker_id":7,"start_time":2174.62,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"To speed on both of the.","index":588,"end_time":2177.66,"speaker_id":6,"start_time":2175.58,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"The other ones that are running.","index":589,"end_time":2179.02,"speaker_id":7,"start_time":2177.66,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"I don''t think we did do the sales enablement for those last two.","index":590,"end_time":2183.9,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2179.66,"speaker_name":"Michael A Hadley"},{"text":"Correct.","index":591,"end_time":2184.86,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2184.3,"speaker_name":"Michael A Hadley"},{"text":"Not as, not as structured as we did for this one.","index":592,"end_time":2189.67,"speaker_id":7,"start_time":2185.98,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"So let''s make sure we do that.","index":593,"end_time":2191.51,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2189.91,"speaker_name":"Michael A Hadley"},{"text":"Okay.","index":594,"end_time":2191.99,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2191.51,"speaker_name":"Michael A Hadley"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":595,"end_time":2192.63,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2192.15,"speaker_name":"Michael A Hadley"},{"text":"All right, thanks.","index":596,"end_time":2194.47,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2193.59,"speaker_name":"Michael A Hadley"},{"text":"Oh, sales enablement.","index":597,"end_time":2202.55,"speaker_id":6,"start_time":2201.19,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Yeah, you read our minds, Mike.","index":598,"end_time":2204.63,"speaker_id":7,"start_time":2202.95,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"We have a whole slide on sales enablement.","index":599,"end_time":2206.79,"speaker_id":7,"start_time":2204.79,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":600,"end_time":2208.63,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2208.15,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"So this is.","index":601,"end_time":2209.51,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2208.79,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"This is an outline of all the.","index":602,"end_time":2211.27,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2209.75,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Sales enablement content that has been created.","index":603,"end_time":2213.91,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2211.27,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"So that once we, we, you know.","index":604,"end_time":2215.66,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2213.91,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Do get people to fill out the form or book a meeting, the sales team is equipped to make the process run smoothly.","index":605,"end_time":2223.18,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2215.66,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"So all these different pieces of content here, they do stuff like handling objections that prospects may have, how to position I Corps, and the assessment, and then also an overview of the full assessment.","index":606,"end_time":2237.58,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2223.74,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Process, what''s included, and what are the outcomes.","index":607,"end_time":2240.06,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2237.58,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"So hopefully for Kirk, your team, this.","index":608,"end_time":2244.59,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2241.51,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Is going to be helpful in making sure that.","index":609,"end_time":2246.55,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2244.59,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Oh, yes.","index":610,"end_time":2248.39,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2247.75,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Oh, yeah.","index":611,"end_time":2249.51,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2248.79,"speaker_name":"Kirk Fackre1"},{"text":"The one thing I think we talked about it, we don''t have it yet.","index":612,"end_time":2253.31,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2249.75,"speaker_name":"Kirk Fackre1"},{"text":"Some kind of.","index":613,"end_time":2253.99,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2253.31,"speaker_name":"Kirk Fackre1"},{"text":"Even if it''s like an excerpt from an actual assessment, a lot of the stuff is internal here.","index":614,"end_time":2261.35,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2254.63,"speaker_name":"Kirk Fackre1"},{"text":"We got the one pager, but we don''t have any kind of sample, I think.","index":615,"end_time":2266.16,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2261.35,"speaker_name":"Kirk Fackre1"},{"text":"Oh, simple assessment.","index":616,"end_time":2267.72,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":2266.16,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"Okay, that''s on me.","index":617,"end_time":2268.56,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":2267.72,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"I''ll get that to you guys.","index":618,"end_time":2269.92,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":2268.64,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"You''ll have that by end of week.","index":619,"end_time":2273.12,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":2271.68,"speaker_name":"Jeffery Lauria"},{"text":"Kind of lower my hand.","index":620,"end_time":2277,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2276.08,"speaker_name":"Kirk Fackre1"},{"text":"Okay, sorry.","index":621,"end_time":2277.92,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2277,"speaker_name":"Kirk Fackre1"},{"text":"Yeah, there we go.","index":622,"end_time":2280.88,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2279.44,"speaker_name":"Kirk Fackre1"},{"text":"Okay, great.","index":623,"end_time":2283.36,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2282.56,"speaker_name":"Michael A Hadley"},{"text":"And again, I would go back, Kirk, and look at what we have for those other campaigns.","index":624,"end_time":2288.32,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2283.68,"speaker_name":"Michael A Hadley"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":625,"end_time":2288.96,"speaker_id":6,"start_time":2288.4,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Great.","index":626,"end_time":2293.37,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2293.13,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"And then looking at the process going forward.","index":627,"end_time":2298.09,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2295.53,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"So I''m going to work on updating.","index":628,"end_time":2300.69,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2298.33,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Those emails and the outreach messaging, send that over to you and then once.","index":629,"end_time":2305.41,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2300.69,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Everything is approved, we''ll get the actual text set up.","index":630,"end_time":2308.29,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2305.41,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"So get the emails loaded in the tools, get the ad set up on LinkedIn and all of that.","index":631,"end_time":2313.13,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2308.29,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"We also go through a warm up period just for the emails that we''re.","index":632,"end_time":2316.57,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2313.37,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Going to be using, just to make.","index":633,"end_time":2318.13,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2316.57,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Sure that they''re delivering well to all of the contacts.","index":634,"end_time":2320.73,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2318.13,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"And then we have a launch day of the 17th, I believe that''s a Monday.","index":635,"end_time":2325.9,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2321.9,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"So start to the week and then ongoing.","index":636,"end_time":2329.26,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2326.22,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Every week our team goes in and.","index":637,"end_time":2330.66,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2329.26,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Looks in at how the campaign is performing.","index":638,"end_time":2332.78,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2330.66,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"We look at stats like our LinkedIn analytics, how many replies are we getting.","index":639,"end_time":2338.18,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2333.02,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"How many email clicks.","index":640,"end_time":2339.42,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2338.18,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"So we do that ongoing to see if there''s anything we should adjust and optimize.","index":641,"end_time":2343.26,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2339.42,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Any questions about the process going forward?","index":642,"end_time":2349.43,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2347.11,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"No, looks good to me.","index":643,"end_time":2353.91,"speaker_id":6,"start_time":2352.63,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Right.","index":644,"end_time":2355.59,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2355.19,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Just need to fix that targeting piece.","index":645,"end_time":2358.31,"speaker_id":6,"start_time":2356.39,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"And those emails and then I think the rest of what you presented, I think looks.","index":646,"end_time":2363.83,"speaker_id":7,"start_time":2358.31,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"We''re all good on that.","index":647,"end_time":2366.95,"speaker_id":6,"start_time":2365.11,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Just a couple of tweaks.","index":648,"end_time":2368.87,"speaker_id":6,"start_time":2367.51,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Okay, so that''s everything for the plan.","index":649,"end_time":2375.6,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2372.56,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Anything else you wanted to discuss or any other questions?","index":650,"end_time":2379.44,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2376.88,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Well, one thing I do have is just going forward, just so we build it in, we never want to go after those two three person firms.","index":651,"end_time":2389.12,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2380.16,"speaker_name":"Michael A Hadley"},{"text":"Okay.","index":652,"end_time":2390.72,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2390.16,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":653,"end_time":2392.6,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2392.16,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Regardless of any product, not an area that we play in.","index":654,"end_time":2395.76,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2392.6,"speaker_name":"Michael A Hadley"},{"text":"Okay.","index":655,"end_time":2397.52,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2396.96,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Understood.","index":656,"end_time":2399.24,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2398.76,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Operated.","index":657,"end_time":2401.08,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2400.36,"speaker_name":"Michael A Hadley"},{"text":"Okay, so I will.","index":658,"end_time":2409.72,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2407.72,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"I''ll send over this plan to you.","index":659,"end_time":2411.36,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2409.72,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Ruby, so you have it.","index":660,"end_time":2413,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2411.36,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"You can also share it with your team and then I''ll work on those emails right away.","index":661,"end_time":2417.56,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2413.08,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Excellent.","index":662,"end_time":2418.84,"speaker_id":7,"start_time":2418.2,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Sounds good.","index":663,"end_time":2421.36,"speaker_id":6,"start_time":2420.68,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"We''ll be on the lookout.","index":664,"end_time":2422.36,"speaker_id":6,"start_time":2421.36,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Thank you so much.","index":665,"end_time":2423.16,"speaker_id":6,"start_time":2422.36,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Good job.","index":666,"end_time":2424.43,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2424.03,"speaker_name":"Michael A Hadley"},{"text":"Thank you.","index":667,"end_time":2426.35,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2425.79,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Thanks everybody.","index":668,"end_time":2427.15,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2426.35,"speaker_name":"Kirk Fackre1"}],"dateString":"2025-11-06T16:30:00.000Z","host_email":"sbagnall@icorps.com","meeting_link":"https://teams.microsoft.com/l/meetup-join/19:meeting_ZTIzN2FhOGQtNWU4NS00MzFhLThjMmQtN2FiNmZiOTBkMWUx@thread.v2/0?context={\"Tid\":\"0188564a-93de-489c-bf54-1927d4a9ed28\",\"Oid\":\"12c1a142-ac12-4942-a3ac-7d7dceb82476\"}","participants":["jlauria@icorps.com,nathalie.mintjens@marketersindemand.com,kfackre@icorps.com,mhadley@icorps.com,rpontbriand@icorps.com,sbagnall@icorps.com","jlauria@icorps.com","nathalie.mintjens@marketersindemand.com","kfackre@icorps.com","mhadley@icorps.com","rpontbriand@icorps.com"],"transcript_url":"https://app.fireflies.ai/view/01K987QV4QAZBQD5CZBC6MB1DT","organizer_email":"nathalie.mintjens@marketersindemand.com"}'::jsonb,
    '{"label":"positive","confidence":0.92,"bullets":["Refocused campaign targeting from micro firms to 20–100 employee legal firms to improve conversion.","Agreed lead scoring assigns 10 points for completing quiz and form fills to trigger sales outreach.","Planned LinkedIn-focused media spend after low commercial search volume for AI assessments on Google.","Sales enablement materials finalized; Jeff to deliver sample assessment excerpt by week’s end.","Campaign launch set for 17th; weekly performance reviews scheduled for optimization."],"highlights":[{"quote":"We never want to go after those two three person firms.","speaker":"Michael A Hadley"},{"quote":"We want to focus on the storytelling of the ROI piece.","speaker":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"quote":"We use a lead scoring model to determine once they become an engaged lead.","speaker":"Nathalie Mintjens"}],"topics":["targeting","delivery","sales","campaign","ads","content"],"model":"openai/gpt-4-1106-preview","version":1,"generated_at":"2025-11-13T00:00:00Z"}'::jsonb,
    '{"fireflies_summary":{"notes":"## **Target Market and Customer Segmentation**\n\nThe team agreed to focus the ABM campaign on **legal services firms with 20 to 100 employees** to maximize business potential and minimize low-value leads (08:50).\n\n- The initial target of firms with **2 to 3 attorneys and small admin teams** was rejected because such small firms often lack IT leadership and rarely generate meaningful business (08:38)\n    - **Michael Hadley** and **Ruby Pontbriand** emphasized that firms under 20 employees tend to generate many leads but little actual business, often becoming costly “C clients” (10:36)\n    - **Kirk Fackre** noted legal firms have reduced admin roles, so targeting firms with around **10 employees** or more better aligns with current structures (12:05)\n    - The group agreed targeting firms with **20 to 100 employees** will reach organizations more likely to invest in AI governance and assessments (11:35)\n    - Marketing and sales teams will revise outreach strategies to reflect this updated firm size focus and explore whether in-house IT teams exist within these firms to tailor targeting (16:13)\n\n- The targeting shift aims to prioritize firms where **I Corps can be the primary IT partner**, rather than competing against established managed IT providers (09:23)\n    - This approach reduces competition and positions the company as a leader in AI readiness in legal tech for SMBs (11:29)\n\n## **ABM Campaign Structure and Engagement Tracking**\n\nThe ABM plan uses a **multi-channel approach** combining brand awareness and targeted outreach to generate qualified leads and enable sales follow-up (17:35).\n\n- The campaign starts with **brand awareness** using three channels: direct emails, direct LinkedIn messages (from Ruby), and paid LinkedIn ads (17:35)\n    - Engagement is tracked through clicks on emails, ads, and LinkedIn responses, feeding into a **lead scoring model** to identify highly engaged leads (18:58)\n    - Once a lead hits a **score of 10**, indicating strong engagement such as form submissions or quiz completions, the lead is passed to sales for personalized follow-up (34:55)\n    - Sales follow-up will also include a new seller who will proactively reach out more aggressively, complementing marketing’s efforts (19:06)\n    - The lead scoring assigns values such as **+3 for page views** and higher scores for direct contact or content downloads, ensuring prioritization of interested prospects (34:05)\n\n- The plan includes ongoing **weekly campaign performance reviews**, analyzing LinkedIn analytics, email clicks, and responses to optimize messaging and budget allocation (39:12)\n    - The initial launch is scheduled for **Monday the 17th**, following an email warm-up period to ensure proper delivery (39:05)\n\n## **Content Strategy and Sales Enablement**\n\nThe campaign is supported by a mix of educational content, interactive tools, and sales enablement assets designed to build credibility and facilitate deal closure (36:48).\n\n- Key content includes an **interactive AI readiness quiz and scorecard** that captures contact info and readiness scores, feeding into lead scoring and follow-up (31:35)\n    - The AI readiness assessment page is optimized for SEO targeting the keyword **“AI for business”**, which has high search volume and low difficulty, to boost organic traffic once published (31:35)\n    - The page is currently under internal review by **Ruby Pontbriand**, **Sam Bagnall**, and **Jeffery Lauria**, with Jeffery expected to finalize approval by the end of the week (32:54)\n\n- Sales enablement materials include **objection handling guides, positioning documents, and assessment overviews** to ensure the sales team can confidently address prospects (36:48)\n    - **Kirk Fackre** requested a sample excerpt from an actual assessment to better equip sales; **Jeffery Lauria** committed to delivering this by week’s end (37:28)\n    - Additional enablement will be developed for other ongoing campaigns to provide consistent support across product lines (35:49)\n\n- Content strategy will also incorporate relevant **blogs and organic LinkedIn posts** aligned with the campaign, focusing on AI governance, compliance, and ROI storytelling to address client concerns (22:20)\n    - Ruby highlighted the importance of differentiating paid ads from organic content to maximize reach and engagement (29:01)\n    - An action was agreed to compile and develop blog ideas surfaced during discussions to support both paid and organic channels (22:55)\n\n## **Paid Media and Keyword Strategy**\n\nLinkedIn is prioritized as the main paid channel for the campaign due to its proven higher engagement rates, while Google search ads are deprioritized because of limited relevant commercial keyword traffic (24:26).\n\n- Keyword research showed **high search volume for general AI and AI for legal services**, but very low search volume for **“AI readiness assessment”** specifically, limiting paid search effectiveness (25:05)\n    - Nathalie Mintjens recommended focusing budget on LinkedIn ads where targeting and engagement are stronger for the niche product (24:26)\n    - Jeffery Lauria raised concerns about aligning product offerings with actual search intent and suggested further analysis to ensure market fit (25:05)\n    - The team agreed to a deeper review of search terms using Google Ads and SEO tools like **Ahrefs**, with Nathalie offering to export keyword lists for internal review (28:04)\n\n- The group recognized the need to integrate high-volume keywords into website content, blogs, and product messaging to better align with customer search behavior and improve organic traffic (27:52)\n    - A sidebar discussion among key team members was proposed to analyze keyword data and refine product-market alignment (28:30)\n\n## **Process Improvements and Next Steps**\n\nClear timelines, responsibilities, and process steps were established to ensure smooth campaign execution and continuous improvement (38:13).\n\n- Nathalie will update outreach emails and targeting to reflect the revised firm size focus and share these with Ruby’s team for review immediately (20:35)\n    - Emails will be loaded into marketing tools and warmed up before the **launch on Monday the 17th** (39:05)\n    - Ongoing weekly monitoring will track performance metrics to refine campaign elements as needed (39:12)\n\n- Ruby will onboard **Kristen** to manage sales enablement tools and ensure alignment with other campaigns (36:12)\n    - This will address previous gaps where sales enablement was less structured (36:25)\n\n- Michael Hadley explicitly confirmed that going forward, the company will **not target firms with fewer than 10 to 20 employees** for any product line, solidifying the strategic focus on SMBs with meaningful IT needs (39:40)\n\n- Jeffery Lauria committed to delivering a **sample assessment excerpt by week’s end** to support sales (37:46)\n- The AI readiness SEO landing page is under final internal review with a goal for prompt publication (32:54)","outline":null,"keywords":["Account-Based Marketing","AI Readiness Assessment","Legal Services","Lead Scoring","LinkedIn Ads","Sales Enablement"],"overview":"- **Focus on Target Market:** ABM campaign targets legal firms with 20 to 100 employees for better engagement.\n\n- **Multi-Channel ABM Approach:** Campaign will use emails, LinkedIn messages, and paid ads for brand awareness and lead generation.\n\n- **Lead Scoring System:** Leads scoring 10 or above will receive personalized follow-up based on engagement metrics.\n\n- **Content and Sales Support:** Educational content and sales materials will enhance credibility and aid in closing deals.\n\n- **Keyword Strategy Emphasis:** Prioritize high-volume keywords in LinkedIn ads; Google search ads are deprioritized due to low relevance.\n\n- **Process and Timeline Clarity:** Weekly monitoring and defined responsibilities will ensure smooth execution and ongoing campaign improvements.","action_items":"\n**Nathalie Mintjens**\nUpdate targeting strategy to focus on firms with 20-100 employees and adjust outreach emails accordingly (15:46)\nShare updated ABM plan and outreach email drafts with Ruby Pontbriand for review (40:07)\nExport and share keyword lists from Google Ads and Ahrefs tools to relevant stakeholders (28:30)\nCoordinate on incorporating AI-related blog and organic LinkedIn content ideas to align with the ABM campaign (24:26)\nManage email domain warm-up ahead of campaign launch (38:13)\n\n**Ruby Pontbriand**\nReview updated ABM plan and outreach emails from Nathalie and provide feedback (40:07)\nMeet with sales enablement lead Kristen to brief her on new and existing campaigns and ensure availability of sales tools (36:12)\n\n**Jeffery Lauria**\nReview and approve the AI readiness assessment SEO landing page currently in internal review (32:54)\nProvide sales team with sample AI readiness assessments by end of week to aid sales enablement (37:46)\n\n**Michael A Hadley**\nSupport Ruby Pontbriand and Kristen in ensuring sales enablement assets are comprehensive and aligned with campaigns (35:49)\n\n**Kirk Fackre**\nReview existing campaign sales enablement materials and identify gaps with marketing team for improvement (38:02)\n"},"migrated_from":"contract_meetings","original_id":"8a24f18b-b468-4963-9948-f444b4d8be0d","master_marketer":{"status":"migrated"}}'::jsonb,
