INSERT INTO compass_notes (contract_id, meeting_id, note_type, title, content_raw, note_date, status, action_items, is_auto_generated)
SELECT
  new_meeting.contract_id,
  new_meeting.meeting_id,
  'meeting',
  'Meeting Notes: New North ABM Presentation - Legal Services/AI Readiness Assessment',
  '## **Target Market and Customer Segmentation**

The team agreed to focus the ABM campaign on **legal services firms with 20 to 100 employees** to maximize business potential and minimize low-value leads (08:50).

- The initial target of firms with **2 to 3 attorneys and small admin teams** was rejected because such small firms often lack IT leadership and rarely generate meaningful business (08:38)
    - **Michael Hadley** and **Ruby Pontbriand** emphasized that firms under 20 employees tend to generate many leads but little actual business, often becoming costly “C clients” (10:36)
    - **Kirk Fackre** noted legal firms have reduced admin roles, so targeting firms with around **10 employees** or more better aligns with current structures (12:05)
    - The group agreed targeting firms with **20 to 100 employees** will reach organizations more likely to invest in AI governance and assessments (11:35)
    - Marketing and sales teams will revise outreach strategies to reflect this updated firm size focus and explore whether in-house IT teams exist within these firms to tailor targeting (16:13)

- The targeting shift aims to prioritize firms where **I Corps can be the primary IT partner**, rather than competing against established managed IT providers (09:23)
    - This approach reduces competition and positions the company as a leader in AI readiness in legal tech for SMBs (11:29)

## **ABM Campaign Structure and Engagement Tracking**

The ABM plan uses a **multi-channel approach** combining brand awareness and targeted outreach to generate qualified leads and enable sales follow-up (17:35).

- The campaign starts with **brand awareness** using three channels: direct emails, direct LinkedIn messages (from Ruby), and paid LinkedIn ads (17:35)
    - Engagement is tracked through clicks on emails, ads, and LinkedIn responses, feeding into a **lead scoring model** to identify highly engaged leads (18:58)
    - Once a lead hits a **score of 10**, indicating strong engagement such as form submissions or quiz completions, the lead is passed to sales for personalized follow-up (34:55)
    - Sales follow-up will also include a new seller who will proactively reach out more aggressively, complementing marketing’s efforts (19:06)
    - The lead scoring assigns values such as **+3 for page views** and higher scores for direct contact or content downloads, ensuring prioritization of interested prospects (34:05)

- The plan includes ongoing **weekly campaign performance reviews**, analyzing LinkedIn analytics, email clicks, and responses to optimize messaging and budget allocation (39:12)
    - The initial launch is scheduled for **Monday the 17th**, following an email warm-up period to ensure proper delivery (39:05)

## **Content Strategy and Sales Enablement**

The campaign is supported by a mix of educational content, interactive tools, and sales enablement assets designed to build credibility and facilitate deal closure (36:48).

- Key content includes an **interactive AI readiness quiz and scorecard** that captures contact info and readiness scores, feeding into lead scoring and follow-up (31:35)
    - The AI readiness assessment page is optimized for SEO targeting the keyword **“AI for business”**, which has high search volume and low difficulty, to boost organic traffic once published (31:35)
    - The page is currently under internal review by **Ruby Pontbriand**, **Sam Bagnall**, and **Jeffery Lauria**, with Jeffery expected to finalize approval by the end of the week (32:54)

- Sales enablement materials include **objection handling guides, positioning documents, and assessment overviews** to ensure the sales team can confidently address prospects (36:48)
    - **Kirk Fackre** requested a sample excerpt from an actual assessment to better equip sales; **Jeffery Lauria** committed to delivering this by week’s end (37:28)
    - Additional enablement will be developed for other ongoing campaigns to provide consistent support across product lines (35:49)

- Content strategy will also incorporate relevant **blogs and organic LinkedIn posts** aligned with the campaign, focusing on AI governance, compliance, and ROI storytelling to address client concerns (22:20)
    - Ruby highlighted the importance of differentiating paid ads from organic content to maximize reach and engagement (29:01)
    - An action was agreed to compile and develop blog ideas surfaced during discussions to support both paid and organic channels (22:55)

## **Paid Media and Keyword Strategy**

LinkedIn is prioritized as the main paid channel for the campaign due to its proven higher engagement rates, while Google search ads are deprioritized because of limited relevant commercial keyword traffic (24:26).

- Keyword research showed **high search volume for general AI and AI for legal services**, but very low search volume for **“AI readiness assessment”** specifically, limiting paid search effectiveness (25:05)
    - Nathalie Mintjens recommended focusing budget on LinkedIn ads where targeting and engagement are stronger for the niche product (24:26)
    - Jeffery Lauria raised concerns about aligning product offerings with actual search intent and suggested further analysis to ensure market fit (25:05)
    - The team agreed to a deeper review of search terms using Google Ads and SEO tools like **Ahrefs**, with Nathalie offering to export keyword lists for internal review (28:04)

- The group recognized the need to integrate high-volume keywords into website content, blogs, and product messaging to better align with customer search behavior and improve organic traffic (27:52)
    - A sidebar discussion among key team members was proposed to analyze keyword data and refine product-market alignment (28:30)

## **Process Improvements and Next Steps**

Clear timelines, responsibilities, and process steps were established to ensure smooth campaign execution and continuous improvement (38:13).

- Nathalie will update outreach emails and targeting to reflect the revised firm size focus and share these with Ruby’s team for review immediately (20:35)
    - Emails will be loaded into marketing tools and warmed up before the **launch on Monday the 17th** (39:05)
    - Ongoing weekly monitoring will track performance metrics to refine campaign elements as needed (39:12)

- Ruby will onboard **Kristen** to manage sales enablement tools and ensure alignment with other campaigns (36:12)
    - This will address previous gaps where sales enablement was less structured (36:25)

- Michael Hadley explicitly confirmed that going forward, the company will **not target firms with fewer than 10 to 20 employees** for any product line, solidifying the strategic focus on SMBs with meaningful IT needs (39:40)

- Jeffery Lauria committed to delivering a **sample assessment excerpt by week’s end** to support sales (37:46)
- The AI readiness SEO landing page is under final internal review with a goal for prompt publication (32:54)',
  '2025-11-06 16:30:00+00',
  'published',
  '[{"text":"Update targeting strategy to focus on firms with 20-100 employees and adjust outreach emails accordingly (15:46)","completed":false},{"text":"Share updated ABM plan and outreach email drafts with Ruby Pontbriand for review (40:07)","completed":false},{"text":"Export and share keyword lists from Google Ads and Ahrefs tools to relevant stakeholders (28:30)","completed":false},{"text":"Coordinate on incorporating AI-related blog and organic LinkedIn content ideas to align with the ABM campaign (24:26)","completed":false},{"text":"Manage email domain warm-up ahead of campaign launch (38:13)","completed":false},{"text":"Review updated ABM plan and outreach emails from Nathalie and provide feedback (40:07)","completed":false},{"text":"Meet with sales enablement lead Kristen to brief her on new and existing campaigns and ensure availability of sales tools (36:12)","completed":false},{"text":"Review and approve the AI readiness assessment SEO landing page currently in internal review (32:54)","completed":false},{"text":"Provide sales team with sample AI readiness assessments by end of week to aid sales enablement (37:46)","completed":false},{"text":"Support Ruby Pontbriand and Kristen in ensuring sales enablement assets are comprehensive and aligned with campaigns (35:49)","completed":false},{"text":"Review existing campaign sales enablement materials and identify gaps with marketing team for improvement (38:02)","completed":false}]'::jsonb,
  true
FROM new_meeting;

-- Meeting: Weekly Marketing Meeting (Shockoe <> New North) (2025-11-06 17:30:00+00)
WITH new_meeting AS (
  INSERT INTO compass_meetings (contract_id, meeting_date, source, external_id, title, participants, duration_seconds, recording_url, transcript, sentiment, raw_metadata, created_at, updated_at)
  VALUES (
    '9e72e3f5-f31f-4c70-870d-79db54b271b2',
    '2025-11-06 17:30:00+00',
    'fireflies',
    '01K8RZDWW43AB8TVAHJX2828NZ',
    'Weekly Marketing Meeting (Shockoe <> New North)',
    '{"Misty Smith","Colin Costigan","Edwin Huertas"}'::text[],
    1899,
    'https://us02web.zoom.us/j/88965765122?pwd=mPL1aFvxXYMYFRYawSa6f5Ez7s5Uv6.1',
    '{"id":"01K8RZDWW43AB8TVAHJX2828NZ","title":"Weekly Marketing Meeting (Shockoe <> New North)","summary":{"notes":"## **Campaign Performance and Budget Reallocation**\n\nThe team decided to concentrate the entire paid media budget on the **Vibe coding campaign** after seeing it drive significantly more engaged website traffic, despite lower form fill rates (07:12).\n\n- The **AI roadmap campaign was turned off** to avoid spreading resources thin and focus outreach on Vibe coding (07:12).\n- Colin highlighted a **large increase in page traffic and a notable drop in bounce rate**, indicating better user engagement (07:12).\n- The shift aims to improve form fills with updated landing page, email copy, and ad messaging emphasizing moving AI prototypes to production (10:23).\n- This reallocation should increase qualified leads by focusing on prospects who have built AI apps and need help launching (10:23).\n\n## **Vibe Coding Campaign Messaging and Landing Page Update**\n\nThe Vibe coding campaign messaging was refined to highlight support for moving AI prototypes from build to launch, aiming to increase conversion by simplifying contact and clarifying offerings (10:23).\n\n- The landing page now focuses on a **simple contact form** instead of a survey, encouraging direct conversation (10:23).\n- Edwin approved a **three-step process** of review, refine, and release for app launch support, aligning expectations (11:39).\n- The messaging clarifies that the **free consultation covers review only**, not a full build-to-launch service, managing scope and client expectations (13:25).\n- Colin suggested a **social post linking Vibe coding to its recognition as Collins Dictionary’s 2025 Word of the Year** to boost brand relevance and engagement (14:04).\n- The updated landing page is ready to go live immediately after final review, aiming for prompt campaign activation (15:39).\n\n## **St. Andrews and Foxwoods Campaign Strategy and Content**\n\nThe campaign for St. Andrews and Foxwoods focuses on storytelling and targeted messaging, with tactical decisions to improve readability and user flow while protecting client relationships (16:07).\n\n- The **600-year legacy language was removed** from St. Andrews content per Kai’s feedback to avoid fuzziness in messaging (16:07).\n- Edwin requested **increased overlay opacity** on hero images to improve text readability on St. Andrews’ landing page (17:05).\n- The pages mix case studies and blogs aimed at guiding visitors to consultation scheduling through multiple call-to-actions, keeping focus on lead capture (18:04).\n- To avoid competitive risks, the team agreed to keep client quotes attributed with full name and title to maintain authority while limiting public access since the page is targeted, not SEO-driven (19:41).\n- Misty suggested replacing generic lifestyle images with more tailored visuals reflecting each client’s environment, especially for St. Andrews’ outdoor, golf-focused feel, enhancing brand alignment (21:34).\n\n## **LinkedIn Lead Gen and Outreach Sequencing**\n\nThe combined St. Andrews and Foxwoods ad will use LinkedIn lead gen forms to reduce friction and improve lead capture effectiveness based on recent success trends (24:26).\n\n- Colin recommended **using LinkedIn lead gen forms** instead of landing pages to lower barriers and speed up form completion (25:21).\n- Edwin agreed with this approach, emphasizing willingness to test new methods while monitoring performance for adjustments (25:57).\n- The email sequence will send both St. Andrews and Foxwoods content to the same contact list, alternating messaging to maximize exposure without segmenting audiences (26:30).\n- Edwin requested access to the contact list for review and management, ensuring proper targeting and list hygiene (27:03).\n\n## **Content Scheduling and Website Asset Coordination**\n\nThe team confirmed blog posts supporting Foxwoods and St. Andrews campaigns will go live just before related social media posts, ensuring content availability for prospects seeking deeper information (08:27, 28:07).\n\n- Misty confirmed blog posts will be scheduled in HubSpot with correct URLs to avoid broken links and maintain user experience (09:39).\n- Colin assured the campaign landing pages are dynamic, with plans for updates every one to two weeks, including adding a resources section as blogs go live (28:52).\n- Misty raised concerns about website content lag potentially deterring informed visitors, but Colin and Edwin agreed the planned timing aligns with campaign rollout and is acceptable (28:07).\n- This sequencing maintains campaign momentum while ensuring content assets support visitor research and engagement (28:52).\n\n## **SBJ Tech Campaign Adaptation and Delivery Timeline**\n\nThe St. Andrews ad creative will be resized to fit SBJ Tech’s ad dimensions, leveraging existing assets to accelerate campaign development (27:53).\n\n- Colin committed to delivering the resized SBJ ad by **early next week**, enabling timely campaign launch (27:54).\n- Edwin expressed satisfaction with the plan, confirming alignment on creative adaptation (27:53).\n- This reuse of assets promises faster deployment and cost efficiency for the SBJ Tech campaign (27:54).","outline":null,"keywords":["Vibe coding","campaign performance","landing page","St. Andrews","Foxwoods","LinkedIn lead gen"],"overview":"- **Budget Shift:** Entire paid media budget now focused on Vibe coding campaign for better engagement and lead quality.  \n- **Updated Messaging:** Vibe campaign messaging emphasizes AI support, simplifying contact to increase conversions.  \n- **St. Andrews Content:** Removed legacy language and enhanced readability for better user experience and storytelling.  \n- **LinkedIn Strategy:** Using LinkedIn lead gen forms for St. Andrews and Foxwoods to improve lead capture efficiency.  \n- **Content Coordination:** Blog posts scheduled to align with social media updates, ensuring valuable resources for prospects.  \n- **SBJ Campaign Timeline:** Resized St. Andrews ad to be delivered early next week, enhancing campaign speed and cost efficiency.","action_items":"\n**Colin Costigan**\nSend updated campaign pages, email copy, and ad creative documents for review to Misty and Edwin (30:28)\nShare contact list for campaign enrollment with Edwin for vetting (30:28)\nLaunch updated Vibe coding landing page upon approval (15:50)\nAdapt and deliver resized SBJ Tech ad creative early next week (27:54)\nExecute blog post scheduling in HubSpot following the approved timeline and URLs (09:20)\n\n**Misty Smith**\nReview updated campaign pages, email copy, and ad creative documents after Colin sends (30:21)\nSchedule blogs in HubSpot per agreed timeline and ensure correct URLs are used (09:10)\nDecide on footer image replacement for St. Andrews and Foxwoods pages, potentially selecting from previously uploaded images in HubSpot or WordPress (21:45)\n\n**Edwin Huertas**\nApprove Vibe coding landing page updates and suggest future tweaks where necessary (15:55)\nReview and vet contact lists for the campaigns to ensure proper targeting (30:40)\nMonitor campaign performance, particularly the effectiveness of lead gen forms on LinkedIn vs. landing page conversions (26:15)\nRequest addition to campaign mailing list to receive and monitor emails sent (27:05)\n"},"duration":31.649999618530273,"speakers":[{"id":0,"name":"Misty Smith"},{"id":1,"name":"Colin Costigan"},{"id":2,"name":"Edwin Huertas"}],"sentences":[{"text":"Hello?","index":0,"end_time":277.62,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":277.22,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"Hi, Misty.","index":1,"end_time":279.18,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":278.5,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"How''s it going?","index":2,"end_time":279.78,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":279.18,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I''m all right.","index":3,"end_time":281.14,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":280.42,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"How are you doing?","index":4,"end_time":282.42,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":281.14,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"All right.","index":5,"end_time":282.9,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":282.42,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Excellent.","index":6,"end_time":284.42,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":283.62,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"That is excellent.","index":7,"end_time":285.94,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":284.82,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"Hopefully we get Kai and Edwin on the call.","index":8,"end_time":291.7,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":287.06,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"I don''t know.","index":9,"end_time":292.42,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":291.7,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"Yeah, I saw.","index":10,"end_time":293.86,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":293.14,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Kai declined it, actually, but I saw.","index":11,"end_time":295.54,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":293.86,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, so we''ll give them a minute, and then otherwise, I''ll just take some good notes and have you recap things in Slack so that we''re good to go.","index":12,"end_time":306.74,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":296.58,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"Yeah, sounds like a plan.","index":13,"end_time":309.42,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":306.98,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"How''s your week been so far?","index":14,"end_time":312.14,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":310.86,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It''s been crazy.","index":15,"end_time":314.86,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":312.94,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"It''s just been very busy, but otherwise good.","index":16,"end_time":318.54,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":314.94,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"How was your Halloween?","index":17,"end_time":319.58,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":318.54,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"It was good.","index":18,"end_time":321.18,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":320.46,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"My daughter''s too young to go trick or treating, but we put her in her costume and stuff and just kind of played around with her.","index":19,"end_time":329.26,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":322.54,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Then she went to bed.","index":20,"end_time":330.38,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":329.34,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Hold on.","index":21,"end_time":334.95,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":334.55,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"Hello?","index":22,"end_time":339.27,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":338.79,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"Hey, Evan.","index":23,"end_time":340.63,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":339.75,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Hello.","index":24,"end_time":342.07,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":341.59,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"Can you hear us?","index":25,"end_time":343.71,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":343.03,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Misty?","index":26,"end_time":344.23,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":343.71,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Hello?","index":27,"end_time":346.07,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":345.59,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"I don''t think she can hear.","index":28,"end_time":348.63,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":347.43,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"Oh, wait, I''m having trouble.","index":29,"end_time":353.11,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":348.71,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"Can you guys hear me?","index":30,"end_time":356.79,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":355.67,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"We can hear you.","index":31,"end_time":357.91,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":357.11,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Can you hear us?","index":32,"end_time":358.55,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":357.91,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right.","index":33,"end_time":366.64,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":366.24,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"My Internet caught back up, I think.","index":34,"end_time":369.12,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":367.36,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"Can you hear us now?","index":35,"end_time":371.2,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":370.24,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yes, I can hear you now.","index":36,"end_time":372.8,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":371.36,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"I don''t know what.","index":37,"end_time":373.72,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":373.04,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"I turned off my video thinking maybe that''s gonna help.","index":38,"end_time":377.2,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":373.72,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"Sorry.","index":39,"end_time":378.32,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":377.76,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"No problem at all.","index":40,"end_time":380.24,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":378.88,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But, yeah.","index":41,"end_time":381.32,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":380.48,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"So you''re saying she was too young, but you put her in a costume?","index":42,"end_time":383.92,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":381.32,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"That''s what I caught.","index":43,"end_time":385.6,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":384.8,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":44,"end_time":385.96,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":385.6,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"Yeah, pretty much.","index":45,"end_time":386.76,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":385.96,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Just.","index":46,"end_time":387.12,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":386.76,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Just let her play around in her little pumpkin costume.","index":47,"end_time":389.84,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":387.68,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"There you go.","index":48,"end_time":390.96,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":390.16,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"I mean, that''s awfully cute.","index":49,"end_time":392.64,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":390.96,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"Yeah, it was.","index":50,"end_time":393.84,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":392.88,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It''s.","index":51,"end_time":395.52,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":395.04,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"It''s.","index":52,"end_time":396,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":395.52,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"It''s not going to matter.","index":53,"end_time":396.8,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":396,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"My kids like to tell me they didn''t have consciousness before the age of 12.","index":54,"end_time":400.4,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":396.8,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"Like, they don''t really remember anything other than, like, through stories we''ve told them.","index":55,"end_time":405.52,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":400.72,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"So if that makes you feel better.","index":56,"end_time":407.6,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":405.52,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":57,"end_time":408.8,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":408.32,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":58,"end_time":410.36,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":409.76,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":59,"end_time":410.76,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":410.36,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"Well, now that we have Edwin here, let''s get started.","index":60,"end_time":412.88,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":410.76,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"Let''s do it.","index":61,"end_time":414.16,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":413.44,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Edwin, great to see you.","index":62,"end_time":415.76,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":414.64,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And bless you on the sneeze.","index":63,"end_time":417.84,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":415.76,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yes.","index":64,"end_time":418.72,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":418.24,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"All right.","index":65,"end_time":421.04,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":420.48,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"A lot of things to go through today.","index":66,"end_time":422.88,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":421.04,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So I want to go through, you know, campaign performance and website updates, and then updates to the Vibe coding campaign, and then the new campaign tweaks based on what I presented last week to the St. Andrews and Foxwoods campaign, an update on what we''re doing for the SBJ ad, and then, as always, our action items.","index":67,"end_time":442.32,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":423.04,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So, as we reviewed last week, the Vibe coding campaign was far more successful as far as driving engaged website traffic, but not form fills.","index":68,"end_time":450.71,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":444.35,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we have turned the AI roadmap campaign off so that we can dedicate budget to the Vibe coding campaign and have all of the emails and LinkedIn messages focused on that campaign, so we''re not spreading as thin.","index":69,"end_time":463.39,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":450.71,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We did see a large uptick in traffic to the page as well as a large drop in bounce rate, which is great metrics to see as far as people engaging.","index":70,"end_time":472.43,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":463.87,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And so what I''m hoping for is that the changes that I''ll present today of the landing page and the email copy and messages and ads resonate a little bit better to drive actual form fills.","index":71,"end_time":483.69,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":472.83,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"As a part of that, we''ll also be moving, like I said, all of the paid media budget towards the vibe coding campaign.","index":72,"end_time":491.21,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":485.05,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then on the website side of things, in a more of a general sense, the case studies are live.","index":73,"end_time":497.45,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":492.09,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then, Misty, I did want to confirm this with you because in your message, these are the dates that you had typed out, but the screenshot had different dates.","index":74,"end_time":505.87,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":497.45,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I was trying to pick the Monday or Thursday launch date prior to sending out the social media post.","index":75,"end_time":517.71,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":507.23,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"That''s why these dates should hopefully all be just before those things go live.","index":76,"end_time":525.31,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":518.11,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"Gotcha.","index":77,"end_time":526.67,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":525.95,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Is that making sense?","index":78,"end_time":528.27,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":527.07,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":79,"end_time":528.96,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":528.76,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So these ones that you sent where you said we need to push the.","index":80,"end_time":532.16,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":528.96,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then you listed these blogs and their dates.","index":81,"end_time":533.92,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":532.16,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So that''s what I have in here.","index":82,"end_time":535,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":533.92,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Uh huh.","index":83,"end_time":536.04,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":535.32,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"Yes.","index":84,"end_time":536.52,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":536.04,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":85,"end_time":536.96,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":536.52,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Like I said, I sent.","index":86,"end_time":538.04,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":536.96,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"Yeah, because the, because the, the dates.","index":87,"end_time":541.08,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":538.2,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"So the 11th, the 13th, the 11th, the 10th.","index":88,"end_time":546.24,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":542.12,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"Let''s see, the 10th, the 13th, and the 20th.","index":89,"end_time":548.68,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":546.24,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"Yes, because those posts are going live on the 12th, the 14th, and the 21st.","index":90,"end_time":554.84,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":548.84,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"Okay, so that, yes, that, that should work just fine.","index":91,"end_time":559.02,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":555.38,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"Like we''ll get them out and then make sure they''re there the next day.","index":92,"end_time":561.78,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":559.02,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"I''m assuming I can use the URL that we typed in manually on when I created the blog post.","index":93,"end_time":567.9,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":561.94,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"Like at the top, I can just do choco.com and then whatever that the verbiage is there so I can get these scheduled.","index":94,"end_time":575.02,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":567.9,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"Is that correct?","index":95,"end_time":575.62,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":575.02,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"Is that how the, Is that how the pages go?","index":96,"end_time":578.66,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":575.62,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":97,"end_time":579.7,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":579.38,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So when you''re, when you build and publish the page in the staging environment, it''ll be the same URL, except you just take out the shock.","index":98,"end_time":585.38,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":579.7,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Like the staging.","index":99,"end_time":586.34,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":585.46,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"The staging thing.","index":100,"end_time":587.49,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":586.73,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"Okay, perfect.","index":101,"end_time":588.13,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":587.49,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"So I just use that.","index":102,"end_time":588.93,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":588.13,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"Okay, perfect.","index":103,"end_time":589.61,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":588.93,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"I just wanted to make sure I, I had that right.","index":104,"end_time":592.81,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":589.61,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"The last thing I want to do is schedule it in advance and then have the wrong URL and then forget to change it.","index":105,"end_time":600.05,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":593.77,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"So as long as that''s.","index":106,"end_time":601.13,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":600.05,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"That is correct, then yes, I''ve copied those over and, and have that all ready to go.","index":107,"end_time":606.65,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":601.29,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"So I will get those all scheduled in HubSpot for all of this because.","index":108,"end_time":613.87,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":606.65,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"Well, at least the first four, because we have all of the assets we need to get those scheduled.","index":109,"end_time":619.79,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":613.87,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"Perfect.","index":110,"end_time":621.47,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":620.99,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":111,"end_time":622.23,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":621.79,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Fantastic.","index":112,"end_time":622.91,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":622.23,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"All right, diving in a little bit further to the Vibe coding campaign.","index":113,"end_time":626.15,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":623.39,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Last week we talked about switching the orientation of this to a, hey, you''ve built something, but now we need to actually get it live.","index":114,"end_time":632.43,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":626.15,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And so I have an updated landing page where we''re taking your Vibe coding from prototype to production is really the push and then simplifying the form instead of a survey, just like really trying to push them towards a conversation.","index":115,"end_time":647.18,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":633.31,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So it''s actually just a simplified contact form collecting their information and then saying like, we''ll reach out to you to schedule a sync.","index":116,"end_time":654.1,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":647.18,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Went with again, a lot of the language around.","index":117,"end_time":658.82,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":655.62,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Like, you''ve built it really fast because you use Vibe coding and AI, but you need to launch it right.","index":118,"end_time":663.86,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":658.82,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And not like a true scare tactic, but more of these are all of the things that you need to have in mind when actually pushing an app live.","index":119,"end_time":673.48,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":664.58,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So I went through a review, refine, and release process.","index":120,"end_time":679.72,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":677,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"This is one thing I definitely want to check with you guys to see if I''m speaking to this accurately.","index":121,"end_time":683.4,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":679.72,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So, Edwin, if we''re in the situation where someone fills this form out, they''re like, hey, I''ve built an app through Vibe coding.","index":122,"end_time":690.68,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":684.68,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"What would be the process to work with you guys to get this live?","index":123,"end_time":693.64,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":690.84,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I thought a pretty simple three step was we''ll review it, we''re or refine, and then we''ll release.","index":124,"end_time":698.47,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":693.96,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That looks good.","index":125,"end_time":699.95,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":699.27,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"Yes.","index":126,"end_time":700.39,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":699.95,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"Fantastic.","index":127,"end_time":701.67,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":700.87,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then just a simple what you''ll get.","index":128,"end_time":704.39,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":702.31,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I''ll have the team go through and I just was really pushing for the design.","index":129,"end_time":707.43,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":704.39,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I''ll have them space some things out a little differently, but, you know, you''ll get the production ready.","index":130,"end_time":712.43,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":707.43,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"App beautiful, secure user tested, your roadmap for updates, scalability, and future features.","index":131,"end_time":718.67,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":712.43,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then a trusted team that''s taken AI prototypes to market across industries.","index":132,"end_time":722.63,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":718.67,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Fantastic.","index":133,"end_time":727.96,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":727.24,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And as part of that, we''ve also updated the ads.","index":134,"end_time":730.84,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":728.44,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So, ready to launch your AI generated app, Bridge the gap between prototype and production and AI built it will make it real.","index":135,"end_time":743.56,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":731.56,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":136,"end_time":748.2,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":747.56,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":137,"end_time":750.79,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":750.39,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Misty, was there something you wanted to add there?","index":138,"end_time":752.63,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":751.03,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Nope, I think that''s fine.","index":139,"end_time":757.59,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":753.11,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":140,"end_time":758.47,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":757.91,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then we''ve updated the email and LinkedIn messages as well.","index":141,"end_time":761.43,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":758.71,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Again, still going for that same sentiment of you''ve built something with AI, let''s get that live.","index":142,"end_time":766.47,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":761.91,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"AI tools only help with the beginning of the process, but you actually need to follow the rules to get this thing live in the right way before you launch that AI app.","index":143,"end_time":778.99,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":767.67,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We help AI prototypes go live fast.","index":144,"end_time":781.23,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":779.07,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then for the last one, I Had kind of that.","index":145,"end_time":785.39,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":782.75,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You know, we normally do this at a $15,000 engagement, but we''re.","index":146,"end_time":789.07,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":786.03,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We''re doing this for free this quarter.","index":147,"end_time":790.67,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":789.07,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then, Edwin, as always, the LinkedIn messages, less salesy and more conversational.","index":148,"end_time":800.03,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":795.55,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"What was the one before this?","index":149,"end_time":806.2,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":805.04,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"About three this quarter.","index":150,"end_time":807.52,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":806.2,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"Just curious.","index":151,"end_time":809.04,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":808.32,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":152,"end_time":809.96,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":809.52,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So when we had originally written the Vibe coding and the AI roadmap, it was about positioning that.","index":153,"end_time":814.88,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":809.96,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"This is typically something you guys charge for, but it''s like a free consultation.","index":154,"end_time":819.6,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":815.76,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":155,"end_time":821.04,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":820.72,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"Like a free consultation.","index":156,"end_time":822.4,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":821.04,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"Okay.","index":157,"end_time":823.36,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":822.72,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"So we''re not necessarily promising to do the whole thing.","index":158,"end_time":828.97,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":826.49,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"We''re just going to do the review.","index":159,"end_time":830.81,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":828.97,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"Part of this, Correct?","index":160,"end_time":832.09,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":830.89,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, I wanted to call that out specifically, like, Vibe coding review.","index":161,"end_time":835.45,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":832.09,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, perfect.","index":162,"end_time":836.69,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":835.85,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"I just want to make sure we''re not saying, hey, we don''t care how messy your stuff is, we''ll get it from where it is to launch for free.","index":163,"end_time":844.41,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":836.69,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"Yeah, absolutely.","index":164,"end_time":846.57,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":844.81,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I hear you there.","index":165,"end_time":848.09,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":847.29,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Then, one thing.","index":166,"end_time":849.61,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":848.89,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Our team actually saw that in Collins Dictionary, which is interesting.","index":167,"end_time":856.31,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":850.49,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I didn''t know that was a dictionary, but Vibe coding was actually the 2025 word of the year, so I thought maybe we could have a cool social post or something to go along with that as well.","index":168,"end_time":866.39,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":856.31,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"What do you.","index":169,"end_time":871.67,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":871.03,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"What do you recommend a saying around that, like, I guess just, hey, did you know this is the word of the year?","index":170,"end_time":882.05,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":871.67,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":171,"end_time":882.85,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":882.53,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I mean, I think it could be, like, just a nice, catchy graphic maybe that, like, highlights, you know, that in Collins dictionary and then points them to the new Vibe coding page.","index":172,"end_time":893.33,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":882.85,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Like a social post.","index":173,"end_time":894.85,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":893.89,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"The rest of the content would be like, have you been testing with Vibe coding?","index":174,"end_time":900.41,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":895.01,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Or something along those lines?","index":175,"end_time":901.65,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":900.41,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Or have you been building an app with Vibe coding and are looking to get it live in the market?","index":176,"end_time":906.05,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":901.65,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So it kind of connects the campaign to the 2025 Word of the year.","index":177,"end_time":909.65,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":906.13,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":178,"end_time":911.97,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":911.57,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"So you would say, obviously, we want to send them to where.","index":179,"end_time":915.41,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":911.97,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"Where.","index":180,"end_time":915.81,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":915.41,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"What''s the call to action?","index":181,"end_time":916.97,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":915.89,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"Like, where would we send them to.","index":182,"end_time":918.45,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":916.97,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"The Vibe coding landing page that I''m showing here, the one that we just updated.","index":183,"end_time":922.29,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":919.01,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":184,"end_time":923.57,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":923.01,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"And.","index":185,"end_time":927.65,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":927.25,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"Okay.","index":186,"end_time":928.61,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":927.97,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"And we have that already in on the site.","index":187,"end_time":931.41,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":928.85,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"This is.","index":188,"end_time":932.69,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":931.97,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"This is just on the staging site.","index":189,"end_time":934.53,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":933.09,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"The one that''s on the current site is the.","index":190,"end_time":936.09,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":934.53,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"The older version of the page.","index":191,"end_time":937.49,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":936.09,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":192,"end_time":938.34,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":938.06,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"And so when do we plan to.","index":193,"end_time":939.54,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":938.34,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"Update this so this.","index":194,"end_time":942.46,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":939.54,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"This can go live today.","index":195,"end_time":943.9,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":942.54,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But I also wanted to give you guys a chance to review the changes before we push it live.","index":196,"end_time":948.3,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":944.3,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Do you, Edwin, have any feedback or comments, or are you good with launching this?","index":197,"end_time":954.54,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":950.14,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"I think we''re good with launching this.","index":198,"end_time":957.34,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":955.98,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"I''m not.","index":199,"end_time":957.82,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":957.34,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"Not.","index":200,"end_time":958.22,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":957.82,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"I mean, we need to Try something.","index":201,"end_time":959.98,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":958.62,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"My hope is that we can continue tweaking it.","index":202,"end_time":962.38,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":960.38,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":203,"end_time":963.1,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":962.62,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":204,"end_time":964.45,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":964.13,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":205,"end_time":968.29,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":967.73,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right.","index":206,"end_time":969.73,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":969.17,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Getting into St. Andrews and Foxwood''s campaign.","index":207,"end_time":973.57,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":970.45,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So last week we talked about.","index":208,"end_time":974.77,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":973.57,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And Edwin, I know this is your favorite picture.","index":209,"end_time":976.85,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":975.17,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I had to leave it in there for you.","index":210,"end_time":978.13,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":976.85,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But we removed the like 600 year legacy.","index":211,"end_time":983.09,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":980.61,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Kai had commented that that was kind of our.","index":212,"end_time":987.17,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":983.33,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I don''t know what the right word is for it, but she said that St. Andrews fuzzy.","index":213,"end_time":991.33,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":987.49,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":214,"end_time":991.73,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":991.33,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we removed that type of language from the page.","index":215,"end_time":995.94,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":993.38,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I do want to check because we went with a slightly different design.","index":216,"end_time":1000.14,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":996.82,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"More of like a hero banner section.","index":217,"end_time":1002.1,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1000.14,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I think that this turned out to look pretty nice.","index":218,"end_time":1004.9,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1002.82,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But if you would like, we can switch back to like the.","index":219,"end_time":1007.38,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1004.9,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"The vibe coding style where it''s top section and then banner.","index":220,"end_time":1010.98,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1007.54,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I think these are working better.","index":221,"end_time":1014.42,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1012.98,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"The only.","index":222,"end_time":1015.3,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1014.74,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"The only feedback from me is the.","index":223,"end_time":1017.3,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1015.38,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"The content, the text.","index":224,"end_time":1019.14,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1017.38,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"It''s hard to read at least from.","index":225,"end_time":1021.08,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1019.56,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"From here.","index":226,"end_time":1021.56,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1021.08,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"I''m not.","index":227,"end_time":1021.92,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1021.56,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"I''m not sure if we''re seeing it.","index":228,"end_time":1023.16,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1021.92,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"Full screen might look better, but that''s the only thing.","index":229,"end_time":1025.6,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1023.16,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah.","index":230,"end_time":1026.44,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1025.6,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We can add more opacity.","index":231,"end_time":1027.48,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1026.44,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We have like a black.","index":232,"end_time":1028.6,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1027.64,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I think it''s at like 33% opacity.","index":233,"end_time":1031.32,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1029.48,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we can increase that for the overlay.","index":234,"end_time":1035.08,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1031.32,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then just diving into like really what the experiences.","index":235,"end_time":1041.56,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1038.84,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"What the experience was with building St. Andrews app, like the journey that why they came to Shako, why what you''re able to do with them and then what it was able to turn into.","index":236,"end_time":1050.639,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1041.64,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then I got this content on the approach from the case studies and other blog content as well.","index":237,"end_time":1057.839,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1052.159,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So I wanted to check this with you guys again.","index":238,"end_time":1060.639,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1058.959,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You don''t have to read it all right now I''ll be sending you review links to take a look at everything so you can read it more in depth.","index":239,"end_time":1065.759,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1060.639,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But that was the approach that we took.","index":240,"end_time":1067.359,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1065.759,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Do these linked out to the case studies or.","index":241,"end_time":1070.999,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1067.839,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"No, I''m just curious.","index":242,"end_time":1072.399,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1070.999,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"Not currently, but we can set that up.","index":243,"end_time":1074.32,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1072.8,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I don''t know if.","index":244,"end_time":1075.4,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1074.72,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"Do we want to, Edwin, or do we want them to rather.","index":245,"end_time":1078.28,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1075.4,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"We''d rather them go to like scheduling the consultation.","index":246,"end_time":1081.52,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1078.28,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"Like do we want to keep them fixed on this page?","index":247,"end_time":1083.76,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1081.52,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"Yeah, I think that''s one of the questions I have for you, Colleen.","index":248,"end_time":1087.44,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1084.96,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"So we''re creating this page, right.","index":249,"end_time":1088.84,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1087.44,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"It''s a new page that contains a mix of both blog posts and case study.","index":250,"end_time":1093.84,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1088.84,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"Ideally.","index":251,"end_time":1095.36,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1094.72,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"And I understand the reasoning behind a landing page, we don''t want people to do anything else other than click on the call to action.","index":252,"end_time":1101.99,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1095.36,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"We want them which is contacting us.","index":253,"end_time":1103.71,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1101.99,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"Right?","index":254,"end_time":1104.11,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1103.71,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":255,"end_time":1104.63,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1104.27,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We want to Guide them there as much as possible.","index":256,"end_time":1106.35,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1104.63,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That''s why I have multiple CTAs baked throughout here as well.","index":257,"end_time":1109.23,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1106.35,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"What we can do, though, is if someone is actually scrolling all the way to the bottom, I mean, we can have like a additional resources section that would point to the case study in the blogs.","index":258,"end_time":1122.59,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1109.55,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, I''m.","index":259,"end_time":1123.87,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1122.99,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"That''s okay.","index":260,"end_time":1127.83,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1127.39,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"I think it''s more of a. Yeah, if that''s the case.","index":261,"end_time":1129.71,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1127.83,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"And we''ll just make sure that we have the code to actions to do that, not to other pages.","index":262,"end_time":1133.95,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1129.71,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"Okay.","index":263,"end_time":1134.99,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1134.35,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"What do you think, Misty or calling.","index":264,"end_time":1139.23,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1137.31,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"I was yesterday looking for more quotes from clients, and the one that we have is there.","index":265,"end_time":1148.43,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1139.47,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"Down there is Tom''s quote.","index":266,"end_time":1150.99,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1148.43,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"And this is me being a little bit concerned or worried that if another company comes in play and say, hey, I know who I know now.","index":267,"end_time":1162.03,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1153.23,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"I know who I need to contact to, you know, bypass Jacobs and probably get a new contract with Tom or St. Andrews.","index":268,"end_time":1172.51,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1162.03,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"Should we just include head of digital instead of in remote Tom?","index":269,"end_time":1177.71,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1173.55,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"Ad hoc.","index":270,"end_time":1178.8,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1178.36,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"Ad hoc.","index":271,"end_time":1179.4,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1178.8,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"So you''re saying maybe like a competitor would land here and try to go after.","index":272,"end_time":1186.04,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1181.64,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":273,"end_time":1187,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1186.52,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"So what I will say is it is a very, like.","index":274,"end_time":1189.16,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1187.16,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It''ll be a targeted list that we''re sending this landing page to.","index":275,"end_time":1192.28,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1189.16,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It''s not going to, like, rank in Google SEO because we want to limit the environment of who''s going there.","index":276,"end_time":1200.36,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1193.16,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Also, a quote with an actual, like, person''s name and their title and job just carries more authority.","index":277,"end_time":1206.92,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1200.92,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I would prefer not to go the route of like, you know, the.","index":278,"end_time":1212.4,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1209.76,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Like the Coca Cola.","index":279,"end_time":1213.44,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1212.4,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Can''t name Coca Cola, so we say bottling plant type thing.","index":280,"end_time":1216.32,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1213.68,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":281,"end_time":1218.72,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1218.16,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"All right.","index":282,"end_time":1220.24,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1219.76,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"That was.","index":283,"end_time":1220.88,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1220.4,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"That was my only concern on that one.","index":284,"end_time":1222.48,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1220.88,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":285,"end_time":1223.12,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1222.64,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then these we pulled from the metrics.","index":286,"end_time":1226.56,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1224.08,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And we also have the Foxwood here.","index":287,"end_time":1234.17,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1226.72,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So from fragmented to a unified app.","index":288,"end_time":1238.25,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1235.77,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Again, kind of telling the story of the approach from the blogs and case study content to anything but ordinary.","index":289,"end_time":1245.85,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1240.65,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then looped in the results, Misty.","index":290,"end_time":1249.37,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1246.33,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That you had shared from Christina, I believe was her name.","index":291,"end_time":1252.25,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1249.37,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yes.","index":292,"end_time":1255.05,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1254.65,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"Can you scroll back up again?","index":293,"end_time":1256.09,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1255.05,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"I''m sorry, I just want to make sure we''re so.","index":294,"end_time":1258.98,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1256.09,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"Same thing.","index":295,"end_time":1259.38,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1258.98,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"You''re looking at the.","index":296,"end_time":1260.66,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1259.38,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"Those are from the three blogs.","index":297,"end_time":1266.02,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1264.34,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"And then you said you have some results.","index":298,"end_time":1267.78,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1266.1,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"Information down below.","index":299,"end_time":1269.22,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1268.02,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"Yes.","index":300,"end_time":1270.1,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1269.62,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":301,"end_time":1270.98,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1270.42,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"And then that''s it.","index":302,"end_time":1271.86,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1271.06,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"Is that all that''s on the page?","index":303,"end_time":1273.02,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1271.86,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"I mean, other than.","index":304,"end_time":1273.94,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1273.02,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":305,"end_time":1274.5,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1274.18,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then the form that we''re pushing them to.","index":306,"end_time":1276.18,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1274.5,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":307,"end_time":1277.54,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1277.06,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"I mean, is that image, by the way, the one that goes with the footer across all the.","index":308,"end_time":1281.86,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1277.78,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"All the proposals, everything.","index":309,"end_time":1284.46,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1281.86,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"I''m just this image we just have on the Foxwoods and St. Andrews page that we just developed.","index":310,"end_time":1289.42,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1284.86,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Mm.","index":311,"end_time":1290.22,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1289.66,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"This is the one that goes across the pages.","index":312,"end_time":1294.06,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1291.18,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":313,"end_time":1294.98,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1294.62,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"I''m just wondering if we should do something that''s more tailored to Foxwoods and St. Andrews in that spot.","index":314,"end_time":1301.02,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1294.98,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"This one right here?","index":315,"end_time":1302.3,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1301.42,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"No, the.","index":316,"end_time":1303.62,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1302.86,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"The one that''s just generic looking from the ground up at all the people with their phones.","index":317,"end_time":1307.42,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1303.62,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"I mean, is this.","index":318,"end_time":1311.55,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1310.07,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"Was this just because, hey, we need a placeholder or was there.","index":319,"end_time":1314.43,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1311.55,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"Is there a specific, like, feeling you''re trying to drive with this particular image?","index":320,"end_time":1322.47,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1314.43,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"Yeah, I mean, the feeling was just people enjoying, like, using an app.","index":321,"end_time":1325.59,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1322.79,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"More of, like a lifestyle type photo.","index":322,"end_time":1328.39,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1326.55,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But we can look for something else if you''d like, if you want to replace this.","index":323,"end_time":1332.07,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1328.71,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, I just, like, when I.","index":324,"end_time":1335.71,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1334.55,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"When I see this one on Foxwoods, I like, it''s not as big of a deal because it''s very like, who.","index":325,"end_time":1341.1,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1335.71,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"Like that party.","index":326,"end_time":1342.54,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1341.5,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"Ish.","index":327,"end_time":1342.9,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1342.54,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"But you know what I mean?","index":328,"end_time":1343.62,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1342.9,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"Like, it''s that feeling.","index":329,"end_time":1344.58,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1343.62,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"But like, on St. Andrews, everything else is very, like, outdoor, open, green, you know, golf coursey feel.","index":330,"end_time":1352.14,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1344.58,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"And this, when you.","index":331,"end_time":1353.18,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1352.22,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"When you get to this picture on that page, it just sticks out.","index":332,"end_time":1357.26,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1353.18,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"And so I was like, you know, I can see maybe on Foxwoods, this one being okay, but not so much for the St. Andrews.","index":333,"end_time":1366.1,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1357.58,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"And so then I was like, oh, if it''s the same on both, is something that''s static across all of these or is it, you know, like.","index":334,"end_time":1374.05,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1366.1,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"Like the image in the footer?","index":335,"end_time":1375.45,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1374.05,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"Or is it just.","index":336,"end_time":1377.37,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1375.45,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"Was it a placeholder or something?","index":337,"end_time":1379.25,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1377.69,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"Yeah, it was more of a design element.","index":338,"end_time":1380.57,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1379.25,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":339,"end_time":1381.25,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1380.89,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"To be like, hey, this is fun.","index":340,"end_time":1382.89,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1381.25,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"Because.","index":341,"end_time":1384.45,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1384.09,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"Yeah, I would think that there''s something.","index":342,"end_time":1386.01,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1384.45,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":343,"end_time":1386.45,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1386.09,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"Because, yeah, I mean, there''s a. Yeah.","index":344,"end_time":1388.73,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1386.45,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"This one, just.","index":345,"end_time":1389.61,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1388.73,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"The rest of this has that, like, old feel.","index":346,"end_time":1394.02,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1389.93,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"You know what I mean?","index":347,"end_time":1395.06,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1394.34,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"Like, yeah, yeah, I hear you.","index":348,"end_time":1396.42,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1395.06,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And there''s also, I mean, great screenshots and.","index":349,"end_time":1398.74,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1396.42,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Or mock ups of the app that we can show in this section as well.","index":350,"end_time":1401.86,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1398.9,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, I think different imagery down there.","index":351,"end_time":1406.02,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1402.66,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"And honestly, there''s a bunch of stuff that''s already in that.","index":352,"end_time":1409.139,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1406.42,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"That.","index":353,"end_time":1409.38,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1409.139,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"That has been uploaded to Hubs, HubSpot, to WordPress already.","index":354,"end_time":1416.18,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1409.38,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"You know, as we created the blogs and as we created the case studies for both of the.","index":355,"end_time":1420.42,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1416.18,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"Both of those clients, like, there''s a ton of images that are.","index":356,"end_time":1423.42,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1420.42,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"That are horizontal that.","index":357,"end_time":1425,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1423.42,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"That would like, maybe pick one of those.","index":358,"end_time":1426.64,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1425,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, absolutely.","index":359,"end_time":1428.24,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1426.8,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":360,"end_time":1429.12,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1428.64,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"And then we had gone over last week, we have St. Andrews oriented ad, a Foxwoods oriented ad, and then one that combines both of them.","index":361,"end_time":1439.68,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1429.92,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So Shaka modernized the home of golf and then this was the Foxwood reimagining the resort experience.","index":362,"end_time":1448.64,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1440.48,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"This is one where we swapped out the image because the last one was kind of.","index":363,"end_time":1452.08,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1449.04,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It wasn''t as high quality.","index":364,"end_time":1454.83,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1453.79,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It was showing like a few different screens.","index":365,"end_time":1456.59,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1454.91,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we swapped out the image there.","index":366,"end_time":1458.27,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1456.91,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then this one was for both.","index":367,"end_time":1463.55,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1461.71,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We build digital experiences at scale.","index":368,"end_time":1465.63,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1463.79,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Where does the link go for this one if it''s both?","index":369,"end_time":1469.95,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1466.03,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"Yeah, I feel like an idiot.","index":370,"end_time":1475.95,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1471.47,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"No, no, no, you don''t need to feel like an idiot.","index":371,"end_time":1478.39,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1476.51,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"Like, I get it.","index":372,"end_time":1479.11,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1478.39,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"No, that''s a great question.","index":373,"end_time":1479.95,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1479.11,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"No, that''s the idea.","index":374,"end_time":1481.71,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1480.35,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"I mean, I think we want to eventually have the two dovetail.","index":375,"end_time":1487.27,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1482.19,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"And you can.","index":376,"end_time":1488.71,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1488.15,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"I''m talking with my hands here and like showing and, you know, bringing my hands together.","index":377,"end_time":1492.23,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1488.71,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"And you guys can''t see it because I''m not on video.","index":378,"end_time":1494.07,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1492.23,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"And I was like, the idea is to take the golf and the resort and to bring them together.","index":379,"end_time":1499.589,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1494.23,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"Right.","index":380,"end_time":1500.11,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1499.75,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"We want to drive the concept of we do this thing.","index":381,"end_time":1502.99,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1500.11,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"We do this thing and bring them together because then we want to move into, like the Zenda world.","index":382,"end_time":1507.31,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1502.99,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"Right.","index":383,"end_time":1507.63,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1507.31,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"So this is like the steps to get there.","index":384,"end_time":1510.79,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1507.63,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"Um, and so I get it.","index":385,"end_time":1512.68,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1511.28,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"I just.","index":386,"end_time":1513,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1512.68,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"I''m like, where does this.","index":387,"end_time":1513.88,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1513,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"Which one does this go to?","index":388,"end_time":1515.32,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1513.88,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"Or is this going to some other page that''s sort of a combined and leading people down the Zenda path?","index":389,"end_time":1521.12,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1515.32,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":390,"end_time":1521.68,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1521.28,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So actually what I would recommend doing here is using this as a LinkedIn lead gen form ad so that they actually would fill out the form directly on LinkedIn and not go to a landing page.","index":391,"end_time":1530.88,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1521.68,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":392,"end_time":1531.84,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1531.2,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"I mean, I, I''m.","index":393,"end_time":1534,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1532.16,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"This is where I''m out of my depth of.","index":394,"end_time":1536.8,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1534.16,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"Yeah, we''ve been seeing success with expertise.","index":395,"end_time":1539.63,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1537.79,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, we''ve been seeing success with lead gen forms because it doesn''t require someone to click and go to another page and then read and then fill out a form.","index":396,"end_time":1546.03,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1539.95,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"When they open it on LinkedIn, it''s all filled out for them.","index":397,"end_time":1548.91,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1546.27,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":398,"end_time":1549.87,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1549.31,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"Does that work for you, Edwin?","index":399,"end_time":1552.43,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1550.99,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"Removing that barrier?","index":400,"end_time":1553.63,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1552.51,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, I think that that''s.","index":401,"end_time":1559.23,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1557.95,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"I mean, like Colleen said.","index":402,"end_time":1561.43,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1559.47,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"Right.","index":403,"end_time":1561.63,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1561.43,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"If that''s working right now or that''s been the trend, use that.","index":404,"end_time":1565.37,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1561.63,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"I''m willing to try stuff.","index":405,"end_time":1569.25,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1567.77,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"Well, as long as we look for.","index":406,"end_time":1571.13,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1569.25,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"Okay, so if this is not working.","index":407,"end_time":1572.25,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1571.13,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"Yep, absolutely.","index":408,"end_time":1576.09,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1574.89,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And we''ve also updated the email and LinkedIn outreach sequence to not dive into the 600 years of history and that type of stuff as well.","index":409,"end_time":1586.73,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1576.97,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So I just want to make sure I understand this.","index":410,"end_time":1592.66,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1590.42,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"The same contacts are going to get a series of emails.","index":411,"end_time":1599.94,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1595.38,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"One or two are going to highlight St. Andrews and then we''re going to turn and highlight Foxwoods, but it''s the same person.","index":412,"end_time":1607.86,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1600.82,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"Let''s say it''s me.","index":413,"end_time":1609.14,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1608.1,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"I''m on this list.","index":414,"end_time":1610.02,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1609.14,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"I''m going to get a series of emails and it''s going to be St. Andrews and Foxwoods.","index":415,"end_time":1615.78,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1610.02,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"Okay.","index":416,"end_time":1616.38,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1615.94,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"I just want to make sure I''m understanding.","index":417,"end_time":1617.82,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1616.38,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"Like, they''re not sending these to separate groups.","index":418,"end_time":1619.67,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1617.82,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"You''re sending them to a group.","index":419,"end_time":1621.87,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1619.67,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"Okay.","index":420,"end_time":1623.71,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1623.15,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Colin, can you add me to the list?","index":421,"end_time":1625.43,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1623.87,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"Or edwin+avm campaign, shackle.com, something like that, so I can receive those?","index":422,"end_time":1631.55,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1625.43,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"Of course, yeah.","index":423,"end_time":1642.23,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1631.95,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And I''ll again share this document so that you have time to read through it.","index":424,"end_time":1645.87,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1642.23,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And I just kind of broke it out as two slides, but that was the campaign there.","index":425,"end_time":1653.03,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1648.87,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then Edwin, after reviewing the options for sbj, I think SBJ Tech is the closest fit.","index":426,"end_time":1658.63,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1653.03,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And so we''re going to take.","index":427,"end_time":1661.59,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1659.91,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"At least.","index":428,"end_time":1662.109,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1661.59,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"My plan was to take the St. Andrews ad creative that we had here and to resize it to fit the SBJ dimensions.","index":429,"end_time":1671.91,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1662.109,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Perfect.","index":430,"end_time":1673.57,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1673.17,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":431,"end_time":1674.85,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1674.37,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right, well, we will be able to deliver that early next week and surprised we got through all of that and have a few minutes.","index":432,"end_time":1686.53,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1674.85,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I have a question.","index":433,"end_time":1688.77,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1687.65,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"When are you going to start?","index":434,"end_time":1692.05,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1691.01,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"When are people going to start receiving the Foxwoods emails from this campaign?","index":435,"end_time":1697.97,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1692.29,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"Because if they get a wild hare and decide to go to our website right now, all that''s there is the case study.","index":436,"end_time":1704.71,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1699.19,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"None of the blogs that go with it that highlight those sort of the three boxes that you had are there yet.","index":437,"end_time":1710.39,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1704.95,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"So I want to like, do.","index":438,"end_time":1712.63,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1710.55,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"Is that okay?","index":439,"end_time":1714.07,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1712.95,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"Is that not really detrimental or is it.","index":440,"end_time":1718.67,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1714.71,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"We should tie getting those blogs out there so that people, if they decide they want to look into this a little bit further for Foxwoods that they can see us talk about these three things that, you know, the strategy, the design, and the technical.","index":441,"end_time":1732.45,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1718.67,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":442,"end_time":1733.33,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1732.93,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So similar to what Edwin said earlier, these.","index":443,"end_time":1734.93,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1733.33,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"These pages aren''t static.","index":444,"end_time":1735.93,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1734.93,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Right.","index":445,"end_time":1736.09,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1735.93,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We''re looking to probably make tweaks every one to two weeks on these.","index":446,"end_time":1739.09,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1736.09,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":447,"end_time":1739.65,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1739.09,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"And so with the schedule, you know, if we.","index":448,"end_time":1741.85,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1739.89,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"If you guys review everything today and you''re like, colin, this is great.","index":449,"end_time":1744.89,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1741.85,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Get it live early next week.","index":450,"end_time":1746.45,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1744.89,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Cool.","index":451,"end_time":1747.57,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1747.09,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We''ll get the page live, start sending the emails out, the messages, get the ads rolling.","index":452,"end_time":1751.49,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1747.57,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"They''ll go to that page and then as the blogs are uploaded, then we can update the page to have like a resources section.","index":453,"end_time":1758.05,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1751.57,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Ye.","index":454,"end_time":1758.28,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1758.05,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"No, I was just thinking more.","index":455,"end_time":1759.95,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1758.59,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"Less about sending them from that page, but just having them there.","index":456,"end_time":1764.67,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1760.27,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"Someone''s going to have to want to do a little bit more research or understand a little.","index":457,"end_time":1769.31,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1765.23,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"I don''t know.","index":458,"end_time":1770.03,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1769.39,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"It''s not these pages.","index":459,"end_time":1771.71,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1770.59,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"I''m just more worried about.","index":460,"end_time":1772.75,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1771.71,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"In our Shaco.com site, we won''t have those blogs until those dates that we reviewed 20 minutes ago.","index":461,"end_time":1780.67,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1773.07,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"Is that detrimental or does it not really matter?","index":462,"end_time":1784.43,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1781.63,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"Okay, perfect.","index":463,"end_time":1785.03,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1784.43,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"I just want to make sure.","index":464,"end_time":1786.11,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1785.03,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"Not that the static page has links out, but if someone was like, oh, well, how did they do this?","index":465,"end_time":1793.43,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1787.83,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"Let me go to their website to find out more information, but, like, there''s no more information there right now.","index":466,"end_time":1799.03,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1793.59,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"But maybe they would just give them a call instead.","index":467,"end_time":1801.23,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1799.35,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"I don''t know.","index":468,"end_time":1801.91,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1801.23,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"Like, this is again, where I''m leaning on your expertise of, like, if you''re saying it''s fine, then, then, well, let''s keep to the schedule.","index":469,"end_time":1809.03,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1801.99,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"We''ll get the blog out the day before the social media camp that, you know, social media information goes out and move on with life.","index":470,"end_time":1816.04,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1809.03,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, absolutely.","index":471,"end_time":1817.64,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1816.28,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":472,"end_time":1819.4,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1818.84,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"Okay.","index":473,"end_time":1821.4,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1820.84,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"Any other questions?","index":474,"end_time":1823.4,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1822.36,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So what do you need from us?","index":475,"end_time":1825.4,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1823.88,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"You need us to say, like, yes, these pages look good.","index":476,"end_time":1827.64,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1825.4,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":477,"end_time":1828.48,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1828.12,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Pages and email copies and ads.","index":478,"end_time":1830.52,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1828.48,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then I''ll also be sending over, like, the list of contacts that we''ve built out that we want to enroll in this campaign.","index":479,"end_time":1837.96,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1830.76,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right.","index":480,"end_time":1839.09,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1838.69,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"Edwin, who typically looks at the list of contacts, Is that you?","index":481,"end_time":1842.37,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1839.33,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"Yeah, I''ll look into that.","index":482,"end_time":1844.05,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1842.77,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"The other thing I''m calling in the ads, are you.","index":483,"end_time":1848.57,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1844.53,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"Or the emails, are you.","index":484,"end_time":1850.05,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1848.57,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"You''re not using HubSpot, right?","index":485,"end_time":1852.29,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1850.05,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"No.","index":486,"end_time":1853.01,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1852.61,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right, and the other thing was ads.","index":487,"end_time":1857.93,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1853.49,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"That''s an ad role still, or is it LinkedIn ads?","index":488,"end_time":1861.41,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1857.93,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"LinkedIn.","index":489,"end_time":1862.45,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1861.81,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, good.","index":490,"end_time":1863.33,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1862.61,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"Right?","index":491,"end_time":1863.69,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1863.41,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":492,"end_time":1864.05,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1863.69,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":493,"end_time":1864.65,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1864.45,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Adroll is.","index":494,"end_time":1865.33,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1864.65,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It''s.","index":495,"end_time":1865.85,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1865.41,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It''s a play for larger budgets.","index":496,"end_time":1867.45,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1865.85,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It''s more of, like, a awareness play, and we need to be much lower in the funnel.","index":497,"end_time":1871.33,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1867.45,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Got it.","index":498,"end_time":1872.37,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1871.73,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"Thank you.","index":499,"end_time":1873.17,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1872.61,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"Of course.","index":500,"end_time":1874.13,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1873.57,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right, well, if there''s anything else, please let me know.","index":501,"end_time":1880.13,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1877.41,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, I''ll be sending all of this.","index":502,"end_time":1881.33,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1880.21,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"The documents or whatever, so for us to review and say, hey, we''re good to go.","index":503,"end_time":1884.85,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1881.49,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"Okay, perfect.","index":504,"end_time":1885.73,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1884.85,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"All right, awesome.","index":505,"end_time":1888.93,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1887.09,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right, well, thank you both so much for your time.","index":506,"end_time":1891.17,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1889.25,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Thank you.","index":507,"end_time":1891.97,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1891.41,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"All right, thank you.","index":508,"end_time":1893.01,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1891.97,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"Bye.","index":509,"end_time":1893.65,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1893.17,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"}],"dateString":"2025-11-06T17:30:00.000Z","host_email":"colin.costigan@marketersindemand.com","meeting_link":"https://us02web.zoom.us/j/88965765122?pwd=mPL1aFvxXYMYFRYawSa6f5Ez7s5Uv6.1","participants":["kylee.anger@shockoe.com,colin.costigan@marketersindemand.com,edwin@shockoe.com,misty.smith@shockoe.com","kylee.anger@shockoe.com","edwin@shockoe.com","misty.smith@shockoe.com"],"transcript_url":"https://app.fireflies.ai/view/01K8RZDWW43AB8TVAHJX2828NZ","organizer_email":"colin.costigan@marketersindemand.com"}'::jsonb,
    '{"label":"positive","confidence":0.92,"bullets":["Shifted full media budget to Vibe coding campaign after high engagement despite low form fills.","Simplified contact form replaces survey to streamline user engagement and increase conversion.","Misty confirmed case study and blog alignment for phased blog launches on November dates.","Colin updated landing pages and ad creative, approved to go live pending final team review.","Edwin and Misty aligned on maintaining form CTA focus over links to case studies or blogs."],"highlights":[{"quote":"We have turned the AI roadmap campaign off so that we can dedicate budget to the Vibe coding campaign.","speaker":"Colin Costigan"},{"quote":"I think we''re good with launching this. My hope is that we can continue tweaking it.","speaker":"Edwin Huertas"},{"quote":"Perfect. I just want to make sure we''re not saying... we’ll get it from where it is to launch for free.","speaker":"Misty Smith"}],"topics":["campaign","launch","ads","email","website"],"model":"openai/gpt-4-1106-preview","version":1,"generated_at":"2025-11-13T00:00:00Z"}'::jsonb,
    '{"fireflies_summary":{"notes":"## **Campaign Performance and Budget Reallocation**\n\nThe team decided to concentrate the entire paid media budget on the **Vibe coding campaign** after seeing it drive significantly more engaged website traffic, despite lower form fill rates (07:12).\n\n- The **AI roadmap campaign was turned off** to avoid spreading resources thin and focus outreach on Vibe coding (07:12).\n- Colin highlighted a **large increase in page traffic and a notable drop in bounce rate**, indicating better user engagement (07:12).\n- The shift aims to improve form fills with updated landing page, email copy, and ad messaging emphasizing moving AI prototypes to production (10:23).\n- This reallocation should increase qualified leads by focusing on prospects who have built AI apps and need help launching (10:23).\n\n## **Vibe Coding Campaign Messaging and Landing Page Update**\n\nThe Vibe coding campaign messaging was refined to highlight support for moving AI prototypes from build to launch, aiming to increase conversion by simplifying contact and clarifying offerings (10:23).\n\n- The landing page now focuses on a **simple contact form** instead of a survey, encouraging direct conversation (10:23).\n- Edwin approved a **three-step process** of review, refine, and release for app launch support, aligning expectations (11:39).\n- The messaging clarifies that the **free consultation covers review only**, not a full build-to-launch service, managing scope and client expectations (13:25).\n- Colin suggested a **social post linking Vibe coding to its recognition as Collins Dictionary’s 2025 Word of the Year** to boost brand relevance and engagement (14:04).\n- The updated landing page is ready to go live immediately after final review, aiming for prompt campaign activation (15:39).\n\n## **St. Andrews and Foxwoods Campaign Strategy and Content**\n\nThe campaign for St. Andrews and Foxwoods focuses on storytelling and targeted messaging, with tactical decisions to improve readability and user flow while protecting client relationships (16:07).\n\n- The **600-year legacy language was removed** from St. Andrews content per Kai’s feedback to avoid fuzziness in messaging (16:07).\n- Edwin requested **increased overlay opacity** on hero images to improve text readability on St. Andrews’ landing page (17:05).\n- The pages mix case studies and blogs aimed at guiding visitors to consultation scheduling through multiple call-to-actions, keeping focus on lead capture (18:04).\n- To avoid competitive risks, the team agreed to keep client quotes attributed with full name and title to maintain authority while limiting public access since the page is targeted, not SEO-driven (19:41).\n- Misty suggested replacing generic lifestyle images with more tailored visuals reflecting each client’s environment, especially for St. Andrews’ outdoor, golf-focused feel, enhancing brand alignment (21:34).\n\n## **LinkedIn Lead Gen and Outreach Sequencing**\n\nThe combined St. Andrews and Foxwoods ad will use LinkedIn lead gen forms to reduce friction and improve lead capture effectiveness based on recent success trends (24:26).\n\n- Colin recommended **using LinkedIn lead gen forms** instead of landing pages to lower barriers and speed up form completion (25:21).\n- Edwin agreed with this approach, emphasizing willingness to test new methods while monitoring performance for adjustments (25:57).\n- The email sequence will send both St. Andrews and Foxwoods content to the same contact list, alternating messaging to maximize exposure without segmenting audiences (26:30).\n- Edwin requested access to the contact list for review and management, ensuring proper targeting and list hygiene (27:03).\n\n## **Content Scheduling and Website Asset Coordination**\n\nThe team confirmed blog posts supporting Foxwoods and St. Andrews campaigns will go live just before related social media posts, ensuring content availability for prospects seeking deeper information (08:27, 28:07).\n\n- Misty confirmed blog posts will be scheduled in HubSpot with correct URLs to avoid broken links and maintain user experience (09:39).\n- Colin assured the campaign landing pages are dynamic, with plans for updates every one to two weeks, including adding a resources section as blogs go live (28:52).\n- Misty raised concerns about website content lag potentially deterring informed visitors, but Colin and Edwin agreed the planned timing aligns with campaign rollout and is acceptable (28:07).\n- This sequencing maintains campaign momentum while ensuring content assets support visitor research and engagement (28:52).\n\n## **SBJ Tech Campaign Adaptation and Delivery Timeline**\n\nThe St. Andrews ad creative will be resized to fit SBJ Tech’s ad dimensions, leveraging existing assets to accelerate campaign development (27:53).\n\n- Colin committed to delivering the resized SBJ ad by **early next week**, enabling timely campaign launch (27:54).\n- Edwin expressed satisfaction with the plan, confirming alignment on creative adaptation (27:53).\n- This reuse of assets promises faster deployment and cost efficiency for the SBJ Tech campaign (27:54).","outline":null,"keywords":["Vibe coding","campaign performance","landing page","St. Andrews","Foxwoods","LinkedIn lead gen"],"overview":"- **Budget Shift:** Entire paid media budget now focused on Vibe coding campaign for better engagement and lead quality.  \n- **Updated Messaging:** Vibe campaign messaging emphasizes AI support, simplifying contact to increase conversions.  \n- **St. Andrews Content:** Removed legacy language and enhanced readability for better user experience and storytelling.  \n- **LinkedIn Strategy:** Using LinkedIn lead gen forms for St. Andrews and Foxwoods to improve lead capture efficiency.  \n- **Content Coordination:** Blog posts scheduled to align with social media updates, ensuring valuable resources for prospects.  \n- **SBJ Campaign Timeline:** Resized St. Andrews ad to be delivered early next week, enhancing campaign speed and cost efficiency.","action_items":"\n**Colin Costigan**\nSend updated campaign pages, email copy, and ad creative documents for review to Misty and Edwin (30:28)\nShare contact list for campaign enrollment with Edwin for vetting (30:28)\nLaunch updated Vibe coding landing page upon approval (15:50)\nAdapt and deliver resized SBJ Tech ad creative early next week (27:54)\nExecute blog post scheduling in HubSpot following the approved timeline and URLs (09:20)\n\n**Misty Smith**\nReview updated campaign pages, email copy, and ad creative documents after Colin sends (30:21)\nSchedule blogs in HubSpot per agreed timeline and ensure correct URLs are used (09:10)\nDecide on footer image replacement for St. Andrews and Foxwoods pages, potentially selecting from previously uploaded images in HubSpot or WordPress (21:45)\n\n**Edwin Huertas**\nApprove Vibe coding landing page updates and suggest future tweaks where necessary (15:55)\nReview and vet contact lists for the campaigns to ensure proper targeting (30:40)\nMonitor campaign performance, particularly the effectiveness of lead gen forms on LinkedIn vs. landing page conversions (26:15)\nRequest addition to campaign mailing list to receive and monitor emails sent (27:05)\n"},"migrated_from":"contract_meetings","original_id":"9e7fd896-d621-42df-a226-e02aada7f3da","master_marketer":{"status":"migrated"}}'::jsonb,
