  'Meeting Notes: Ricoh // New North: Weekly Meeting',
  '## **Wedding Costs and Planning Insights**

The discussion highlighted the steep costs and complexity involved in wedding planning, underscoring the need to balance budget and experience effectively.

- **Roz** shared that her wedding for **about 50 people cost around $15,000** (08:57), with venue, food, and decor being major expenses.
    - She secured a private club venue for **$500 in August and September**, which included tables, chairs, linens, plates, and cutlery (04:20).
    - The event manager’s exceptional service was critical to a smooth experience, earning a generous tip for her role (11:00).
    - Unforeseen personal issues arose, such as a family member''s injury and last-minute Covid infections, impacting attendance (06:30).
    - Roz emphasized the hidden workload in wedding logistics even when the venue is fully equipped (11:28).

- **Lou Bogani** described his brother’s upcoming wedding in **Buenos Aires with 180 guests and a budget over $40,000** (09:16).
    - The event will feature a relaxed style with food islands and a late-night party, reflecting a more informal reception approach (10:00).
    - Lou recognized the value of the special moment but questioned the cost-to-duration ratio of weddings (11:54).
    - He is personally juggling significant wedding prep stress while also planning to attend a major concert the day after (14:00).

- Both Roz and Lou agreed smaller, more intimate weddings or eloping followed by a party could be cost-effective alternatives without losing the celebration’s spirit (12:16).
    - Roz’s husband preferred a traditional ceremony with details like cake cutting and first dance, illustrating varying expectations that impact planning (13:18).

## **Event Scheduling and Personal Impact**

The timing of Lou’s brother’s wedding and the adjacent major concert created logistical and personal challenges, affecting resource and energy planning.

- The wedding is scheduled for **Saturday, November 15th**, followed by attending an **Oasis concert at River Plate Stadium with 100,000 attendees** the next day (14:15).
    - Lou expects the wedding to end around **6 AM**, leaving limited recovery time before heading to the stadium at **4 PM** for the concert starting at **9 PM** (15:56).
    - He anticipates arriving home around **2 AM the following morning**, risking exhaustion and vocal strain (17:38).
    - Lou plans to request a **day off on Monday for recovery**, acknowledging the physical toll of back-to-back events (15:46).

- The concert is a major event as part of Oasis’s world tour after a **16-year hiatus since 2009**, with two sold-out shows totaling **approximately 200,000 attendees** (18:30).
    - The scale and timing of the wedding and concert combination reflect complex personal scheduling challenges for Lou and his family (16:52).

## **Venue and Service Provider Selection**

Choosing the right venue and service providers proved crucial to managing costs and ensuring a quality experience.

- Roz praised the private club’s all-inclusive setup, which reduced vendor coordination by providing furniture, tableware, and kitchen facilities, saving time and complexity (04:20).
    - The event manager’s hands-on role ensured smooth operations, reducing stress and allowing the couple to focus on the celebration (11:00).
    - The florist delivered a large quantity of high-quality flowers for **$1,800**, which Roz felt was underpriced given the quality (05:30).

- Lou described his brother’s wedding at a golf club venue with an outdoor tent, emphasizing a relaxed but well-styled atmosphere that fits their budget and guest experience goals (09:30).

## **Product Brochure and Marketing Collateral Progress**

The team is advancing the Optimizer brochure and related assets with a focus on finalizing content and visuals ahead of critical deadlines.

- **Lou Bogani** committed to completing the Optimizer brochure template today, aiming to deliver it to **Natalie Mintjens by Wednesday** for storyboard review (27:02, 33:02).
    - He presented new icon options including outlined and solid versions to provide design flexibility for client feedback (28:00).
    - Roz emphasized the need for content fine-tuning specifically tailored for Optimizer, with a goal to finalize by **December 10th** for the January 10th launch (33:09).
    - The team is reusing existing icon assets where possible to speed up delivery and maintain consistency (29:40).
    - Roz asked to retain specific hero image adjustments and content positioning to preserve the intended look and feel (30:35).

- Natalie confirmed receipt of all necessary video and graphic files, enabling ongoing progress on animation and brochure development (27:14, 31:38).
    - Roz plans to prepare similar collateral for Info Print Manager and RICO Process Director, aiming for early review cycles with product managers (33:53).

## **Market and Event Ticketing Context**

The conversation revealed frustration around sports event ticket availability and pricing, highlighting challenges in large-scale event accessibility.

- Roz described the **FIFA World Cup ticket situation in Vancouver**, where the largest stadium holds just over **54,000 seats** and premium tickets sell for thousands of dollars, limiting access (19:51).
    - She criticized FIFA’s pricing and early ticketing practices as a cash grab, echoing dissatisfaction with similar issues in other markets (20:30).
    - Lou noted that high demand is driven by star players like **Messi**, especially as this might be his last World Cup, increasing pressure on ticket sales in Miami and Argentina (21:00).
    - Roz explained a recent incident where Messi did not attend a promoted event in Vancouver, causing public outrage and accusations of false advertising (22:30).
    - Both Roz and Nathalie shared examples of fan disappointment and frustration in Hong Kong and Vancouver due to incomplete player appearances at matches (23:00).

- The team watched the Netflix documentary **FIFA Uncovered**, confirming widespread corruption and financial motives behind FIFA’s operations, which further erodes fan trust (25:20).

## **Team Coordination and Deadlines**

Clear deadlines and collaborative coordination are driving the final stages of the Optimizer launch preparations.

- Roz’s meeting with the product manager is set for **Wednesday at 10 AM**, requiring an updated brochure draft beforehand to secure approval (33:00).
    - Lou is prioritizing final icon adjustments, balloon design arcs, and hero image fixes to meet this deadline (30:28).
    - Roz is actively preparing content for additional product brochures, signaling a broader refresh initiative within marketing collateral (33:50).
    - Natalie is tasked with integrating all assets and ensuring files are ready for animation and final edits (31:38).
    - The launch timeline demands all materials be finalized by **December 10th**, supporting the **January 10th Optimizer product launch** (33:09).',
  '2025-11-06 17:30:00+00',
  'published',
  '[{"text":"Finalize and deliver the Optimizer/template brochure by end of day (27:36)","completed":false},{"text":"Provide both outline and solid versions of new icons for selection by Linea (27:43)","completed":false},{"text":"Prepare storyboard for the upcoming video by Wednesday (27:02)","completed":false},{"text":"Submit rough content drafts of brochures for Info Print Manager and RICO Process Director to team for further refinement (34:58)","completed":false},{"text":"Share finalized brochure copy with product manager by Friday meeting for sign-off (27:36)","completed":false}]'::jsonb,
  true
FROM new_meeting;

-- Meeting: New North <> ThreatMark: Weekly Marketing Meeting (2025-11-12 14:30:00+00)
WITH new_meeting AS (
  INSERT INTO compass_meetings (contract_id, meeting_date, source, external_id, title, participants, duration_seconds, recording_url, transcript, sentiment, raw_metadata, created_at, updated_at)
  VALUES (
    '75b32155-1255-4d17-b437-152e300521a0',
    '2025-11-12 14:30:00+00',
    'fireflies',
    '01K9AJMT8K0HJWBRB2PDPJYF5T',
    'New North <> ThreatMark: Weekly Marketing Meeting',
    '{"Kate ThreatMark","Colin Costigan"}'::text[],
    2236,
    'https://us02web.zoom.us/j/84564648866?pwd=JR6eWxlxKbgogzCqTNUawSLUUhQoEa.1',
    '{"id":"01K9AJMT8K0HJWBRB2PDPJYF5T","title":"New North <> ThreatMark: Weekly Marketing Meeting","summary":{"notes":"## **Team and Resource Updates**\n\nThe team is expanding with new skilled members to improve collaboration and timezone coverage.\n\n- **Nina, a new team member with about 10 years of experience,** has been supporting Colin’s team for the last **three to four weeks** and will now join all relevant calls and Slack channels (00:30).\n    - Nina''s proximity to the client’s timezone will enhance real-time responsiveness.\n    - Colin highlighted past issues with onboarding Monica to emphasize smoother integration this time.\n    - This addition aims to strengthen account management and execution quality.\n    - Nina’s involvement will free Colin to focus on higher-level strategy and oversight.\n\n- **Kate announced a new marketing hire starting next week, based in London,** focusing on event sponsorship and APM activities (01:21).\n    - The new hire will undergo onboarding for a couple of weeks before engaging in meetings.\n    - Kate will decide which calls the new marketer should attend, ensuring targeted involvement.\n    - This role supports expanding marketing reach and campaign execution in the UK market.\n    - The addition aligns with broader marketing growth and event-driven lead generation plans.\n\n## **Website and Technical Infrastructure**\n\nUpdating and synchronizing environments is critical for efficient development and consistent production quality.\n\n- **WordPress core and plugins were updated across the test environment,** with a full functional test confirming no broken pages (03:53).\n    - Colin stressed the importance of syncing staging with the live environment to streamline future updates.\n    - Kate agreed this task should be handled by the IT team or delegated with proper admin access.\n    - Current hosting is on **AWS for production** and **Azure** for other systems, with security controls limiting access (04:48).\n    - Aligning environments will allow building and testing features like the homepage banner on staging before going live, reducing risk.\n\n- **The security vulnerability related to SRI was patched on both environments,** with verification ongoing to ensure script integrity (06:57).\n    - Andres from IT managed the patching process, ensuring compliance and security.\n    - This work was necessary to maintain system stability and protect against exploits.\n    - Continuous monitoring is planned to prevent future vulnerabilities.\n    - The update supports the overall IT security posture and website reliability.\n\n## **Product and Content Updates**\n\nRefining content presentation and creative assets will better engage users and drive conversions.\n\n- **A new rotating homepage design will showcase four key elements:** the “Talk to a fraud fighter” callout replacing “Win the war against Fraud,” the AI versus fraud white paper, a Scan Flag push, and an episode titled \"Why can''t I fry something? Fry, Aaron, fry\" (07:49).\n    - Colin plans to finalize episode titles by Thursday with multiple options for flexibility.\n    - Kate emphasized keeping titles simple and tied closely to campaign messaging.\n    - This refresh aims to improve visitor engagement and clarity of messaging on the homepage.\n    - The episode content serves as a user engagement tool within the campaign framework.\n\n- **Scan Flag landing page video placement will be improved by adding a distinct section with a darker background and a title,** inspired by the Q2 page resource section style (22:37).\n    - Kate requested repositioning the video to create a stronger visual callout.\n    - Colin noted all Scan Flag creative has been updated with the new logo and will share final assets as files.\n    - This update is expected to increase product visibility and user interaction.\n    - The redesign aligns with broader branding consistency efforts.\n\n- **HubSpot landing pages require new modules: a scrolling resources section to expand beyond three columns,** supporting more dynamic content on the Q2 landing page (14:32).\n    - Colin will assign his team to build this customized module.\n    - This will improve content management flexibility and user navigation.\n    - Enhancements will support ongoing campaign resource linking.\n    - Kate’s request highlights a need for easier content scalability within HubSpot.\n\n- **A monthly newsletter and a new fraud news roundup bulletin will launch,** requiring fresh creative templates modeled on the existing “Behind Enemy Lines” style (33:43).\n    - Kate requested creative assets for both formats to maintain brand consistency.\n    - Colin confirmed the team will build these templates after receiving design specs.\n    - This initiative aims to increase regular audience engagement with timely content.\n    - The bulletin will integrate ThreatMark insights to differentiate from generic news.\n\n## **Marketing Campaigns and Performance**\n\nCampaigns are being reviewed and refreshed to improve lead quality while managing budget effectively.\n\n- **LinkedIn targeting for fraud professionals is being refined with ongoing campaign adjustments,** and a broader awareness campaign is planned for discussion next week (18:24).\n    - Kate flagged a slowdown in LinkedIn lead volume, prompting the need for creative refresh and performance review.\n    - Colin noted strong lead quality from recent forms, including submissions from large firms like TD Bank.\n    - The budget and campaign effectiveness will be reassessed to optimize spend and results.\n    - This reflects a shift toward quality leads and more strategic ad placements.\n\n- **Google Ads broad match campaigns were paused due to generic search traffic,** with click-through rates below target effectiveness and poor channel fit identified by Colin (32:25).\n    - The current benchmark CTR is **0.44%**, which Q2 campaigns are achieving but with low landing page conversions.\n    - AdRoll geo-targeting campaigns showed clicks doubling from **3 to 6 week-over-week**, with the “bill for bank” ad as the top performer.\n    - Future recommendations include focusing on platforms with better conversion potential like LinkedIn.\n    - This adjustment aims to improve ROI by concentrating on high-impact channels.\n\n- **Lead source tracking was enhanced with a detailed spreadsheet mapping various event names and channels,** ready for review and integration with HubSpot and Salesforce by Greg (19:35).\n    - Colin explained the need for Greg to create specific lead source properties in Salesforce for smooth data flow.\n    - This ensures accurate attribution and improves marketing analytics.\n    - Kate will review the sheet and update HubSpot folder structures accordingly.\n    - Precise tracking supports better campaign measurement and decision making.\n\n## **Workflow and Process Improvements**\n\nAdjustments in marketing automation and access management will increase operational efficiency.\n\n- **HubSpot email workflow delays were shortened from five to four days to align with Wednesday send targets,** but changing steps for contacts already in delay proved challenging (10:02).\n    - Colin will investigate options to remove or adjust contacts in active delay steps for future flexibility.\n    - He highlighted HubSpot’s limitation without a business-days add-on, which complicates scheduling.\n    - Future workflows will be designed more cautiously to avoid weekend sends without extra costs.\n    - These changes aim to reduce errors and improve timing precision in email campaigns.\n\n- **Access issues with the FDE portal and deliverable links were identified,** with Colin committing to review and restore proper permissions for Kate (29:34).\n    - The problem caused some links to redirect incorrectly to Google access requests.\n    - Fixing this will streamline content review and reduce friction in collaboration.\n    - This action supports smoother project management and stakeholder communication.\n    - Ensuring correct access is critical for timely feedback and approvals.\n\n- **Discussions are ongoing about which pages should remain on WordPress versus HubSpot,** with a tentative view to keep HubSpot for landing pages related to campaigns and paid channels (25:02).\n    - Kate and Greg are evaluating whether to invest in fixing WordPress or to migrate more content.\n    - Colin confirmed flexibility to rebuild product and solution pages on either platform.\n    - This decision will impact future development workflows and content management.\n    - Aligning platform use with marketing strategy will improve site performance and user experience.","outline":null,"keywords":["Website Staging","GA4 Events","HubSpot Workflows","Scan Flag","LinkedIn Ads","Newsletter Design"],"overview":"- **Team Expansion:** Nina joins the team to enhance real-time client support, improving account management and strategic focus for Colin.\n\n- **Marketing Hire:** New marketer starts next week in London, focusing on UK event sponsorship and targeted campaign engagement.\n\n- **Technical Updates:** WordPress environments updated and secured; synchronizing staging with production for smoother future updates and reduced risk.\n\n- **Content Enhancements:** Homepage redesign includes new engagement tools; improved video placement will boost product visibility and branding consistency.\n\n- **Campaign Analysis:** LinkedIn targeting adjustments are needed; AdRoll campaigns show improved click performance; focus on quality leads is essential for ROI.\n\n- **Workflow Improvements:** HubSpot workflows streamlined for better timing; access issues in FDE portal will be resolved to improve collaboration efficiency.","action_items":"\n**Colin Costigan**\nIntegrate new team member Nina into calls and Slack channels (00:30)\nPatch verification for SRI vulnerability on live and staging environments (07:49)\nAdjust padding on November newsletter hero section after content finalized by client (15:54)\nDevelop a new scrollable resource module for Q2 landing page in HubSpot (14:43)\nRefresh LinkedIn creative and update PDF form language to increase lead quantity (19:35)\nShare lead source mapping spreadsheet with Kate for review (20:52)\nRedesign Scan Flag landing page video section with darker background and added title (25:52)\nUpdate Scan Flag ad creative per markup notes and send finalized files to client (29:34)\nProvide client with access to portal documents and resolve access issues (30:54)\nUpdate FDE whitepaper text as per feedback and proceed with no additional product element (31:47)\nPrepare performance report and budget recommendation for paid ads (35:04)\nDesign newsletter and bulletin creative templates after receiving specs (34:44)\n\n**Kate Burwood**\nConfirm any new GA4 event tracking requirements (03:46)\nFinalize newsletter content and complete email draft by end of day (17:54)\nConsider and decide on the balance of HubSpot versus WordPress pages (25:18)\nShare design package specs for newsletter and bulletin creative (34:44)\n\n**Gregory Smith**\nCreate or update lead source specific properties in HubSpot Salesforce integration (20:57)\nAssist with syncing staging and production website environments on AWS (04:42)\n"},"duration":37.2599983215332,"speakers":[{"id":0,"name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"id":1,"name":"Colin Costigan"}],"sentences":[{"text":"Up with everyone yesterday in London.","index":0,"end_time":2.8,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":0.24,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"They''re all there today.","index":1,"end_time":3.92,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2.88,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Just doing all the senior stuff but yeah, all good.","index":2,"end_time":8.24,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":4.72,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":3,"end_time":8.6,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":8.24,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It''s exciting.","index":4,"end_time":9.28,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":8.6,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":5,"end_time":10.32,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":9.84,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"All right, well let''s crack into it.","index":6,"end_time":13.36,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":11.2,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, that''s why I didn''t respond to your message yesterday.","index":7,"end_time":15.24,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":13.52,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But I did get our team into where we''ll go over that.","index":8,"end_time":18.92,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":15.24,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"The test environment of the website.","index":9,"end_time":21.68,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":18.92,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So I have some updates already there.","index":10,"end_time":25.04,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":23.44,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right.","index":11,"end_time":29.37,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":28.89,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"And one thing that I don''t want to forget had a new team member named Nina that''s been helping me out for the last several weeks on our account.","index":12,"end_time":37.45,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":30.81,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So she''ll be joining our calls moving forward and but it''s not going to be like when we had Monica join.","index":13,"end_time":45.85,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":37.61,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I''m going to be on everything even though I''d only missed one meeting with Monica.","index":14,"end_time":49.21,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":46.17,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But things got a little derailed.","index":15,"end_time":50.97,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":49.21,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So yeah, we''ll be working together on all the everything Threatmark but you''ll see her joining the Slack channel and our teams or our meetings in the future.","index":16,"end_time":61.45,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":50.97,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Cool, that''s good.","index":17,"end_time":63.93,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":62.49,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Yeah, she''s got a lot of great, a lot of great experience.","index":18,"end_time":66.49,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":64.17,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"She''s closer to your guys time zone as well.","index":19,"end_time":68.41,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":66.49,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"She''s serpent based.","index":20,"end_time":70.25,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":68.97,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, comes with I think about 10 years of experience and she''s been helping me out for the last three or four weeks on the account everything that we''ve been doing.","index":21,"end_time":77.89,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":71.05,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So.","index":22,"end_time":78.25,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":77.89,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"On the same note actually we have a new marketing person starting next week as well.","index":23,"end_time":87.06,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":81.82,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Oh, exciting.","index":24,"end_time":87.74,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":87.06,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, they are going to be ULIA based in London.","index":25,"end_time":93.54,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":88.14,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"They''re going to be focused on event sponsorship, some APM activity and something else.","index":26,"end_time":102.7,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":93.54,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Sounds awesome.","index":27,"end_time":105.19,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":104.39,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Should I invite them to any meetings or do you just want to handle that like for any that you want them to come to?","index":28,"end_time":109.91,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":105.43,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I''ll let you know.","index":29,"end_time":113.43,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":112.55,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"It depends.","index":30,"end_time":114.27,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":113.59,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"I think there''s going to be a couple of weeks of onboarding anyway so yeah, we''ll talk about it next week or whatever.","index":31,"end_time":123.19,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":114.27,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"That all sounds good.","index":32,"end_time":124.87,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":123.75,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right.","index":33,"end_time":125.99,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":125.59,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"We''ll go through several project updates, things that we''re working on, things that are ready for review and then just review of the metrics.","index":34,"end_time":133.43,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":125.99,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we did go through the GA4 events that are set up and there was only one that was broken so we resolved that and then I just have a table breakdown here of these are the only custom events that are set up on the website.","index":35,"end_time":148.79,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":133.43,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So this is pretty much the entire audit is just these four.","index":36,"end_time":152.31,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":149.03,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So if we want to set up any other ones moving forward we can do so we have almost basically a clean slate of Google Analytics custom events.","index":37,"end_time":160.79,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":153.35,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I think we do want to set up some new Ones.","index":38,"end_time":166.04,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":164.04,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Yeah, I think that sounds like a good idea, especially with GA4.","index":39,"end_time":171.76,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":167.48,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I mean we have some like scroll items in here, but scan flag looks like it was the priority for setting this up and we maybe we might have even done that just as part of conversions for LinkedIn ads and Google Ads.","index":40,"end_time":186.28,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":171.76,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Right?","index":41,"end_time":187.01,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":186.77,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":42,"end_time":188.33,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":187.97,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So I mean it looks like the GA4 account is pretty much a clean slate.","index":43,"end_time":191.73,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":188.33,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Is there anything in mind that you guys were like, we should measure this.","index":44,"end_time":196.61,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":192.61,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Is it specific button clicks?","index":45,"end_time":198.45,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":196.69,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Is it.","index":46,"end_time":199.01,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":198.45,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Let''s get crazy with tracking everything that they do.","index":47,"end_time":203.09,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":200.05,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"No, I think we keep it as clean as possible, in my opinion.","index":48,"end_time":207.25,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":203.97,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"I''ll get back to you on that though.","index":49,"end_time":209.89,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":208.21,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"I feel like I''m a little slow and foggy today, so forgive me.","index":50,"end_time":229.42,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":226.3,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But I''m.","index":51,"end_time":232.18,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":231.58,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Mine''s self inflicted.","index":52,"end_time":233.26,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":232.18,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"So we do have VPN access, so we''re all set there.","index":53,"end_time":237.42,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":233.26,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We also had to go in through smtp, but our access still worked for that.","index":54,"end_time":241.5,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":237.42,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"The reason we had to do that is through the VPN we were able to go through and update WordPress core and plugins across the test environment.","index":55,"end_time":250.98,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":242.34,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And we also ran a functional test to confirm that everything is operating correctly.","index":56,"end_time":256.14,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":251.38,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So just went through all the pages and made sure that nothing was broken.","index":57,"end_time":258.7,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":256.14,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I do think now that everything is updated as far as like plugins and things.","index":58,"end_time":262.34,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":258.7,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I know you guys currently control the push of both environments.","index":59,"end_time":267.62,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":263.22,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I would highly recommend getting them in sync.","index":60,"end_time":269.9,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":267.98,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I completely agree.","index":61,"end_time":273.66,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":271.5,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"I think it was a task that we need our IT team to do.","index":62,"end_time":278.66,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":274.54,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Right.","index":63,"end_time":279.02,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":278.66,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"In terms of doing a copy of Live.","index":64,"end_time":282.14,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":279.26,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Either they need to do it or just give us access to do it.","index":65,"end_time":285.5,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":282.54,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"What level of access would you need?","index":66,"end_time":287.74,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":285.9,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"We would need like wherever they''re managed, wherever the environments are hosted.","index":67,"end_time":292.54,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":288.3,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We would need admin access there, which I think is why your team was hesitant to do that before.","index":68,"end_time":296.38,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":292.54,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, there was a no for that because it''s an already AWS environment, which is where all of our.","index":69,"end_time":304.05,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":296.93,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Yeah, I mean you guys are Azure.","index":70,"end_time":306.57,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":305.33,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You got security and everything in there.","index":71,"end_time":308.37,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":306.57,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That''s right.","index":72,"end_time":309.17,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":308.53,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":73,"end_time":309.81,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":309.33,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":74,"end_time":311.53,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":311.17,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So I mean what they would basically need to do is just pull like push the LIVE environment back to the staging environment and then in the future we can, we can make updates to just the staging environment.","index":75,"end_time":323.37,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":311.53,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"The reason we want weren''t doing that is because we couldn''t do like a push in a timely manner where we controlled everything.","index":76,"end_time":328.96,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":323.37,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":77,"end_time":332.84,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":332.32,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Just to talk through.","index":78,"end_time":333.76,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":332.84,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Then when staging is updated and is live live and is as current as live is for future updates, then as in like improvements rather than maintenance, would we need to do it on staging and then Production.","index":79,"end_time":358.17,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":333.76,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"That is best practice.","index":80,"end_time":359.69,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":358.33,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Because then you guys.","index":81,"end_time":361.53,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":360.49,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It is interesting the way that you guys have the test website locked down.","index":82,"end_time":365.57,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":362.33,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I mean, you would have to get your IP and Greg''s ip.","index":83,"end_time":367.89,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":365.57,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I know you guys are both having issues with that or maybe it got resolved of just viewing the test website.","index":84,"end_time":372.57,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":367.89,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But yes, best practice would be like, for example, the homepage banner that we''re designing and want to build.","index":85,"end_time":377.93,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":373.61,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Would love to build that first on the staging site.","index":86,"end_time":380.36,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":378.28,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Sure.","index":87,"end_time":381,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":380.6,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"That way you guys can interact with it, play around, and then before it''s like live on the site for everyone to see.","index":88,"end_time":385.88,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":381.16,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, so I did have an outstanding ticket with Andre, who''s the IT guy.","index":89,"end_time":394.68,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":387.48,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"I''m sure he does other things other than what I just said IT guy, but he is like, that''s the big bucket.","index":90,"end_time":402.12,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":395.96,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Yeah, exactly.","index":91,"end_time":403.24,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":402.28,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"But I think it was just a too low priority.","index":92,"end_time":406.94,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":404.78,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"So maybe Greg can.","index":93,"end_time":409.02,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":407.9,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Yeah, it might have been at the same time we were doing HubSpot and all sorts of stuff, so.","index":94,"end_time":412.7,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":409.42,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, exactly.","index":95,"end_time":413.82,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":412.86,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Okay.","index":96,"end_time":414.86,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":414.3,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":97,"end_time":418.06,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":417.5,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"As part of that though, I do have an update on another section.","index":98,"end_time":421.42,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":418.06,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So.","index":99,"end_time":421.7,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":421.42,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Based on what I can''t remember if it was Alesh or it might have been Voita that sent over.","index":100,"end_time":431.66,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":421.7,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I''m skipping through all these.","index":101,"end_time":433.3,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":432.34,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That sent over, like the SRI vulnerability.","index":102,"end_time":435.78,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":433.7,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So that''s what we had to go through the SMTP access.","index":103,"end_time":439.3,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":436.02,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And so we have everything running and patching right now and we''re checking it today.","index":104,"end_time":442.82,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":439.3,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Everything was like run through and patched.","index":105,"end_time":445.18,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":442.98,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And we''re just doing a verification that it all went smooth today because it has to run through every script that is on the site.","index":106,"end_time":453.7,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":445.18,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So.","index":107,"end_time":455.86,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":455.54,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And we''re doing that on both environments.","index":108,"end_time":457.54,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":455.86,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, that was Andre.","index":109,"end_time":460.49,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":459.61,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Andres.","index":110,"end_time":461.77,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":460.57,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Andres.","index":111,"end_time":462.65,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":462.01,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, so I was right the first time.","index":112,"end_time":464.57,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":462.65,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, cool.","index":113,"end_time":470.69,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":469.93,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Thank you.","index":114,"end_time":471.29,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":470.69,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"The design for the new homepage here with the four rotating, that being the talk to a fraud fighter, which is essentially going to replace the Win the war against Fraud.","index":115,"end_time":481.29,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":472.33,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then the new white paper, the AI versus fraud white paper, and then a push for scan flag.","index":116,"end_time":487.41,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":482.33,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Those are the four that''ll be rotating that we''re designing.","index":117,"end_time":490.53,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":487.41,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Cool.","index":118,"end_time":491.33,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":490.85,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"And then the episode with why can''t I fry something?","index":119,"end_time":497.69,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":491.65,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Fry, Aaron, fry.","index":120,"end_time":499.01,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":497.69,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That will be all produced and ready.","index":121,"end_time":502.77,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":500.21,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Today''s Wednesday, so tomorrow I do want to ask on that if you had a.","index":122,"end_time":510.69,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":502.85,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Sorry, I''m jumping around so much.","index":123,"end_time":512.01,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":510.69,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"If you had a specific title in mind for the episode based on any of the conversation or.","index":124,"end_time":516.59,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":512.01,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I think you''ve always been good with the titles that we suggest generally.","index":125,"end_time":520.83,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":516.99,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, I mean, I generally just think let''s not overcomplicate it and just go with something that sounds good, something we specifically are using as part of our campaign, which this is, isn''t right.","index":126,"end_time":534.27,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":520.83,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"And that''s why I asked Mike too, in the like, because sometimes he''ll have his.","index":127,"end_time":537.87,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":534.27,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"His office, security walked in, his dog, things like that.","index":128,"end_time":541.63,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":538.03,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So I just wanted to make sure there was nothing.","index":129,"end_time":543.15,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":541.63,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So.","index":130,"end_time":545.85,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":545.69,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Okay, cool.","index":131,"end_time":546.37,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":545.85,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So then we should be good Thursday.","index":132,"end_time":547.81,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":546.37,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we''ll pick some title options.","index":133,"end_time":549.69,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":547.81,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Typically in the show notes we have like three or four options for titles.","index":134,"end_time":554.53,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":551.69,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then on the quote card or whatever, we just establish a title card.","index":135,"end_time":557.49,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":554.53,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We establish a title and then we can rotate that if you want a different one.","index":136,"end_time":560.41,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":557.49,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":137,"end_time":562.81,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":562.17,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"I feel so, like discombobulated.","index":138,"end_time":565.53,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":563.69,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So I feel the same, but I''m actually feeling better.","index":139,"end_time":569.77,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":566.33,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"My apologies for the cyber fraud Fusion trial.","index":140,"end_time":573.49,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":569.85,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We worked through and tested the issue that Greg was having with the form.","index":141,"end_time":576.63,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":573.49,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So I think we''re all good there.","index":142,"end_time":577.91,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":576.63,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Sorry about if you guys got like 10 or 15 tests from us, but I''m going to go through and just based on what we talked about last week, just swap some images and add some backgrounds and fix some spacing to the page.","index":143,"end_time":592.87,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":579.67,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then we also talked about just writing one email.","index":144,"end_time":597.43,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":593.67,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So should we write that email?","index":145,"end_time":599.19,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":597.59,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Did you guys already have an email written for the holiday fishing?","index":146,"end_time":602.07,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":599.19,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yep, already written, already implemented in the workflow.","index":147,"end_time":606.54,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":602.58,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"I did have a question on the workflow, specifically that when I was updating it, I changed the delay to four days so that it sends today because we were targeting Wednesday.","index":148,"end_time":622.9,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":606.54,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"My question was, if the contacts are already in the step in the delay step, how do I change that step?","index":149,"end_time":636.11,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":625.14,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Because you can''t change the type of delay when they''re already in it.","index":150,"end_time":645.31,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":638.91,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Is this Q2 Blitz?","index":151,"end_time":646.898,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":645.47,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Q2 Blitz?","index":152,"end_time":647.91,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":647.002,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":153,"end_time":648.31,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":647.91,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"So step five, where the contact''s already in the action, I''ve changed that to four days.","index":154,"end_time":653.55,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":648.31,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"So it should be sending today.","index":155,"end_time":654.75,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":653.55,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah.","index":156,"end_time":660.07,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":658.95,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Remaining time in action is an hour and two minutes.","index":157,"end_time":662.63,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":660.07,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Here, let me show you what I''m looking at.","index":158,"end_time":665.03,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":663.59,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So I just clicked on the action and where we can edit it or you can see the contacts that are in it.","index":159,"end_time":670.63,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":666.63,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And it looks like remaining time here is an hour.","index":160,"end_time":672.87,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":670.63,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":161,"end_time":673.59,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":673.11,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"So they should be getting that email.","index":162,"end_time":675.19,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":673.75,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And I did that because I changed it from a five day to a four day.","index":163,"end_time":679.19,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":676.15,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"But my question was, how do I get the contacts to go into a different step?","index":164,"end_time":683.84,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":679.27,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Because what I was trying to do was change it to like step seven, which is on a specific date rather than a set amount of time.","index":165,"end_time":695.6,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":684.08,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"So I''ve just changed it to a shorter delay to hit Wednesday rather than Thursday because I didn''t know how to change that to a specific date when they''re already in the action.","index":166,"end_time":707.6,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":697.68,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":167,"end_time":708.57,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":708.25,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"I''ll have to check with the team.","index":168,"end_time":711.89,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":710.65,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I think we could honestly just even remove this step and push them into just receiving this.","index":169,"end_time":719.85,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":711.89,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"To be fair, it doesn''t actually matter now, but it was just like, for future reference, how do I do it?","index":170,"end_time":725.21,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":720.57,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"And if I can''t do it, I guess that''s the.","index":171,"end_time":728.89,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":725.69,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Yeah, the day.","index":172,"end_time":730.97,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":730.25,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So, like, for this campaign, we could have done.","index":173,"end_time":733.05,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":731.13,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Because it was a list upload and we had like emails that we wanted to send, we could have done this for all of them.","index":174,"end_time":737.13,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":733.05,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":175,"end_time":738.36,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":738.04,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":176,"end_time":741.72,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":741.32,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That''s the annoying thing about HubSpot is they require you to subscribe to a whole new, like, segment workflow.","index":177,"end_time":745.88,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":741.72,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Add on that they have to do like business days.","index":178,"end_time":748.52,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":746.04,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So in the future we either.","index":179,"end_time":754.6,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":751.56,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"If we wanted to send only on business days and we don''t want to get that upgrade, then we either need to be very cautious about like the days we can set up specific days for them to go out.","index":180,"end_time":766.44,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":754.76,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"The only issue that comes with that is if it''s an active list and new people are being added to it, they could get email three before email one and two.","index":181,"end_time":774.48,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":766.44,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":182,"end_time":775.28,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":774.8,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"So I''ll work through.","index":183,"end_time":778.96,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":777.92,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So see what we can do for workflows in the future to avoid sending on weekends.","index":184,"end_time":788.48,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":781.6,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But yeah, it looks like everything should be good here.","index":185,"end_time":794.05,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":792.29,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then they would be getting this.","index":186,"end_time":798.13,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":796.77,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Another couple of random ones on HubSpot.","index":187,"end_time":806.37,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":803.25,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Just whilst we''re in it.","index":188,"end_time":808.93,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":807.73,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"On the landing page for Q2, we''ve got a resources section on there which has three columns of.","index":189,"end_time":816.61,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":809.01,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Sorry, hold on, before we jump into that.","index":190,"end_time":821.33,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":818.45,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we want to send this just as a plain HTML.","index":191,"end_time":824.21,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":821.33,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yes.","index":192,"end_time":824.85,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":824.37,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Okay, just wanted to confirm.","index":193,"end_time":827.89,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":825.01,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then.","index":194,"end_time":828.93,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":828.29,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"There''S no UTMs in there.","index":195,"end_time":832.21,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":831.17,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Do you think we need one UTM parameters?","index":196,"end_time":835.97,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":832.21,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, I don''t think so.","index":197,"end_time":837.97,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":836.29,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I mean, it''s one specific page that we''re sending people to, so we already know where they''re coming from and how they''re getting it.","index":198,"end_time":844.21,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":837.97,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Cool.","index":199,"end_time":847.01,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":846.53,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"All right, so I guess it''s too late then for me to make changes to the phishing page.","index":200,"end_time":850.53,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":847.25,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I always do that as well.","index":201,"end_time":856.25,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":855.09,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"I look for the landing pages in marketing.","index":202,"end_time":857.85,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":856.25,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"It doesn''t make sense that they''re in content.","index":203,"end_time":859.25,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":857.85,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"To me, it''s because if you guys wanted to build your entire website.","index":204,"end_time":863.25,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":859.25,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, that''s where they have it.","index":205,"end_time":864.97,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":863.65,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, so that page is live.","index":206,"end_time":865.89,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":864.97,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right, so we''re all good then.","index":207,"end_time":866.85,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":865.89,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right.","index":208,"end_time":868.4,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":868.16,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Sorry, you were asking about another page and resources.","index":209,"end_time":871.84,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":868.4,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yes, in the Q2 landing page, we''ve got a resources Section in here.","index":210,"end_time":875.68,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":872.32,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"The stuff we''re linking out to.","index":211,"end_time":879.2,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":875.76,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"How do I add more than three on, like a scroller?","index":212,"end_time":883.12,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":879.68,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"We''d have to build a new module to go into that.","index":213,"end_time":887.76,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":883.92,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So I can have our team work on that.","index":214,"end_time":890.72,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":889.28,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, that''d be good.","index":215,"end_time":893.65,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":892.89,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Please.","index":216,"end_time":893.93,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":893.65,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"I could add a second set of resources, but I thought scroll.","index":217,"end_time":900.01,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":894.41,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Yeah, we can build that.","index":218,"end_time":902.65,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":901.53,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I think HubSpot has one and like kind of native one.","index":219,"end_time":906.01,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":902.65,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Can just redesign the colors and everything.","index":220,"end_time":908.65,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":906.01,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Anything else on this or anything in HubSpot?","index":221,"end_time":916.33,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":913.45,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We''re sending a newsletter.","index":222,"end_time":920.41,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":918.25,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Were going to aim for the 14th, but that is a Friday.","index":223,"end_time":924.98,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":920.82,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"I''m just.","index":224,"end_time":927.3,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":926.66,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"It''s not got any content in there yet, so there''s nothing to look at.","index":225,"end_time":930.42,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":927.54,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"But I''m just playing around with it.","index":226,"end_time":932.74,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":930.42,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"I did have a question about that first top bit, though, and how to.","index":227,"end_time":935.94,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":932.74,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"The padding.","index":228,"end_time":936.74,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":936.02,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"How to edit the padding.","index":229,"end_time":939.22,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":937.94,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, it looks all right when there''s a CTA in there, but I didn''t think it needed a CTA at that level.","index":230,"end_time":954.03,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":939.38,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":231,"end_time":955.15,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":954.67,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So should be adjusting.","index":232,"end_time":969.35,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":955.23,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I don''t know why it''s not.","index":233,"end_time":970.35,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":969.35,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Might have to go.","index":234,"end_time":988.36,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":987.56,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Because there''s a custom module that we built, so I might have to.","index":235,"end_time":995.4,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":989.08,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Unless we can go negative here.","index":236,"end_time":1000.53,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":999.01,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, I think we''re gonna have to update the Hubble code that''s in here.","index":237,"end_time":1010.29,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1004.85,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":238,"end_time":1014.57,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1014.21,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Because there''s a custom module that we wrote.","index":239,"end_time":1016.37,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1014.57,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Edit styles.","index":240,"end_time":1023.73,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1022.21,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That just brings me back there.","index":241,"end_time":1025.09,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1023.81,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So what we need to do.","index":242,"end_time":1027.69,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1025.77,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, I''ll just have the team update the padding on this.","index":243,"end_time":1072.9,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1068.98,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Let me build the rest of the email because I might have some other changes.","index":244,"end_time":1077.94,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1074.58,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Okay, I''ll try to do that by the end of the day.","index":245,"end_time":1081.15,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1078.35,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Perfect.","index":246,"end_time":1093.95,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1093.39,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"And then so for LinkedIn, we''re still tightening targeting for fraud professionals.","index":247,"end_time":1108.64,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1104.28,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That''s happening today.","index":248,"end_time":1109.8,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1108.64,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then we also talked about creating a broader awareness campaign.","index":249,"end_time":1114.44,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1110.04,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And so I''d like to talk more about that next week because we have some campaigns in the works right now.","index":250,"end_time":1122.56,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1116.68,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then that''ll get us to about halfway through the month this week.","index":251,"end_time":1126.36,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1122.56,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then I want to have a larger conversation around the budget.","index":252,"end_time":1130.04,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1127.64,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I think we also probably need to do a performance review as we haven''t had probably since the end of Q2.","index":253,"end_time":1136.75,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1131.35,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Really?","index":254,"end_time":1137.11,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1136.75,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Q2, Q3, Q2 as part of the FDE white paper.","index":255,"end_time":1146.069,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1137.43,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"We also need creative for that.","index":256,"end_time":1148.15,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1146.069,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"And Greg and I were also talking about LinkedIn''s kind of slowed down recently in terms of leads, so it might be worth doing a refresh and creative and reviewing the performance the last couple of months as kind of a same activity.","index":257,"end_time":1168.11,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1149.43,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":258,"end_time":1171.27,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1170.91,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"But I do agree on the budget point that we need to review that.","index":259,"end_time":1174.75,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1171.27,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":260,"end_time":1175.55,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1175.07,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"The good thing about the ad or the form fills that have come through is they''ve been very qualified, like TD bank and some other very large firms that have been filling out those forms.","index":261,"end_time":1187.57,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1176.27,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But yeah, I''ll work with the team to get some fresh creative.","index":262,"end_time":1191.85,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1188.61,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Maybe we even update the language on the form to see how we can improve or increase lead quantity.","index":263,"end_time":1198.69,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1191.85,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I met with Greg last week to set up like lead source and lead source specific.","index":264,"end_time":1208.13,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1203.41,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And so the first step that we landed on this is what we established in our call.","index":265,"end_time":1212.76,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1208.53,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then I just added in a bunch more things that we''ve been working on or pretty much any source that I can think of.","index":266,"end_time":1219.16,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1212.76,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So I can give this to you in a sheet if you want to review and see if there''s anything you want to add or remove or change.","index":267,"end_time":1228.52,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1219.16,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"These will just be like event names and webinar names.","index":268,"end_time":1232.64,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1230.28,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So those are just placeholders that we''ll do when those come up.","index":269,"end_time":1235.8,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1232.64,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But other than that, I think.","index":270,"end_time":1237.4,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1235.88,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I don''t even know if you guys post on Facebook, but it''s in the footer of the website, so I added it here.","index":271,"end_time":1243.36,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1238.64,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Everything other than that is pretty.","index":272,"end_time":1247.36,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1245.76,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Should be everything that we have in.","index":273,"end_time":1252.08,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1249.6,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Terms of the organic search one.","index":274,"end_time":1253.68,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1252.08,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"How are we carrying that through to Salesforce?","index":275,"end_time":1257.76,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1254.88,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"HubSpot, that''s what we would.","index":276,"end_time":1260.64,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1257.76,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So if it comes through on their token, like if, if, if HubSpot''s able to read it, then we would have this in a lead source specific property and then we would just pass that through.","index":277,"end_time":1273.3,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1261.44,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Greg would have to.","index":278,"end_time":1274.14,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1273.3,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I don''t think we have permission to create properties anymore, but I can check.","index":279,"end_time":1277.14,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1274.14,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Greg would have to just create the lead source specific property and then add these options and then it''ll pass through one to one.","index":280,"end_time":1283.38,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1277.38,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We already built that when I met him on Friday.","index":281,"end_time":1291.28,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1285.94,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We built that into here.","index":282,"end_time":1293.6,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1292.24,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So if we go to.","index":283,"end_time":1295.28,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1294.24,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Actually, if we go to integrations, connected apps and Salesforce and Contacts and mapping.","index":284,"end_time":1306.16,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1297.04,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So lead source specific we already mapped.","index":285,"end_time":1314.48,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1312.08,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we just need to update the values that go in there.","index":286,"end_time":1317.36,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1315.12,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, just share the link to the sheet.","index":287,"end_time":1322.98,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1321.1,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"I think that''d be great.","index":288,"end_time":1323.9,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1322.98,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"I still have the task of updating the folder structures in HubSpot.","index":289,"end_time":1335.82,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1331.1,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Gotcha.","index":290,"end_time":1336.78,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1336.14,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":291,"end_time":1337.66,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1337.1,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"We talked about podcast being done Thursday and we already Talked about the SRI issue.","index":292,"end_time":1343.34,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1339.02,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Also already talked about GA4.","index":293,"end_time":1346.3,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1344.06,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So the scam flag video has been added below the hero here.","index":294,"end_time":1352.54,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1347.66,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So this is now, huh?","index":295,"end_time":1357.42,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1354.86,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I don''t like that.","index":296,"end_time":1358.46,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1357.5,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"You don''t like where it is?","index":297,"end_time":1359.74,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1358.7,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"No.","index":298,"end_time":1360.299,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1359.9,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Do we want like more of a section call out?","index":299,"end_time":1366.34,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1364.14,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Like have a different background or something?","index":300,"end_time":1367.98,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1366.34,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, Even just because I have it off of my other screen.","index":301,"end_time":1379.59,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1372.07,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Even like the resources section, which is the.","index":302,"end_time":1382.63,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1379.67,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, that would work on the page, I think.","index":303,"end_time":1392.23,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1389.03,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Oh, this is on WordPress, isn''t it?","index":304,"end_time":1394.23,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1392.31,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Rather, this is WordPress.","index":305,"end_time":1395.27,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1394.23,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":306,"end_time":1395.59,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1395.27,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I mean we can build a whole new one.","index":307,"end_time":1398.13,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1396.93,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We were building one and then we kept it on WordPress.","index":308,"end_time":1400.69,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1398.13,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But we can go back to building it in HubSpot.","index":309,"end_time":1402.53,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1400.69,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Well, after that it''s a conversation that Greg and I also having because I was doing that web audit and I stopped doing it because I don''t know whether we should even bother continuing to fix things on the WordPress site.","index":310,"end_time":1421.81,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1404.77,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"I don''t know if it''s actually worth the effort.","index":311,"end_time":1423.56,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1422.04,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"The effort.","index":312,"end_time":1424.6,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1423.8,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"So I asked Greg, like, is it something we want to look to invest in sooner rather than later or should I actually continue doing the fixes?","index":313,"end_time":1437.08,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1426.12,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Where I was going with this.","index":314,"end_time":1439.12,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1438.28,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Sorry, that was a really rambly way of getting there.","index":315,"end_time":1442,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1439.12,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"But after the homepage, I think the next priority for us to look at should be the product pages.","index":316,"end_time":1447.8,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1442,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Yeah, Product solutions pages.","index":317,"end_time":1451.2,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1449.28,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Pages are what they are, but they shouldn''t be convert.","index":318,"end_time":1457.04,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1454.08,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Shouldn''t really be converting pages.","index":319,"end_time":1460.36,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1458.64,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"The product pages I think are probably more important.","index":320,"end_time":1464.08,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1460.36,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah.","index":321,"end_time":1477.41,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1475.29,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Because the only like band aid that we put on was just adding a cta.","index":322,"end_time":1480.73,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1477.41,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":323,"end_time":1482.57,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1482.09,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"I mean these are things we can build in HubSpot.","index":324,"end_time":1487.01,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1484.97,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"If you guys prefer to.","index":325,"end_time":1487.93,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1487.01,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"To do that.","index":326,"end_time":1488.81,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1488.09,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We could rebuild them in.","index":327,"end_time":1490.33,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1488.97,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Sorry, we can rebuild them in WordPress or HubSpot.","index":328,"end_time":1500.66,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1495.13,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We could do whatever that''s like.","index":329,"end_time":1502.38,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1500.66,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"The other question is then what pages do we want as core website?","index":330,"end_time":1506.58,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1502.38,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Which ones do we want?","index":331,"end_time":1507.58,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1506.58,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Is HubSpot.","index":332,"end_time":1508.42,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1507.58,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"In my head, I thought HubSpot was just for landing pages for campaigns and paid channels and etc.","index":333,"end_time":1516.18,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1509.06,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Yeah, I mean, I think because of the subdomain.","index":334,"end_time":1521.22,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1518.74,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I think that''s a good idea.","index":335,"end_time":1522.98,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1521.22,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And obviously we can build anything in WordPress.","index":336,"end_time":1527.47,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1525.31,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We can do a full redesign and build.","index":337,"end_time":1532.59,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1530.11,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, let''s just table that one for now.","index":338,"end_time":1538.99,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1535.79,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"But yeah, if we could add a new section of, similar to like this resources section in the HubSpot page, I think that would just be it.","index":339,"end_time":1549.15,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1538.99,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"To the scam flag page.","index":340,"end_time":1550.75,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1549.47,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"The scanf black page.","index":341,"end_time":1551.91,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1550.95,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":342,"end_time":1552.31,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1551.91,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Okay, so we''ll update the video section, change the color, add a title above it and then add a resources section.","index":343,"end_time":1559.43,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1552.79,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"No, sorry, don''t need a resources section.","index":344,"end_time":1564.71,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1562.39,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"I was just saying that the resources section on the HubSpot landing page would be a good.","index":345,"end_time":1570.15,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1565.11,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"On the Q2.","index":346,"end_time":1580.24,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1579.44,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":347,"end_time":1581.04,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1580.48,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Oh, you''re saying it would be good to add the video flag to this.","index":348,"end_time":1589.76,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1586.48,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"No, sorry, I was saying that the the darker background of this as a section would work better in the Scan Flag product page with the video in that.","index":349,"end_time":1601.84,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1591.44,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Oh, okay.","index":350,"end_time":1602.96,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1601.92,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That was a really bad way of describing it.","index":351,"end_time":1605.27,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1603.55,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"That was my bad.","index":352,"end_time":1606.75,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1605.27,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"No, no, no, you''re fine.","index":353,"end_time":1608.19,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1606.99,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":354,"end_time":1617.15,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1616.51,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, we can do that.","index":355,"end_time":1618.27,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1617.23,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We did update all of the creative with the new Scan Flag logo.","index":356,"end_time":1625.99,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1620.43,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So I have.","index":357,"end_time":1626.59,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1625.99,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We have that in markup.","index":358,"end_time":1628.55,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1627.47,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Or would you prefer if we just send the files over and then the team that''s working on those ads can replace them?","index":359,"end_time":1633.71,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1628.55,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Do we want to remove this?","index":360,"end_time":1638.13,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1637.17,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yes.","index":361,"end_time":1639.25,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1638.77,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"And I think we have a version of that graphic with the ScanFag logo in the phone.","index":362,"end_time":1646.45,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1641.49,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Yeah, we do.","index":363,"end_time":1648.21,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1647.33,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Do you want that up top and in the phone?","index":364,"end_time":1650.61,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1648.21,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That''s a good point.","index":365,"end_time":1653.85,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1653.09,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Because it''s also in WhatsApp.","index":366,"end_time":1655.17,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1653.85,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"That looks like it''s.","index":367,"end_time":1656.69,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1655.41,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Yeah, it''s in WhatsApp rather than in the app.","index":368,"end_time":1659.97,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1656.93,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":369,"end_time":1661.17,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1660.97,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And it''s also just a square image in this example.","index":370,"end_time":1663.37,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1661.17,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So, I mean, seeing that would be kind of tough versus having it kind of called out up top.","index":371,"end_time":1667.45,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1663.45,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":372,"end_time":1680.73,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1680.17,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Otherwise that looks fine.","index":373,"end_time":1682.49,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1680.89,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"What about this?","index":374,"end_time":1685.45,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1684.65,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I think it makes sense there because it''s in the app, which.","index":375,"end_time":1693.9,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1688.74,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Suggesting that''s in the app.","index":376,"end_time":1695.14,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1693.9,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"I prefer that red background rather than the pink one.","index":377,"end_time":1705.14,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1702.42,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Instead of this one currently.","index":378,"end_time":1708.5,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1706.98,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But just for that one.","index":379,"end_time":1711.78,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1708.82,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":380,"end_time":1723.74,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1723.34,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Can we move the text up a bit on that one?","index":381,"end_time":1730.06,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1728.22,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Black and blue.","index":382,"end_time":1749.79,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1749.03,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"I think that works well.","index":383,"end_time":1750.87,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1749.79,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"And these are just smaller versions to run if needed.","index":384,"end_time":1757.03,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1751.59,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we have.","index":385,"end_time":1766.76,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1766.24,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It looks like probably 10 or 12 good variations that we can toss over the team.","index":386,"end_time":1770.6,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1766.76,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So I''ll get these updates made and then do you want a markup link or do you want me just send you the files?","index":387,"end_time":1774.16,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1770.6,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Send me the files if you can, please.","index":388,"end_time":1776.16,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1774.56,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Talking of the portal, actually, I don''t know why, but I can''t seem to access many of the links in there.","index":389,"end_time":1784.24,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1777.92,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"They just go to a Google link that I need.","index":390,"end_time":1790.02,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1785.44,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Do you mind sharing your screen?","index":391,"end_time":1794.02,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1792.74,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So can you give me Access to the FDE1?","index":392,"end_time":1801.94,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1798.98,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"This one just goes to.","index":393,"end_time":1816.53,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1815.41,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"I''m pretty sure there was looking at the next one last week and that one''s fine.","index":394,"end_time":1826.13,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1820.45,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":395,"end_time":1828.85,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1828.37,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"And that was.","index":396,"end_time":1834.21,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1833.33,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So is the fde.","index":397,"end_time":1836.85,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1835.57,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Oh, can you see it now?","index":398,"end_time":1854.14,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1853.18,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, I can.","index":399,"end_time":1855.38,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1854.78,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"I think you gave me access to this one specifically because I went.","index":400,"end_time":1858.54,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1855.38,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"I did the request access thing, but usually I just can normally click through.","index":401,"end_time":1862.38,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1858.94,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Yeah, all right, I''ll go back through.","index":402,"end_time":1868.39,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1862.78,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I decided that''s my TO dos.","index":403,"end_time":1886.71,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1884.95,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And for the white paper.","index":404,"end_time":1894.88,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1892.8,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So Wojtek only added one comment.","index":405,"end_time":1899.2,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1895.52,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"There''s just a text change.","index":406,"end_time":1903.28,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1901.92,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Was there anything else that we were waiting on before we start?","index":407,"end_time":1906.16,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1903.84,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"No, he liked it he didn''t have any other feedback.","index":408,"end_time":1910.96,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1907.2,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"He did question whether or not we want to include a new element of the Scan Flag product, which is the agentic fraud analyst.","index":409,"end_time":1922.17,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1912.88,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"But I think content wise I don''t want to change it.","index":410,"end_time":1928.73,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1923.85,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"So I might just ignore that suggestion.","index":411,"end_time":1932.17,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1930.09,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Ignore this one?","index":412,"end_time":1933.29,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1932.41,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"No, from the other suggestion.","index":413,"end_time":1935.29,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1933.53,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Oh, our first Game Flag.","index":414,"end_time":1937.93,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1936.49,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":415,"end_time":1938.57,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1938.09,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Okay.","index":416,"end_time":1939.29,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1938.73,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right, cool.","index":417,"end_time":1939.97,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1939.37,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we''ll start working through that then.","index":418,"end_time":1941.29,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1939.97,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":419,"end_time":1942.25,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1941.77,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"And then we''ll do a more in depth analysis like we talked about for performance and budgets.","index":420,"end_time":1951.46,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1945.7,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But we did pause more broad match campaigns in Google Ads.","index":421,"end_time":1956.02,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1951.46,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Click through Rate''s good, but the searches are just too generic.","index":422,"end_time":1958.7,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1956.1,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I really don''t think Google Ads is your channel and I think that''s going to be part of my recommendation.","index":423,"end_time":1962.5,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1958.7,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"LinkedIn ads.","index":424,"end_time":1965.78,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1964.74,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It is time to rotate this because we''re seeing people click but not fill out the form for the PDF downloads.","index":425,"end_time":1974.37,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1967.94,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"The Q2 campaign is getting Click through Rate pretty high.","index":426,"end_time":1979.21,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1975.81,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I mean 0.44 is the industry benchmark that we shoot for.","index":427,"end_time":1982.05,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1979.21,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we''re going through that but we''re not seeing people convert on the landing page.","index":428,"end_time":1986.69,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1983.41,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then on Adroll it''s the geo targeting campaign.","index":429,"end_time":1994.45,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1989.57,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Clicks did double on that from three to six, week over week.","index":430,"end_time":1997.73,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1994.93,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And the bill for bank ad is the top performer.","index":431,"end_time":2000.76,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1998.76,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But we''ll put together a more in depth analysis and that is everything that I had.","index":432,"end_time":2012.68,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2004.04,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Any questions on.","index":433,"end_time":2013.6,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2012.68,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Anything, anything else you wanted to dive into?","index":434,"end_time":2015.16,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2013.6,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I actually had a new request for some creative.","index":435,"end_time":2026.12,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2023,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"So we''re going to start the newsletter on a monthly basis going forward.","index":436,"end_time":2033.6,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2028.6,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"And we''ve also started a content series which is we''re calling a bulletin.","index":437,"end_time":2038.12,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2033.6,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"It''s basically a fraud in the news roundup from the last month with one threat mark element point chucked in can.","index":438,"end_time":2048.04,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2038.44,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"I''d like to get some creative that I can use as a template for the monthly content, both the newsletter and for the article.","index":439,"end_time":2060.11,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2049.72,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"But I''d like it to be similar to the Behind Enemy Lines style.","index":440,"end_time":2066.11,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2060.67,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"If I give you the specs for what I would use, can you build me some templates?","index":441,"end_time":2072.67,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2067.63,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Yeah, of course.","index":442,"end_time":2073.55,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2072.83,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Great.","index":443,"end_time":2074.59,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2074.19,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"You said newsletter and bulletin.","index":444,"end_time":2087.96,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2084.84,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I think we''re calling it the.","index":445,"end_time":2089.96,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2088.84,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"The Banking Threat Bulletin.","index":446,"end_time":2091.8,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2090.2,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Banking Intel Bulletin.","index":447,"end_time":2093.72,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2092.12,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"My God, my head is all over the place today.","index":448,"end_time":2097.16,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2095.32,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Seems like it''s one of those days.","index":449,"end_time":2101.24,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2099.96,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, okay.","index":450,"end_time":2104,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2101.56,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Yeah, we can do that.","index":451,"end_time":2104.76,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2104,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So let me recap.","index":452,"end_time":2105.96,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2105,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Unless you have anything else.","index":453,"end_time":2107.08,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2105.96,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":454,"end_time":2108.67,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2108.27,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we''ll see what we can do for workflows in the future.","index":455,"end_time":2112.79,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2108.67,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"To avoid sending on weekends.","index":456,"end_time":2114.43,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2112.79,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Build a rotating resources module for the Q2 page.","index":457,"end_time":2121.55,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2115.07,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Update padding on the hero section of the November Newsletter Goodness gracious.","index":458,"end_time":2126.03,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2121.63,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"November Newsletter Email Once you finalize content, we''ll write a performance report and budget recommendation for paid ads, Design fresh creative and see how we can increase Lead Quantity for PDF LinkedIn Lead Gen Update the ScanFlag landing page video section to have the background of the Q2 page resources section and add a title to call it out.","index":459,"end_time":2150.85,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2126.03,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Update designs for the scanflag ads based on the markup comments that we just left and then share that finalized folder with you.","index":460,"end_time":2158.05,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2151.73,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Review the final deliverable links in Pulse to make sure that you can access all of them.","index":461,"end_time":2162.93,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2159.25,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Update the FDE white paper based on markup feedback and then once you share specs for a design package for newsletter and bulletin will design new creative similar to the Behind Enemy Lines.","index":462,"end_time":2174.19,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2163.09,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then on your side, think through any GA4 events that you want to set up.","index":463,"end_time":2181.23,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2175.23,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Get the two website environments in sync, finalize content for November newsletter, review the lead source and lead source specific breakdown and I have a link to that spreadsheet and think through what pages we would like for HubSpot versus what pages should live on WordPress and then sharing the design package spec.","index":464,"end_time":2200.49,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2181.87,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I think that''s everything.","index":465,"end_time":2206.17,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2205.13,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yep.","index":466,"end_time":2207.61,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2206.97,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"All right.","index":467,"end_time":2209.45,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2208.81,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And when you click on the link for the lead source thing, just make sure you go to the updated instead of the original tab.","index":468,"end_time":2214.81,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2209.45,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":469,"end_time":2215.77,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2215.29,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"All right, well thank you very much.","index":470,"end_time":2218.81,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2216.65,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right.","index":471,"end_time":2221.06,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2220.82,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Have a great rest of your day.","index":472,"end_time":2222.02,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2221.06,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Feel better.","index":473,"end_time":2222.82,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2222.18,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Thank you.","index":474,"end_time":2223.78,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2223.22,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Hope your day smooths out as well.","index":475,"end_time":2226.5,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2224.98,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Thanks.","index":476,"end_time":2227.38,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2226.9,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Bye Bye.","index":477,"end_time":2228.82,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2228.02,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"}],"dateString":"2025-11-12T14:30:00.000Z","host_email":"colin.costigan@marketersindemand.com","meeting_link":"https://us02web.zoom.us/j/84564648866?pwd=JR6eWxlxKbgogzCqTNUawSLUUhQoEa.1","participants":["colin.costigan@marketersindemand.com,kate.burwood@threatmark.com,gregory.smith@threatmark.com","kate.burwood@threatmark.com","gregory.smith@threatmark.com"],"transcript_url":"https://app.fireflies.ai/view/01K9AJMT8K0HJWBRB2PDPJYF5T","organizer_email":"colin.costigan@marketersindemand.com"}'::jsonb,
    '{"label":"positive","confidence":0.91,"bullets":["Introduced two new team members to support marketing and client work across time zones.","Resolved GA4 tracking issue; site now has only four clean custom events configured.","Patched SRI vulnerability across both environments; QA completed to ensure stability.","Planned creative refresh and performance review for LinkedIn and Google Ads campaigns.","Agreed to sync staging and production websites; IT task assigned and tracked to Andre."],"highlights":[{"quote":"The GA4 account is pretty much a clean slate.","speaker":"Colin Costigan"},{"quote":"We also probably need to do a performance review.","speaker":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"quote":"We patched it and we''re checking it today.","speaker":"Colin Costigan"}],"topics":["delivery","hiring","tracking","ads","security"],"model":"openai/gpt-4-1106-preview","version":1,"generated_at":"2025-11-13T00:00:00Z"}'::jsonb,
    '{"fireflies_summary":{"notes":"## **Team and Resource Updates**\n\nThe team is expanding with new skilled members to improve collaboration and timezone coverage.\n\n- **Nina, a new team member with about 10 years of experience,** has been supporting Colin’s team for the last **three to four weeks** and will now join all relevant calls and Slack channels (00:30).\n    - Nina''s proximity to the client’s timezone will enhance real-time responsiveness.\n    - Colin highlighted past issues with onboarding Monica to emphasize smoother integration this time.\n    - This addition aims to strengthen account management and execution quality.\n    - Nina’s involvement will free Colin to focus on higher-level strategy and oversight.\n\n- **Kate announced a new marketing hire starting next week, based in London,** focusing on event sponsorship and APM activities (01:21).\n    - The new hire will undergo onboarding for a couple of weeks before engaging in meetings.\n    - Kate will decide which calls the new marketer should attend, ensuring targeted involvement.\n    - This role supports expanding marketing reach and campaign execution in the UK market.\n    - The addition aligns with broader marketing growth and event-driven lead generation plans.\n\n## **Website and Technical Infrastructure**\n\nUpdating and synchronizing environments is critical for efficient development and consistent production quality.\n\n- **WordPress core and plugins were updated across the test environment,** with a full functional test confirming no broken pages (03:53).\n    - Colin stressed the importance of syncing staging with the live environment to streamline future updates.\n    - Kate agreed this task should be handled by the IT team or delegated with proper admin access.\n    - Current hosting is on **AWS for production** and **Azure** for other systems, with security controls limiting access (04:48).\n    - Aligning environments will allow building and testing features like the homepage banner on staging before going live, reducing risk.\n\n- **The security vulnerability related to SRI was patched on both environments,** with verification ongoing to ensure script integrity (06:57).\n    - Andres from IT managed the patching process, ensuring compliance and security.\n    - This work was necessary to maintain system stability and protect against exploits.\n    - Continuous monitoring is planned to prevent future vulnerabilities.\n    - The update supports the overall IT security posture and website reliability.\n\n## **Product and Content Updates**\n\nRefining content presentation and creative assets will better engage users and drive conversions.\n\n- **A new rotating homepage design will showcase four key elements:** the “Talk to a fraud fighter” callout replacing “Win the war against Fraud,” the AI versus fraud white paper, a Scan Flag push, and an episode titled \"Why can''t I fry something? Fry, Aaron, fry\" (07:49).\n    - Colin plans to finalize episode titles by Thursday with multiple options for flexibility.\n    - Kate emphasized keeping titles simple and tied closely to campaign messaging.\n    - This refresh aims to improve visitor engagement and clarity of messaging on the homepage.\n    - The episode content serves as a user engagement tool within the campaign framework.\n\n- **Scan Flag landing page video placement will be improved by adding a distinct section with a darker background and a title,** inspired by the Q2 page resource section style (22:37).\n    - Kate requested repositioning the video to create a stronger visual callout.\n    - Colin noted all Scan Flag creative has been updated with the new logo and will share final assets as files.\n    - This update is expected to increase product visibility and user interaction.\n    - The redesign aligns with broader branding consistency efforts.\n\n- **HubSpot landing pages require new modules: a scrolling resources section to expand beyond three columns,** supporting more dynamic content on the Q2 landing page (14:32).\n    - Colin will assign his team to build this customized module.\n    - This will improve content management flexibility and user navigation.\n    - Enhancements will support ongoing campaign resource linking.\n    - Kate’s request highlights a need for easier content scalability within HubSpot.\n\n- **A monthly newsletter and a new fraud news roundup bulletin will launch,** requiring fresh creative templates modeled on the existing “Behind Enemy Lines” style (33:43).\n    - Kate requested creative assets for both formats to maintain brand consistency.\n    - Colin confirmed the team will build these templates after receiving design specs.\n    - This initiative aims to increase regular audience engagement with timely content.\n    - The bulletin will integrate ThreatMark insights to differentiate from generic news.\n\n## **Marketing Campaigns and Performance**\n\nCampaigns are being reviewed and refreshed to improve lead quality while managing budget effectively.\n\n- **LinkedIn targeting for fraud professionals is being refined with ongoing campaign adjustments,** and a broader awareness campaign is planned for discussion next week (18:24).\n    - Kate flagged a slowdown in LinkedIn lead volume, prompting the need for creative refresh and performance review.\n    - Colin noted strong lead quality from recent forms, including submissions from large firms like TD Bank.\n    - The budget and campaign effectiveness will be reassessed to optimize spend and results.\n    - This reflects a shift toward quality leads and more strategic ad placements.\n\n- **Google Ads broad match campaigns were paused due to generic search traffic,** with click-through rates below target effectiveness and poor channel fit identified by Colin (32:25).\n    - The current benchmark CTR is **0.44%**, which Q2 campaigns are achieving but with low landing page conversions.\n    - AdRoll geo-targeting campaigns showed clicks doubling from **3 to 6 week-over-week**, with the “bill for bank” ad as the top performer.\n    - Future recommendations include focusing on platforms with better conversion potential like LinkedIn.\n    - This adjustment aims to improve ROI by concentrating on high-impact channels.\n\n- **Lead source tracking was enhanced with a detailed spreadsheet mapping various event names and channels,** ready for review and integration with HubSpot and Salesforce by Greg (19:35).\n    - Colin explained the need for Greg to create specific lead source properties in Salesforce for smooth data flow.\n    - This ensures accurate attribution and improves marketing analytics.\n    - Kate will review the sheet and update HubSpot folder structures accordingly.\n    - Precise tracking supports better campaign measurement and decision making.\n\n## **Workflow and Process Improvements**\n\nAdjustments in marketing automation and access management will increase operational efficiency.\n\n- **HubSpot email workflow delays were shortened from five to four days to align with Wednesday send targets,** but changing steps for contacts already in delay proved challenging (10:02).\n    - Colin will investigate options to remove or adjust contacts in active delay steps for future flexibility.\n    - He highlighted HubSpot’s limitation without a business-days add-on, which complicates scheduling.\n    - Future workflows will be designed more cautiously to avoid weekend sends without extra costs.\n    - These changes aim to reduce errors and improve timing precision in email campaigns.\n\n- **Access issues with the FDE portal and deliverable links were identified,** with Colin committing to review and restore proper permissions for Kate (29:34).\n    - The problem caused some links to redirect incorrectly to Google access requests.\n    - Fixing this will streamline content review and reduce friction in collaboration.\n    - This action supports smoother project management and stakeholder communication.\n    - Ensuring correct access is critical for timely feedback and approvals.\n\n- **Discussions are ongoing about which pages should remain on WordPress versus HubSpot,** with a tentative view to keep HubSpot for landing pages related to campaigns and paid channels (25:02).\n    - Kate and Greg are evaluating whether to invest in fixing WordPress or to migrate more content.\n    - Colin confirmed flexibility to rebuild product and solution pages on either platform.\n    - This decision will impact future development workflows and content management.\n    - Aligning platform use with marketing strategy will improve site performance and user experience.","outline":null,"keywords":["Website Staging","GA4 Events","HubSpot Workflows","Scan Flag","LinkedIn Ads","Newsletter Design"],"overview":"- **Team Expansion:** Nina joins the team to enhance real-time client support, improving account management and strategic focus for Colin.\n\n- **Marketing Hire:** New marketer starts next week in London, focusing on UK event sponsorship and targeted campaign engagement.\n\n- **Technical Updates:** WordPress environments updated and secured; synchronizing staging with production for smoother future updates and reduced risk.\n\n- **Content Enhancements:** Homepage redesign includes new engagement tools; improved video placement will boost product visibility and branding consistency.\n\n- **Campaign Analysis:** LinkedIn targeting adjustments are needed; AdRoll campaigns show improved click performance; focus on quality leads is essential for ROI.\n\n- **Workflow Improvements:** HubSpot workflows streamlined for better timing; access issues in FDE portal will be resolved to improve collaboration efficiency.","action_items":"\n**Colin Costigan**\nIntegrate new team member Nina into calls and Slack channels (00:30)\nPatch verification for SRI vulnerability on live and staging environments (07:49)\nAdjust padding on November newsletter hero section after content finalized by client (15:54)\nDevelop a new scrollable resource module for Q2 landing page in HubSpot (14:43)\nRefresh LinkedIn creative and update PDF form language to increase lead quantity (19:35)\nShare lead source mapping spreadsheet with Kate for review (20:52)\nRedesign Scan Flag landing page video section with darker background and added title (25:52)\nUpdate Scan Flag ad creative per markup notes and send finalized files to client (29:34)\nProvide client with access to portal documents and resolve access issues (30:54)\nUpdate FDE whitepaper text as per feedback and proceed with no additional product element (31:47)\nPrepare performance report and budget recommendation for paid ads (35:04)\nDesign newsletter and bulletin creative templates after receiving specs (34:44)\n\n**Kate Burwood**\nConfirm any new GA4 event tracking requirements (03:46)\nFinalize newsletter content and complete email draft by end of day (17:54)\nConsider and decide on the balance of HubSpot versus WordPress pages (25:18)\nShare design package specs for newsletter and bulletin creative (34:44)\n\n**Gregory Smith**\nCreate or update lead source specific properties in HubSpot Salesforce integration (20:57)\nAssist with syncing staging and production website environments on AWS (04:42)\n"},"migrated_from":"contract_meetings","original_id":"8ebcd98f-cf24-4f90-bd9d-34147cc42643","master_marketer":{"status":"migrated"}}'::jsonb,
