  'meeting',
  'Meeting Notes: New North <> ThreatMark: Weekly Marketing Meeting',
  '## **Team and Resource Updates**

The team is expanding with new skilled members to improve collaboration and timezone coverage.

- **Nina, a new team member with about 10 years of experience,** has been supporting Colin’s team for the last **three to four weeks** and will now join all relevant calls and Slack channels (00:30).
    - Nina''s proximity to the client’s timezone will enhance real-time responsiveness.
    - Colin highlighted past issues with onboarding Monica to emphasize smoother integration this time.
    - This addition aims to strengthen account management and execution quality.
    - Nina’s involvement will free Colin to focus on higher-level strategy and oversight.

- **Kate announced a new marketing hire starting next week, based in London,** focusing on event sponsorship and APM activities (01:21).
    - The new hire will undergo onboarding for a couple of weeks before engaging in meetings.
    - Kate will decide which calls the new marketer should attend, ensuring targeted involvement.
    - This role supports expanding marketing reach and campaign execution in the UK market.
    - The addition aligns with broader marketing growth and event-driven lead generation plans.

## **Website and Technical Infrastructure**

Updating and synchronizing environments is critical for efficient development and consistent production quality.

- **WordPress core and plugins were updated across the test environment,** with a full functional test confirming no broken pages (03:53).
    - Colin stressed the importance of syncing staging with the live environment to streamline future updates.
    - Kate agreed this task should be handled by the IT team or delegated with proper admin access.
    - Current hosting is on **AWS for production** and **Azure** for other systems, with security controls limiting access (04:48).
    - Aligning environments will allow building and testing features like the homepage banner on staging before going live, reducing risk.

- **The security vulnerability related to SRI was patched on both environments,** with verification ongoing to ensure script integrity (06:57).
    - Andres from IT managed the patching process, ensuring compliance and security.
    - This work was necessary to maintain system stability and protect against exploits.
    - Continuous monitoring is planned to prevent future vulnerabilities.
    - The update supports the overall IT security posture and website reliability.

## **Product and Content Updates**

Refining content presentation and creative assets will better engage users and drive conversions.

- **A new rotating homepage design will showcase four key elements:** the “Talk to a fraud fighter” callout replacing “Win the war against Fraud,” the AI versus fraud white paper, a Scan Flag push, and an episode titled "Why can''t I fry something? Fry, Aaron, fry" (07:49).
    - Colin plans to finalize episode titles by Thursday with multiple options for flexibility.
    - Kate emphasized keeping titles simple and tied closely to campaign messaging.
    - This refresh aims to improve visitor engagement and clarity of messaging on the homepage.
    - The episode content serves as a user engagement tool within the campaign framework.

- **Scan Flag landing page video placement will be improved by adding a distinct section with a darker background and a title,** inspired by the Q2 page resource section style (22:37).
    - Kate requested repositioning the video to create a stronger visual callout.
    - Colin noted all Scan Flag creative has been updated with the new logo and will share final assets as files.
    - This update is expected to increase product visibility and user interaction.
    - The redesign aligns with broader branding consistency efforts.

- **HubSpot landing pages require new modules: a scrolling resources section to expand beyond three columns,** supporting more dynamic content on the Q2 landing page (14:32).
    - Colin will assign his team to build this customized module.
    - This will improve content management flexibility and user navigation.
    - Enhancements will support ongoing campaign resource linking.
    - Kate’s request highlights a need for easier content scalability within HubSpot.

- **A monthly newsletter and a new fraud news roundup bulletin will launch,** requiring fresh creative templates modeled on the existing “Behind Enemy Lines” style (33:43).
    - Kate requested creative assets for both formats to maintain brand consistency.
    - Colin confirmed the team will build these templates after receiving design specs.
    - This initiative aims to increase regular audience engagement with timely content.
    - The bulletin will integrate ThreatMark insights to differentiate from generic news.

## **Marketing Campaigns and Performance**

Campaigns are being reviewed and refreshed to improve lead quality while managing budget effectively.

- **LinkedIn targeting for fraud professionals is being refined with ongoing campaign adjustments,** and a broader awareness campaign is planned for discussion next week (18:24).
    - Kate flagged a slowdown in LinkedIn lead volume, prompting the need for creative refresh and performance review.
    - Colin noted strong lead quality from recent forms, including submissions from large firms like TD Bank.
    - The budget and campaign effectiveness will be reassessed to optimize spend and results.
    - This reflects a shift toward quality leads and more strategic ad placements.

- **Google Ads broad match campaigns were paused due to generic search traffic,** with click-through rates below target effectiveness and poor channel fit identified by Colin (32:25).
    - The current benchmark CTR is **0.44%**, which Q2 campaigns are achieving but with low landing page conversions.
    - AdRoll geo-targeting campaigns showed clicks doubling from **3 to 6 week-over-week**, with the “bill for bank” ad as the top performer.
    - Future recommendations include focusing on platforms with better conversion potential like LinkedIn.
    - This adjustment aims to improve ROI by concentrating on high-impact channels.

- **Lead source tracking was enhanced with a detailed spreadsheet mapping various event names and channels,** ready for review and integration with HubSpot and Salesforce by Greg (19:35).
    - Colin explained the need for Greg to create specific lead source properties in Salesforce for smooth data flow.
    - This ensures accurate attribution and improves marketing analytics.
    - Kate will review the sheet and update HubSpot folder structures accordingly.
    - Precise tracking supports better campaign measurement and decision making.

## **Workflow and Process Improvements**

Adjustments in marketing automation and access management will increase operational efficiency.

- **HubSpot email workflow delays were shortened from five to four days to align with Wednesday send targets,** but changing steps for contacts already in delay proved challenging (10:02).
    - Colin will investigate options to remove or adjust contacts in active delay steps for future flexibility.
    - He highlighted HubSpot’s limitation without a business-days add-on, which complicates scheduling.
    - Future workflows will be designed more cautiously to avoid weekend sends without extra costs.
    - These changes aim to reduce errors and improve timing precision in email campaigns.

- **Access issues with the FDE portal and deliverable links were identified,** with Colin committing to review and restore proper permissions for Kate (29:34).
    - The problem caused some links to redirect incorrectly to Google access requests.
    - Fixing this will streamline content review and reduce friction in collaboration.
    - This action supports smoother project management and stakeholder communication.
    - Ensuring correct access is critical for timely feedback and approvals.

- **Discussions are ongoing about which pages should remain on WordPress versus HubSpot,** with a tentative view to keep HubSpot for landing pages related to campaigns and paid channels (25:02).
    - Kate and Greg are evaluating whether to invest in fixing WordPress or to migrate more content.
    - Colin confirmed flexibility to rebuild product and solution pages on either platform.
    - This decision will impact future development workflows and content management.
    - Aligning platform use with marketing strategy will improve site performance and user experience.',
