    '{"id":"01K9E41XHB5QXHVDWWZXPBX0BV","title":"Weekly Marketing Meeting (Shockoe <> New North)","summary":{"notes":"## **Campaign Strategy and Budget Allocation**\n\nThe team shifted the entire campaign budget to the **Vibe coding campaign** from last week to improve lead generation results, moving away from a previously underfunded **$16 daily** AI lead gen campaign that reached a broad audience of **310,000 people** but saw low conversions (23:24).  \n- Colin explained that the prior campaign’s budget was too thin to deliver meaningful conversions despite some impressions.  \n- The new budget allocation aims to focus resources effectively on a smaller, more targeted audience to improve lead quality and conversion rates.  \n- The team expects to monitor early results next week to evaluate the impact of this reallocation.  \n- This decision aligns with the need to improve ROI by prioritizing campaigns with clearer target segments and higher engagement potential.\n\nThe outreach target list focuses on businesses in the **United States**, **United Kingdom**, and New Zealand, within hospitality, hotels, marketing, and leisure travel sectors, filtered for companies with revenues between **$10 million and $1 billion** and employee sizes from **10 to 5,000** (17:09).  \n- Targeted roles include engineers, marketing directors, creative directors, product operations, and VPs of technology.  \n- The list limits outreach to **five contacts per company** to maintain focused and quality engagement.  \n- Colin plans to enrich contact info with emails and proceed with outreach pending final asset approvals.  \n- The outreach strategy targets decision-makers aligned with tech and design to increase relevance and response rates.\n\n## **Creative and Messaging Updates**\n\nThe team updated the **Vibe coding landing page** and LinkedIn ads to simplify user experience, replacing lengthy forms with a quick, simple form and embedding lead gen forms directly on LinkedIn to reduce friction (08:05).  \n- This streamlining is designed to increase conversion rates by lowering barriers for lead submission.  \n- Misty highlighted the need for more dynamic and relevant imagery, especially on screens featuring **St. Andrews links**, suggesting golf course visuals over generic phone images for better engagement (09:47).  \n- Colin and Edwin agreed to incorporate a background image showing both the **castle** and golf course to better represent the client’s brand and product.  \n- Kylee emphasized refining copy alignment and margin spacing to improve ad polish and professionalism, especially clarifying that the app is presented, not the company name.\n\nThe **Foxwoods and St. Andrews** campaigns had content updates, removing outdated language like “600 year legacy” and shifting focus toward emphasizing technology collaboration and user experience (08:05; 14:27).  \n- Kylee suggested tying the messaging to the **Sports Business Journal (SBJ) Tech Award** nomination category focusing on collaboration and technology integration.  \n- Colin committed to making the messaging cohesive across campaigns and softer in tone to reinforce authenticity and the existing partnership narrative.  \n- Tom’s LinkedIn posts about partnerships and user experience will be leveraged to support campaign messaging and award submissions.\n\n## **Content and Website Development**\n\nThe team is preparing to launch a new **product page for Venda (Zenda)**, targeting a launch early next week, with the page mostly designed but requiring final reviews and approvals (29:11).  \n- Misty noted the page will differ from existing landing pages because it uses a distinct product brand requiring a new template rather than reusable components.  \n- Kylee indicated that while reusable components exist for the site, this product page will need special development, but the goal remains to create a reusable template for future products.  \n- Colin expects to provide a timeline for development once Figma designs are finalized and submitted.  \n- The team agreed on a quick turnaround approach similar to the blog process: build a draft version first, then finalize the template after content approval.\n\nContent quality control improvements were discussed regarding blog posts, where some URLs led to **404 errors** because content was made private or links were broken (22:41).  \n- Colin will have developers conduct a sweep to clean up typos and dead links that caused over **1,200 broken links** in the Google Search Console sitemap over the past two months.  \n- Edwin emphasized the importance of fixing these 404s to improve SEO and user experience, as Google continues to crawl invalid URLs.  \n- Misty flagged an image in the **strategy blog** appearing blurry due to incorrect rendering size; Colin confirmed a fix will be applied immediately to ensure images display correctly without compression issues (26:20).\n\n## **Timelines, Feedback, and Process Improvements**\n\nThe team agreed on a deadline of **next Monday, end of day** for feedback on campaign assets, including landing pages, email copy, and ad creatives, to enable a launch the following week (25:56).  \n- Colin emphasized flexibility if delays occur, allowing the launch schedule to adjust accordingly.  \n- Misty committed to reviewing the materials and providing consolidated feedback by the deadline.  \n- The team will refresh caches regularly to prevent delays and confusion caused by stale content showing outdated blog posts or incorrect landing pages.  \n- A process was reinforced to double-check URLs and content status in platforms like WordPress and HubSpot to avoid similar issues in the future.\n\nColin and Kylee discussed aligning messaging and formatting to maintain brand consistency, including spacing and copy adjustments based on feedback from the strategist team (12:37).  \n- Misty and Kylee shared internal PDFs and best practices to ensure ad and landing page compliance with platform requirements and brand guidelines.  \n- The team agreed on a workflow where content is reviewed collaboratively before final deployment to avoid errors and improve user engagement.  \n- Monitoring and quick issue resolution protocols, such as image replacements and URL fixes, were established to maintain campaign quality post-launch.\n\n## **Award Submission and Competitive Positioning**\n\nThe team is leveraging the **Sports Business Journal Tech Award** opportunity to showcase the company’s collaboration with St. Andrews and other tech partners, focusing on API integrations and technology innovation (15:24).  \n- Kylee has engaged with Tom and reviewed award criteria to align messaging strategically with SBJ expectations.  \n- Colin plans to craft messaging that highlights genuine collaboration without overstating achievements, reinforcing credibility.  \n- The award submission serves as a platform to differentiate the company in a competitive market by spotlighting tech partnerships and user experience enhancements.  \n- This initiative supports long-term brand positioning as a technology leader in sports-related software solutions.\n\n## **Speaker and Team Integration**\n\nNew team member **Nina** was introduced and integrated into strategy calls, working closely with Colin on backend tasks supporting campaign execution (03:17).  \n- Nina’s involvement helps increase strategic capacity and supports data analysis for ongoing campaigns.  \n- Edwin and Misty continue to coordinate closely with Colin and Kylee to ensure alignment across marketing, strategy, and development teams.  \n- The team emphasized open communication channels, including Slack and email, for swift feedback and issue resolution during campaign build and launch phases.  \n- Colin and Kylee’s ongoing collaboration ensures that design, copy, and technical elements remain aligned with business goals and brand standards.","outline":null,"keywords":["Vibe Coding","St. Andrews Campaign","SBJ Awards","Landing Pages","Google Search Console","Email Outreach"],"overview":"- **Campaign Budget Shift:** Entire budget redirected to Vibe coding campaign for better lead generation, moving from a $16 daily AI campaign.  \n- **Targeting Strategy:** Focus on US, UK, and NZ businesses in hospitality with revenues of $10 million to $1 billion.  \n- **Creative Updates:** Simplified landing pages and LinkedIn ads to enhance user experience and boost conversion rates.  \n- **404 Error Resolution:** Developers will address over 1,200 broken links to improve SEO and user experience.  \n- **Feedback Deadline:** Feedback due by Monday to ensure timely campaign asset launches the following week.  \n- **Award Submission Focus:** Emphasizing collaboration for Sports Business Journal Tech Award to enhance brand positioning in the tech market.","action_items":"\n**Colin Costigan**\nShare updated SBJ ads based on received feedback (25:32)\nReview and enrich the target company/contact list including addition of New Zealand; send the updated list to Edwin (17:28)\nInvestigate reported Google Search Console 404 errors and coordinate with developers to fix broken links and typos; provide status update to Edwin (22:41)\nReplace blurry image on strategy blog with the new file provided by Misty and republish (26:01)\nDeliver timeline and development plan for Zenda product page upon receipt of design files from Misty/Daniela (30:34)\n\n**Edwin Huertas**\nShare SBJ PDF specs with Colin; build new target list adding New Zealand in HubSpot (18:50)\nReview HubSpot list for campaign alignment and report on sitemap issues for broken links/404s seen in Google Search Console (22:41)\n\n**Misty Smith**\nProvide feedback on campaign marketing assets by next Monday EOD to meet launch schedule (25:56)\nFinalize and send Zenda product page design to Colin for development review (29:31)\nFix image upload/rendering issue on strategy blog and other associated blogs by adjusting image render sizes (27:03)\n"},"duration":34.40999984741211,"speakers":[{"id":0,"name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"id":1,"name":"Misty Smith"},{"id":2,"name":"Colin Costigan"},{"id":3,"name":"Colin Costigan"},{"id":4,"name":"Kylee Anger"}],"sentences":[{"text":"All right.","index":0,"end_time":180.1,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":179.62,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"Hey, Nina.","index":1,"end_time":183.06,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":182.18,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"Hello.","index":2,"end_time":184.42,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":183.94,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"How are you?","index":3,"end_time":186.02,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":185.22,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"Hey, Coin.","index":4,"end_time":186.9,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":186.1,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"Edwin.","index":5,"end_time":187.7,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":187.22,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You''re just trying to beat me to these calls, aren''t you?","index":6,"end_time":189.46,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":187.7,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Always.","index":7,"end_time":190.34,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":189.94,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"Every time.","index":8,"end_time":191.7,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":190.98,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"Oh, it''s good to see you.","index":9,"end_time":193.98,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":192.74,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":10,"end_time":194.34,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":193.98,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I wanted to introduce you to Nina as well.","index":11,"end_time":195.98,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":194.34,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Sorry, Nina, I cut you off.","index":12,"end_time":197.14,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":195.98,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Oh, no, I was just saying hello.","index":13,"end_time":201.38,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":197.86,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"So I''m.","index":14,"end_time":203.14,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":202.34,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"The new strategies on the team.","index":15,"end_time":206.93,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":203.54,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"So, yeah, I''m joining my first call with Colin.","index":16,"end_time":209.81,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":207.09,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":17,"end_time":211.33,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":210.77,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"You have a lot of fun and good.","index":18,"end_time":213.01,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":211.57,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"I. I hope.","index":19,"end_time":213.89,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":213.01,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":20,"end_time":215.97,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":215.57,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Nina''s been working with us for a few weeks now.","index":21,"end_time":218.61,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":215.97,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"She''s been in the back end helping out with shocker stuff, so wanted to start getting her on these calls moving forward.","index":22,"end_time":223.81,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":218.77,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And just always, always enhance the.","index":23,"end_time":227.73,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":225.73,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Value that we''re providing.","index":24,"end_time":228.69,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":227.73,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Of course.","index":25,"end_time":230.01,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":229.49,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"Thank you.","index":26,"end_time":230.61,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":230.01,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"Nice to meet you, Nina.","index":27,"end_time":231.69,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":230.81,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"How are you doing, Edwin?","index":28,"end_time":234.09,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":233.13,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"How was your weekend?","index":29,"end_time":234.81,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":234.09,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Pretty good.","index":30,"end_time":238.05,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":237.37,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"No, no changes until the usuals, I guess.","index":31,"end_time":241.37,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":238.05,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":32,"end_time":242.09,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":241.61,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Were you guys closed yesterday or.","index":33,"end_time":243.69,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":242.09,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"No, we.","index":34,"end_time":244.97,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":244.33,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"We.","index":35,"end_time":245.69,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":245.29,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"We.","index":36,"end_time":246.09,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":245.69,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"We worked.","index":37,"end_time":247.21,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":246.33,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"I. I didn''t even know.","index":38,"end_time":248.69,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":247.45,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"That was probably until Monday afternoon.","index":39,"end_time":251.93,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":248.69,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":40,"end_time":252.73,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":252.25,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, the weekend was too fast, as always.","index":41,"end_time":258.1,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":254.49,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Right?","index":42,"end_time":258.58,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":258.18,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Usually it''s cold too.","index":43,"end_time":261.3,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":259.46,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"Yeah, I''m guessing it''s probably.","index":44,"end_time":263.38,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":261.78,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":45,"end_time":264.18,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":263.7,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Nina, where are you located?","index":46,"end_time":265.94,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":264.66,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"I''m located in Belgrade, Serbia.","index":47,"end_time":273.86,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":269.94,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"Oh, nice.","index":48,"end_time":275.38,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":274.42,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"It''s cold.","index":49,"end_time":276.26,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":275.62,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"It''s not fall over there, is it?","index":50,"end_time":277.62,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":276.26,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"Not yet.","index":51,"end_time":278.18,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":277.62,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"No, not.","index":52,"end_time":279.74,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":279.06,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"Not as the rest of Europe.","index":53,"end_time":281.62,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":279.74,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"So.","index":54,"end_time":282.26,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":281.86,"speaker_name":"Kylee Anger"},{"text":"Yeah, we''re good in the south.","index":55,"end_time":284.02,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":282.26,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"Yourself, I guess.","index":56,"end_time":285.65,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":284.61,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"I figured.","index":57,"end_time":286.45,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":285.65,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"All right, Miss is almost there.","index":58,"end_time":289.25,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":286.53,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"She''s joining.","index":59,"end_time":290.17,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":289.25,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"My.","index":60,"end_time":290.49,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":290.17,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"My computer''s really slow.","index":61,"end_time":293.41,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":290.49,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"Are you guys in the same office right now?","index":62,"end_time":295.57,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":293.97,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We are in the same office right now.","index":63,"end_time":297.41,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":295.97,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"That''s cool.","index":64,"end_time":298.05,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":297.41,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We.","index":65,"end_time":298.45,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":298.13,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"On Wednesdays.","index":66,"end_time":299.17,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":298.45,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"We''re now trying.","index":67,"end_time":299.89,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":299.17,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"Trying a new thing.","index":68,"end_time":300.93,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":299.89,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"Gotcha.","index":69,"end_time":302.53,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":301.89,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":70,"end_time":302.93,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":302.53,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Did you.","index":71,"end_time":303.65,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":303.09,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"Did you have fun and rich one?","index":72,"end_time":305.05,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":303.65,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"You never.","index":73,"end_time":305.45,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":305.05,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"You never See?","index":74,"end_time":306.17,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":305.45,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"I told you.","index":75,"end_time":306.73,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":306.17,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"You''re gonna invite me and then you''re gonna disinvite me.","index":76,"end_time":308.73,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":306.73,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"Any.","index":77,"end_time":308.97,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":308.73,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"Any.","index":78,"end_time":309.33,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":308.97,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"I''ll tell you, I actually ended up feeling kind of sick later on in the day, so.","index":79,"end_time":316.19,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":311.79,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, I wasn''t much.","index":80,"end_time":317.15,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":316.19,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Much fun either.","index":81,"end_time":318.43,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":317.23,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I mean, we.","index":82,"end_time":321.55,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":319.55,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We had a good day of planning.","index":83,"end_time":322.95,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":321.55,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then, yeah, very quick dinner and.","index":84,"end_time":326.07,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":322.95,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I was like, I need to get.","index":85,"end_time":326.91,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":326.07,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Back to the hotel room and lay down.","index":86,"end_time":328.43,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":326.91,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Nice.","index":87,"end_time":329.67,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":329.23,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"Oh, it''s fine.","index":88,"end_time":330.47,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":329.67,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"At least you.","index":89,"end_time":331.15,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":330.47,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"You enjoyed some food and then went back to.","index":90,"end_time":333.75,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":331.79,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"That''s okay.","index":91,"end_time":334.43,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":333.75,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":92,"end_time":334.87,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":334.51,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"There she is.","index":93,"end_time":335.27,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":334.87,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"And I keep hearing that I need to go downtown into Richmond, and I''m just.","index":94,"end_time":338.43,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":335.27,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, you should next time.","index":95,"end_time":340.53,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":339.17,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"Where in Richmond are you right now?","index":96,"end_time":343.97,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":341.73,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"I was there last Monday.","index":97,"end_time":345.65,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":344.53,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We were at.","index":98,"end_time":347.25,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":346.37,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"What''s the name?","index":99,"end_time":348.21,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":347.25,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Short Pump.","index":100,"end_time":350.29,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":349.49,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"Yeah, the hotel I stayed at was.","index":101,"end_time":352.77,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":350.93,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It had Short Pump in the name.","index":102,"end_time":354.45,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":353.01,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I''m trying to remember where we had.","index":103,"end_time":356.33,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":355.09,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Our actual meeting itself, though.","index":104,"end_time":358.21,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":356.33,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It was Dominion Club.","index":105,"end_time":362.53,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":360.13,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"If you guys know that.","index":106,"end_time":365.58,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":364.78,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, it''s nice over there.","index":107,"end_time":367.9,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":366.46,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"Yeah, it was a cool time.","index":108,"end_time":369.74,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":367.9,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Is Kai joining us today?","index":109,"end_time":371.66,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":370.38,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"She should.","index":110,"end_time":373.5,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":372.78,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"I don''t know.","index":111,"end_time":374.46,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":373.82,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"She normally is.","index":112,"end_time":375.98,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":374.94,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":113,"end_time":376.94,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":376.46,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"And should.","index":114,"end_time":378.1,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":377.5,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Having some issues.","index":115,"end_time":378.86,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":378.1,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Ah, that''s what she said.","index":116,"end_time":382.14,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":379.98,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"Having some Zoom issues beyond as soon as possible.","index":117,"end_time":385.9,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":383.82,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"There you go.","index":118,"end_time":387.18,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":386.46,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"Yeah, I. I understand.","index":119,"end_time":389.66,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":388.22,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"I''m in the.","index":120,"end_time":390.38,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":389.74,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"Was in the same boat.","index":121,"end_time":391.54,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":390.7,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"It was moving.","index":122,"end_time":392.06,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":391.54,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"My cable.","index":123,"end_time":392.54,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":392.06,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"My computer as a whole was moving a little slow.","index":124,"end_time":394.54,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":392.54,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"Yeah, well, and it''s not even only that.","index":125,"end_time":397.22,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":395.34,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It''s.","index":126,"end_time":397.58,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":397.22,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"This has been a weird year for the Internet.","index":127,"end_time":400.14,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":398.14,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I mean, Azure going down.","index":128,"end_time":402.38,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":400.14,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"AWS having issues.","index":129,"end_time":403.82,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":402.38,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Google having issues.","index":130,"end_time":405.18,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":404.14,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Like it''s everyone''s.","index":131,"end_time":406.42,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":405.18,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Someone''s playing with the.","index":132,"end_time":407.54,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":406.42,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"The Internet plug and just ruining days.","index":133,"end_time":410.22,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":407.54,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Misty, how was your weekend?","index":134,"end_time":414.86,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":413.5,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Resetting the router, I guess.","index":135,"end_time":416.54,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":415.02,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":136,"end_time":417.26,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":416.94,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"Yeah, it''s time to unplug and plug it back in.","index":137,"end_time":419.74,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":417.5,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"It was good.","index":138,"end_time":421.42,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":420.7,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"I can''t even remember what we did that.","index":139,"end_time":425.06,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":422.54,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"That''s sad.","index":140,"end_time":425.82,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":425.06,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"Oh, I gotcha.","index":141,"end_time":428.42,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":427.58,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And I''m sorry if you had a heart attack this morning.","index":142,"end_time":430.54,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":428.42,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I''m glad that everything was clean.","index":143,"end_time":431.9,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":430.54,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"For most users, it was a caching issue.","index":144,"end_time":433.74,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":431.9,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":145,"end_time":434.54,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":434.06,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"Your browser.","index":146,"end_time":435.46,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":434.78,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So.","index":147,"end_time":435.74,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":435.46,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":148,"end_time":436.78,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":436.14,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"Yeah, I just.","index":149,"end_time":437.7,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":436.94,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"I was like, hey, wait a second.","index":150,"end_time":439.58,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":437.7,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"This.","index":151,"end_time":440.7,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":440.3,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"Something''s not right.","index":152,"end_time":441.66,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":440.7,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":153,"end_time":442.18,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":441.82,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And when I click on it, I''m like, in a 404.","index":154,"end_time":444.3,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":442.18,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"Oh, my God.","index":155,"end_time":445.1,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":444.3,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"Oh, yeah.","index":156,"end_time":446.18,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":445.46,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Please, if anything you ever see, please let me know and we''ll check into it.","index":157,"end_time":450.18,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":446.18,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And hopefully 99% of the time it is.","index":158,"end_time":453.06,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":450.18,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Or hopefully 100% of the time it.","index":159,"end_time":454.94,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":453.06,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Is, it''s actually shown correctly for everyone.","index":160,"end_time":457.18,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":454.94,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":161,"end_time":457.54,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":457.18,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"Yeah, that was.","index":162,"end_time":458.06,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":457.54,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":163,"end_time":458.3,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":458.06,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"Hopefully that made me feel better once it was resolved.","index":164,"end_time":461.86,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":458.3,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":165,"end_time":462.26,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":461.86,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"Great.","index":166,"end_time":462.9,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":462.5,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we''ll go through some project updates and things we''re working on.","index":167,"end_time":466.06,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":463.46,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Edwin, I want to go over also the spreadsheet that you sent over on Monday, and then we''ll go through some analytics.","index":168,"end_time":472.74,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":466.06,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Oh, and Misty, you joined after we introduced Nina, so wanted to introduce you to Nina.","index":169,"end_time":477.31,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":473.59,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"She joined our team a few weeks ago, working on the strategist side of things, and she''s been working in the.","index":170,"end_time":482.55,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":477.31,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"In the back end with me on Shotgun.","index":171,"end_time":484.39,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":482.55,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Fantastic.","index":172,"end_time":486.19,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":485.35,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"Nice to meet you.","index":173,"end_time":487.11,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":486.19,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"All right, let''s get going.","index":174,"end_time":491.83,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":490.39,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So, as we talked about, we reallocated budget to the Vibe coding campaign.","index":175,"end_time":498.39,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":493.35,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And here''s Kai joining.","index":176,"end_time":499.99,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":498.39,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And as I dive into the data and analytics slide, that''ll support why we made that decision.","index":177,"end_time":506.68,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":502.92,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So that is set up.","index":178,"end_time":510.44,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":507.72,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Moving forward, we''ve also.","index":179,"end_time":511.88,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":510.44,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Hey, Kai, how are you doing?","index":180,"end_time":513.16,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":511.96,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We''ve also updated the Vibe coding landing page as we showed to the prototype to production approach and simplified the process so it''s not a bunch of questions they have to answer, but instead just.","index":181,"end_time":525.8,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":514.28,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"A pretty quick, simple form that they.","index":182,"end_time":527.96,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":525.88,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Fill out if they make it to the landing page.","index":183,"end_time":529.44,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":527.96,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then for the LinkedIn ads, switching that to a lead gen form so.","index":184,"end_time":533.16,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":529.44,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"They don''t even have to leave LinkedIn.","index":185,"end_time":534.96,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":533.16,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"They can submit a lead form right there.","index":186,"end_time":536.72,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":535.04,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"For the St. Andrews.","index":187,"end_time":539.6,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":538.32,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Oh my goodness.","index":188,"end_time":540.56,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":539.68,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I felt Kai yelling at me.","index":189,"end_time":543.68,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":542.24,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"For the St. Andrews and Foxwoods campaign removed and switched over from the 600 year legacy type language.","index":190,"end_time":553.04,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":546.08,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And so I shared all of those assets over this morning.","index":191,"end_time":556,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":553.36,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I know that was a lot of.","index":192,"end_time":556.8,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":556,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Markup links to go through, so I.","index":193,"end_time":558.52,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":556.8,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Don''T imagine you''ve had a chance to review them all, but let me know.","index":194,"end_time":561.32,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":558.52,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then we can spin those up.","index":195,"end_time":562.64,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":561.32,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then also Edwin, we created a few variations for the SVJ add.","index":196,"end_time":571.04,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":567.12,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Misty, I do see what you mean.","index":197,"end_time":572.52,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":571.28,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Of this Foxwood screenshot that made it.","index":198,"end_time":574.479,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":572.52,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"In there, but we wanted to give a few different options that we can run or we can come up with.","index":199,"end_time":581,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":574.479,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Something totally new here.","index":200,"end_time":582.16,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":581,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"My only initial thought and looking at this, like very quickly, I literally like opened it, scrolled through it and that''s it.","index":201,"end_time":594.37,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":587.45,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"I didn''t read it in.","index":202,"end_time":595.37,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":594.37,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"I didn''t read the provision detail was that on the screens where you have St. Andrew''s links, we should use a different image because it''s the most boring image that is there.","index":203,"end_time":609.29,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":595.37,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"If you have, if you already have the name of the.","index":204,"end_time":611.85,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":609.45,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"The name of the client, then like, yeah, that.","index":205,"end_time":616.43,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":612.55,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"Like, why not a golf course?","index":206,"end_time":617.91,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":616.43,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"Like, why not one of the.","index":207,"end_time":619.19,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":618.07,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"One of the.","index":208,"end_time":619.83,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":619.19,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"Something a little more dynamic or exciting because that shows nothing other than the name of the client.","index":209,"end_time":626.63,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":620.31,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"I see.","index":210,"end_time":627.07,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":626.63,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"What.","index":211,"end_time":627.27,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":627.07,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"You know, if you pair that with where it says Shako because you don''t have the client''s name.","index":212,"end_time":631.15,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":627.27,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"Okay.","index":213,"end_time":631.67,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":631.15,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"But I don''t think that''s our best foot forward, you know, from that perspective.","index":214,"end_time":639.2,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":631.83,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"I don''t know if I don''t have a specific recommendation in mind and this is where Kai could probably weigh in a lot better.","index":215,"end_time":644.56,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":639.2,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"But I just, you know, as you scroll down, some of the other options that you had, you know, like that one say it says St. Andrews League, the great big letters and Modernize t