elated because.","index":316,"end_time":928.49,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":924.46,"speaker_name":"Kylee Anger"},{"text":"Sorry, maybe not related.","index":317,"end_time":929.93,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":928.57,"speaker_name":"Kylee Anger"},{"text":"These.","index":318,"end_time":930.33,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":929.93,"speaker_name":"Kylee Anger"},{"text":"Yeah, no, it is related because these are for your SBA sbj campaign.","index":319,"end_time":933.65,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":930.33,"speaker_name":"Kylee Anger"},{"text":"Right.","index":320,"end_time":934.01,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":933.65,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"So for the SBJ Tech award, the category, I think that actually fits the best because it''s not for fans necessarily.","index":321,"end_time":945.17,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":935.29,"speaker_name":"Kylee Anger"},{"text":"It''s not for, like, real athletes or, like, real leagues is the collaboration one.","index":322,"end_time":951.21,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":945.17,"speaker_name":"Kylee Anger"},{"text":"And if you think about all the teams that we needed to collaborate to bring together a cool technology.","index":323,"end_time":955.13,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":951.21,"speaker_name":"Kylee Anger"},{"text":"Right.","index":324,"end_time":956.72,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":956.6,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"Like, there were all of those golf integrations and obviously we were working closely with St Andrews, so it''s the collaboration in tech category.","index":325,"end_time":967.92,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":956.72,"speaker_name":"Kylee Anger"},{"text":"And I''ve already talked to Tom about this as well and seeing if they have any input for us.","index":326,"end_time":971.2,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":967.92,"speaker_name":"Kylee Anger"},{"text":"And it''s really focused on, like, APIs and technologies.","index":327,"end_time":973.44,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":971.2,"speaker_name":"Kylee Anger"},{"text":"I don''t know if there''s an opportunity to.","index":328,"end_time":975.44,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":973.44,"speaker_name":"Kylee Anger"},{"text":"Colin.","index":329,"end_time":976.04,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":975.44,"speaker_name":"Kylee Anger"},{"text":"For us to, like, tie all of this together.","index":330,"end_time":978.44,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":976.36,"speaker_name":"Kylee Anger"},{"text":"Like, I think that if we''re trying to nail on the same message, hopefully if, like, the person reviewing the SBJ nomination, like, sees that we''re really.","index":331,"end_time":987.56,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":979.72,"speaker_name":"Kylee Anger"},{"text":"And we''re not just making up on the fly, I think it might be cool to.","index":332,"end_time":990.9,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":987.56,"speaker_name":"Kylee Anger"},{"text":"To try to, like, make sure we''re thinking all of that.","index":333,"end_time":994.18,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":990.9,"speaker_name":"Kylee Anger"},{"text":"Yeah, I''ll think through some ways that we can make it not, like, so in your face, but like, like, nice.","index":334,"end_time":1001.22,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":994.42,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All works together type of thing.","index":335,"end_time":1002.58,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1001.22,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Right.","index":336,"end_time":1003.1,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1002.82,"speaker_name":"Kylee Anger"},{"text":"Like, we already have the content out there about how we collaborated with all these different tech teams.","index":337,"end_time":1009.3,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1003.1,"speaker_name":"Kylee Anger"},{"text":"Tech, you know, vendors in sports.","index":338,"end_time":1011.38,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1009.3,"speaker_name":"Kylee Anger"},{"text":"Like, then we''re.","index":339,"end_time":1012.3,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1011.38,"speaker_name":"Kylee Anger"},{"text":"Yeah, we''re not just making anything up like that.","index":340,"end_time":1014.58,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1012.3,"speaker_name":"Kylee Anger"},{"text":"That content already is out there.","index":341,"end_time":1016.03,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1014.75,"speaker_name":"Kylee Anger"},{"text":"And I don''t know if you''ve seen the award categories, but I can send you the link as well so that you can understand, like, what SBJ is looking for us to answer specifically.","index":342,"end_time":1026.99,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1016.03,"speaker_name":"Kylee Anger"},{"text":"Yeah, that would be great.","index":343,"end_time":1029.07,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1028.11,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":344,"end_time":1029.71,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1029.07,"speaker_name":"Kylee Anger"},{"text":"And Kai, your, like, your rule and.","index":345,"end_time":1035.87,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1031.55,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And really their brand rule.","index":346,"end_time":1037.03,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1035.87,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Is so ingrained in my head now that anytime I see St. Andrews mentioned, like, I always see it with the period.","index":347,"end_time":1042.98,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1037.03,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I''ve not seen it one time without the period.","index":348,"end_time":1045.54,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1043.54,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Like in Netflix shows, like all sorts.","index":349,"end_time":1048.74,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1045.7,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Of stuff, everybody''s doing it wrong.","index":350,"end_time":1050.42,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1048.74,"speaker_name":"Kylee Anger"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":351,"end_time":1050.98,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1050.5,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That''S so funny.","index":352,"end_time":1054.1,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1053.14,"speaker_name":"Kylee Anger"},{"text":"I mean, that''s like a general thing for me.","index":353,"end_time":1057.34,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1055.54,"speaker_name":"Kylee Anger"},{"text":"Like, anytime I look at an app, I''m instantly like, ah, you did this wrong.","index":354,"end_time":1060.38,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1057.34,"speaker_name":"Kylee Anger"},{"text":"Or.","index":355,"end_time":1060.66,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1060.38,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"Yeah, that''s marketing, right?","index":356,"end_time":1062.9,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1060.66,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":357,"end_time":1063.5,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1063.06,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":358,"end_time":1064.02,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1063.5,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":359,"end_time":1064.9,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1064.34,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then, Edwin, I''ll also share this with you.","index":360,"end_time":1066.78,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1064.98,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I wanted to walk through it a little bit though.","index":361,"end_time":1068.18,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1066.78,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Actually, I already had it open.","index":362,"end_time":1069.24,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1068.36,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"This is the company list and then contact list that we''ve put together for the outreach for the new campaign.","index":363,"end_time":1074.76,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1069.64,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And so we went with United States and United Kingdom Focus and businesses with.","index":364,"end_time":1081.8,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1075.64,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I can actually pull up the parameters here.","index":365,"end_time":1085.4,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1083.32,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So, like a lot of around hospitality, hotels, marketing, leisure travel, sports revenue starting at the 10 million and going up to a billion range.","index":366,"end_time":1103.09,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1094.69,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then employee sizes 10 to 50.","index":367,"end_time":1106.69,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1103.89,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All the way up to 5,000 for the team count.","index":368,"end_time":1110.37,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1106.69,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":369,"end_time":1111.49,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1111.01,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"In HubSpot yesterday, I created a new target list that almost matches this or hospitality resource call.","index":370,"end_time":1122.5,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1112.45,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"I will add New Zealand in this.","index":371,"end_time":1128.26,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1125.46,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"Okay.","index":372,"end_time":1129.38,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1128.82,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I think everything else should be.","index":373,"end_time":1132.54,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1130.98,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"Should be fine.","index":374,"end_time":1133.38,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1132.54,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"Okay, perfect.","index":375,"end_time":1134.58,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1133.7,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And we went ahead and also.","index":376,"end_time":1137.22,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1135.62,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And we can add to this list, but identified some top titles of people that we want to talk to.","index":377,"end_time":1143.86,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1137.46,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So engineer, marketing director, creative director, a.","index":378,"end_time":1148.35,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1143.86,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Mix of those types of titles, and.","index":379,"end_time":1149.67,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1148.35,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We limited it to five people per company.","index":380,"end_time":1151.43,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1149.67,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You know, product operations, VP of technology.","index":381,"end_time":1156.15,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1153.59,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So all the titles that we''ve kind of established through the months.","index":382,"end_time":1160.95,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1157.19,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But I''ll send this over if you wanted to take a deeper look and.","index":383,"end_time":1163.55,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1161.19,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"See if there''s anything that jumps out.","index":384,"end_time":1164.87,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1163.55,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"No, that''s good.","index":385,"end_time":1166.71,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1165.99,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"Yeah, you can send it over whenever you''re ready.","index":386,"end_time":1168.39,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1166.71,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"All right, perfect.","index":387,"end_time":1169.43,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1168.55,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then once we''re good there, I''ll.","index":388,"end_time":1171.47,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1170.07,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We''ll enrich and get their email addresses and then we can.","index":389,"end_time":1173.83,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1171.47,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"If there''s no changes made to the campaign after all the links we sent.","index":390,"end_time":1177.32,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1174.72,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Over today, then we can get this live next week.","index":391,"end_time":1179.8,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1177.32,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"The one thing there is, we are creating new emails because the server that.","index":392,"end_time":1185.12,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1179.8,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We were using was blacklisted.","index":393,"end_time":1187.56,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1185.12,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And so we caught that and we''re rotating how we''re creating our email domains.","index":394,"end_time":1191.16,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1187.56,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Again so they''ll go through some warm.","index":395,"end_time":1193.6,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1191.16,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Up, but they''ll also be sending just at a slower cadence while they warm up.","index":396,"end_time":1197.36,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1193.6,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right, so after you guys give some feedback on all the resources we sent over today, we''ll finalize all of those for the vibe coding and the.","index":397,"end_time":1212.97,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1204.41,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Foxwoods and St Andrews.","index":398,"end_time":1214.57,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1212.97,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So that''s the landing pages, Email, copy, ad, creative, everything.","index":399,"end_time":1218.17,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1214.97,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then Misty, I put the titles in here just to double, triple, quadruple, check that.","index":400,"end_time":1224.21,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1218.97,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We''re always referring to tech and design.","index":401,"end_time":1225.85,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1224.21,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"The.","index":402,"end_time":1226.15,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1225.93,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"That.","index":403,"end_time":1226.38,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1226.22,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I know exactly what you guys are referring to.","index":404,"end_time":1228.02,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1226.38,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So design is elevating the Foxwoods experience.","index":405,"end_time":1230.14,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1228.02,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That''s live tomorrow.","index":406,"end_time":1231.82,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1230.3,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yes.","index":407,"end_time":1232.78,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1232.3,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"Great.","index":408,"end_time":1233.74,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1233.34,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And Fox Tech Blog is Foxwood''s powering a premium experience next week.","index":409,"end_time":1238.78,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1233.82,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yes.","index":410,"end_time":1239.54,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1239.1,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"I got confused because, like I said when I.","index":411,"end_time":1241.9,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1239.54,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"The screen that I.","index":412,"end_time":1243.02,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1241.9,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"The way the web.","index":413,"end_time":1244.46,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1243.5,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"The way the webpage looked when I loaded it, the link, the URL was going to elevating the fox was experience, and that was the verbiage that was on the page.","index":414,"end_time":1253.18,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1244.46,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"So I just assumed, okay, this is where it''s going.","index":415,"end_time":1255.41,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1253.57,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"And I was like, wait a second, something''s not right.","index":416,"end_time":1257.61,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1255.41,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"And so I would just.","index":417,"end_time":1258.45,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1257.61,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"It was obviously thoroughly confusing for me, but we''re.","index":418,"end_time":1262.61,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1259.41,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"You guys got it squared away, and if we could just.","index":419,"end_time":1265.17,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1262.77,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":420,"end_time":1265.45,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1265.17,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"Maybe refresh the cache every.","index":421,"end_time":1267.53,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1265.45,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"Reset the cache every time.","index":422,"end_time":1268.85,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1267.53,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"Because it''s.","index":423,"end_time":1271.09,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1270.21,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"It''s odd that it went from no blog at all to the wrong blog to now.","index":424,"end_time":1277.29,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1271.81,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"It''s fine.","index":425,"end_time":1277.89,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1277.29,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"So I''m just like, if we could skip that intermediary step, then.","index":426,"end_time":1280.53,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1277.89,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, yeah, of course.","index":427,"end_time":1281.89,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1280.53,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":428,"end_time":1283.47,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1283.31,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And I did go into HubSpot and the social calendar just to make sure.","index":429,"end_time":1287.23,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1283.47,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That I was looking at all the right blogs and everything too.","index":430,"end_time":1289.27,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1287.23,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Perfect.","index":431,"end_time":1289.71,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1289.27,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"Perfect.","index":432,"end_time":1290.43,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1289.95,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"That''s great.","index":433,"end_time":1291.11,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1290.51,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"Yes.","index":434,"end_time":1291.43,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1291.11,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"And I mean, I might be pushing some of that out as we bring in, you know, some of this lovely award stuff or tie it to.","index":435,"end_time":1299.39,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1291.43,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"To this post we were just looking at for Tom.","index":436,"end_time":1301.87,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1299.63,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"But it''s still.","index":437,"end_time":1303.71,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1302.35,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"It won''t change the order you''ve gotten it in right now or the timing.","index":438,"end_time":1308.15,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1303.79,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"So it''s perfect.","index":439,"end_time":1308.87,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1308.15,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"Thank you.","index":440,"end_time":1309.39,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1308.87,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":441,"end_time":1309.95,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1309.39,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right.","index":442,"end_time":1310.91,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1310.43,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then, Edwin, I want to go through this.","index":443,"end_time":1313.75,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1312.03,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So I know in your message when you had sent this over, you said you thought maybe it was a difference of having, like, the blog slug in there.","index":444,"end_time":1320.99,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1313.75,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"WordPress actually.","index":445,"end_time":1322.83,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1321.95,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So these are posts that were changed to private at some point.","index":446,"end_time":1325.95,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1322.83,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So someone had decided, like, I don''t want this out there.","index":447,"end_time":1328.91,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1326.11,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"If it.","index":448,"end_time":1329.63,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1329.07,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Even if it had slash blog in it and it was live, it would automatically redirect through WordPress to a live blog.","index":449,"end_time":1335.55,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1329.63,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But what we can do is just go through, like, I noticed some typos in there of URLs.","index":450,"end_time":1342.4,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1337,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So, like, instead of Virginia Credit Union, like, I want to really.","index":451,"end_time":1345.36,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1342.4,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I need to discover where that link came from.","index":452,"end_time":1347.56,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1345.36,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Where did someone click on that?","index":453,"end_time":1348.84,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1347.56,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Because it should be credit, not create.","index":454,"end_time":1350.6,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1348.84,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And that case study isn''t even written or live in its new form, but we can go through and do a.","index":455,"end_time":1358.08,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1351.64,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Sweep of information like that.","index":456,"end_time":1359.48,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1358.08,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, the recently broadcast, it jumped to me because it was 1200 links that were disappeared, like in the last two months.","index":457,"end_time":1371.88,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1361.16,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"So on our Google Search console, it shows that we still have it on our.","index":458,"end_time":1378.04,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1373.64,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"What is it called?","index":459,"end_time":1382,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1381.24,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"Side map.","index":460,"end_time":1383.8,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1382,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"Oh, sitemap.","index":461,"end_time":1385.48,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1384.52,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"And it''s trying to crawl these, but they''re not.","index":462,"end_time":1389.8,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1386.44,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"They''re not working.","index":463,"end_time":1390.44,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1389.96,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"So these are 404s.","index":464,"end_time":1392.188,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1390.44,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"404s.","index":465,"end_time":1393.64,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1392.452,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"So you can go into the Google Search console.","index":466,"end_time":1396.56,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1394.52,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"You see them there.","index":467,"end_time":1397.4,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1396.56,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"Okay.","index":468,"end_time":1398.32,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1397.8,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right, I''ll have our developers review that again and then I''ll get you.","index":469,"end_time":1402.04,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1398.32,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"An update on that.","index":470,"end_time":1402.84,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1402.04,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Thank you.","index":471,"end_time":1404.44,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1403.88,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"Yeah, of course.","index":472,"end_time":1405.24,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1404.52,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then the last thing was this is kind of the supporting piece to what we started out with of moving the budget over to Vibe coding.","index":473,"end_time":1414.2,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1407.96,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"The budget previously for the lead gen AI campaign was $16 a day, which is a very thin budget to spread across the audience.","index":474,"end_time":1421.97,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1415.57,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We were seeing some impressions, but not people converting.","index":475,"end_time":1424.77,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1422.45,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So that''s why we made the decision to move it away.","index":476,"end_time":1426.53,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1424.77,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Same with the ABM company list.","index":477,"end_time":1429.57,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1427.33,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That was a much broader.","index":478,"end_time":1431.01,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1429.57,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we had reached almost 400, but again, a budget restraint there out of the 310,000 people that we had built into the audience.","index":479,"end_time":1438.69,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1431.489,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So again, this all supports moving, which we have already done and talked about last week, all of the budget to the Vibe coding campaign.","index":480,"end_time":1445.94,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1439.65,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":481,"end_time":1451.06,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1450.42,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"And that is everything that we had ready to talk today.","index":482,"end_time":1455.86,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1452.66,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Since when you change the budget last week or this week?","index":483,"end_time":1460.02,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1456.5,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"Nina, do you know off the top of your head?","index":484,"end_time":1462.34,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1460.82,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I think that we allocated the budget.","index":485,"end_time":1468.82,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1466.98,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"Around the beginning of last week, so.","index":486,"end_time":1472.28,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1469.46,"speaker_name":"Kylee Anger"},{"text":"Or beginning.","index":487,"end_time":1473.96,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1472.92,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"No, it would have been the end.","index":488,"end_time":1474.8,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1473.96,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Of last week because we had enough.","index":489,"end_time":1478.04,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1474.8,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Data to find out if it''s good or not yet.","index":490,"end_time":1480.04,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1478.04,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, yeah.","index":491,"end_time":1480.92,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1480.04,"speaker_name":"Kylee Anger"},{"text":"We''re too early to know, like, the impact of it.","index":492,"end_time":1483.32,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1480.92,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":493,"end_time":1485.48,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1484.84,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"Was there any questions or anything that you guys wanted to walk through?","index":494,"end_time":1492.44,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1489.96,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I don''t have anything else.","index":495,"end_time":1497.81,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1496.61,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"Sorry.","index":496,"end_time":1500.21,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1499.89,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"I decided to unmute.","index":497,"end_time":1501.49,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1500.21,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"So as far as the.","index":498,"end_time":1503.17,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1501.57,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"I just want to get a few things straight from a timing perspective or in my head, from a sports business journal perspective.","index":499,"end_time":1509.17,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1503.25,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"Are you.","index":500,"end_time":1510.21,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1509.65,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"What are the next steps?","index":501,"end_time":1511.29,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1510.37,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"Are you going to make some tweaks to the imagery in the.","index":502,"end_time":1514.13,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1511.29,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"In the files and get those back over to us?","index":503,"end_time":1516.13,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1514.13,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"Okay, cool.","index":504,"end_time":1516.85,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1516.13,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"I just wanted to double check, so then it''ll be on us to again review and provide any feedback to you.","index":505,"end_time":1523.97,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1516.85,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"I believe that those are due.","index":506,"end_time":1525.89,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1524.45,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"Well, the Original date was December 3rd.","index":507,"end_time":1529.23,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1526.99,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"We''ve got a little bit of time, but not a ton.","index":508,"end_time":1532.43,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1529.47,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, we can definitely make that.","index":509,"end_time":1534.91,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1532.99,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, awesome.","index":510,"end_time":1536.27,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1535.23,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"And then the campaign stuff, when do you need that feedback?","index":511,"end_time":1543.15,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1536.59,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"Like, you sent us a whole bunch of links this morning, and for better or worse, we''ve all been occupied with other things, so I''m just trying to.","index":512,"end_time":1551.15,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1543.15,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"How quickly do you need feedback on those?","index":513,"end_time":1553.07,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1551.23,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"Like, when are you trying to launch those campaigns, send those emails, et cetera?","index":514,"end_time":1556.43,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1553.07,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"Yeah, I would like to get them live next week.","index":515,"end_time":1558.45,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1556.77,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Whatever''s realistic.","index":516,"end_time":1560.89,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1559.97,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"On your end, though, I don''t want to put you guys into a bind, so I''m not sure if, like, by Monday end of day would be possible.","index":517,"end_time":1567.09,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1560.89,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, next Monday, end of day.","index":518,"end_time":1569.33,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1567.65,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"Yes.","index":519,"end_time":1569.89,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1569.41,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, perfect.","index":520,"end_time":1571.33,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1570.29,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"I think we can.","index":521,"end_time":1572.489,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1571.65,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"I think we can figure that one out.","index":522,"end_time":1574.13,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1572.489,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"And just let me know if anything comes up and we can adjust things on our side for launch and everything.","index":523,"end_time":1580.05,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1574.37,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, fantastic.","index":524,"end_time":1582.37,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1580.69,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"And then the other thing is, I sent over a Slack while we were in this meeting.","index":525,"end_time":1586.65,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1582.77,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"One of the images in the blog is.","index":526,"end_time":1589.37,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1587.37,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"It looks a little blurry, so it didn''t when we previewed it, but now that it''s live, it does.","index":527,"end_time":1595.85,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1589.37,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"So I just sent over a new file.","index":528,"end_time":1599.21,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1596.33,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"If we could get that replaced or.","index":529,"end_time":1603.69,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1599.61,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"I don''t know if it''s something to do with some sort of compression or something else that''s happening, but we''ll find out.","index":530,"end_time":1609.41,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1603.69,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"Once you replace that file, if we''re still seeing that problem, then it''s something else.","index":531,"end_time":1613.77,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1609.41,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"But if you could get that done sooner rather than later, like sort of off schedule, that would be fantastic.","index":532,"end_time":1620.85,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1615.41,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"I got you.","index":533,"end_time":1621.89,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1621.17,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Thank you.","index":534,"end_time":1623.01,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1622.37,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":535,"end_time":1623.37,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1623.01,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"And that is the strategy blog.","index":536,"end_time":1625.93,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1623.37,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, so that''s the one.","index":537,"end_time":1626.61,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1625.93,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It is the strategy blog.","index":538,"end_time":1628.21,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1626.61,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"Yes, it is the strat.","index":539,"end_time":1630.33,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1628.45,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"Insights and whatever.","index":540,"end_time":1631.73,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1630.33,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"Something.","index":541,"end_time":1633.25,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1632.85,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":542,"end_time":1633.65,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1633.33,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"From insight to impact.","index":543,"end_time":1634.37,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1633.65,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That''s it.","index":544,"end_time":1635.65,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1635.01,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"That''s it.","index":545,"end_time":1636.33,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1635.81,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"Yes, it''s the strategy blog and it''s.","index":546,"end_time":1638.29,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1636.33,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"You''ll see which image because it''s the one that matched.","index":547,"end_time":1641.9,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1639.74,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"I see what happened.","index":548,"end_time":1643.34,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1641.9,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":549,"end_time":1644.22,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1643.66,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"Was it something we did or something that helps?","index":550,"end_time":1647.02,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1644.7,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":551,"end_time":1647.78,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1647.34,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So when you go in here and you put the image in, you have to make sure that it renders to full size.","index":552,"end_time":1652.78,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1647.78,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Otherwise it would show, like, a really small one in a large space.","index":553,"end_time":1657.18,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1653.42,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Oh, okay.","index":554,"end_time":1658.54,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1657.58,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"No, Misty, Colin and I went through the blog thing, and I don''t think you were in that meeting and I was not.","index":555,"end_time":1664.06,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1658.54,"speaker_name":"Kylee Anger"},{"text":"No, that was one step that wasn''t just copying or like.","index":556,"end_time":1667.27,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1664.3,"speaker_name":"Kylee Anger"},{"text":"Yeah, okay.","index":557,"end_time":1668.59,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1667.27,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":558,"end_time":1668.83,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1668.59,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"Then that''s on me.","index":559,"end_time":1669.71,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1668.83,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"Then.","index":560,"end_time":1670.15,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1669.87,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"I did that.","index":561,"end_time":1670.83,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1670.15,"speaker_name":"Kylee Anger"},{"text":"So I will.","index":562,"end_time":1671.91,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1671.23,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":563,"end_time":1672.23,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1671.91,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"Then I won''t fix the other blogs and make that magic happen.","index":564,"end_time":1676.75,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1672.23,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"Cool.","index":565,"end_time":1677.83,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1677.39,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"Now I know I would have forgotten until I did my.","index":566,"end_time":1680.51,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1677.83,"speaker_name":"Kylee Anger"},{"text":"My own to tell you so, no, not your fault, Misty.","index":567,"end_time":1683.95,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1680.67,"speaker_name":"Kylee Anger"},{"text":"Okay, cool.","index":568,"end_time":1685.07,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1684.19,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"Well, fantastic.","index":569,"end_time":1686.39,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1685.23,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"If we could just get that republished and that would be fantastic.","index":570,"end_time":1691.27,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1686.39,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"And then like I said, I''ll fix the other two.","index":571,"end_time":1692.91,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1691.27,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"The kitty split, no problem.","index":572,"end_time":1695.12,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1693.6,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"Thank you.","index":573,"end_time":1695.76,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1695.2,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"I appreciate you getting on that so quickly.","index":574,"end_time":1698.96,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1696.56,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"Of course.","index":575,"end_time":1699.56,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1699.04,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Now I know how I. I messed this up, though.","index":576,"end_time":1702.08,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1699.56,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"Now I know.","index":577,"end_time":1702.6,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1702.08,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":578,"end_time":1702.92,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1702.6,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And so here''s just a quick preview.","index":579,"end_time":1704.48,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1702.92,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"What''s the thing?","index":580,"end_time":1706.56,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1705.76,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"Weird thing is the preview came up fine for me before, but like I said, it could be just the way I was looking at it, you know?","index":581,"end_time":1713.84,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1706.64,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"Oh, yep, yep.","index":582,"end_time":1714.44,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1713.84,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"There''s.","index":583,"end_time":1714.72,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1714.44,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"Everything''s there.","index":584,"end_time":1715.36,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1714.72,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"All right, cool.","index":585,"end_time":1717,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1716.24,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right, I''ll get this updated and then I''ll.","index":586,"end_time":1718.48,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1717,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You change them all in that file.","index":587,"end_time":1721.91,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1720.47,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"Right?","index":588,"end_time":1722.23,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1721.91,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"Okay.","index":589,"end_time":1723.11,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1722.63,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"Yes.","index":590,"end_time":1723.43,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1723.11,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, just in that post.","index":591,"end_time":1724.23,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1723.43,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And I''m going to go do the same thing on staging so that we''re one to one.","index":592,"end_time":1726.71,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1724.23,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, cool.","index":593,"end_time":1728.19,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1727.27,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"And then I''ll fix this other two in staging so that way.","index":594,"end_time":1731.03,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1728.19,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"Okay, perfect.","index":595,"end_time":1731.75,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1731.03,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"Thank you.","index":596,"end_time":1732.95,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1732.31,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"All right.","index":597,"end_time":1733.55,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1733.03,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":598,"end_time":1733.91,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1733.55,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Thank you all.","index":599,"end_time":1734.55,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1733.91,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right, have a great rest of your day, everybody.","index":600,"end_time":1737.39,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1735.43,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":601,"end_time":1737.71,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1737.39,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"Sorry, I just have one more question.","index":602,"end_time":1738.95,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1737.71,"speaker_name":"Kylee Anger"},{"text":"I''m sorry.","index":603,"end_time":1739.39,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1738.95,"speaker_name":"Kylee Anger"},{"text":"Yeah, I know I wasn''t in the last meeting, so I''m gonna see.","index":604,"end_time":1742.39,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1739.39,"speaker_name":"Kylee Anger"},{"text":"We.","index":605,"end_time":1742.67,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1742.39,"speaker_name":"Kylee Anger"},{"text":"We spoke with Danielle this week about doing the.","index":606,"end_time":1744.55,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1742.67,"speaker_name":"Kylee Anger"},{"text":"The product pages.","index":607,"end_time":1746.94,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1744.7,"speaker_name":"Kylee Anger"},{"text":"Have we already spoken with you, north, about that?","index":608,"end_time":1750.06,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1747.42,"speaker_name":"Kylee Anger"},{"text":"Product pages.","index":609,"end_time":1752.3,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1751.42,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"Remember we talked about doing a broadcast.","index":610,"end_time":1755.66,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1753.9,"speaker_name":"Kylee Anger"},{"text":"Like the landing pages.","index":611,"end_time":1756.78,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1755.74,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"We have not talked about that.","index":612,"end_time":1759.02,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1757.18,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"That''s a great, great point.","index":613,"end_time":1760.38,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1759.02,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"Thank you, Kai.","index":614,"end_time":1761.18,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1760.38,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"No problem.","index":615,"end_time":1761.9,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1761.34,"speaker_name":"Kylee Anger"},{"text":"No problem.","index":616,"end_time":1763.02,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1762.38,"speaker_name":"Kylee Anger"},{"text":"So I know that that was like top of Daniela''s list, and I think that that was probably our own internal timeline.","index":617,"end_time":1769.06,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1763.18,"speaker_name":"Kylee Anger"},{"text":"Then if we hadn''t spoken about this with New North.","index":618,"end_time":1770.7,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1769.06,"speaker_name":"Kylee Anger"},{"text":"We didn''t give them.","index":619,"end_time":1771.42,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1770.7,"speaker_name":"Kylee Anger"},{"text":"Okay, yeah, yeah, we have not.","index":620,"end_time":1773.26,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1771.5,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"So.","index":621,"end_time":1773.74,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1773.34,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"So yes, we are.","index":622,"end_time":1775.02,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1773.74,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"We are creat for Denda.","index":623,"end_time":1778.04,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1775.02,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"It''s gonna.","index":624,"end_time":1780.08,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1779.24,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"We''re gonna have a link on the top nav.","index":625,"end_time":1782.44,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1780.08,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"It''s going to be different.","index":626,"end_time":1785.32,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1783.48,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"Different.","index":627,"end_time":1787.16,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1786.76,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"Some different layout things than.","index":628,"end_time":1788.88,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1787.16,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"Than the existing, like, landing pages that we have.","index":629,"end_time":1791.48,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1788.88,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"So I think we want to get a.","index":630,"end_time":1793.96,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1791.56,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"Another template created.","index":631,"end_time":1797,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1795.24,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"However, we also want to try to get this website live early next week, which I know might be a big ask.","index":632,"end_time":1806.67,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1797.96,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"So the question is like, how quickly can we turn around a page?","index":633,"end_time":1811.11,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1806.83,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"And then.","index":634,"end_time":1811.63,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1811.11,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"And then we worry about turning it into a template after that.","index":635,"end_time":1815.79,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1811.87,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":636,"end_time":1816.63,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1816.27,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Is it already designed in figma?","index":637,"end_time":1817.99,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1816.63,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Has Danielle already?","index":638,"end_time":1818.75,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1817.99,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It is mostly done.","index":639,"end_time":1820.83,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1818.91,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"I have to.","index":640,"end_time":1821.55,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1820.91,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"We just need to double check to, you know, so if it.","index":641,"end_time":1824.47,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1821.63,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"If it has to be, say, next Wednesday, you know, that won''t be the end of the world.","index":642,"end_time":1829.63,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1824.47,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"And.","index":643,"end_time":1829.85,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1829.69,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"But.","index":644,"end_time":1830.32,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1830.08,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"But I will get that over to you as soon as we can.","index":645,"end_time":1834,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1831.52,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"Yeah, if you can.","index":646,"end_time":1835.2,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1834.4,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, if you can send that over, I can get you a timeline on when we could get that live, but I don''t see that being a problem.","index":647,"end_time":1840.64,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1835.6,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":648,"end_time":1841.68,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1841.12,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"Yeah, I left.","index":649,"end_time":1843.72,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1842.48,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"I looked.","index":650,"end_time":1844.2,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1843.72,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"Was this morning and she.","index":651,"end_time":1845.28,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1844.2,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"It looked like it was about, I guess, two thirds done.","index":652,"end_time":1847.76,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1845.28,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"But we''ll need to get a few sets of eyes on it to sort of bless it.","index":653,"end_time":1853.36,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1848.72,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"But otherwise, I think.","index":654,"end_time":1856.16,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1853.36,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"Well, I mean, really, all that other matters is Edwin.","index":655,"end_time":1858.16,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1856.16,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"Edwin''s got to say it''s fine.","index":656,"end_time":1859.43,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1858.16,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"And then you don''t know why you''re here.","index":657,"end_time":1863.98,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1860.78,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"To approve web pages?","index":658,"end_time":1864.94,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1863.98,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"No.","index":659,"end_time":1865.54,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1865.18,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"And Misty.","index":660,"end_time":1866.42,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1865.54,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I''m sorry, what did you say the.","index":661,"end_time":1867.26,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1866.42,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Name of the page was?","index":662,"end_time":1868.3,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1867.26,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Oh, it''s Venda Z E N D A. Gotcha.","index":663,"end_time":1874.34,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1868.62,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"Okay.","index":664,"end_time":1874.86,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1874.34,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":665,"end_time":1877.58,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1877.18,"speaker_name":"Kylee Anger"},{"text":"So.","index":666,"end_time":1877.9,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1877.58,"speaker_name":"Kylee Anger"},{"text":"So the.","index":667,"end_time":1878.54,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1877.9,"speaker_name":"Kylee Anger"},{"text":"The caveat here, I think, Colin, is, like, it''s because it''s a product.","index":668,"end_time":1883.66,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1879.18,"speaker_name":"Kylee Anger"},{"text":"Okay, I''m on mute.","index":669,"end_time":1887.07,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1885.83,"speaker_name":"Kylee Anger"},{"text":"I''m on mute.","index":670,"end_time":1887.75,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1887.07,"speaker_name":"Kylee Anger"},{"text":"I noticed that I was, like, looking at the figma.","index":671,"end_time":1890.07,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1887.91,"speaker_name":"Kylee Anger"},{"text":"So the difference here, Colin, is that we had created, like, reusable components, like, for the rest of the website, because we wanted everything to be standard.","index":672,"end_time":1898.07,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1891.19,"speaker_name":"Kylee Anger"},{"text":"This is going to be different.","index":673,"end_time":1898.95,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1898.07,"speaker_name":"Kylee Anger"},{"text":"This is products.","index":674,"end_time":1900.23,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1899.19,"speaker_name":"Kylee Anger"},{"text":"So we''re using the products brand.","index":675,"end_time":1902.07,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1900.23,"speaker_name":"Kylee Anger"},{"text":"So keep that in mind.","index":676,"end_time":1904.39,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1902.87,"speaker_name":"Kylee Anger"},{"text":"Yeah, we''ll get it to you as soon as possible, but it will be different.","index":677,"end_time":1907.63,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1904.63,"speaker_name":"Kylee Anger"},{"text":"You won''t have components to already play with.","index":678,"end_time":1910.63,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1907.63,"speaker_name":"Kylee Anger"},{"text":"I''m hoping Daniela has created a component system for it, but I''m guessing she has not since she''s just trying to get this page done.","index":679,"end_time":1916.86,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1911.51,"speaker_name":"Kylee Anger"},{"text":"So like Misty said, if we can get it developed quickly and maybe not do it the normal way of, like, creating components first, like, we might have to do that.","index":680,"end_time":1925.45,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1917.49,"speaker_name":"Kylee Anger"},{"text":"But the goal here is we have our services page with the dropdown in the menu.","index":681,"end_time":1929.57,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1925.45,"speaker_name":"Kylee Anger"},{"text":"Ideally, this is.","index":682,"end_time":1931.57,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1930.21,"speaker_name":"Kylee Anger"},{"text":"This is a template that we can, you know, reuse again so that if we create more products, we now have a product dropdown and it can follow the same.","index":683,"end_time":1938.85,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1931.57,"speaker_name":"Kylee Anger"},{"text":"Same concept.","index":684,"end_time":1939.57,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1938.85,"speaker_name":"Kylee Anger"},{"text":"So Danielle is keeping that in mind as she creates the layout for the product page so that we can throw other things in there later if we, you know, create a similar product for a different.","index":685,"end_time":1947.97,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1939.57,"speaker_name":"Kylee Anger"},{"text":"Um, but I just wanted to put all that out there now, while it might not matter to get this out quickly, I wanted you to know what might be coming later.","index":686,"end_time":1957.27,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1948.91,"speaker_name":"Kylee Anger"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, yeah, yeah.","index":687,"end_time":1958.67,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1957.27,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And I think we follow a similar process to what we did with the blog, where we, like, make a version, you guys review it, and then we build the post type after.","index":688,"end_time":1965.35,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1958.67,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Like, that is complete.","index":689,"end_time":1966.47,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1965.35,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Final.","index":690,"end_time":1966.83,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1966.47,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, yeah.","index":691,"end_time":1968.27,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1967.07,"speaker_name":"Kylee Anger"},{"text":"Um, and I just took a glance and the Only thing, she''s got all the elements in the page except the final call to action.","index":692,"end_time":1975.55,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1968.59,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"Kai''s nodding because she''s like, I just looked at it too.","index":693,"end_time":1978.39,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1976.39,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"It does look good.","index":694,"end_time":1980.63,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1979.51,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"So.","index":695,"end_time":1981.03,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1980.63,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"So what we can do is have.","index":696,"end_time":1982.63,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1981.11,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"Is we''ll get everyone to start looking at it to.","index":697,"end_time":1985.99,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1982.79,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"To make sure it''s got the right content and the right format and all that jazz.","index":698,"end_time":1989.75,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1986.07,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"And then.","index":699,"end_time":1990.55,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1989.99,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"And then hopefully, we''ll be able to get it over to you sooner rather than later.","index":700,"end_time":1994.39,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1991.11,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":701,"end_time":1995.59,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1994.95,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right, as a recap, so we''ll get the updated SPJ ads over to you guys based on the feedback.","index":702,"end_time":2001.59,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1996.23,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And Edwin, I''m going to take a look at that target list that you built in HubSpot.","index":703,"end_time":2007.21,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2003.69,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We''ll also add New Zealand to our target outreach.","index":704,"end_time":2010.01,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2007.21,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then, Kai, I saw you already sent the Tech Award category, so thank you for that.","index":705,"end_time":2015.69,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2011.29,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then I just need the SBJ updated PDF and the new Zenda page design when that is ready.","index":706,"end_time":2023.05,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2016.25,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Miss, you.","index":707,"end_time":2024.01,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2023.53,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"Already shared with you the SBJ PDF specs.","index":708,"end_time":2027.65,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2024.01,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"Oh, I see.","index":709,"end_time":2028.48,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2027.65,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Everything.","index":710,"end_time":2028.76,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2028.48,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah.","index":711,"end_time":2030.92,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2030.12,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"Okay.","index":712,"end_time":2031.84,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2031.32,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I will take that out of the list.","index":713,"end_time":2033.08,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2031.84,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"One less thing, but we owe you feedback by Monday on all the links that you sent.","index":714,"end_time":2040.68,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2035.24,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"Yep.","index":715,"end_time":2041.4,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2040.84,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right, got it.","index":716,"end_time":2043.16,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2041.8,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"All right, well, thank you all very much.","index":717,"end_time":2046.88,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2045.24,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"If anything else pops up, please let me know.","index":718,"end_time":2048.32,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2046.88,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And Edwin will keep you updated on what we do with Google Search Console.","index":719,"end_time":2051.48,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2048.32,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Perfect.","index":720,"end_time":2052.72,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2052.2,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"Thank you, Colin.","index":721,"end_time":2053.56,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2052.72,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"Thank you, Nina.","index":722,"end_time":2054.44,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2053.64,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"Thank you.","index":723,"end_time":2055.72,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2055.08,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"Bye, everybody.","index":724,"end_time":2057.8,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2057,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Bye.","index":725,"end_time":2058.17,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2057.88,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"}],"dateString":"2025-11-12T18:00:00.000Z","host_email":"colin.costigan@marketersindemand.com","meeting_link":"https://us02web.zoom.us/j/88965765122?pwd=mPL1aFvxXYMYFRYawSa6f5Ez7s5Uv6.1","participants":["kylee.anger@shockoe.com,colin.costigan@marketersindemand.com,edwin@shockoe.com,misty.smith@shockoe.com,nina.belina@marketersindemand.com","kylee.anger@shockoe.com","edwin@shockoe.com","misty.smith@shockoe.com","nina.belina@marketersindemand.com"],"transcript_url":"https://app.fireflies.ai/view/01K9E41XHB5QXHVDWWZXPBX0BV","organizer_email":"colin.costigan@marketersindemand.com"}'::jsonb,
    '{"label":"positive","confidence":0.91,"bullets":["Reallocated full budget from underperforming AI campaign to Vibe coding for improved lead conversion.","Updated Vibe landing page to streamline experience and added LinkedIn lead gen for simpler submissions.","Team aligned on using stronger imagery and message focus for St. Andrews and Foxwoods campaigns.","Identified and corrected sitemap 404 issues; development team to review and revalidate links.","Set internal review deadline for SBJ assets and campaigns by next Monday for on-time launch."],"highlights":[{"quote":"We reallocated budget to the Vibe coding campaign.","speaker":"Colin Costigan"},{"quote":"It''s the collaboration in tech category... all the teams we needed to collaborate to bring together a cool technology.","speaker":"Kylee Anger"},{"quote":"Then we can get this live next week.","speaker":"Colin Costigan"}],"topics":["launch","delivery","budget","campaign","analytics","branding"],"model":"openai/gpt-4-1106-preview","version":1,"generated_at":"2025-11-13T00:00:00Z"}'::jsonb,
    '{"fireflies_summary":{"notes":"## **Campaign Strategy and Budget Allocation**\n\nThe team shifted the entire campaign budget to the **Vibe coding campaign** from last week to improve lead generation results, moving away from a previously underfunded **$16 daily** AI lead gen campaign that reached a broad audience of **310,000 people** but saw low conversions (23:24).  \n- Colin explained that the prior campaign’s budget was too thin to deliver meaningful conversions despite some impressions.  \n- The new budget allocation aims to focus resources effectively on a smaller, more targeted audience to improve lead quality and conversion rates.  \n- The team expects to monitor early results next week to evaluate the impact of this reallocation.  \n- This decision aligns with the need to improve ROI by prioritizing campaigns with clearer target segments and higher engagement potential.\n\nThe outreach target list focuses on businesses in the **United States**, **United Kingdom**, and New Zealand, within hospitality, hotels, marketing, and leisure travel sectors, filtered for companies with revenues between **$10 million and $1 billion** and employee sizes from **10 to 5,000** (17:09).  \n- Targeted roles include engineers, marketing directors, creative directors, product operations, and VPs of technology.  \n- The list limits outreach to **five contacts per company** to maintain focused and quality engagement.  \n- Colin plans to enrich contact info with emails and proceed with outreach pending final asset approvals.  \n- The outreach strategy targets decision-makers aligned with tech and design to increase relevance and response rates.\n\n## **Creative and Messaging Updates**\n\nThe team updated the **Vibe coding landing page** and LinkedIn ads to simplify user experience, replacing lengthy forms with a quick, simple form and embedding lead gen forms directly on LinkedIn to reduce friction (08:05).  \n- This streamlining is designed to increase conversion rates by lowering barriers for lead submission.  \n- Misty highlighted the need for more dynamic and relevant imagery, especially on screens featuring **St. Andrews links**, suggesting golf course visuals over generic phone images for better engagement (09:47).  \n- Colin and Edwin agreed to incorporate a background image showing both the **castle** and golf course to better represent the client’s brand and product.  \n- Kylee emphasized refining copy alignment and margin spacing to improve ad polish and professionalism, especially clarifying that the app is presented, not the company name.\n\nThe **Foxwoods and St. Andrews** campaigns had content updates, removing outdated language like “600 year legacy” and shifting focus toward emphasizing technology collaboration and user experience (08:05; 14:27).  \n- Kylee suggested tying the messaging to the **Sports Business Journal (SBJ) Tech Award** nomination category focusing on collaboration and technology integration.  \n- Colin committed to making the messaging cohesive across campaigns and softer in tone to reinforce authenticity and the existing partnership narrative.  \n- Tom’s LinkedIn posts about partnerships and user experience will be leveraged to support campaign messaging and award submissions.\n\n## **Content and Website Development**\n\nThe team is preparing to launch a new **product page for Venda (Zenda)**, targeting a launch early next week, with the page mostly designed but requiring final reviews and approvals (29:11).  \n- Misty noted the page will differ from existing landing pages because it uses a distinct product brand requiring a new template rather than reusable components.  \n- Kylee indicated that while reusable components exist for the site, this product page will need special development, but the goal remains to create a reusable template for future products.  \n- Colin expects to provide a timeline for development once Figma designs are finalized and submitted.  \n- The team agreed on a quick turnaround approach similar to the blog process: build a draft version first, then finalize the template after content approval.\n\nContent quality control improvements were discussed regarding blog posts, where some URLs led to **404 errors** because content was made private or links were broken (22:41).  \n- Colin will have developers conduct a sweep to clean up typos and dead links that caused over **1,200 broken links** in the Google Search Console sitemap over the past two months.  \n- Edwin emphasized the importance of fixing these 404s to improve SEO and user experience, as Google continues to crawl invalid URLs.  \n- Misty flagged an image in the **strategy blog** appearing blurry due to incorrect rendering size; Colin confirmed a fix will be applied immediately to ensure images display correctly without compression issues (26:20).\n\n## **Timelines, Feedback, and Process Improvements**\n\nThe team agreed on a deadline of **next Monday, end of day** for feedback on campaign assets, including landing pages, email copy, and ad creatives, to enable a launch the following week (25:56).  \n- Colin emphasized flexibility if delays occur, allowing the launch schedule to adjust accordingly.  \n- Misty committed to reviewing the materials and providing consolidated feedback by the deadline.  \n- The team will refresh caches regularly to prevent delays and confusion caused by stale content showing outdated blog posts or incorrect landing pages.  \n- A process was reinforced to double-check URLs and content status in platforms like WordPress and HubSpot to avoid similar issues in the future.\n\nColin and Kylee discussed aligning messaging and formatting to maintain brand consistency, including spacing and copy adjustments based on feedback from the strategist team (12:37).  \n- Misty and Kylee shared internal PDFs and best practices to ensure ad and landing page compliance with platform requirements and brand guidelines.  \n- The team agreed on a workflow where content is reviewed collaboratively before final deployment to avoid errors and improve user engagement.  \n- Monitoring and quick issue resolution protocols, such as image replacements and URL fixes, were established to maintain campaign quality post-launch.\n\n## **Award Submission and Competitive Positioning**\n\nThe team is leveraging the **Sports Business Journal Tech Award** opportunity to showcase the company’s collaboration with St. Andrews and other tech partners, focusing on API integrations and technology innovation (15:24).  \n- Kylee has engaged with Tom and reviewed award criteria to align messaging strategically with SBJ expectations.  \n- Colin plans to craft messaging that highlights genuine collaboration without overstating achievements, reinforcing credibility.  \n- The award submission serves as a platform to differentiate the company in a competitive market by spotlighting tech partnerships and user experience enhancements.  \n- This initiative supports long-term brand positioning as a technology leader in sports-related software solutions.\n\n## **Speaker and Team Integration**\n\nNew team member **Nina** was introduced and integrated into strategy calls, working closely with Colin on backend tasks supporting campaign execution (03:17).  \n- Nina’s involvement helps increase strategic capacity and supports data analysis for ongoing campaigns.  \n- Edwin and Misty continue to coordinate closely with Colin and Kylee to ensure alignment across marketing, strategy, and development teams.  \n- The team emphasized open communication channels, including Slack and email, for swift feedback and issue resolution during campaign build and launch phases.  \n- Colin and Kylee’s ongoing collaboration ensures that design, copy, and technical elements remain aligned with business goals and brand standards.","outline":null,"keywords":["Vibe Coding","St. Andrews Campaign","SBJ Awards","Landing Pages","Google Search Console","Email Outreach"],"overview":"- **Campaign Budget Shift:** Entire budget redirected to Vibe coding campaign for better lead generation, moving from a $16 daily AI campaign.  \n- **Targeting Strategy:** Focus on US, UK, and NZ businesses in hospitality with revenues of $10 million to $1 billion.  \n- **Creative Updates:** Simplified landing pages and LinkedIn ads to enhance user experience and boost conversion rates.  \n- **404 Error Resolution:** Developers will address over 1,200 broken links to improve SEO and user experience.  \n- **Feedback Deadline:** Feedback due by Monday to ensure timely campaign asset launches the following week.  \n- **Award Submission Focus:** Emphasizing collaboration for Sports Business Journal Tech Award to enhance brand positioning in the tech market.","action_items":"\n**Colin Costigan**\nShare updated SBJ ads based on received feedback (25:32)\nReview and enrich the target company/contact list including addition of New Zealand; send the updated list to Edwin (17:28)\nInvestigate reported Google Search Console 404 errors and coordinate with developers to fix broken links and typos; provide status update to Edwin (22:41)\nReplace blurry image on strategy blog with the new file provided by Misty and republish (26:01)\nDeliver timeline and development plan for Zenda product page upon receipt of design files from Misty/Daniela (30:34)\n\n**Edwin Huertas**\nShare SBJ PDF specs with Colin; build new target list adding New Zealand in HubSpot (18:50)\nReview HubSpot list for campaign alignment and report on sitemap issues for broken links/404s seen in Google Search Console (22:41)\n\n**Misty Smith**\nProvide feedback on campaign marketing assets by next Monday EOD to meet launch schedule (25:56)\nFinalize and send Zenda product page design to Colin for development review (29:31)\nFix image upload/rendering issue on strategy blog and other associated blogs by adjusting image render sizes (27:03)\n"},"migrated_from":"contract_meetings","original_id":"f8ac7071-55dc-4f3b-9882-86352f6f6ef2","maste